Ben and Lily are friends. They like to play together. One day, they go to the park with their moms. They see a big truck. The truck has a sign. The sign says "Popcorn".

"Look, popcorn!" Ben says. "I like popcorn. Do you like popcorn, Lily?"

"Yes, I do. Popcorn is yummy. Can we have some, mom?" Lily says.

Their moms nod and smile. They give them some money. Ben and Lily run to the truck. They see a man. The man has a big machine. The machine makes popcorn. The popcorn pops and pops. It smells good.

"Hello, kids. Do you want some popcorn?" the man says.

"Yes, please!" Ben and Lily say.

The man gives them two bags. One bag is white. One bag is yellow.

"This is original popcorn. It has salt and butter. This is cheese popcorn. It has cheese and more butter. Which one do you want?" the man says.

Ben and Lily look at the bags. They think hard.

"I want the original popcorn. It looks good." Ben says.

"I want the cheese popcorn. It looks different." Lily says.

They take their bags and say thank you. They go back to their moms. They sit on a bench. They open their bags. They eat their popcorn. They share with their moms. They are happy.

"This popcorn is delicious. Thank you, mom." Ben says.

"This popcorn is tasty. Thank you, mom." Lily says.

Their moms hug them and kiss them. They are proud of them.

"You are welcome, Ben. You are welcome, Lily. You are very good kids. You are original kids." their moms say.
<|end|>


