<|asst|>
Lily and Ben were twins who liked to play with their toys. They had a lot of toys, but their favorite was a big parrot that could talk. The parrot was very noisy and liked to say funny things.

One day, their mom told them to clean their room before they could go to the park. Lily and Ben did not want to clean their room. They wanted to play with the parrot. They said to the parrot, "Can you help us clean our room?"

The parrot said, "No, I can't. I want to play with you. Cleaning is boring. Let's have fun." Lily and Ben agreed with the parrot. They decided to delay cleaning their room and play with the parrot instead.

They had fun with the parrot, but they also made a big mess. They threw their toys everywhere, they spilled their juice, and they tore their books. The parrot laughed and said, "This is fun. You are the best friends ever."

Soon, their mom came to check on them. She was very angry when she saw their room. She said, "What have you done? This is a disaster. You did not listen to me. You did not clean your room. Now you can't go to the park. You have to stay here and clean up."

Lily and Ben were very sad. They realized they made a mistake. They said to their mom, "We are sorry, mom. We were bad. We listened to the parrot. He told us to delay cleaning our room and play with him. He was very noisy and funny, but he was also very bad."

Their mom said, "The parrot is not your friend. He is a toy. He does not care about you. He only repeats what he hears. You should not listen to him. You should listen to me. I care about you. I want you to be good and happy. Cleaning your room is good for you. It teaches you to be responsible and organized. It also makes more space for you to play. If you had cleaned your room, you could have gone to the park and had more fun."

Lily and Ben understood their mom. They said, "You are right, mom. We are sorry. We will clean our room now. We will not listen to the parrot anymore. He is not our friend. He is just a toy. You are our friend. You are our mom. We love you."

Their mom smiled and hugged them. She said, "I love you too. I forgive you. But you have to clean your room first. Then we can go to the park later. And next time, do not delay doing what I tell you. It is better to do it right away."

Lily and Ben nodded and started to clean their room. They put away their toys, they wiped their juice, and they taped their books. They also put the parrot in a box and closed it. They did not want to hear him anymore. They learned their lesson. They learned to listen to their mom and not to delay doing what is good.
<|end|>


