Lily and Ben were playing in the park. They liked to ride their bikes on the path. Lily had a pink helmet and Ben had a blue helmet. They always wore their helmets to be safe.

One day, they saw a big hill. Ben wanted to go down the hill very fast. He said to Lily, "Come on, let's try it. It will be fun." Lily was scared. She said, "No, Ben, it looks too steep. What if we fall?" Ben said, "Don't be a baby. It's easy. Just follow me." He pedaled hard and zoomed down the hill.

Lily watched him go. She felt helpless. She wanted to be brave like Ben, but she also wanted to be careful. She prayed in her heart, "Please, God, keep Ben safe. Don't let him get hurt." She waited for him to come back up.

But Ben did not come back up. Lily heard a loud crash. She saw Ben's bike lying on the ground. She saw Ben lying next to it. He was not moving. He was bleeding. Lily screamed. She ran down the hill. She cried, "Ben, Ben, are you okay?"

Ben opened his eyes. He groaned. He said, "Lily, I'm sorry. I was wrong. It was too fast. It was not fun. It was scary. It hurt." Lily hugged him. She said, "It's okay, Ben. I'm here. I love you. Help is coming." She saw a lady with a phone. She saw a car with a siren. She saw a man with a bag. They came to help Ben. They put him on a stretcher. They took him to the hospital. Lily went with him. She held his hand. She prayed, "Thank you, God, for saving Ben. Please, make him better. Please, don't let him do that again."
<|end|>


