Anna and Ben are twins. They like to play in the kitchen when Mom is busy. They see a big cake on the table. It looks yummy.

"Let's taste the cake," Ben says.

"No, we can't. Mom will be mad," Anna says.

But Ben does not listen. He takes a big bite of the cake. It is sweet and soft. He smiles.

"See, it is good. You try too," he says.

Anna is scared, but she is also curious. She takes a small bite of the cake. It is good, but she feels bad.

"Ben, we should not do this. Mom made the cake for Dad's birthday. She will be sad if she sees it," she says.

But Ben does not care. He takes another bite of the cake. He makes a mess on the table.

"Ben, stop it. You are naughty," Anna says.

But Ben does not stop. He eats and eats until the cake is gone. He is full and happy.

"Ben, look what you did. The cake is gone. Mom will be very mad. What will we do?" Anna says.

But Ben does not answer. He falls asleep on the chair. He snores.

Anna is worried. She tries to clean the table, but it is too hard. She hears Mom coming. She is afraid.

She hides under the table. She hopes Mom will not see her. She hopes Mom will not see the cake. She hopes Mom will not hear Ben snoring.

She is quiet. She waits. She hears silence.
<|end|>


