Tom and Lily were playing in the park. They liked to run and chase each other. Sometimes they pretended to be pirates or superheroes. They had a lot of fun.

But the sun was going down and it was time to go home. Tom's mom called him from the bench. "Tom, it's time to go. Come on, let's go."

Tom did not want to go. He wanted to play more. He said to Lily, "Let's hide from my mom. She can't find us. We can play more."

Lily was nervous. She knew they had to go home. She said to Tom, "No, Tom. We can't hide. That's not nice. Your mom will be sad and angry. And it's getting dark. We have to go."

Tom did not listen. He ran behind a big tree. He said, "You can't catch me. I'm a pirate. You have to surrender."

Lily sighed. She ran after Tom. She saw him behind the tree. She said, "Tom, please. Come out. Don't be silly. Look, the sun is almost gone. It's a pretty sunset. Let's go see it with your mom."

Tom peeked from behind the tree. He saw the sky was orange and pink. He saw his mom was waiting for him. He felt sorry. He said, "Okay, Lily. You win. I surrender. Let's go."

Tom and Lily came out from behind the tree. They ran to Tom's mom. She hugged them and smiled. She said, "I'm glad you're here. Did you have fun?"

Tom and Lily nodded. They said, "Yes, we did. But we're sorry we hid from you. That was not nice."

Tom's mom said, "It's okay. I forgive you. But next time, listen to me when I call you. Okay?"

Tom and Lily said, "Okay."

They all walked to the car. They looked at the sunset. It was beautiful. They were happy.
<|end|>


