Lily and Ben are friends. They like to play with blocks. They have many blocks of different colors and shapes. They can make towers, houses, cars and animals with the blocks.

One day, they decide to make a big castle with the blocks. They work hard and use many blocks. They make walls, windows, doors and a flag. The castle is very impressive. It is taller than Lily and Ben.

"Look at our castle!" Lily says. "It is so big and pretty!"

"Yes, it is!" Ben says. "We are good at making castles!"

They are happy and proud of their castle. They want to show it to their teacher and their friends.

But then, Max comes. Max is a boy who does not like to share. He sees the castle and wants to play with it. He does not ask Lily and Ben. He just takes some blocks from the castle and makes his own tower.

"Hey, stop!" Lily says. "Those are our blocks! We made the castle!"

"Give them back!" Ben says. "You are ruining our castle!"

But Max does not listen. He takes more blocks and makes his tower bigger. He does not care about Lily and Ben's feelings. He is selfish and rude.

Lily and Ben are sad and angry. They do not like Max. They want to protect their castle. They try to take the blocks back from Max. But Max pushes them away. He is stronger than Lily and Ben.

They start to fight. They pull and tug and shout. The blocks fall and break. The castle and the tower are destroyed. The blocks are scattered everywhere.

The teacher hears the noise and comes. She sees the mess and the fight. She is not happy. She scolds Max, Lily and Ben. She tells them to stop fighting and to share the blocks. She tells them to say sorry to each other and to help clean up the blocks.

Max, Lily and Ben feel ashamed. They know they did wrong. They say sorry to each other and to the teacher. They share the blocks and help clean up. They learn to be more respectful and kind.

They decide to make a new castle together. They use all the blocks and cooperate. They make a bigger and better castle than before. It is more impressive than ever. They are happy and proud of their castle. They show it to their teacher and their friends. They have fun playing with it.

The end.
<|end|>


