Lily and Tom were friends. They liked to play in the park. One day, they saw a big slide. Lily wanted to try it. She said, "Let's go on the slide, Tom. It looks fun."

Tom was scared. He said, "No, Lily. The slide is too high. I don't want to go."

Lily said, "Don't be scared, Tom. I will go first. You can watch me. Then you can go after me. It will be easy."

Lily ran to the slide. She climbed the steps. She sat on the top. She said, "Look, Tom. I'm not scared. I'm ready to go." She pushed herself down the slide. She went very fast. She laughed and shouted, "Whee!"

Tom watched Lily. He saw her smile. He saw her have fun. He wanted to have fun too. He said, "Maybe I can try it. Maybe it's not so bad." He walked to the slide. He climbed the steps. He sat on the top. He said, "OK, Lily. I will go now. I hope I don't fall."

Lily said, "You won't fall, Tom. You will be fine. Just hold on and enjoy the ride." She cheered for him. She said, "You can do it, Tom. You are brave."

Tom took a deep breath. He pushed himself down the slide. He went very fast. He felt the wind in his hair. He felt a thrill in his stomach. He smiled and shouted, "Whee!"

Lily and Tom met at the bottom. They hugged each other. They said, "That was awesome. That was fun. Let's do it again."

They ran to the slide. They climbed the steps. They sat on the top. They pushed themselves down the slide. They went very fast. They laughed and shouted, "Whee!"

Lily and Tom gained a new start. They were not scared of the slide anymore. They were happy and proud. They were friends.
<|end|>


