Tom and Lily liked to play in the woods. They liked to find new things and have fun. One day, they saw a big hole in the hill. It was a cave. They wanted to see what was inside.

They went into the cave. It was dark and cold. They used a flashlight to look around. They saw rocks and bats and spiders. They heard water and wind. They were not scared. They were brave.

They walked deeper into the cave. They saw two paths. One path went left and one path went right. They had to choose. Tom wanted to go left. He said it looked more interesting. Lily wanted to go right. She said it looked safer.

They argued for a while. They did not agree. They did not listen to each other. They were deaf to each other's words. They got angry and sad. They decided to go their own way.

They split up. Tom went left and Lily went right. They walked alone in the dark. They did not see or hear each other. They did not have fun. They missed each other. They wished they had stayed together. They learned a lesson. They should have been kind and respectful. They should have worked together and compromised. They should have chosen to be friends.
<|end|>


