Tom and Sue were friends who liked to play with toys. One day, they found a big book with many words in it. They wanted to learn the words, so they opened the book and looked at the pages.

But the words were not like the words they knew. They were from a different language that they did not understand. They tried to say the words, but they sounded funny and hard. They laughed at the words and made fun of them.

A man saw them and heard them. He was not happy. He came to them and said, "Why are you laughing at the language? It is the language of my home. It is a beautiful and old language. You should not laugh at it, you should respect it."

Tom and Sue felt bad. They did not know the man or his language. They did not mean to hurt him. They said, "We are sorry, sir. We did not know. We were just curious and silly. We regret laughing at your language. Please forgive us."

The man saw that they were humble and sorry. He smiled and said, "It is okay, children. I forgive you. You are young and curious. It is good to learn new things, but it is also good to be kind and respectful. Do you want to learn some words from my language?"

Tom and Sue nodded and said, "Yes, please. We want to learn." The man sat with them and taught them some words from his language. They listened and repeated the words. They learned and had fun. They thanked the man and said goodbye. They were happy and proud. They had made a new friend and learned a new language.
