Tom and Sam were brothers who liked to play by the river. One day, they saw a big raft made of wood and rope. They wanted to ride on it and have fun.

"Let's go on the raft, Sam!" Tom said. "It looks like a boat!"

"OK, Tom, but be careful. The water is fast and deep," Sam said. He was older and wise.

They climbed on the raft and pushed it into the water. The raft moved with the current and they laughed and waved. They felt like pirates.

But soon, the raft went too far and they could not see the shore. They tried to paddle with their hands, but it was hard. The water was cold and strong.

"Help! Help!" Tom and Sam shouted. "We want to go back!"

But no one heard them. The raft gained speed and went towards a big rock. It hit the rock and broke into pieces. Tom and Sam fell into the water and sank. They did not know how to swim.

The end.
