Lily was very enthusiastic about her birthday. She wanted to have a big cake, lots of balloons and many friends to play with. She helped her mom and dad decorate the house and make the invitations.

The next day, Lily woke up early and put on her favorite dress. She ran downstairs and saw the cake on the table. It was pink and white, with candles and sprinkles. Lily clapped her hands and smiled.

"Happy birthday, Lily!" her mom and dad said, and gave her a hug and a kiss. "Do you like your cake?"

"I love it! Thank you, mom and dad!" Lily said. "Can I try a piece?"

"Not yet, sweetie. You have to wait for your friends to come. They will be here soon. Why don't you open your presents first?" her dad said, and pointed to a pile of wrapped boxes.

Lily nodded and ran to the presents. She tore the paper and saw many wonderful things. She got a doll, a book, a puzzle, a hat and a ball. She thanked her mom and dad for each one and hugged them.

Soon, the doorbell rang and Lily's friends arrived. They all wished her a happy birthday and gave her more presents. Lily was so happy and excited. She invited them to play with her toys and games.

After a while, her mom called them to the table. She lit the candles and sang "Happy Birthday" to Lily. Lily blew out the candles and made a wish. Then, she cut the cake and gave everyone a slice.

"Wow, this cake is delicious!" Lily's friend Ben said.

"Yes, it is! Thank you, Lily, for sharing it with us!" Lily's friend Anna said.

"You're welcome! I'm glad you like it!" Lily said. "This is the best birthday ever!"
