Lily and Ben are playing hide and seek in the park. Lily is the seeker and Ben is the hider. Lily counts to ten and then looks for Ben.

She sees a big tree with many leaves. She thinks Ben might be hidden behind the tree. She runs to the tree and says, "I found you, Ben!"

But Ben is not there. She only sees a dog with a red collar. The dog wags its tail and licks Lily's face. Lily laughs and pets the dog.

"Hello, dog. What is your name? Do you have a friend?" Lily asks.

The dog barks and points its nose to a bush. Lily looks at the bush and sees Ben's shoes sticking out. She smiles and says, "I see you, Ben! You are not very good at hiding!"

Ben comes out of the bush and says, "You are too smart, Lily! And you have a new friend. Can I pet the dog too?"

Lily nods and says, "Yes, you can. The dog is very nice. Maybe he is lost. We should look for his owner."

They look at the dog's collar and see a tag with a phone number. They call the number and a man answers. He says he is the dog's owner and he is looking for him. He thanks Lily and Ben for finding his dog and says he will come to the park soon.

Lily and Ben are happy. They play with the dog until the man arrives. He gives them a hug and a treat. He says his dog's name is Spot and he ran away from home. He is very glad they found him.

Lily and Ben say goodbye to Spot and his owner. They decide to play hide and seek again. But this time, they will hide together. They think it will be more fun.
