Tom and Lily are brother and sister. They like to play with their toys in the living room. They have a big box of toys with cars, dolls, balls and books. Sometimes they share their toys, and sometimes they fight over them.

One day, Tom finds a long string in the box. He has an idea. He ties one end of the string to his car, and the other end to Lily's doll. He pulls the string and makes the car and the doll move together. He thinks it is funny.

Lily does not think it is funny. She does not like Tom to touch her doll. She wants to play with her doll by herself. She tries to untie the string, but it is too tight. She gets angry and cries.

"Tom, stop it! Give me back my doll!" she shouts.

"No, it is my car! I want to play with it!" Tom shouts back.

They pull the string and make the car and the doll crash into each other. They make a lot of noise.

Mom hears the noise and comes to the living room. She sees Tom and Lily fighting over the string. She is not happy.

"Tom, Lily, what are you doing? You are making a mess! And you are hurting your toys!" she says.

She takes the string from them and unties the car and the doll. She puts them back in the box.

"Time for dinner, kids. Come to the kitchen and wash your hands. And no more fighting, please. You need to be nice to each other and to your toys," she says.

Tom and Lily follow Mom to the kitchen. They are hungry and sorry. They say sorry to each other and to their toys. They promise to be more playful and less mean. They hug and smile. They enjoy their dinner and have a good night.
