Sara and Tom love to play with their kayak. It is brown and has two seats. They like to paddle on the lake and see the fish and the ducks. Sometimes they race with each other and laugh.

One day, they see a big boat on the lake. It is white and has a loud horn. Sara and Tom are curious and want to get closer. They paddle faster and faster.

"Be careful!" their mom shouts from the shore. "The big boat is not for playing. It can hurt you and your kayak. Stay away from it!"

Sara and Tom hear their mom and slow down. They remember that the big boat is not friendly. They turn around and paddle back to the shore.

"Sorry, mom," Sara says. "We just wanted to see the big boat."

"I know, sweetie," their mom says. "But you have to be safe. The big boat is for grown-ups. Your kayak is for fun. I'm glad you came back."

