<|asst|>
Tom and Mia are busy. They have to clean their room. Mom said so. They put their toys in the box. They make their bed. They throw away the trash.

But Tom has a problem. He has an itch on his nose. He rubs it with his hand. But it does not help. The itch is still there.

"Ow, ow, ow!" Tom says. "My nose is itchy!"

Mia looks at him. She sees a red spot on his nose. She knows what it is. It is a mosquito bite.

"Tom, you have a bite!" Mia says. "A mosquito bit you!"

Tom does not like mosquitoes. They are mean. They make him itch.

"How can I make it stop?" Tom asks.

Mia thinks. She remembers what Mom does when she has a bite. She gets a wet cloth. She puts it on the bite. She says it makes it cool and better.

"Mia, can you help me?" Tom says.

Mia nods. She goes to the bathroom. She gets a wet cloth. She comes back to the room. She puts the cloth on Tom's nose.

"Does it feel better?" Mia asks.

Tom nods. He feels the cloth on his nose. It is cool and nice. The itch is gone.

"Thank you, Mia!" Tom says.

"You're welcome, Tom!" Mia says.

They hug. They are happy. They finish cleaning their room. They are good. Mom is proud.
<|end|>


