<|asst|>
Tim and Kim are twins. They like to play with their toys and books. But they do not like to clean their room. They are lazy.

One day, Mom comes to their room. She sees a big mess. She is angry. She says, "Tim and Kim, you need to clean your room now. It is not nice to leave your toys and books everywhere. You will lose them or break them. And you will have no space to play. You are big enough to help me. Do not be lazy."

Tim and Kim do not want to clean their room. They want to play. They say, "Mom, we are tired. We do not want to clean. Can we do it later?"

Mom says, "No, you cannot do it later. You need to do it now. If you do not clean your room, you will not get any dessert. And you will have to listen to a lecture from me. Do you want that?"

Tim and Kim do not want to miss dessert. And they do not want to listen to a lecture. They know Mom is serious. They say, "OK, Mom, we will clean our room. But can you help us?"

Mom says, "I will help you a little bit. But you have to do most of the work. It is your room. And you have to learn to be responsible. Now, let's start. First, we will weigh your toys and books. We will put the heavy ones in the big box. And we will put the light ones in the small box. Then, we will put the boxes on the shelf. Do you understand?"

Tim and Kim nod. They say, "Yes, Mom, we understand. We will weigh our toys and books. And we will put them in the boxes. And we will put the boxes on the shelf. We will make our room clean and nice. And we will not be lazy anymore."

Mom smiles. She says, "That's good. I am proud of you. Now, let's get to work. And when we are done, we will have some dessert. And we will read a story. How does that sound?"

Tim and Kim smile. They say, "That sounds great. Thank you, Mom. We love you."

Mom says, "I love you too. Now, let's go."
<|end|>


