<|asst|>
Jenny and Max were best friends. They liked to play in the park every day. They enjoyed the swings, the slide and the sandbox. But their favorite thing was the zip line. It was a long rope with a handle that they could hold and fly across the air.

One day, they saw a new kid in the park. He had a red hat and a blue bike. He looked sad and lonely. Jenny and Max wanted to be nice, so they said hello to him.

"Hi, I'm Jenny and this is Max. What's your name?" Jenny asked.

"I'm Leo. I just moved here. I don't have any friends," Leo said.

"Do you want to play with us? We can show you the zip line. It's very fun," Max said.

Leo nodded and smiled. He followed Jenny and Max to the zip line. They took turns holding the handle and flying across the air. Leo was a little scared at first, but he soon liked it. He laughed and shouted with joy.

Jenny and Max were happy to see Leo having fun. They thought he was adorable with his red hat and his blue bike. They decided to invite him to their next play date.

"Leo, do you want to come to our house tomorrow? We have more toys and games. We can be friends," Jenny said.

"Yes, please. I would love that. Thank you, Jenny and Max. You are very kind," Leo said.

They hugged and said goodbye. They looked forward to seeing each other again. They enjoyed their new friendship.
<|end|>


