<|asst|>
Tom and Lily were playing with their toy cars in the garden. They liked to make them zoom and crash on the grass. But then, Tom's car broke. One of its wheels came off and rolled away.

"Oh no!" Tom cried. "My car is broken! I need to repair it!"

Lily saw Tom's sad face and wanted to help. She looked around and found the wheel under a flower. She picked it up and ran to Tom.

"Here, Tom, I found your wheel!" she said. "Let me help you repair your car!"

But Tom was grumpy. He did not want Lily to touch his car. He snatched the wheel from her hand and said, "No, Lily, this is my car! You can't repair it! You don't know how!"

Lily felt hurt and angry. She crossed her arms and said, "Fine, Tom, be grumpy! I don't want to play with you anymore!"

She took her car and walked away. Tom tried to repair his car by himself, but he could not. He needed Lily's help. He realized he was mean to her and felt sorry.

"Lily, wait!" he called. "I'm sorry, Lily! Please come back and play with me! Please help me repair my car!"

Lily heard Tom's voice and turned around. She saw his sorry face and felt sorry too. She smiled and said, "OK, Tom, I forgive you. Let's repair your car together!"

She walked back to Tom and they fixed his car. They hugged and said, "We are friends again!"

They played with their cars happily and shared them with each other. They learned to be kind and helpful and not grumpy.
<|end|>


