Sara and Ben are friends. They like to play together. Sara has a journal. She draws and writes in it. Ben has a chubby cat. He likes to pet and feed it.

One day, Sara and Ben go to the park. They bring their journal and cat. They find a big tree. They sit under the tree and play.

"Look, Ben, I draw a flower in my journal. Do you like it?" Sara asks.

"Yes, Sara, it is pretty. Can I draw something too?" Ben says.

"Sure, Ben, here is a crayon. What do you want to draw?" Sara says.

"I want to draw my cat. He is chubby and soft. He likes to sleep and eat. He is my best friend." Ben says.

Sara and Ben take turns to draw in the journal. They show each other their pictures. They are happy.

The cat is happy too. He lies on the grass and purrs. He watches the birds and the bugs. He is not hungry or thirsty. He is with his friends.

Sara and Ben and the cat have a fun day at the park. They play and draw and talk. They are glad they have each other. They are good friends.
<|end|>


