Lily and Ben are playing in the park. They see a big tree with many leaves. Lily wants to examine the leaves. She picks one and looks at it. She sees the veins and the color.

"Look, Ben, this leaf is green and tough. It does not break when I bend it." Lily says.

Ben picks another leaf. His leaf is yellow and soft. It breaks when he bends it.

"Look, Lily, this leaf is yellow and soft. It breaks when I bend it." Ben says.

They compare their leaves. They wonder why they are different. They decide to write a note to ask their teacher.

They find a paper and a crayon. They write: "Why are some leaves green and tough and some leaves yellow and soft?"

They put the note in their backpack. They hope their teacher will answer their question. They go back to playing in the park. They are curious and happy.
<|end|>


