<|asst|>
Ben and Lily like to play in the park. They like to run, jump, and slide. They also like to sing and dance. Sometimes they perform for the birds and the squirrels. They think they are very good.

One day, they see a stream in the park. It is shiny and clear. They want to play in the water. They take off their shoes and socks. They roll up their pants. They run to the stream.

But when they get there, they see a big boy. He is sitting on a rock. He has a stick. He is poking the water. He says, "This is my stream. Go away. You are too small and silly. You can't play here."

Ben and Lily are sad and angry. They want to play in the stream. They think the big boy is mean and rude. They say, "No, this is not your stream. This is for everyone. You can't tell us what to do. We can play here."

The big boy laughs. He says, "Oh, yeah? What can you do? You can't stop me. You are weak and dumb. You can't do anything."

Ben and Lily have an idea. They say, "We can do something. We can perform for you. We can sing and dance. We can show you how good we are. Maybe then you will be nice and share."

The big boy is curious. He says, "Okay, fine. Perform for me. But you have to be very good. Or else I will splash you with water."

Ben and Lily nod. They start to sing and dance. They sing a happy song. They dance with grace and joy. They smile and clap. They look very fit and fun.

The big boy watches them. He is surprised. He thinks they are not so bad. He thinks they are kind of cute. He starts to smile and clap. He says, "Wow, you are very good. You can sing and dance. You are not so small and silly. You are fit and fun."

Ben and Lily are happy. They say, "Thank you. You are not so mean and rude. You are kind and cool. You can play with us. We can share the stream."

The big boy agrees. He says, "Okay, fine. I will play with you. I will share the stream. But you have to teach me how to sing and dance. I want to be fit and fun too."

Ben and Lily nod. They say, "Sure. We will teach you. We can be friends. We can perform together."

They all hug and laugh. They play in the stream. They sing and dance. They perform for the birds and the squirrels. They have a lot of fun.
<|end|>


