<|asst|>
Tim and Mia are friends. They live in a big city with many cars and people. They like to play in the park near their home. One day, they see a new slide in the park. It is very big and shiny. They want to try it.

"Let's go on the slide!" Tim says.

"OK!" Mia says.

They run to the slide. But there is a problem. There is a thick rope around the slide. There is a sign that says "Do not use. Slide is broken."

Tim and Mia are sad. They really want to go on the slide.

"Maybe we can go under the rope," Tim says.

"No, Tim. That is bad. The sign says no. The slide is broken. It can hurt us," Mia says.

"But it looks so fun. I want to try it. Just one time," Tim says.

He tries to go under the rope. Mia pulls him back.

"Stop, Tim. Please. Listen to me. We can play on the swings or the seesaw. They are not broken. They are fun too," Mia says.

Tim does not listen. He tries to go under the rope again. Mia pulls him harder.

"Tim, no! Resist! Resist!" Mia says.

Tim resists. He does not want to listen to Mia. He wants to go on the slide. He pushes Mia away. He goes under the rope. He climbs on the slide.

"Tim, come back! It is dangerous!" Mia shouts.

But Tim does not hear her. He slides down the slide. He slides very fast. He slides too fast. He cannot stop. He falls off the slide. He lands on the ground. He hurts his knee. He cries.

Mia runs to him. She helps him up. She hugs him.

"I am sorry, Tim. Are you OK?" Mia says.

Tim is not OK. His knee is bleeding. It hurts a lot. He is also sorry. He knows he was wrong. He should have listened to Mia. He should have resisted his want.

"I am sorry, Mia. You were right. I was bad. I should have resisted. I should have played with you," Tim says.

Mia smiles. She is happy that Tim is sorry. She is still his friend.

"It is OK, Tim. I forgive you. Come on. Let's go to the nurse. She will make your knee better. Then we can play together. OK?" Mia says.

"OK, Mia. Thank you. You are a good friend," Tim says.

They hold hands. They walk to the nurse. They are still friends. They learned a lesson. They will resist their bad wants. They will listen to each other. They will have fun. The end.
<|end|>


