<|asst|>
Lila liked to play the flute. She had a flexible flute that she could bend and twist. She made funny sounds with it. She played the flute for her mom and dad, and they clapped and smiled.

One day, Lila saw a man playing the flute on the street. He had a big flute that was shiny and straight. He made beautiful sounds with it. Lila wanted to try his flute. She ran to the man and asked, "Can I play your flute?"

The man looked at Lila and said, "No, you can't. This is my flute. I play it to get money. People pay me to hear me play. See, they put money in this hat. If you want to play my flute, you have to pay me too."

Lila was sad. She did not have any money. She only had her flexible flute. She said, "I don't have money. But I have this flute. Can I trade you my flute for your flute?"

The man laughed. He said, "No, you can't. Your flute is not a real flute. It is a toy. It is not worth anything. My flute is a real flute. It is worth a lot. Go away, little girl. You are bothering me."

Lila was angry. She did not like the man. She thought he was mean and greedy. She said, "You are a bad man. You don't share. You don't care. You are not nice. I don't like you." She took her flexible flute and ran away. She played her flute loud and proud. She did not need his flute. She liked her flute better. She had fun with her flute. She was happy.
<|end|>


