<|asst|>
Mia and Leo were twins who liked to play together. But sometimes they fought over their toys and games. Mia was bossy and wanted to do everything her way. Leo was quiet and did not like to argue.

One day, they were playing with their toy kitchen. Mia wanted to make a soup with a potato and some water. Leo wanted to make a cake with a potato and some sugar. They both grabbed the same potato and pulled hard.

"Let go of my potato!" Mia shouted. "I need it for my soup!"

"No, it's my potato!" Leo yelled back. "I want to make a cake!"

They pulled and pulled until the potato broke in half. Mia and Leo both fell to the floor and started to cry.

Mom heard the noise and came to see what was wrong. She saw the broken potato and the tears on their faces. She comforted them and hugged them.

"I'm sorry, Mom," Mia said. "We were fighting over the potato."

"I'm sorry, too," Leo said. "We were not sharing."

Mom smiled and said, "It's okay, my loves. Fighting is not fun, and it can hurt your feelings and your toys. Next time, why don't you try to take turns or find a way to play together? Maybe you can make a soup and a cake with two potatoes, or use something else for your recipes. What do you think?"

Mia and Leo nodded and said, "Yes, Mom. That sounds good. We're sorry for being loud and mean."

Mom kissed them and said, "I'm proud of you for saying sorry and for being kind. Now, why don't you go and wash your hands and I'll make you a real snack with some real potatoes. How does that sound?"

Mia and Leo smiled and said, "Yay! Thank you, Mom. We love you."

They hugged Mom and ran to the bathroom. They learned that playing nicely was more fun than fighting, and that potatoes were good for many things.
<|end|>


