<|asst|>
Lily was a little girl who liked to play with her dolls. She had many dolls, but her favorite one was Anna. Anna had long hair, a pink dress and a big smile. Lily loved to brush Anna's hair and make her talk.

One day, Lily went to the park with her mom and Anna. She saw some other kids playing with their dolls too. She wanted to join them and make new friends. She walked over to them with Anna in her hand.

But when she got closer, she saw that their dolls were different from Anna. Their dolls had short hair, blue dresses and no smiles. They were all gray. Lily felt sad and scared. She wondered why their dolls were gray and not colorful like Anna.

The other kids saw Lily and Anna. They pointed at them and laughed. They said that Lily's doll was weird and ugly. They said that Lily should get a gray doll like them. They said that Anna did not belong there.

Lily felt hurt and angry. She did not like what they said. She did not want a gray doll. She loved Anna. She hugged Anna and ran back to her mom. She told her mom what happened and cried.

Her mom hugged her and wiped her tears. She told her that Anna was a beautiful doll and that Lily was a brave girl. She told her that it was okay to be different and to like different things. She told her that some people might not understand or accept that, but that did not mean that Lily or Anna were wrong. She told her that she was proud of her and that she loved her.

Lily smiled and thanked her mom. She felt better and stronger. She looked at Anna and told her that she was her best friend. She decided to stand up for herself and Anna. She did not care what the other kids said. She knew that Anna was special and so was she.
<|end|>


