Anna and Ben were twins who liked to play outside. One day, they saw a big church near their house. They wanted to see what was inside, so they ran to the door. But the door was locked, and the church looked old and dull.

"Let's go around and find another way in," Ben said. He was brave and curious.

"No, let's go back. Mom said we should not go near the church. It might be scary," Anna said. She was careful and obedient.

But Ben did not listen to Anna. He ran to the back of the church and found a window. He climbed on a box and looked inside. He saw dark shadows and dusty statues. He felt a cold wind and heard a strange noise.

"Boo!" someone shouted from behind him.

Ben screamed and fell off the box. He turned around and saw a man with a long coat and a hat. The man was laughing.

"Who are you? What are you doing here?" Ben asked, shaking with fear.

"I'm the caretaker of the church. I saw you sneaking around and I wanted to scare you. You should not be here. This is not a place for children. Go back to your home and stay away from the church," the man said, sternly.

Ben ran to Anna, who was waiting for him. He hugged her and said, "I'm sorry, Anna. You were right. The church was scary. I should have listened to you and Mom. Let's go home and never come back here."

Anna nodded and said, "It's okay, Ben. I'm glad you're safe. Let's go home and tell Mom what happened. Maybe she will give us a hug and a cookie."

They walked home, holding hands. They learned a lesson that day. They learned to respect the rules and to be careful of strangers. They also learned to listen to their sister and brother, who loved them and wanted them to be happy.
<|end|>


