<|asst|>
Tom and Mia are friends. They like to play in the park. One day, they have a picnic with their moms. They bring sandwiches, apples, and cookies. They sit on a big blanket and eat.

"Look, a ball!" Tom says. He sees a red ball near a tree. He runs to get it.

"Can I play too?" Mia asks. She follows Tom.

"Sure, let's kick the ball!" Tom says. He kicks the ball to Mia. Mia kicks it back. They have fun.

But then, an old man comes. He is angry. He has a cane. He says the ball is his.

"Hey, you kids, give me back my ball!" he shouts. He walks to Tom and Mia.

"Sorry, mister, we didn't know," Tom says. He gives the ball to the old man.

"Next time, ask before you take things," the old man says. He takes the ball and leaves.

Tom and Mia are sad. They go back to their moms.

"Don't worry, we have another ball," Mia's mom says. She takes out a blue ball from her bag.

"Really? Thank you!" Tom and Mia say. They smile.

They play with the blue ball. They forget about the old man. They have a happy picnic.
<|end|>


