<|asst|>
Lily and Ben were bored. They had played with all their toys and read all their books. They wanted to do something fun.

"Let's dance!" Lily said. She liked to dance and sing. She turned on the radio and found a happy song.

"OK!" Ben said. He liked to dance too. He followed Lily to the living room. They moved their arms and legs and jumped and spun.

They saw a big cushion on the sofa. It was soft and fluffy. Lily had an idea.

"Let's use the cushion as a stage!" she said. She put the cushion on the floor and climbed on it. She pretended to be a star.

"Wow, you are amazing!" Ben said. He clapped his hands. He wanted to join her. He took another cushion and put it next to hers. He climbed on it and danced with her.

They had so much fun. They danced and sang and laughed. They felt happy and free. They forgot they were bored. They made their own show.
<|end|>


