<|asst|>
Sara and Tom were playing in the garden. They saw a big hole in the ground. It was a well. Sara wanted to look inside.

"Can we see the water?" she asked Tom.

"I don't know. Maybe. Let's try," Tom said.

They went to the well and looked down. It was very dark. They could not see anything.

"Maybe there is a fairy in the well," Sara said.

"Or a monster," Tom said.

They were both scared and curious.

"Let's guess what is in the well," Sara said.

"OK. You go first," Tom said.

Sara thought for a moment.

"I guess there is a beautiful bird in the well. It has blue feathers and a yellow beak. It sings a nice song," she said.

Tom smiled.

"That sounds nice. But I guess there is a big frog in the well. It has green skin and a long tongue. It jumps and croaks," he said.

Sara made a face.

"That sounds gross. I don't like frogs," she said.

They both laughed.

They kept guessing what was in the well. They had fun. They forgot to be scared. They made up many stories. They did not know that there was nothing in the well. Only water and rocks. But they did not care. They used their imagination. And that was the best thing.
<|end|>


