<|asst|>
Ben and Lily liked to play in the farm. They liked to see the cows, the pigs and the chickens. They also liked to run and jump in the grass. But they did not like the well. The well was deep and dark and scary. Mama told them to stay away from the well.

One day, Ben and Lily were playing hide and seek. Ben was the seeker and Lily was the hider. Lily wanted to find a good hiding spot. She saw the well and thought it would be a good place to hide. She ran to the well and hid behind it. She was very quiet and cheerful. She thought Ben would never find her.

Ben looked for Lily everywhere. He looked in the barn, in the coop, in the shed. He could not find her. He started to get worried and sad. He yelled, "Lily, where are you? Come out, come out, please!" He heard a faint voice from behind the well. It was Lily. She said, "I'm here, Ben. I'm hiding behind the well."

Ben ran to the well and saw Lily. He was angry and scared. He yelled, "Lily, what are you doing? You know the well is dangerous. Mama told us to stay away from the well. You could have fallen in and hurt yourself. You are very naughty and silly."

Lily was sorry and scared. She did not mean to make Ben angry and scared. She did not know the well was so dangerous. She just wanted to have fun and win the game. She said, "I'm sorry, Ben. I didn't know. I won't do it again. Please don't be mad at me."

Ben hugged Lily and said, "I'm not mad at you, Lily. I'm just glad you are safe. I love you, Lily. You are my sister and my friend. Let's go back to Mama and tell her what happened. Maybe she will give us some cookies and milk."

Lily hugged Ben and said, "I love you, Ben. You are my brother and my friend. Let's go back to Mama and say sorry. Maybe she will be cheerful and not angry."

Ben and Lily held hands and walked back to the house. They learned their lesson and never played near the well again. They were happy and safe. Mama was cheerful and not angry. She gave them some cookies and milk and kissed them. They said thank you and ate their cookies and milk. They were good children. The end.
<|end|>


