Tom and Lily are twins. They like to play in the park. One day, they see a big rope hanging from a tree. Tom is curious. He wants to swing on the rope. Lily is scared. She thinks the rope is dangerous.

Tom runs to the rope. He grabs it with his hands. He feels happy. He swings back and forth. He laughs. Lily watches him. She feels worried. She calls him. "Tom, come back! The rope is not safe!"

Tom does not listen. He swings higher and higher. He feels brave. He lets go of the rope. He flies in the air. He feels free. He lands on the grass. He feels proud. He looks at Lily. He smiles.

Lily runs to Tom. She feels angry. She pushes him. He falls on the grass. He feels hurt. He cries. Lily feels sorry. She hugs him. He feels better. He hugs her back. They feel love. They say sorry. They play with the rope together. They feel fun.
<|end|>


