One day, a little boy named Tim went to the park with his mom. They saw a big bench near the swings. Tim's mom sat on the bench and watched Tim play.

Tim saw a girl named Sue on the swings. She looked sad. Tim asked, "Why are you sad, Sue?" Sue said, "I took my friend's toy and now I regret it. I feel sorry."

Tim thought for a moment and said, "You should give the toy back and say sorry. Then you will feel better." Sue nodded and went to find her friend.

Sue found her friend and gave back the toy. She said, "I am sorry I took your toy. I regret it." Her friend hugged her and said, "Thank you for saying sorry."

After that, Tim, Sue, and her friend played together. They had a great day at the park, and Sue learned that saying sorry can make things better.
<|end|>


