One day, a little boy named Tim found a rare bug. He was very happy. Tim wanted to tell his mom about the bug. He ran to her and said, "Mom, look! I found a rare bug!"

His mom looked at the bug and smiled. She said, "Wow, Tim! That's a special bug. It's not often we see one like that. It has a rare life."

Tim asked his mom, "What does 'rare' mean?" His mom told him, "Rare means not many like it. This bug has a special life."

Tim wanted to learn more about the rare bug. He asked his mom, "Can you tell me more about it?" His mom said, "I don't know much, but we can learn together."

So, Tim and his mom read a book about the rare bug. They learned a lot about its life. Tim was happy he could tell his mom about the rare bug.
<|end|>


