Once upon a time, in a big forest, there lived a graceful deer named Daisy. Daisy loved to play games with her friends. They would run, jump, and laugh all day long.

One sunny day, Daisy and her friends were playing a game of "carry the stick." Daisy's friend, Bobby the bunny, said, "Let's see who can carry the stick to the big tree the fastest!" All the animals got ready to race.

Daisy picked up the stick with her mouth and started running. She was so graceful and fast! Her friends cheered her on as she raced to the big tree. "Go Daisy, go!" they shouted.

Daisy reached the big tree first and won the game. Her friends gathered around and said, "Wow, Daisy! You carried the stick so fast and you looked so graceful doing it!" Daisy smiled and thanked her friends.

From that day on, Daisy and her friends played the "carry the stick" game every day. They had so much fun and loved spending time together in the big forest.
<|end|>


