Once upon a time, in a small town, there was a clumsy driver named Tom. Tom drove a big, red car. Every day, he would drive around the town, but sometimes he would bump into things.

One day, Tom was driving down the street when he saw a big tree. The tree had a long branch that was in the way. "Oh no," said Tom, "I need to cut the branch so I can keep driving." Tom got out of his car and took a small saw from the trunk.

Tom started to cut the branch, but it was hard work. A little boy named Tim saw Tom and wanted to help. "Can I help you, Tom?" asked Tim. Tom smiled and said, "Yes, Tim. You can hold the branch while I cut it."

Together, they cut the branch and moved it out of the way. Tom thanked Tim and got back in his car. From that day on, Tom tried to be more careful when driving, and he and Tim became good friends. They would always help each other when they needed it.
<|end|>


