One day, a little girl named Mia was playing in her room. It was very quiet. She had many toys, but her favorite was a doll named Lucy. Mia and Lucy were best friends. They played together all the time.

Mia noticed that Lucy was sad. "What's wrong, Lucy?" Mia asked. Lucy said, "I feel lonely. I want more friends to play with." Mia thought for a moment and then smiled. "I have an idea!" she said.

Mia took Lucy to the park. There, they met other kids with dolls. They all played together and had a great time. Lucy was happy again. Mia and Lucy made many new friends that day, and they all played together every day after that.
