The rain and the wind made loud noises, but Tim's mom and dad made it easy for him to feel brave. They played games and sang songs together. The hurricane went away, and the sun came out again.

After the storm, Tim, his mom, and his dad went outside to play. They jumped in the puddles and laughed. Tim was not scared of the rain anymore. He knew that with his mom and dad, everything would be okay.
