One day, a little boy named Tim went for a walk. He wanted to find something fun to do. The sun was shining and the sky was blue. It was a fine day.

As Tim walked, he saw a big tree. He wanted to resist climbing it, but it looked so fun. So, he started to climb the tree. When he reached the top, he saw a bird. The bird said, "Hello, I am going to the west. Do you want to come with me?"

Tim thought for a moment and said, "Yes, I want to go to the west too!" So, Tim climbed down the tree and followed the bird. They walked and walked until they found a big lake.

At the lake, they saw many fish and ducks. Tim and the bird had a great time playing by the water. As the sun began to set, they knew it was time to go home. They said goodbye and promised to meet again soon. Tim walked back home, happy with his new friend and the fun day they had.
