Once upon a time, there was a little boy named Tim. Tim had a rare toy, a microscope. He loved to look at things with it. He wanted to find a friend who had the same toy, so they could match and play together.

One day, Tim went to the park to find a friend. He saw a girl named Sue with a toy that looked like his microscope. Tim was very happy. He went to Sue and said, "We have the same toy! Let's play together!" Sue smiled and they started to play.

After they played for a while, Tim saw that Sue's toy was not a microscope, but a telescope. Tim was sad because they did not match. He told Sue, "Our toys are not the same, so I cannot play with you anymore." Sue was sad too, and they both went home.

The next day, Tim's mom told him that it was not nice to leave Sue just because their toys did not match. Tim felt bad and went back to the park to say sorry to Sue. But Sue was not there. Tim never saw Sue again and he was very sad.

The moral of the story is to not judge friends by what they have, but by who they are.
<|end|>


