Once upon a time, in a small town, there lived a little boy named Tim. Tim was a good boy who liked to listen to his mom and dad. One day, it was very hot outside, so Tim's mom said, "Tim, please stay inside today. It is too hot to play outside."

Tim listened to his mom and stayed inside. He played with his toys and read his books. As he was playing, he heard an alarm coming from the kitchen. Tim ran to see what was happening. His mom was cooking, and the alarm was telling her that the food was ready. "Mom, what is that noise?" Tim asked. His mom said, "That is the alarm, Tim. It tells me when the food is cooked."

Tim was curious about the alarm, so he asked his mom if he could listen to it again. His mom agreed and showed him how the alarm worked. She said, "Tim, remember to always listen to the alarm. It can help keep us safe."

Later that day, Tim and his mom went to the store. As they were shopping, they heard an alarm. Tim remembered what his mom said and knew that they needed to listen to the alarm. They quickly left the store, and it turned out there was a small fire in the back. Because they listened to the alarm, they were safe.

The moral of the story is to always listen to alarms and to the people who care for you. They can help keep you safe and happy.
