One day, a little boy named Tim went to the park with his mom. Tim had a small cart that he wanted to pack with toys to play with. He put his ball, his toy car, and his teddy bear in the cart.

At the park, Tim met a girl named Sue. Sue had a big, filthy toy truck. "Can I play with your truck?" Tim asked. Sue said, "Only if I can play with your toys in your cart."

Tim didn't want Sue to play with his toys because her truck was filthy, and he didn't want his toys to get dirty. He said, "No, thank you. My toys don't want to get dirty."

Sue was sad, but Tim had an idea. He said, "Let's clean your truck, and then we can play together." They found a water tap and cleaned the truck. After that, Tim and Sue played with their toys, and they became good friends.
<|end|>


