Once upon a time, in a small house, there lived a little boy named Tim. Tim had a big, heavy chair in his room. He loved to sit on it and read his favorite books. One day, as he was playing with his ball, he had an idea. He wanted to throw the ball at the chair to see what would happen.

"Mom, can I throw my ball at the heavy chair?" Tim asked. His mom thought for a moment and said, "No, Tim. Throwing the ball at the chair might break it, and then you won't have a place to sit and read your books."

Tim was sad, but he listened to his mom. Instead of throwing the ball at the chair, he went outside and threw the ball with his friends. They had so much fun playing together. Tim learned that it was better to play with his friends and take care of his things.

The moral of the story is to listen to your parents and take care of your belongings.
<|end|>


