One day, a boy named Tim wanted to sail on a boat. He asked his mom, "Can I sail on the boat today?" His mom said, "Yes, but be careful."

Tim went to the river and saw a boat. He got in and started to sail. The wind was strong, and the boat went fast. Tim was having a lot of fun.

As he sailed, he saw a big fish jump out of the water. The fish said, "You are sailing too fast, and that is stupid!" Tim laughed and said, "I will slow down." He sailed slower and saw more fish and birds.

When Tim got home, he told his mom about his adventure. His mom said, "Let's make a video of you telling your story." They made a video, and Tim was happy. He learned that it's important to be safe and not do stupid things while sailing.
<|end|>


