One day, a little reindeer named Remy was walking in the forest. He saw a blue bird sitting on a tree. The bird was sad because it did not understand how to fly.

"Hi, bird! Why are you sad?" Remy asked. The blue bird looked at Remy and said, "I don't understand how to fly. Can you help me?"

Remy wanted to help the blue bird. He thought for a moment and said, "I can't fly, but I have an idea. Let's ask my friend, the wise owl. He can help you understand how to fly."

Remy and the blue bird went to find the wise owl. The owl listened to the bird's problem and said, "To fly, you need to flap your wings fast and jump!"

The blue bird tried to do what the owl said. It flapped its wings fast and jumped. The bird started to fly! The blue bird was so happy and said, "Thank you, Remy and wise owl! Now I understand how to fly!"

Remy was happy to help his new friend. They all played together in the forest, and the blue bird flew high in the sky.
<|end|>


