Once upon a time, there was a little child named Tim. Tim loved to run and play outside. One day, Tim saw a butterfly and wanted to catch it. He tried and tried, but he couldn't catch the butterfly. Tim felt frustrated.

Tim's mom saw him and asked, "What's wrong, Tim?" Tim said, "I want to catch the butterfly, but I can't." His mom smiled and said, "Let's try together."

So, Tim and his mom tried to catch the butterfly. They ran and ran, but the butterfly was too fast. Tim was still frustrated, but his mom said, "Don't worry, Tim. We can try again tomorrow."

The next day, Tim and his mom went outside to catch the butterfly. This time, they were ready. They ran and ran, and finally, they caught the butterfly. Tim was so happy, and he said, "Thank you, mom!"

From that day on, Tim and his mom always played together, and they caught many more butterflies. Tim was not frustrated anymore, and they both had a lot of fun.
<|end|>


