Once upon a time, in a sunny park, there was a little dog named Buddy. Buddy had a big, happy face and a dry, waggy tail. He loved to play and run all day long.

One day, Buddy met a new friend, a rabbit named Rosie. Rosie had long ears and a cute, twitchy nose. Buddy and Rosie decided to have a race to see who was the fastest.

"Ready, set, go!" shouted Buddy, and they started to race. Buddy ran as fast as he could, and Rosie hopped as quickly as her little legs would go. They raced all the way to the big tree at the end of the park.

Buddy and Rosie were both very fast, but Rosie hopped just a little bit faster. They both reached the big tree, tired and out of breath. "Good race, Rosie!" said Buddy, with a big smile on his face. "You're very fast!"

From that day on, Buddy and Rosie were the best of friends. They played and raced together every day, and their happy faces could be seen all over the park. And they lived happily ever after.
<|end|>


