Once upon a time, there was an enormous cauliflower. It lived in a big garden with many other vegetables. The cauliflower had lots of friends like carrots, peas, and potatoes. They all played together in the garden every day.

One day, the cauliflower saw a little girl named Lily. Lily was walking in the garden with her mom. The cauliflower wanted to be friends with Lily. It thought of a plan to remind Lily to come back to the garden and play with it.

The next day, the cauliflower asked its friends to help. They all worked together to make a big, beautiful flower out of their leaves. When Lily came to the garden with her mom, she saw the flower and smiled. The flower reminded her of the fun she had in the garden.

Lily came back to the garden every day to play with the cauliflower and its friends. They had so much fun together, and the enormous cauliflower was very happy to have a new friend in Lily. And Lily always remembered to visit the garden because of the special flower that reminded her of her vegetable friends.
<|end|>


