Once upon a time, there was a swan named Sam. Sam was not very smart, and his friends would call him stupid. Sam did not like it when his friends called him that. One day, Sam wanted to show his friends that he could do something great.

Sam saw his friends building a big nest. They were using sticks, leaves, and mud. Sam wanted to help, but his friends said, "No, Sam, you are too stupid to help us." Sam felt sad, but he had an idea.

Sam went to find his own sticks, leaves, and mud. He started to build his own nest. It was hard work, but Sam did not give up. He wanted to finish his nest and show his friends that he was not stupid. 

As Sam was working, his friend Sue came to see him. She saw Sam's nest and said, "Wow, Sam, you are not stupid! You can build a nest too!" Sam smiled and said, "Thank you, Sue. I just needed to try."

In the end, Sam finished his nest, and his friends were proud of him. They never called him stupid again. Sam showed them that he could do great things, just like them.
<|end|>


