Once upon a time, there was a cheerful sailor named Tom. Tom had a big boat with a large sail. He loved to sail on the blue sea with his friends.

One sunny day, Tom and his friends were sailing when they saw a little bird with a hurt wing. The bird could not fly. Tom said to his friends, "We must help this little bird. Let's support it and make it feel better."

Tom's friends agreed, and they all worked together to take care of the bird. They gave it food and a safe place to rest on the boat. The bird felt much better, and soon it could fly again.

Before the bird flew away, it said, "Thank you, Tom and friends, for supporting me. You are all very kind." Tom and his friends felt happy, and they continued to sail on the sea, always ready to help when needed.
