Once upon a time, there was a happy dolphin named Dolly. Dolly loved to swim and play in the big blue ocean. One day, Dolly saw a big wave coming towards her. She swam as fast as she could and dove under the wave. It was so much fun!

Dolly had a friend named Danny who was not as dependable as Dolly. Danny would often cancel their playdates or forget to show up. Dolly didn't like that. She wanted a friend who she could always count on. 

One day, Dolly met a new dolphin named Daisy. Daisy was very kind and always showed up when she said she would. Dolly was so happy to have a dependable friend like Daisy. They swam and played together every day, diving under the waves and having a blast. From that day on, Dolly knew that she could always depend on Daisy to be there for her. The end.
