Once upon a time, there was a little girl named Lily. She lived in a house with her mommy and daddy. One day, Lily heard a noise coming from the backyard. She went to check it out and saw a wild rabbit running around. Lily thought it was so cute and wanted to play with it.

But her mommy told her that wild animals can be dangerous and it's better to stay away from them. Lily was sad, but she listened to her mommy. Later that day, Lily's daddy came home and told her a story about a boy who didn't listen to his mommy and tried to play with a wild animal. The animal didn't like it and bit the boy. Lily learned that it's important to listen to her mommy and daddy.

The next day, Lily saw the wild rabbit again. But this time, she remembered what her daddy told her and didn't try to play with it. Instead, she watched it from a safe distance. Lily felt proud of herself for being a good listener and not lying to her parents about playing with the wild animal.
