Once upon a time, there was a chicken named Penny. Penny lived on a farm with other animals. One day, Penny saw a new chicken on the farm. It was unknown to her. 

Penny went to the new chicken and said, "Hi, I'm Penny. Who are you?" The new chicken said, "I'm Ruby. Nice to meet you." Penny and Ruby became friends. 

One day, all the animals had a race. Penny and Ruby wanted to race too. They were both nervous because they had never raced before. But they encouraged each other and said, "Let's do our best!" 

In the end, Penny and Ruby didn't win the race, but they had fun and learned that it's important to try your best and have fun, even if you don't win. They also learned that making new friends, like they did, is always a good thing.
