Once upon a time, there was a little girl named Lily. She loved to play with her colorful toys and run around outside. One day, she saw some other children playing together and wanted to join in. But they said she couldn't play because she didn't have a mother to unite with them.

Lily felt sad because she missed her mother who had passed away. She went to her room and cried. Suddenly, she heard a knock on the door. It was her grandmother who came to visit her. Lily's grandmother told her that she could be her mother for the day and they could unite with the other children.

Lily was so happy and ran outside to play with her grandmother and the other children. They all had so much fun playing together and Lily felt like she had a new family. She realized that even though her mother was gone, she still had people who loved her and would unite with her.
