Once upon a time, there was a little girl named Lily. She loved going for walks with her mommy and daddy. One day, they walked past a mailbox that looked fake. Lily thought it was funny and wanted to lean on it. 

But as soon as she did, the mailbox fell over and crushed her foot. She cried and cried until her mommy and daddy came to help her. They took her to the hospital, but the doctors couldn't fix her foot. 

Lily had to wear a cast for a very long time and couldn't play with her friends like she used to. She learned that sometimes things that look fake can still be dangerous. From then on, she never leaned on anything without making sure it was safe first.
