Once upon a time, there was a big brown dog named Max. Max loved to run and play in the park with his friends. One day, Max hurt his leg while playing with his ball. His leg felt tough and sore. 

Max's owner, a kind lady named Sarah, took him to the vet. The vet said that Max needed to rest his leg and eat good food to make it better. Sarah decided to cook a special meal for Max. She made him some chicken with soft vegetables and rice. 

Max loved the meal and he felt much better after eating it. He rested his leg for a few days and soon he was able to run and play again with his friends. From that day on, Sarah made sure to cook healthy food for Max so that he would always be strong and healthy.
