Once upon a time, there was a humble man named Jack. Jack lived in a small house with his wife and their cat, Mr. Whiskers. One day, Jack found an old chest in the attic. He opened it and saw a shiny necklace inside. Jack showed the necklace to his wife and said, "Look at this! It's beautiful!" His wife replied, "We should sell it and make some money." Jack agreed and took the necklace to a pawn shop. 

The pawnbroker looked at the necklace and said, "This is worth a lot of money. I will give you $500 for it." Jack was happy and took the money. But, as he was leaving the pawn shop, the necklace vanished from his pocket! Jack looked around but it was nowhere to be found. He went back to the pawnbroker, but he didn't believe Jack's story. Jack went home empty-handed and sad. 

When Jack told his wife what happened, she got angry and said, "You should have been more careful with the necklace! Now we have lost all that money." Jack felt terrible and wished he had never found the chest in the first place. The end.
<|end|>


