Once upon a time, there was a little boy named Timmy. Timmy loved playing with his toy cars, but he had a problem. His toy box was too full, and he couldn't find his favorite car. 

One day, Timmy's dad came into his room and said, "Timmy, let's load up all your toys into a big box and put them in the attic. Then, we can bring down your toy box and fill it with your favorite cars." Timmy thought this was amazing and helped his dad put all his toys into the big box. 

After they loaded up the box, Timmy's dad said, "Let's drain the water from the bathtub before we put your toy box in there." Timmy didn't understand why they needed to drain the water, but he helped his dad anyway. 

Later that day, Timmy's dad brought down the toy box filled with his favorite cars. Timmy was so happy and thanked his dad for helping him find his favorite car. His dad smiled and said, "I told you it was amazing what we could do if we worked together."
