Once upon a time, there was a man who had a big axe. The axe was very flexible and could cut through anything. One day, the man went into the forest to chop some wood. He swung his axe and it hit a tree. Suddenly, the axe flew out of his hand and hit him on the foot. He cried out in pain.

A little girl who was walking in the forest heard the man crying. She went over to him and asked what happened. The man told her that his axe had hit him on the foot. The little girl said, "You should be careful with your axe. It's very dangerous." The man said, "You're right. I will be more careful from now on."

But the man didn't listen to the little girl. He picked up his axe and started chopping again. This time, the axe flew out of his hand and hit him on the head. He cried out again, but this time he didn't get up. The little girl ran to get help, but it was too late. The man had died from his injuries. The little girl cried and cried because she was sad that the man had died.
