Once upon a time, there was a little girl named Lily. She had a diary where she wrote all her secrets and feelings. One day, Lily's friend, Tommy, came to play. Tommy saw the diary and wanted to read it. 

Lily said, "No, Tommy. That's my diary. It's kind of you to ask, but it's private." 

Tommy paused and thought about what Lily said. He realized that he wouldn't want someone to read his diary either. 

"I'm sorry, Lily. You're right. It's important to be kind and respect other people's things," said Tommy. 

Lily smiled and said, "It's okay, Tommy. I forgive you. Let's play together instead." 

The moral of the story is that it's important to be kind and respect other people's things, even if we're curious.
<|end|>


