Once upon a time, there was a sailor named Jack. He had a gray boat and he loved to sail. One day, Jack went to the store to buy a present for his friend, Lily. He wanted to wrap it nicely.

At the store, Jack met a little girl named Sarah. Sarah asked Jack, "What are you buying?" Jack said, "I am buying a present for my friend, Lily. It's a surprise!" Sarah said, "I love surprises. Can I help you wrap it?" Jack said, "That's very kind of you. Thank you!"

Together, Jack and Sarah wrapped the present with pretty paper and a bow. Jack was very happy with how it looked. He said, "Thank you for your help, Sarah. Lily will love it!" Sarah smiled and said, "I'm happy to help. Bye-bye, Jack!" Jack waved goodbye and sailed away on his gray boat.
