Once upon a time, there was a little girl named Lily. She loved to read books with her mommy every night before bed. One day, while they were reading a story about a princess, Lily's leg started to hurt. She said, "Mommy, my leg hurts." Her mommy looked at her leg and saw a big scratch. It was filthy and needed to be cleaned.

Lily's mommy said, "Let's go clean your leg and then we can finish reading the story." So, they went to the bathroom and washed Lily's leg with soap and water. After it was clean, they went back to Lily's room to continue reading. Lily was happy because her leg didn't hurt anymore and she could enjoy the story.

As they were reading, Lily's mommy asked her, "Do you want to be a princess like the one in the story?" Lily replied, "Yes, I want to wear a pretty dress and have a crown on my head." Her mommy smiled and said, "You already are a princess to me, even without a fancy dress or a crown." Lily felt happy and loved as they finished reading the story together.
