Once upon a time, there was a big worm who lived in a garden. He loved to wriggle and squirm in the dirt all day long. One day, he saw a big apple on a tree and wanted to eat it. But the apple was too high up and he couldn't reach it.

The worm thought and thought about how he could get the apple. Suddenly, he saw a big leaf on the ground. He thought he could use it to climb the tree. So, he crawled onto the leaf and started to climb. But as he climbed, the leaf slipped and he fell down to the ground.

The worm was sad and frustrated. But then he had an idea. He crawled over to a group of ants and asked for their help. The ants were happy to help and together they climbed up the tree and got the apple. The worm was so happy and grateful that he shared the apple with all the ants. From that day on, they were all friends and helped each other whenever they needed it.
<|end|>


