Once upon a time, there was a little girl named Lily. She loved to play outside in the garden. One day, while she was playing, she noticed a fairy sitting on a flower. The fairy had unusual wings that sparkled in the sun.

Lily ran to her mommy and said, "Mommy, look! A fairy with pretty wings!" Her mommy smiled and said, "That's nice, Lily."

Lily went back to the garden to play, but she accidentally stepped on the fairy's flower. The fairy got angry and said, "You ruined my home! Now I will curse you!" Lily didn't know what a curse was, but she could tell it wasn't good.

The next day, Lily woke up with a rash all over her body. Her mommy took her to the doctor, but they couldn't find a cure. Lily felt very sad and wished she hadn't stepped on the fairy's flower.
<|end|>


