"It means you can do things by yourself, like chew your food and brush your teeth," his mommy explained. 

Timmy was excited to be independent. He wanted to try chewing his food all by himself. So, at dinner that night, he picked up his spoon and tried to chew his food. It was hard at first, but he kept trying. And soon enough, he was chewing like a big boy. 

"Good job, Timmy!" his mommy said. "You're growing up so fast." Timmy smiled and felt proud of himself. He couldn't wait to be even more independent.
