Once upon a time, there was a little duck named Muffin. Muffin loved to play in the water. Every day, Muffin would go to the pond and splash around with his friends.

One day, Muffin met a new friend named Bitter. Bitter was a small fish who lived in the pond. They played together all day. Muffin would splash and Bitter would jump high in the air.

"Let's play a game," said Muffin to Bitter. "I will splash and you try to jump over the water I make." Bitter agreed and they had lots of fun playing their new game.

As the sun started to go down, Muffin and Bitter said goodbye to each other. They promised to play together again the next day. Muffin went home to his family and told them all about his new friend and the fun game they played.

From that day on, Muffin and Bitter were the best of friends. They played together every day, splashing and jumping in the pond. And they lived happily ever after.
<|end|>


