Once upon a time, in a small town, there was a little girl named Lucy. She loved to gather pretty rocks and shiny things. One day, while she was playing outside, she saw a strange figure. It was a big, scary animal with sharp teeth. Lucy knew it was dangerous, so she hid behind a tree.

The dangerous animal saw Lucy and said, "Hello, little girl. I am not here to hurt you. I am looking for my lost baby. Can you help me find her?" Lucy thought for a moment and then said, "Okay, but we have to be careful."

Lucy and the dangerous animal walked together, gathering clues to find the lost baby. They saw footprints and broken branches, and they followed them. They walked and walked until they found the baby, safe and sound.

The dangerous animal hugged her baby and said, "Thank you, Lucy, for helping me find my baby. You are very brave." Lucy smiled and said, "You're welcome. I'm glad we could help each other." And from that day on, Lucy and the dangerous animal became the best of friends.
<|end|>


