One day, a girl named Sue and her dog, Max, went to the river. They saw a raft made of wood. It was tight and strong. They wanted to go on an adventure.

Sue and Max got on the raft. They floated down the river. They saw fish and birds. The sun was shining, and the water was calm. Sue said, "Max, let's mix things up and race with the fish!"

Max barked, and they started to paddle fast. They raced with the fish and won. They laughed and had so much fun.

At the end of the day, Sue and Max went back home. They were tired but happy. They had a great adventure on the tight raft and loved to mix things up. They couldn't wait for their next fun day at the river.
