Once upon a time, there was a wise old owl. He lived in a wide tree in the forest. The owl was known for his wisdom. All the animals would come to him when they needed help.

One day, a little squirrel came to the owl. He wanted to pick the best nuts to store for winter. The wise owl told the squirrel to look for the wide tree with the most nuts. The squirrel thanked the wise owl and went to find the tree.

The squirrel found the wide tree and started to pick the nuts. He picked and picked until he had enough for the winter. The squirrel was very happy and grateful for the owl's wisdom. Thanks to the wise owl, the squirrel and his family had a warm and cozy winter.
