One day, a little girl named Mia found a bottle of lotion. She thought it looked harmless, so she picked it up to look at it. The bottle was very pretty, with a picture of a happy sun on it. Mia liked the sun, so she thought the lotion must be good too.

Mia took the lotion to her mom and asked if she could use it. Her mom said yes, but told her to only use a little bit. Mia was excited and put some lotion on her hands. She rubbed it all over her face and arms. It felt nice and cool on her skin.

Later, Mia went outside to play in the sun. She noticed that her skin did not feel hot and itchy like it usually did. Mia was happy that she had used the lotion. She learned that it is important to listen to her mom and that some things, like the harmless lotion, can help keep her safe and happy.
