One day, a little girl named Lucy was walking to school. She had a big math book in her bag. Lucy loved math because she liked to count and add numbers. The sky was pale blue with big, white clouds.

While walking, Lucy saw a small cat. The cat was lost and did not know where to go. Lucy wanted to help the cat find its home. She picked up the cat and put it in her bag with the math book.

Lucy walked around asking people if they knew the cat. Finally, an old lady said the cat was hers. She was so happy to see her cat again. Lucy gave the cat back to the old lady, and they both smiled. Then, Lucy went to school to learn more math.
