Once upon a time, there was a boy named Tim. Tim was an honest boy who always told the truth. One day, Tim went for a walk near a creek. The water in the creek was clear and cold. Tim liked to watch the fish and the frogs.

As Tim walked by the creek, he saw a pretty flower. He wanted to pick it for his mom. Tim kneeled down to get a closer look at the flower. It was red and smelled nice. He knew his mom would love it.

Tim picked the flower and went back home. He gave the flower to his mom and told her about the creek. His mom was happy and proud of her honest boy. They hugged and smiled, and Tim felt good about his day by the creek.
