One day, a mole was trying to balance on a log. The mole was very serious about it. He wanted to show his friends that he could do it. He tried and tried, but it was hard. The log was big and the mole was small.

A bird saw the mole and asked, "What are you doing, little mole?" The mole looked up and said, "I am trying to balance on this log. I want to show my friends that I can do it." The bird thought for a moment and then said, "I can help you. I can hold your hand, so you don't fall."

The mole was happy and said, "Yes, please help me." The bird held the mole's hand and together they balanced on the log. The mole was so proud of himself. He thanked the bird and they became good friends. From that day on, they played and balanced on logs together, always helping each other.
