Once upon a time, there was a little crab named Tim. Tim was a very independent crab. He loved to play near the shore all by himself. One sunny day, Tim met a new friend, a small fish named Finn.

Finn asked, "Do you want to play with me?" Tim thought for a moment and then he shrugged. "Okay, let's play together," he said. They played in the water and had lots of fun.

As the sun began to set, Tim and Finn said goodbye. They promised to meet at the shore again soon. Tim learned that even independent crabs can have fun with friends. And from that day on, Tim and Finn became the best of friends.
