One day, a little girl named Lucy found a big scale in her house. She did not know what it was for. She asked her mom, "What is this big thing?" Her mom said, "That is a scale. We use it to see how heavy things are."

Lucy thought the scale was perfect to play with. She put her toys on the scale and watched the numbers go up and down. But her little brother, Tim, wanted to play too. He tried to put his toys on the scale, but Lucy did not want to share. She ignored Tim when he asked to play.

Tim was sad and went to tell their mom. Their mom told Lucy, "You should share the scale with Tim. It is not nice to ignore him." Lucy felt bad and went to find Tim. She said, "I am sorry, Tim. Let's play with the scale together." They played with the scale and had a lot of fun. From that day on, they always shared their toys and played together.
