One day, a boy named Tim went to the woods with his dad. They wanted to find wood for their fire. Tim's dad had an axe to cut the wood. The woods were mild and nice. Tim saw a squirrel and wanted to play with it.

"Look, Dad! A squirrel!" Tim said, pointing at the furry animal. Tim's dad smiled and nodded. Tim tried to make the squirrel come to him, but it was too shy. Tim's dad told him to be slow and quiet, so the squirrel would not be scared.

As they walked, they found a big tree. Tim's dad started to cut it with the axe. Tim saw a branch that was low. He wanted to shoot it with his toy bow and arrow. He pulled the string back and let go. The arrow flew and hit the branch. Tim was very happy.

"Great shot, Tim!" his dad said, proud of his son. They took the wood home and made a warm fire. Tim and his dad sat by the fire, talking about their fun day in the woods.
