Fin held Shell in his mouth and swam to the water. He was careful not to swim too fast, so Shell would not be scared. When they reached the water, Shell was so happy she could swim again. She thanked Fin, and they became best friends. They swam together in the light blue water, having fun and playing with their other friends.
