Once upon a time, there was a little yellow bird. The bird was very happy and loved to fly around. One day, the bird saw a big tree and wanted to sit on its branch.

The little yellow bird was ready to fly to the tree, but it started to worry. "What if I can't fly that high?" the bird thought. But the bird knew it had to try, so it took a deep breath and flew up to the tree.

When the little yellow bird reached the tree, it was so happy! It sat on the branch and sang a pretty song. The bird was proud of itself for not letting worry stop it from trying. From that day on, the little yellow bird knew it could do anything it set its mind to.
