Lily and Ben are in school. They like to draw on the blackboard with chalk. They make flowers and cars and stars. But today, Lily is sad. She has a hurt on her knee. She fell down in the park and scraped it.

Ben sees Lily's hurt and says, "Oh no, Lily, your knee is red and ouchy. Does it hurt a lot?"

Lily nods and says, "Yes, it hurts a lot. I want to go home and see Mommy. She can make it better."

Ben says, "I have an idea. Why don't we draw a big heart on the blackboard and tell the teacher that it is for Lily's knee? Maybe that will make her feel better."

Lily smiles and says, "That is a good idea, Ben. You are a good friend. Let's do it."

They take the chalk and draw a big heart on the blackboard. They write "For Lily's knee" inside the heart. They are very proud of their drawing. They wait for the teacher to come and see it.

The teacher comes and sees the heart on the blackboard. She says, "Wow, what a beautiful heart! Who made it?"

Lily and Ben raise their hands and say, "We did, teacher. It is for Lily's knee. She has a hurt and we want to make her feel better."

The teacher smiles and says, "That is very sweet of you, Lily and Ben. You are very kind and caring. I'm sure Lily's knee will heal soon. But just in case, let me put a band-aid on it. That will help too."

She takes a band-aid from her desk and puts it on Lily's knee. Lily says, "Thank you, teacher. That feels better."

The teacher says, "You're welcome, Lily. And thank you, Ben, for being a good friend. Now, why don't you both show me your other drawings on the blackboard? I'm sure they are wonderful too."

Lily and Ben are happy. They show the teacher their flowers and cars and stars. They forget about the hurt and have fun. They like to draw on the blackboard with chalk.
<|end|>


