Lila loves her bracelet. It is pink and shiny and has many beads. She wears it every day. It makes her feel comfortable and happy.

One day, Lila goes to the park with her mom. She sees a big sandbox. She wants to play with the sand. She takes off her bracelet and puts it on a bench. She runs to the sandbox and fills a bucket with sand. She makes a castle with the sand.

"Look, mom, I made a castle!" she says.

Mom smiles and says, "That's very nice, Lila. You are very good at making castles."

Lila feels proud. She wants to show her bracelet to mom. She runs back to the bench. But her bracelet is not there. She looks around. She does not see her bracelet. She feels sad and scared.

"Mom, mom, where is my bracelet?" she cries.

Mom comes to the bench. She hugs Lila and says, "Don't worry, Lila. We will find your bracelet. Maybe someone took it by mistake. Let's ask the other kids in the park."

They walk around the park and ask the other kids. They see a boy with a blue shirt. He has Lila's bracelet on his wrist. He is playing with a ball.

"Excuse me, boy, is that your bracelet?" mom asks.

The boy looks at his wrist. He says, "No, I found it on the bench. I thought it was pretty. Can I keep it?"

Mom says, "No, you can't. That bracelet belongs to Lila. She loves it very much. She is very sad that you took it. Please give it back to her."

The boy feels sorry. He says, "I'm sorry, Lila. I didn't know it was yours. Here, you can have it back."

He gives the bracelet to Lila. Lila smiles and says, "Thank you, boy. You are very nice."

She puts the bracelet on her wrist. She feels comfortable and happy again.

Mom says, "Thank you, boy, for being honest and kind. You did the right thing."

The boy says, "You're welcome, mom. I'm sorry for making Lila sad. Can we be friends?"

Lila says, "Yes, we can be friends. Do you want to play with me in the sandbox?"

The boy says, "Yes, I do. I like sand. Can I help you make a castle?"

Lila says, "Yes, you can. Come on, let's go."

They run to the sandbox and fill another bucket with sand. They make a bigger castle with the sand. They have fun together. Mom watches them and smiles. She is glad that Lila found her bracelet and made a new friend.
<|end|>


