Ben and Lily were at the beach with their mom and dad. They liked to play in the sand and splash in the water. Sometimes they saw fish and crabs and shells.

One day, the sky became dark and the wind became strong. Mom and dad said it was a hurricane and they had to go home. Ben and Lily were scared and sad. They wanted to stay at the beach.

"Can we take one more dive, please?" Ben asked.

"No, Ben, it's too dangerous. The waves are big and the water is angry. We have to go now," dad said.

"But I want to see the fish one more time," Lily said.

"Lily, you can't hear the fish. You are deaf. You have to use your eyes and your hands to talk to them. But now is not the time. The hurricane can hurt you and the fish. We have to go now," mom said.

Ben and Lily nodded. They loved their mom and dad and they trusted them. They grabbed their toys and followed them to the car. They looked back at the beach and waved goodbye to the fish. They hoped the fish would be safe and happy. They hoped they would see them again.
<|end|>


