Tom and Anna are friends. They like to play in the park. They see a big fish tank with many fish. The fish tank has a sign that says "Oxygen". Tom and Anna do not know what oxygen is.

"Look at the fish, Anna. They are so pretty. Do you think they can talk?" Tom asks.

"I don't know, Tom. Maybe they can talk to each other. But we cannot hear them. They are in the water." Anna says.

"Maybe they need oxygen to talk. Like we need air to talk." Tom says.

"Maybe. But what is oxygen?" Anna asks.

Tom and Anna see a man who works at the park. He is wearing a blue shirt and a hat. He is feeding the fish.

"Excuse me, sir. What is oxygen?" Tom asks.

The man smiles and kneels down to talk to Tom and Anna.

"Oxygen is a very important thing, kids. It is in the air we breathe. It helps us live and talk. The fish also need oxygen, but they get it from the water. The water has oxygen too, but not as much as the air. That's why the fish tank has a machine that makes bubbles. The bubbles give more oxygen to the water and the fish." The man explains.

"Wow, that is very interesting. Thank you, sir." Tom says.

"Yes, thank you. You are very smart." Anna says.

The man laughs and says, "You are very welcome, kids. You are very curious and polite. I'm glad you like the fish. They are very beautiful and special. But remember, they are also very poor. They cannot leave the fish tank. They cannot see the sky or the trees or the flowers. They cannot play with other animals. They only have each other. So we have to be kind and respectful to them. We have to take care of them and their oxygen. Okay?"

"Okay, sir. We understand. We will be kind and respectful to the fish. We will not touch them or make noise or throw things at them. We will just watch them and learn from them." Tom and Anna say.

"Good. That's very nice of you. I'm sure the fish appreciate it. Now, have fun and enjoy the park. But don't forget to breathe. Oxygen is good for you too." The man says.

Tom and Anna wave goodbye to the man and the fish. They go to play on the swings and the slide. They breathe the fresh air and feel happy. They have learned something new today. They have learned about oxygen.
<|end|>


