<|asst|>
Lily had a hurt arm. She fell from the swing and cried a lot. Mom took her to the doctor. The doctor was nice and had a white coat.

The doctor said, "Lily, I need to see inside your arm. I have a special machine that can do that. It is called an x-ray. It will not hurt you, I promise. But you need to be very still and let me take a picture of your arm. Can you do that?"

Lily nodded. She was scared, but she wanted her arm to feel better. Mom held her hand and said, "You are very brave, Lily. I am proud of you."

The doctor put Lily's arm on a table and covered it with a soft cloth. Then he moved a big machine over her arm. It made a funny noise. Lily closed her eyes and did not move.

The doctor said, "All done, Lily. You did great. Let me show you the picture of your arm." He took a paper from the machine and showed it to Lily and Mom. It had a black and white image of Lily's arm, with bones and shapes.

The doctor said, "See, Lily, this is your arm. And this is where it is broken. You need a cast to help it heal. A cast is a hard bandage that will keep your arm in place. You can choose the color you like. And you can have your friends sign it and draw on it. How does that sound?"

Lily smiled. She liked the idea of a cast. She said, "Can I have a pink cast, please?"

The doctor said, "Of course, Lily. Pink is a lovely color. Let me get it for you." He went to get the cast and came back with a roll of pink material. He wrapped it around Lily's arm and made it smooth and hard.

Lily looked at her arm and said, "Wow, it looks cool. Thank you, doctor."

The doctor said, "You are very welcome, Lily. You are a strong and brave girl. Now you need to rest and take care of your arm. And you can show it to your friends and family. They will love it."

Lily hugged Mom and said, "Thank you, Mom. I love you."

Mom said, "I love you too, Lily. You are my sweet girl." They left the doctor's office and went home. Lily felt better and was happy with her pink cast.
<|end|>


