Tom and Sam are friends. They like to play with trucks and cars. One day, they see a big truck with many barrels on it. The truck stops near their house.

"Wow, look at the truck!" Tom says. "It has so many barrels. What are they for?"

"I don't know," Sam says. "Maybe they have water or juice or something inside. Let's go and see."

They run to the truck and see a man with a hat and a shirt. He is the driver. He is taking the barrels off the truck and putting them on a cart.

"Hello, sir," Tom says. "What are you doing with the barrels?"

"Hello, boys," the man says. "I am delivering the barrels to the store. They have different things inside. Some have apples, some have oranges, some have bananas. Do you like fruits?"

"Yes, we do," Sam says. "We like apples and oranges and bananas. Can we have some?"

"Sure, you can," the man says. "But you have to help me first. Can you help me push the cart to the store? It is very heavy."

"OK, we can help you," Tom says. "We are strong. We can push the cart."

They help the man push the cart to the store. The man gives them each a barrel with fruits inside. They say thank you and goodbye to the man. They take the barrels to their house and share the fruits with their families. They are happy and full. They like to deliver barrels.
<|end|>


