<|asst|>
Lily likes to write. She has a big box of crayons and many sheets of paper. She writes her name, her mom's name, and her dog's name. She writes big and small, red and blue, happy and sad.

One day, Lily wants to write a story. She thinks of a story about a princess and a dragon. She writes the first word: "Once". Then she thinks of the next word. But she does not know how to write it. She tries to remember, but she cannot. She feels angry and sad.

She asks her mom for help. "Mom, how do you write 'upon'?" she says. Her mom is busy in the kitchen. She says, "Not now, Lily. I'm making dinner. You can write later." Lily does not like this answer. She says, "But I want to write now! Please, mom, help me!"

Her mom sighs and comes to Lily. She sees the sheet of paper with the word "Once". She says, "Lily, this is not how you write 'once'. You forgot the 'e' at the end. And you wrote it backwards. This is a stupid way to write." She takes the crayon from Lily and writes "Once" the right way.

Lily feels hurt and angry. She does not like her mom's word. She says, "No, mom, you are stupid! This is my story, and I can write it any way I want!" She snatches the crayon and the sheet of paper from her mom. She tears the paper in half and throws it on the floor. She runs to her room and slams the door.

Her mom feels sorry and sad. She did not mean to hurt Lily's feelings. She knows Lily is trying to write. She goes to Lily's room and knocks on the door. She says, "Lily, I'm sorry. I did not mean to call your writing stupid. I was just trying to help you. Can I come in and talk to you?" She waits for Lily to answer. She hopes Lily will forgive her and write again.
<|end|>


