Lila and Sam loved to look at the stars at night. They would lie on a big blanket in the garden and point at the bright dots in the sky. Lila liked the star that was very big and yellow. She called it the sun-star. Sam liked the star that was very small and red. He called it the fire-star.

One night, they saw a star that was very different. It was not a dot, but a line. It was moving very fast across the sky. It was brilliant, like a spark. Lila and Sam were amazed. They wondered what it was.

"Look, look!" Lila shouted. "A star that flies!"

"Wow!" Sam said. "Maybe it is a magic star!"

They watched the flying star until it disappeared behind the trees. They wished they could follow it and see where it went.

The next day, they went to the park with their mom. They saw a big poster on a wall. It had a picture of a rocket and some words. Their mom read the words to them.

"It says, 'Space Mission: Protect the Earth from Asteroids'. It is a story about some people who go to space in a rocket. They try to stop big rocks from hitting the earth. They are brave and smart."

Lila and Sam looked at the picture of the rocket. They remembered the flying star they saw last night.

"Mom, mom!" Lila said. "We saw a rocket last night! It was a brilliant star that flew!"

"Really?" their mom said. "That's amazing! Maybe it was one of the rockets from the space mission. Maybe they were protecting the earth from asteroids."

Lila and Sam felt excited. They imagined they were in the rocket, flying to space. They wanted to protect the earth and see the stars up close. They decided they wanted to be space heroes when they grew up.
<|end|>


