One day, a boy named Tom saw a big green ball in the park. He wanted to play with it, but it belonged to another boy named Sam. Sam was not nice. He did not like to share his toys.

"Can I play with your ball, please?" Tom asked Sam.

"No, it is mine. Go away!" Sam said. He pushed Tom and ran away with the ball.

Tom felt sad and angry. He wanted to have the ball too. He ran after Sam and tried to grab the ball. Sam resisted. He held the ball tight and kicked Tom.

"Stop it! You are mean!" Tom shouted.

A lady who was watching them came over. She was Sam's mom. She saw what Sam did and scolded him.

"Sam, that is not how you treat your friends. You have to share your toys and be kind. Say sorry to Tom and let him play with the ball too."

Sam did not want to say sorry. He did not want to share his ball. He resisted. He pouted and crossed his arms.

"Sam, don't be stubborn. You have to listen to me. If you don't share your ball, I will take it away and you will have no toys to play with. Do you understand?"

Sam understood. He did not want to lose his ball. He sighed and said sorry to Tom. He gave him the ball and asked him to play with him.

Tom was happy. He thanked Sam and said yes. He threw the ball and Sam caught it. They played together and had fun. They became friends. The lady smiled and watched them. She was proud of Sam. He learned to share and be kind.
<|end|>


