<|asst|>
Ben and Mia like to play with their toys. They have many toys, but their favorite is the dragon. The dragon is big and green and can make fire. They pretend the dragon is their friend and they go on adventures.

One day, they take the dragon to the park. They find a big hill and climb to the top. They see many things from the hill: trees, birds, cars, people. They say hello to the things they see.

"Hello, tree!" Ben says.

"Hello, bird!" Mia says.

The dragon wants to say hello too. He opens his mouth and makes a flame. The flame is bright and hot and goes very high. Ben and Mia are surprised and scared. They think the flame will hurt the things they see.

"Dragon, no!" Ben says.

"Stop, dragon!" Mia says.

The dragon does not understand. He thinks the flame is funny. He likes to see the things run and scream. He makes more flames and laughs.

"Ha ha ha!" the dragon says.

Ben and Mia are not happy. They do not like to see the things scared. They do not think the flame is funny. They want the dragon to stop. They pull the dragon's tail and try to make him stop.

"Dragon, please stop!" Ben says.

"Dragon, you are bad!" Mia says.

The dragon feels the pull on his tail. He turns his head and sees Ben and Mia. He sees their faces. They are angry and sad. He does not like to see them angry and sad. He likes them. They are his friends. He stops making flames and looks at them.

"Sorry, Ben. Sorry, Mia." the dragon says.

Ben and Mia see the dragon's face. He is sorry and sad. They do not like to see him sorry and sad. They like him. He is their friend. They hug him and forgive him.

"It's okay, dragon. We still love you." Ben says.

"But no more flames, okay?" Mia says.

The dragon nods and smiles. He promises no more flames. He hugs them back and says he loves them too. They are happy again. They play with the dragon and have fun. They are careful not to make flames. They are good friends.
<|end|>


