Lily and Ben liked to play in the forest. They liked to look for animals and flowers and rocks. One day, they saw a big mushroom. It was red and white and high. Lily wanted to pick it.

"Look, Ben, a mushroom! Can I have it?" Lily asked.

Ben shook his head. "No, Lily, you can't. That mushroom is not good. It can make you sick. We have to keep away from it."

Lily frowned. "But it is so pretty. I want to touch it."

Ben grabbed Lily's hand. "No, Lily, don't. Come with me. I will show you something better."

He led her to a sunny spot. There were many yellow flowers. They smelled nice. Ben picked one and gave it to Lily.

"Here, Lily, this is for you. A flower. You can keep it. It is good. It will make you happy."

Lily smiled. She took the flower and smelled it. She hugged Ben.

"Thank you, Ben. You are a good brother. I like the flower. It is better than the mushroom."

They played with the flowers and forgot about the mushroom. They were happy.
