Anna and Ben are playing in the park. They like to slide, swing and run. But today, they see something new. It is a big box with many books inside. A sign says: "Free books. Take one and share."

Anna and Ben love books. They run to the box and look inside. They see many books with pictures and words. They want to find a good book to read.

"Look, Ben, this book has a dog and a cat. They are friends. Do you want to read it?" Anna asks.

"Yes, Anna, that looks fun. And look, this book has a dragon and a knight. They are brave. Do you want to read it?" Ben asks.

"Yes, Ben, that looks exciting. Let's take both books and read them together," Anna says.

They take the books and sit on a bench. They open the books and start to read. They like the stories and the pictures. They laugh and smile.

But then, they see a boy crying. He is sitting on the grass. He has a book in his hand, but it is dirty and wet. He dropped it in a puddle.

Anna and Ben feel sorry for the boy. They want to help him.

"Hello, what is your name?" Anna asks.

"I'm Tom. I like books, but I ruined this one. It was my favorite book. Now it is spoiled," Tom says.

"Don't cry, Tom. We have books too. Maybe we can share with you," Ben says.

"Really? You would do that? You are very kind," Tom says.

Anna and Ben give Tom their books. They wipe his tears and his book. They tell him the stories and the pictures. They make him happy.

Tom likes Anna and Ben. He likes their books. He thanks them and hugs them.

They become friends. They read and play together. They share and care. They have fun.
<|end|>


