Ben and Mia are friends. They like to play with blocks. They build a big tower with red and blue and yellow blocks. They are very proud of their tower.

"Look, our tower is so high!" Ben says.

"Yes, it is. We are good builders!" Mia says.

They want to show their tower to their mom and dad. But they have to be quiet. Mom and dad are working in the other room. They do not like noise.

"Let's make a promise," Ben says. "We will not knock down our tower. We will not shout or run. We will be quiet until mom and dad finish working."

"OK, I promise," Mia says. "We will be quiet and careful."

They hold hands and nod. They are good friends. They keep their promise. They wait for mom and dad to come and see their tower. They smile and whisper. They are happy.
