It was Timmy's birthday and he was very happy. He had a big cake with candles and many presents. His friends and family came to his house to celebrate with him.

"Happy birthday, Timmy!" they all said and sang a song. Timmy smiled and blew out the candles. He wished for a new bike.

"Can I have some cake, please?" he asked his mom.

"Of course, sweetie. Here you go." She gave him a big slice of cake and a glass of milk.

Timmy ate his cake and drank his milk. He liked the cake. It was sweet and soft. He did not like the milk. It was spicy and hot.

"Mom, this milk is spicy!" he said and made a face.

"Oh, no! I'm sorry, Timmy. I gave you the wrong milk. This is the milk for daddy. He likes spicy food. Your milk is in the refrigerator. Let me get it for you." She ran to the kitchen and opened the refrigerator.

She took out a carton of milk and poured some in a new glass. She brought it to Timmy and apologized.

"Here you go, Timmy. This is your milk. It is cold and fresh. I'm sorry for the mistake. Do you forgive me?"

Timmy nodded and took a sip of the milk. He liked the milk. It was cold and fresh. He smiled and hugged his mom.

"I forgive you, mom. I love you. Thank you for the cake and the milk and the party. This is the best birthday ever!" he said.

"I love you too, Timmy. You're welcome. I'm glad you're happy. You're the best son ever!" she said.

They kissed and cuddled. Then they joined the others and continued to celebrate. Timmy had a lot of fun. He opened his presents and played with his friends. He got a new bike and a helmet. He was very happy. It was a good day.
<|end|>


