Sam and Lily are friends. They like to play with toys and books. One day, they go to the library with their moms. The library has many books and toys. Sam and Lily see a huge book on a shelf. The book has many pictures of animals and words in different languages.

"Wow, look at that book!" Sam says. "It is so big and colorful. I want to read it."

"Me too," Lily says. "But it is too high. We cannot reach it."

Sam has an idea. He sees a librarian at a desk. The librarian helps people find books. Sam and Lily walk to the desk. They say hello to the librarian.

"Hello, kids. How can I help you?" the librarian says.

"Can you please help us get that book?" Sam says. He points to the huge book on the shelf.

"Sure, I can help you," the librarian says. She smiles and walks with them to the shelf. She takes the book and gives it to Sam and Lily.

"Thank you, thank you!" Sam and Lily say. They are very happy. They sit on a couch and open the book. They see pictures of lions, elephants, monkeys, and more. They also see words in different languages.

"What is this word?" Sam asks. He points to a word under a picture of a lion.

"That is 'lion' in Spanish. It is 'leon'," the librarian says. She shows them how to say it.

"Leon," Sam and Lily repeat. They like the sound of the word.

They ask the librarian more words in different languages. They learn how to say 'elephant' in French, 'monkey' in Chinese, and 'giraffe' in Swahili. They have fun learning new words and sounds.

Sam and Lily love the huge book. They request to borrow it from the library. The librarian says yes. She writes their names on a card. She tells them to bring the book back in two weeks.

Sam and Lily say goodbye to the librarian. They hug the book and walk to their moms. They are excited to read the book at home and learn more languages. They are happy friends.
<|end|>


