Lily and Tom were best friends. They liked to play with boats in the harbor. They made boats from paper, wood, and cans. They put their boats in the water and watched them sail.

One day, a big storm came. The wind blew hard and the rain poured down. Lily and Tom ran to their homes. They were scared for their boats. They hoped their boats were safe.

The next day, the sun came out. Lily and Tom went to the harbor. They looked for their boats. They saw some boats on the shore, some boats in the water, and some boats broken. They ran to find their own boats.

Lily saw her boat on the shore. It was wet but not broken. She was happy. She picked up her boat and hugged it. She said, "I value you, boat. You are my favorite."

Tom saw his boat in the water. It was broken. He was sad. He said, "Oh no, boat. You are not ready to sail anymore. You are my favorite."

Lily saw Tom. She felt sorry for him. She said, "Tom, I have an idea. Why don't we share my boat? We can fix it and make it better. We can sail it together. We are best friends."

Tom smiled. He said, "Lily, you are very kind. I like your idea. We can share your boat. We are best friends."

Lily and Tom hugged. They took Lily's boat and went to find some tools. They fixed the boat and made it better. They put their boat in the water and watched it sail. They were happy. They valued their boat and their friendship.
<|end|>


