Lily and Ben like to play near the lake. They see many ducks and fish in the water. They also see some stones on the ground. Lily has an idea. She picks up a stone and says to Ben, "Let's throw stones in the lake and see how many splashes we can make!"

Ben thinks that is a fun game. He picks up a stone too and throws it in the lake. He makes a big splash. Lily claps and says, "Good job, Ben! Now it's my turn!" She throws her stone in the lake and makes a bigger splash. Ben cheers and says, "Wow, Lily, you are clever!"

They take turns throwing stones in the lake and counting the splashes. They have a lot of fun. But then they hear a loud quack. They look up and see a duck swimming towards them. The duck is angry. It does not like the stones in the water. It says, "Stop throwing stones in my lake! You are scaring the fish and hurting my friends!"

Lily and Ben are scared. They did not know they were bothering the duck. They say, "Sorry, duck, we did not mean to be bad. We were just playing a game. We will stop throwing stones now."

The duck says, "Thank you for being sorry. Next time, please be more careful and kind. The lake is for everyone to share and enjoy. You can still play here, but do not throw stones. You can feed the ducks and fish instead. They will like that more."

Lily and Ben nod and say, "Okay, duck, we will do that. Thank you for teaching us. You are clever too." They put down the stones and look for some bread to feed the ducks and fish. They make new friends in the lake and learn to be more respectful. They have a happy day.
<|end|>


