Lily and Tom are friends. They like to play in the park. They see a big swing. Lily wants to swing high. Tom wants to swing low.

"Can I swing first?" Lily asks.

"OK, but only for a little bit," Tom says.

Lily gets on the swing. She pushes with her feet. She swings high and fast. She feels the wind in her hair. She laughs.

"Wow, you are so good at swinging!" Tom says.

"Thank you, Tom. Do you want to try?" Lily asks.

Tom nods. He gets on the swing. He does not push with his feet. He swings low and slow. He feels bored.

"This is not fun," Tom says.

"Why don't you push with your feet?" Lily asks.

"I don't want to. I am lazy," Tom says.

Lily sees something shiny on the ground. She gets off the swing. She runs to the shiny thing. It is an egg.

"Look, Tom, I found an egg!" Lily says.

"Where did it come from?" Tom asks.

"I don't know. Maybe a bird left it here," Lily says.

"Can we open it?" Tom asks.

"I don't know. Maybe we should leave it alone," Lily says.

"But I want to see what is inside," Tom says.

He gets off the swing. He runs to Lily. He takes the egg from her hand. He tries to crack it.

"Tom, don't do that!" Lily says.

But it is too late. The egg breaks. A baby bird comes out. It is wet and scared. It cries.

"Tom, you hurt the baby bird!" Lily says.

"I'm sorry, Lily. I didn't know," Tom says.

They feel bad. They don't know what to do. They hear a loud noise. They look up. They see a big bird. It is the baby bird's mom. She is angry. She flies to them. She takes the baby bird in her beak. She flies away.

"Bye, baby bird," Lily says.

"Bye, baby bird," Tom says.

They are sad. They are sorry. They hug each other.

"Let's go home," Lily says.

"OK, let's go home," Tom says.

They walk away. They don't play with the swing anymore. They don't play with eggs anymore. They learn a lesson. They are not lazy anymore. They are careful and kind.
<|end|>


