<|asst|>
Tim and Jen went to the zoo with Mom and Dad. They saw many animals, like lions, monkeys, and birds. But their favorite was the hippo. The hippo was big and gray, and had a huge mouth. He liked to swim in the water and splash with his friends.

"Look, Mom, the hippo is spraying water!" Tim said, pointing at the hippo. The hippo was using his nose to blow water in the air, like a fountain. It made a funny sound, and the water fell on the other hippos and the grass.

"Wow, that's cool!" Jen said. She wanted to spray water too. She saw a hose near the fence, and ran to it. She turned on the tap, and held the hose. She aimed at the hippo, and squeezed the handle.

"Jen, no!" Mom shouted. "That's not nice! You can't spray the hippo!"

But it was too late. Jen sprayed the hippo with the hose, and the hippo did not like it. He roared and opened his mouth, showing his big teeth. He sprayed water back at Jen, and hit her in the face. Jen dropped the hose and screamed. She was wet and scared.

"Jen, I'm sorry, I'm sorry!" Tim said, running to her. He hugged her and tried to calm her down. He felt bad for her and the hippo.

"Jen, that was a bad thing to do," Dad said, picking her up. "You should never spray the animals. They have feelings too, and they don't like to be bothered."

"I'm sorry, Dad," Jen said, sobbing. "I just wanted to have fun. I didn't mean to make the hippo angry."

"It's okay, Jen," Mom said, wiping her face. "You made a mistake, but you learned from it. Next time, you can watch the hippo spray, but not spray him yourself."

"Okay, Mom," Jen said, nodding. She looked at the hippo, who was still swimming and splashing. She felt sorry for him too. She wanted to say sorry, but she didn't know how.

"Can we buy a toy hippo, Mom?" Jen asked. "A cheap one, please?"

"Sure, Jen," Mom said, smiling. "A cheap toy hippo sounds like a good idea. Maybe you can play with it and spray it with water at home. But only if the hippo likes it."

"Okay, Mom," Jen said, smiling too. She hoped the hippo would like it. She hoped the hippo would forgive her. She hoped the hippo would be her friend.
<|end|>


