Sara and Ben wanted to decorate the big tree in the yard. They had many shiny things to hang on the branches. But they had a problem. The tree was too high for them to reach.

"Let's get a ladder," Sara said.

"No, let's get a chair," Ben said.

They argued and argued. They were both stubborn. They did not want to listen to each other.

Then they saw their big brother, Tom, coming home. He was tall and strong. He could help them.

"Tom, Tom, can you help us?" Sara and Ben shouted.

"What do you need?" Tom asked.

"We want to decorate the tree, but it's too high," Sara said.

"Can you lift us up?" Ben said.

Tom smiled. He liked to help his siblings. He agreed to lift them up, one by one, so they could decorate the tree.

Sara and Ben were happy. They thanked Tom and gave him a hug. They hung the shiny things on the branches. The tree looked beautiful.

Then they saw their mom coming out of the house. She had a big box in her hands.

"What's that, mom?" Sara and Ben asked.

"It's a surprise for you," mom said. "Do you want to open it?"

Sara and Ben nodded. They ran to mom and opened the box. Inside, there were more shiny things to decorate the tree. There were also cookies and hot chocolate.

"Wow, thank you, mom!" Sara and Ben said.

They shared the cookies and hot chocolate with Tom and mom. They enjoyed the warm and sweet treats. They looked at the tree and smiled. They had a fun and cozy afternoon.
