Anna and Ben were playing with balloons in the park. They liked to blow them up and let them go. They watched the balloons fly high in the sky. Sometimes they popped and made a loud noise.

"Let's play hide and seek with the balloons," Ben said. "You hide first and I will find you."

Anna nodded and ran to find a good spot. She saw a big tree with many leaves. She hid behind the tree and held her balloon. She hoped Ben would not see her.

Ben counted to ten and then opened his eyes. He looked around the park. He saw some swings, a slide, a bench, and a fountain. But he did not see Anna or her balloon.

"Where are you, Anna?" he called. "I can't find you."

Anna heard Ben's voice. She wanted to surprise him. She waited for him to come closer. Then she jumped out from behind the tree and shouted, "Boo!"

Ben was startled and dropped his balloon. The balloon flew away and landed on the fountain. The water sprayed the balloon and made it pop.

"Oh no, my balloon!" Ben cried. He ran to the fountain and tried to get his balloon. But it was too late. The balloon was gone.

Anna felt sorry for Ben. She saw that he was sad. She wanted to be helpful. She ran to him and gave him a hug.

"I'm sorry, Ben. I didn't mean to scare you. Here, you can have my balloon. I have another one at home."

Ben smiled and hugged Anna back. He took her balloon and thanked her.

"Thank you, Anna. You are very helpful. And you are a good hider. You are my best friend."

Anna and Ben smiled and played with the balloon. They had fun in the park. They were happy.
