Lily and Ben were excited to go to the park. They put on their hats and shoes and ran to the door. But when they looked outside, they saw dark clouds and heard loud thunder. It was a storm!

"Oh no!" Lily said. "We can't go to the park now. It's too wet and scary."

Ben was sad too. He wanted to play on the swings and slide. He started to cry.

"Shh, it's okay," Mom said. "We can do something fun inside. How about we make some cookies?"

Lily and Ben liked cookies. They wiped their tears and followed Mom to the kitchen. Mom gave them aprons and spoons and bowls. They helped Mom measure and mix and roll the dough. They cut out shapes like stars and hearts and flowers. They put them on a tray and Mom put them in the oven.

"Now we have to wait," Mom said. "Be patient, my loves. The cookies will be ready soon."

Lily and Ben smelled the cookies baking. They smelled sweet and yummy. They heard the timer beep. Mom took out the tray and put it on the table. She let the cookies cool a little and then gave one to each child.

"Mmm, these are delicious!" Lily said.

"Thank you, Mom!" Ben said.

They ate their cookies and drank some milk. They smiled and hugged Mom. They forgot about the storm. They were happy.
