Lily and Tom are twins. They like to play with their toys and books. One day, their mom says, "We are going to see a big place. It is called a university. There are many people who learn and teach there. Do you want to go?"

Lily and Tom say, "Yes, mom, we want to go. What can we see there?"

Mom says, "You can see many things. You can see big buildings, green grass, pretty flowers, and funny statues. You can also see people who read, write, draw, and sing. Maybe you can make some new friends too."

Lily and Tom are very happy. They get in the car with mom and dad. They drive for a long time. They see many cars, buses, and bikes on the road. They also see some cows, horses, and sheep on the farms. They say, "Moo, neigh, and baa" to them.

They finally arrive at the university. They get out of the car and look around. They see a big sign that says, "Welcome to the University". They see many people walking, talking, and smiling. They see some people wearing funny hats and gowns. They say, "Hello, hello" to them.

They follow mom and dad to a big building. They go inside and see a big hall. They see many chairs, tables, and balloons. They see a big stage with a microphone and a screen. They see some people sitting on the stage. They hear some music playing.

Mom says, "This is a special day. It is called a graduation. It means that some people have finished learning and they get a paper that says they did a good job. Your dad is one of them. He worked very hard and he learned a lot. We are very proud of him."

Lily and Tom say, "Wow, dad, you are amazing. We are proud of you too."

They sit on their chairs and wait for the ceremony to start. They clap their hands and cheer for dad when he goes on the stage and gets his paper. They see dad smile and wave at them. They see mom cry and hug dad. They say, "We love you, dad. You are the best."

They have a lovely day at the university. They see many new things and meet many new people. They learn a lot and have a lot of fun. They say, "Thank you, mom and dad, for taking us to the university. It is a wonderful place. Maybe we can come back again."
<|end|>


