Tom and Sam are brothers. They like to play with cars and trucks. They have many cars and trucks of different colors and sizes. They make noises like vroom and beep when they play.

One day, they find a big steel truck in the garage. It is shiny and strong. It has big wheels and a loud horn. Tom and Sam want to play with it. They push it and pull it and make it go fast and slow.

"Look, Sam, this truck is so cool!" Tom says. "It can chew anything!"

"Chew anything?" Sam asks. "What do you mean?"

Tom points to a pile of wood and nails. "Watch this!" he says. He drives the truck towards the pile and crashes into it. The truck makes a crunching sound and breaks some of the wood and nails.

"Wow!" Sam says. "That is amazing! Can it chew anything else?"

Tom smiles. He sees a big red ball on the grass. He drives the truck towards the ball and tries to chew it. But the ball is too big and soft. The truck bounces off the ball and flips over.

"Uh-oh!" Tom says. "The truck is stuck!"

Sam runs to help him. He tries to lift the truck, but it is too heavy. He pushes it, but it does not move.

"Tom, what do we do?" Sam says. "The truck is too big and strong!"

Tom thinks. He has an idea. He sees a rope on the wall. He grabs the rope and ties it to the truck. He gives the other end to Sam.

"Sam, pull the rope!" he says. "Maybe we can make the truck move!"

Sam nods. He pulls the rope with all his might. Tom pushes the truck with all his might. Together, they make the truck move. The truck rolls back to its place.

"Yay!" Tom and Sam say. "We did it!"

They hug each other and laugh. They are happy. They love the steel truck, but they love each other more. They decide to play with their smaller cars and trucks instead. They are more fun and easier to chew.
<|end|>


