Tim and Sam were playing knights in the garden. They had sticks for swords and pots for helmets. They pretended to fight dragons and bad guys.

"Look, there is a big dragon!" Tim said, pointing to a bush. "Let's go and beat him!"

"OK, but be careful!" Sam said, following Tim. They ran to the bush and swung their swords at the leaves.

"Roar!" the dragon said. It was not a real dragon, but Tim's old dog, Rex. He liked to play with the boys, but he did not like their swords. He barked and jumped out of the bush.

"Ah, it's Rex!" Tim said, dropping his sword. "He scared me!"

"Me too!" Sam said, dropping his sword too. "But he is a good dragon, right?"

"Yes, he is a good dragon," Tim said, hugging Rex. "He just wants to play with us."

"OK, let's play with him then," Sam said, petting Rex. "But we have to finish our knight game first. We have to save the princess!"

"Where is the princess?" Tim asked, looking around.

"She is in the castle," Sam said, pointing to the shed. "We have to rescue her from the bad guy!"

"OK, let's go then!" Tim said, picking up his sword. "But we have to be quiet, so the bad guy does not hear us."

"OK, let's be quiet," Sam said, picking up his sword too. They tiptoed to the shed, ready to save the princess.
