Sam and Mia like to play pirates. They have a big box that is their ship. They put a flag on it and some toys that are their treasure. They also have a rope that is their anchor.

One day, they are playing pirates in the park. They see a big hill that looks like an island. They want to go there and find more treasure. They pull their ship with the rope and go to the hill.

"Look, Mia, there is a cave!" Sam says. He points to a hole in the hill. "Maybe there is gold inside!"

"Let's go and see!" Mia says. She follows Sam to the cave. They kneel down and crawl inside. It is dark and cold.

They hear a loud roar. It is a bear! The bear is angry and hungry. It wants to eat them!

"Run, Mia, run!" Sam shouts. He grabs Mia's hand and they run out of the cave. The bear chases them.

They run to their ship and throw the rope. The rope has a hook that catches the bear's fur. The bear is stuck. It roars louder.

"Ha, ha, we caught you, bear!" Sam says. He waves his sword. "You are our prisoner now!"

The bear tries to break free. It pulls the rope and the ship. The ship falls over and the treasure spills out.

"Oh, no, our ship!" Mia says. She cries. "Our treasure is gone!"

Sam hugs Mia. He says, "Don't cry, Mia. We still have each other. We are brave pirates. We can make a new ship and find more treasure."

Mia smiles. She says, "You are right, Sam. We are brave pirates. And we have a big bear for our anchor!"

The bear is still roaring. But Sam and Mia don't hear it. They are deaf to the bear. They only hear each other. They laugh and play. They are happy.
