Lily and Ben are friends. They like to play and read books. One day, they go to the library with their mom. The library has many books and toys. Lily and Ben are happy.

They see a big book with pictures of animals. They want to read it. But the book is too high for them. They try to reach it, but they cannot. They ask their mom for help, but she is busy talking to the librarian.

"Who can help us?" Lily asks.

"Maybe we can ask someone else," Ben says.

They look around and see a girl with glasses and a ponytail. She is reading a book on a chair. She looks kind and smart.

"Excuse me, can you help us?" Lily says.

The girl looks at them and smiles. She puts down her book and walks to them.

"Sure, what do you need?" she says.

"We want to read that book, but it is too high for us. Can you get it for us, please?" Ben says.

The girl nods and reaches for the book. She takes it down and gives it to Lily and Ben.

"Here you go. This is a nice book. I like animals, too. What are your names?" she says.

"I'm Lily and this is Ben. Thank you for helping us. You are very kind. What is your name?" Lily says.

"I'm Mia. You're welcome. Do you want to read the book with me? We can share it," Mia says.

Lily and Ben nod. They follow Mia to her chair. They sit together and open the book. They see many pictures of animals and learn their names and sounds. They have fun and make a new friend. They are happy.
<|end|>


