<|asst|>
Lily liked to play in the garden with her doll. She pretended that her doll was a princess and she was a fairy. She made a tea party with leaves and flowers and served them to her doll.

One day, she saw a rat in the garden. It was big and brown and had a long tail. Lily was scared of the rat. She thought it would bite her doll or steal her tea. She ran to her mom and told her about the rat.

"Mom, there is a rat in the garden! It is scary and mean!" Lily said.

"Where is the rat, Lily?" Mom asked.

"It is behind the bush, near the fence. It is hiding there. It is mysterious and sneaky!" Lily said.

Mom took Lily's hand and walked to the garden. She looked behind the bush and saw the rat. It was not a rat, but a rabbit. It had big ears and a fluffy tail. It was eating a carrot.

"Lily, that is not a rat, that is a rabbit. It is not scary or mean, it is cute and friendly. It is not mysterious or sneaky, it is hungry and curious." Mom said.

"Really? A rabbit? Can I touch it?" Lily asked.

"Sure, but be gentle and quiet. Maybe it will let you pet it." Mom said.

Lily and Mom approached the rabbit slowly. The rabbit looked at them and twitched its nose. Lily reached out her hand and stroked the rabbit's fur. It was soft and warm. The rabbit did not run away. It liked Lily's touch.

Lily smiled and said, "Hello, rabbit. Do you want to join my tea party? I can serve you some leaves and flowers. They are yummy and pretty. You can be my friend and play with me and my doll."

The rabbit nodded and followed Lily to her tea party. Lily was happy. She had a new friend in the garden. She forgot about the rat and the fear. She only felt the joy and the love.
<|end|>


