Lily and Tom are friends. They like to play on the farm. The farmer is nice. He lets them feed the chickens and the cows. He is strong. He can lift big bags of hay.

One day, the farmer asks them to help him. He says, "Can you please finish picking the apples from the tree? I have to go to the market soon." Lily and Tom say, "Yes, we can help you!"

They run to the apple tree. They see many red and green apples. They are shiny and sweet. They use a basket to collect the apples. They take turns to climb the ladder and reach the high ones. They are careful not to fall.

They work hard and fast. They fill the basket with apples. They are proud of themselves. They say, "We did it! We finished picking the apples!" They carry the basket to the farmer. He is happy. He says, "Thank you, Lily and Tom! You are very helpful and kind. You can have some apples as a reward. They are delicious!"

Lily and Tom smile. They say, "Thank you, farmer! We like to help you. We like to play on the farm. We like the apples. They are yummy!" They eat some apples and share them with the chickens and the cows. They are happy. They are friends.
<|end|>


