Ben and Lily were playing in the park. They liked to run and slide and swing. They saw a squirrel on a tree. The squirrel had a big nut in its mouth. It looked happy.

"Look, a squirrel!" Ben said. "It has a nut. I want a nut too."

Ben ran to the tree and tried to climb it. But it was difficult. The tree was tall and slippery. Ben could not reach the squirrel. He fell down and hurt his knee.

"Ow, ow, ow!" Ben cried. "I want a nut. I want a nut."

Lily ran to Ben and hugged him. She saw a bench near the tree. On the bench, there was a bag of nuts. Someone had left it there.

"Ben, look!" Lily said. "There are nuts on the bench. Maybe we can have some."

Lily took Ben's hand and walked to the bench. She opened the bag and took out two nuts. She gave one to Ben and kept one for herself.

"Here, Ben. Have a nut. It will make you feel better." Lily said.

Ben took the nut and smiled. He bit it and tasted it. It was crunchy and sweet. He liked it.

"Thank you, Lily. You are a good sister." Ben said.

Lily smiled too. She bit her nut and tasted it. It was crunchy and sweet. She liked it.

They looked at the squirrel on the tree. The squirrel looked at them and nodded. It seemed to say thank you too. It had enough nuts for itself.

Ben and Lily shared the nuts and played in the park. They were happy.
<|end|>


