Sara and Tom are playing in the park. They like to swing, slide and run. Sara has a pink dress and Tom has a blue shirt. They are friends and share their toys.

One day, they see a big hill with many flowers. They want to climb the hill and see what is on the other side. They hold hands and start to walk up the hill. They see yellow, purple and white flowers. They smell nice and make them happy.

But the hill is steep and slippery. Sara steps on a rock and loses her balance. She falls down and rolls down the hill. She screams and cries. Tom sees her fall and runs after her. He is scared and worried.

He reaches her at the bottom of the hill. She is dirty and has a scratch on her knee. She is still crying and holding her dress. Tom hugs her and says, "Don't cry, Sara. You are okay. You are powerful. You can stand up and smile."

Sara looks at him and wipes her tears. She smiles and says, "Thank you, Tom. You are powerful too. You are a good friend. You helped me."

They hug again and stand up. They look at the hill and decide to go back to the park. They don't want to climb the hill anymore. They want to swing, slide and run. They are happy and safe. They are powerful.
<|end|>


