Lily loved to play with her doll, Rose. She hugged her, dressed her, and talked to her every day. Rose was her best friend. But one day, Lily's mom said they had to move to a new house. Lily was sad. She did not want to leave her old house and her old friends.

"Mom, can I take Rose with me?" Lily asked.

"Of course, sweetie. You can take Rose and all your other toys. Don't worry, you will make new friends in the new house," Mom said.

Lily packed Rose in a box with her other toys. She wrote "Lily's toys" on the box with a crayon. She hoped Rose would not be scared in the dark box. She kissed her goodbye and said, "I love you, Rose. I will see you soon."

The next day, they got in the car and drove to the new house. It was very far away. Lily looked out the window and saw the trees and the sky. She missed her old house and her old friends. She felt a tear roll down her cheek. She wanted to see Rose again.

When they arrived at the new house, Lily ran to find her box of toys. She opened it and looked for Rose. But she could not find her. She searched in all the other boxes, but Rose was not there. She felt a lump in her throat. She started to weep.

"Mom, where is Rose? I can't find her. She is lost," Lily cried.

Mom came and hugged Lily. She looked at the boxes and saw a label that said "Donate". She realized that Lily's box of toys had been mixed up with the box of toys they were giving away to other children.

"Oh, Lily, I'm so sorry. There was a mistake. Your box of toys was taken to the donation center. We have to go there and get it back. Maybe Rose is still there," Mom said.

Lily and Mom got in the car and drove to the donation center. It was a big building with many boxes and bags of things. Lily and Mom asked the people there if they had seen a box with Lily's toys. They said they had, but they did not know where it was. They said they had given some boxes to other places, like schools and hospitals and shelters.

Lily felt her heart sink. She wondered if Rose was in one of those places. She wondered if Rose was happy or sad. She wondered if Rose missed her. She wished she could see her again.

She looked at the distant pine trees outside the window. They reminded her of her old house and her old friends. She felt a sob in her chest. She wept.
<|end|>


