Tim and Anna are friends. They like to play outside. One day, they see a big truck with many fruits and vegetables. They run to the truck and ask the man, "Where are you going?"

The man smiles and says, "I am a farmer. I grow these fruits and vegetables on my farm. I am going to the market to sell them."

Tim and Anna are curious. They ask, "Can we see your farm? Is it far?"

The farmer says, "Sure, you can come with me. But you have to ask your parents first. And yes, it is far. We have to drive for a long time."

Tim and Anna run to their parents and ask them. Their parents say yes, but they have to be back before dark. They hug their parents and say thank you. Then they hop on the truck with the farmer.

The farmer drives and drives. He shows them the fields, the trees, the animals, and the barn. He lets them pick some fruits and vegetables. He gives them some milk and cookies. He tells them stories about his farm. Tim and Anna have a lot of fun. They feel comfortable with the farmer. He is very kind and friendly.

When the sun is low, the farmer says, "It is time to go back. The market is closed. I will take you home." He puts the fruits and vegetables back on the truck. He helps Tim and Anna get on. He says goodbye to his farm.

On the way back, Tim and Anna say to the farmer, "Thank you for showing us your farm. We had a great time. You are a good farmer."

The farmer says, "You are welcome. I am glad you enjoyed it. You are good kids."

They reach their homes. They wave to the farmer. They run to their parents and tell them about their adventure. They show them the fruits and vegetables they picked. They say thank you to their parents. They go to bed. They dream of the farm.
<|end|>


