Tom and Mia are playing with blocks in the living room. They like to build towers and houses with the blocks. But Tom is bored of building. He wants to do something else.

"Let's throw the blocks!" he says to Mia. "It will be fun!"

Mia is not sure. She likes the blocks and does not want to break them. But Tom does not listen. He picks up a block and throws it across the room. It hits the lamp and makes a loud noise.

"Tom, stop!" Mia says. "You will make a mess!"

But Tom does not stop. He throws another block and another. The blocks fly everywhere. They knock over the books, the vase, the pictures. They make a big mess.

Mom hears the noise and comes to the living room. She sees the mess and is very angry.

"Tom and Mia, what are you doing?" she asks. "Look at this mess! You have to clean it up right now!"

Tom and Mia are sorry. They did not mean to make a mess. They say sorry to Mom and start to pick up the blocks. They learn that throwing blocks is not a good idea. It only makes a mess and a problem. They decide to play with the blocks nicely next time.
