Ben and Lily were twins who liked to play with their toys. They had many toys, but they did not share them well. They always said, "This is mine, you can't have it!" and "No, you can't play with that, it's mine!"

One day, they found a new toy in their room. It was a cord that made sounds when you pulled it. It had a red end and a blue end, and it was very long. Ben and Lily both wanted to own the cord. They grabbed it and pulled it hard.

"Give me the cord, it's mine!" Ben shouted.

"No, it's mine, I saw it first!" Lily yelled.

They pulled and pulled, but the cord did not break. It only made louder and louder sounds. The sounds were like a siren, a horn, a bell, and a whistle. They were very loud and annoying.

Mom and Dad heard the noise and came to their room. They saw Ben and Lily fighting over the cord. They were not happy.

"What are you doing?" Mom asked.

"Stop that noise!" Dad said.

They took the cord away from Ben and Lily. They looked at it and saw a tag. The tag said, "This is not a toy. This is an ordinary cord for the fire alarm. Do not pull it or you will make a false alarm."

Mom and Dad explained to Ben and Lily that the cord was not a toy, but a tool for safety. They said that pulling the cord could make the firemen come for no reason, and that was not good. They said that Ben and Lily should not fight over things, but share them nicely. They said that they had many toys that were more fun than an ordinary cord.

Ben and Lily felt sorry for what they did. They said sorry to Mom and Dad, and to each other. They hugged and said, "Let's play together with our toys."

Mom and Dad smiled and gave them back their toys. They also gave them a new toy to share. It was a book with pictures and words. Ben and Lily liked the book. They took turns reading it and looking at it. They learned new words and had fun. They did not fight over the book, or the cord, or any other toy. They were happy and kind.
<|end|>


