Lily was a baby girl who liked to play in her crib. She had a brown teddy bear, a yellow ball and a blue blanket. She liked to hug her teddy bear, roll her ball and cover herself with her blanket. She was happy in her crib.

One day, her mommy came to her crib and said, "Lily, it's time to leave your crib. You are a big girl now. You can sleep in a big bed like mommy and daddy." Lily did not want to leave her crib. She liked her crib. She said, "No, mommy, no. I want to stay in my crib. I love my crib."

Mommy smiled and said, "I know, Lily, I know. But you can take your teddy bear, your ball and your blanket with you. You can have them in your big bed. And you can have more toys and books in your big bed. You will like your big bed. It's very cozy and soft."

Lily was not sure. She looked at her crib and then at her big bed. She saw that her big bed had a pink pillow, a purple quilt and a white lamp. She saw that there were more toys and books on a shelf near her big bed. She wondered if she would like her big bed.

Mommy picked her up and said, "Come on, Lily, let's try your big bed. You can always go back to your crib if you don't like it. But I think you will like it. You are a brave and smart girl." Mommy carried her to her big bed and put her down. She gave her her teddy bear, her ball and her blanket. She kissed her and said, "Good night, Lily. I love you."

Lily hugged her teddy bear, rolled her ball and covered herself with her blanket. She felt cozy and soft. She looked at her pink pillow, her purple quilt and her white lamp. She looked at her toys and books on the shelf. She smiled and said, "I like my big bed, mommy. I love you too." She closed her eyes and fell asleep.
