Lily and Ben are playing in the snow. They make a big snowman with a hat and a scarf. They give him a carrot nose and two coal eyes. They are happy and laugh.

But then the wind blows hard and cold. It makes the snowman's hat fly away. It makes Lily and Ben shiver. They are not happy and cry.

"Let's go home," Lily says. "I'm cold and hungry."

"Me too," Ben says. "But what about the snowman? He will be cold too."

They look at the snowman. He has no hat and his scarf is loose. He looks sad.

Lily has an idea. She takes off her mittens and puts them on the snowman's hands. Ben takes off his boots and puts them on the snowman's feet.

"There," Lily says. "Now he is warm and cozy."

Ben smiles. He hugs Lily. "You are very gentle and kind," he says.

They wave goodbye to the snowman and run home. They have hot chocolate and cookies. They are warm and happy. They win the day.
