Lila and Sam were best friends. They liked to play in the park with their kites. One day, they found a big, red kite in a tree. It was stuck on a branch.

"Wow, look at that kite!" Sam said. "It is incredible. Can we get it?"

Lila nodded. She had an idea. She saw a cherry tree near the kite. The cherries were ripe and juicy. She picked some and put them in her pocket.

"Follow me," she said to Sam. "We can use the cherries to help us."

They climbed the cherry tree, careful not to fall. They reached the branch where the kite was. Lila threw a cherry at the kite. It hit the string and made it loose. The kite fell to the ground.

"Yay, we did it!" Sam cheered. "Let's fly the kite!"

They ran to the kite and picked it up. It was bigger than them. They tied a long string to it and ran across the grass. The wind lifted the kite and made it soar in the sky. It looked like a bird.

Lila and Sam smiled. They felt happy. They shared the cherries and watched the kite soar. They had a fun day.
