Lily and Ben wanted to build a snowman. They put on their hats and gloves and went outside. The snow was soft and white. They rolled big balls of snow and stacked them on top of each other. They found a carrot, a scarf, and some buttons for the snowman's face and clothes.

"Look, our snowman is done!" Lily said. "He is very big and happy."

Ben nodded. "He is. But I am cold and thirsty. Can we go inside and have some cocoa?"

