Sara and Ben are friends. They like to play in the park. They jog and run and jump and laugh. They have fun.

One day, they see a big car in the park. It is shiny and new. A man and a woman get out of the car. They have nice clothes and bags and shoes. They look rich.

"Wow, look at them!" Sara says. "They have so much stuff!"

"Maybe they are happy," Ben says. "Maybe they like their stuff."

The man and the woman walk to a bench. They sit down and look at their phones. They do not talk. They do not smile. They look bored.

Sara and Ben jog to the swings. They push each other and go high. They giggle and shout. They look happy.

"Maybe they are sad," Sara says. "Maybe they do not like their stuff."

"Maybe they need friends," Ben says. "Maybe they need to play."

Sara and Ben jog to the man and the woman. They smile and wave. They say hello.

"Hi, we are Sara and Ben. Do you want to play with us?" Sara asks.

The man and the woman look up. They see Sara and Ben. They see their smiles and waves. They put down their phones. They smile back.

"Hi, we are Sam and Lisa. We would love to play with you," Lisa says.

Sara and Ben are happy. They jog and run and jump and laugh with Sam and Lisa. They have fun.

The end.
