Ben and Lily were twins who liked to play in the garden. One day, they saw a big cloud of mist in the sky. It was white and soft and looked like cotton candy.

"Wow, look at that!" Ben said. "What is it?"

"It's mist," Lily said. "It's like water, but in the air. Sometimes it comes down and makes everything wet."

"Can we touch it?" Ben asked.

"I don't know," Lily said. "Maybe if we climb up the tree."

They ran to the big oak tree and started to climb. They were careful not to fall or hurt themselves. They reached the top and looked at the mist. It was very close and very quiet.

"Hello, mist!" Ben shouted. "Can we play with you?"

The mist did not answer. It just moved slowly and gently.

"Maybe it's sleeping," Lily whispered. "Maybe it's dreaming of something nice."

"Like what?" Ben wondered.

"Like rainbows and flowers and birds," Lily said. "Or maybe it's dreaming of us."

They smiled and waved at the mist. They felt happy and curious. They wanted to know what the mist was dreaming of. They closed their eyes and tried to dream too.
