<|asst|>
Lily likes to think of names for her pets. She has a dog, a cat, and a bird. The dog is brown and big, the cat is black and soft, and the bird is yellow and small. Lily calls the dog Spot, the cat Fluffy, and the bird Sunny.

One day, Lily sees a new bird in the garden. It is pink and pretty, and it sings a sweet song. Lily wants to make friends with the pink bird. She runs to the house and gets her birdcage. She puts some seeds and water in the cage, and then she goes back to the garden.

She sees the pink bird on a branch. She says, "Hello, pink bird. Do you want to come with me? I have a nice cage for you, and some food and water. You can be my new pet, and I will give you a name. How about Rosie?"

The pink bird looks at Lily and the cage. It thinks for a moment. It likes the seeds and the water, but it does not like the cage. It likes to fly and be free. It says, "No, thank you, Lily. I do not want to go with you. I do not want to be in a cage. I want to stay in the garden, and sing with my friends. I already have a name. It is Ruby."

Lily feels sad. She likes the pink bird, and she wants to play with it. She says, "Please, Ruby, come with me. I will be nice to you, and you will be happy in the cage. You can still sing, and I will listen to you."

Ruby shakes her head. She says, "No, Lily, I cannot come with you. I will not be happy in the cage. I will miss the sky, and the trees, and the flowers. I will miss my friends, and they will miss me. You have other pets, and they need you. You should go back to them, and leave me alone."

Lily understands. She knows that Ruby is right. She loves her pets, and they love her. She does not want to make Ruby unhappy. She says, "OK, Ruby, I will go back to them. I am sorry for bothering you. You are a beautiful bird, and I hope you have a good life. Goodbye, Ruby."

Ruby smiles. She says, "Goodbye, Lily. You are a kind girl, and I hope you have a good life, too. Thank you for the seeds and the water. Maybe I will see you again, someday."

Lily takes her cage and goes back to the house. She hugs her dog, her cat, and her bird. She tells them about Ruby, and they listen to her. She is happy with her pets, and she does not think about the pink bird anymore.
<|end|>


