<|asst|>
Jenny liked to look at the magazines in the store. She liked the pictures of the animals and the toys and the dresses. She asked her mom if she could have one. Her mom said no, they were too expensive and they had to go home soon.

"But mom, please, just one!" Jenny begged. She saw a magazine with a big pink pony on the cover. She loved ponies. She reached for it and tried to pull it out of the rack.

"Jenny, stop that!" her mom said. She grabbed her hand and pulled her away. "You are making a mess and you are being rude. You have to promise me you will not do that again."

Jenny felt embarrassed. She saw some other people looking at her and shaking their heads. She did not like it when people were mad at her. She wanted to make her mom happy. She nodded and said, "I promise, mom. I will not do that again."

Her mom smiled and hugged her. She said, "Thank you, Jenny. I love you. You are a good girl. Maybe next time we can get a magazine from the library. They have many nice ones there."

Jenny felt better. She loved her mom too. She said, "Okay, mom. I'm sorry. Let's go home."

They walked out of the store, holding hands. Jenny forgot about the pony magazine. She was happy to be with her mom.
<|end|>


