Lily and Ben were at the zoo with their mom. They saw many animals, like monkeys, lions, and giraffes. They were happy and excited. But when they came to the rhinoceros, they saw that he was gloomy. He was sitting in a corner of his pen, not moving or making any noise.

"Why is he so gloomy, mom?" Lily asked.

"Maybe he is lonely, or bored, or misses his home," mom said. "Rhinoceroses are very big and strong, but they also have feelings."

"Can we make him happy, mom?" Ben asked.

Mom thought for a moment. Then she said, "Maybe we can. Why don't we try to talk to him and cheer him up?"

Lily and Ben nodded. They walked closer to the rhinoceros and said, "Hello, Mr. Rhinoceros. We are Lily and Ben. We came to see you and your friends at the zoo. You are very big and strong and cool. We like you a lot."

The rhinoceros lifted his head and looked at them. He saw their smiling faces and heard their kind words. He felt a little bit of warmth in his heart. He snorted softly and moved closer to them.

"Hello, Lily and Ben. I am Rocco. Thank you for talking to me and liking me. You are very sweet and brave and nice. I like you too."

Lily and Ben giggled. They reached out their hands and touched his rough skin gently. He lowered his horn and let them stroke it. He felt a little bit of joy in his soul.

Mom smiled and took a picture of them. She was proud of her children and happy for the rhinoceros. She said, "See, you made him happy. You are very good and kind and smart. I love you very much."

Lily and Ben hugged their mom and said, "We love you too, mom. And we love Rocco. He is our new friend."

Rocco nodded and said, "Me too. You are my new friends. You made me less gloomy. Thank you very much."
<|end|>


