<|asst|>
Sara and Ben were twins who liked to play in their room. They had many toys and books and games. But they also liked to eat dessert, especially cake and ice cream. One day, their mom made a big cake and put it in the fridge. She told Sara and Ben not to touch it until after dinner.

But Sara and Ben were very hungry and curious. They wanted to taste the cake. They waited until their mom went to the store. Then they sneaked to the kitchen. They saw the cake in the fridge. It looked yummy and sweet. They tried to open the fridge, but it was locked. Their mom had put a lock on it to keep them away from the cake.

Sara and Ben looked around. They saw a key on the counter. They thought it was the key to the fridge. They grabbed it and ran to the fridge. They put the key in the lock and turned it. They heard a click. They had unlocked the fridge!

They opened the fridge and took out the cake. They cut two big slices and put them on plates. They also took out some ice cream and scooped it on top of the cake. They were very happy and excited. They took their plates to the table and started to eat.

But then they heard a noise. It was their mom. She had come back from the store. She saw Sara and Ben eating the cake and ice cream. She was very angry and surprised. She said, "Sara and Ben, what are you doing? You were not supposed to touch the cake! That was for after dinner! And how did you unlock the fridge?"

Sara and Ben were very scared. They knew they had done something bad. They dropped their forks and looked at their mom. They said, "We are sorry, mom. We were hungry and curious. We saw the key and unlocked the fridge. We just wanted to taste the cake. Please don't be mad at us."

Their mom sighed. She was still angry, but she also loved Sara and Ben. She said, "Sara and Ben, you should not have taken the cake and ice cream. That was not nice or polite. You should have waited until I said it was time for dessert. And you should not have used the key. That was not the key to the fridge. That was the key to the car. Now I have to find another key to drive the car. You have made a big mess and a big problem."

Sara and Ben felt very sorry and sad. They said, "We are very sorry, mom. We did not know that was the key to the car. We did not mean to make a mess and a problem. We will help you clean up and find another key. We will not do it again. We love you, mom."

Their mom smiled. She said, "I love you too, Sara and Ben. But you still have to learn to listen and follow the rules. And you have to eat your dinner before you have dessert. Now come on, let's go to the living room and talk about what you did and how you can make it better."
<|end|>


