Lily and Ben like to watch films on the large TV. They sit on the sofa with their snacks and blankets and choose a film. Today they want to watch a film about animals.

"Look, Ben, there is a lion!" Lily says, pointing at the screen. "He is very large and has a big mane. He can roar very loud."

"Yes, he is the king of the animals," Ben says. "But I like the monkey better. He is funny and can swing on the trees. He can also make funny faces."

They watch the film and laugh and learn about the animals. They see elephants, giraffes, zebras, and more. They also see a bird that can talk.

"Hello, hello, I am a parrot," the bird says on the film. "I can call your name. What is your name?"

Lily and Ben are surprised and excited. They want to talk to the bird.

"My name is Lily," Lily says to the TV.

"My name is Ben," Ben says to the TV.

The bird repeats their names and says hello again. Lily and Ben clap and giggle.

"Wow, he can call our names!" Lily says. "He is very smart and colorful. I wish we had a parrot like him."

"Me too," Ben says. "Maybe we can ask mom and dad if we can get one."

They finish the film and hug each other. They had a lot of fun watching the film about animals. They hope they can watch another one soon.
<|end|>


