Lily and Ben were playing in the park with their mom. They liked to run, slide, swing and climb. They saw a big truck with a loud siren and flashing lights. It was a fire truck. They wanted to see it up close.

"Can we go, mom?" Lily asked.

"OK, but be careful. Fire trucks are dangerous. They are very big and fast. Stay close to me," mom said.

They followed the fire truck to the other side of the park, where there was a lot of smoke. Some people were standing outside a house that was on fire. The firemen got out of the truck and put on their uniforms. They had helmets, jackets, boots and hoses. They looked brave and strong.

"Wow, look at them!" Ben said.

"They are heroes. They help people and animals when there is a fire," mom said.

Lily and Ben waved at the firemen. They hoped they would wave back. One of them did. He smiled and waved his hand.

"Hi, kids! Thank you for waving. We appreciate your support. Stay safe and have fun," he said.

Lily and Ben felt happy and proud. They waved again and said, "Thank you, fireman! You are awesome!"

They watched the firemen work hard to put out the fire. They hoped everyone was OK. They learned a lot about fire trucks and firemen that day. They decided they wanted to be firemen when they grew up.
<|end|>


