Anna and Ben are friends. They like to play in the park. One day, they see a big truck with a loud horn. The truck has a big bow on it. It is a gift for the park.

"Wow, look at the truck!" Anna says. "It has a bow like my hair!"

"Maybe it has toys inside!" Ben says. "Let's go see!"

They run to the truck. But they are careful. They look both ways before they cross the street. They hold hands. They do not want to get hurt.

The truck driver sees them. He smiles and waves. He opens the back of the truck. He shows them what is inside.

"Hello, kids!" he says. "Do you want to see the gift for the park?"

"Yes, please!" Anna and Ben say.

The truck driver pulls out a big slide. It is red and yellow and blue. It has a ladder and a tunnel and a curve. It looks like fun.

"This is the new slide for the park!" he says. "I will put it over there, next to the swings. Do you want to help me?"

"Yes, please!" Anna and Ben say.

They help the truck driver carry the slide. They are careful. They do not drop it. They do not run. They listen to the truck driver.

They put the slide in the right place. They thank the truck driver. He thanks them back. He gives them each a sticker. It has a picture of a truck and a bow.

"Bye, kids!" he says. "Have fun with the new slide!"

"Bye, mister!" Anna and Ben say. "Thank you for the gift!"

They wave to the truck driver. He waves back. He drives away with his truck. He honks his horn.

Anna and Ben run to the slide. They take turns going down. They laugh and shout. They have fun. They like the new slide. They like the truck driver. They like the bow. They are happy.
<|end|>


