Tom and Lily were playing in the garden. They liked to dig in the dirt and make mud pies. They had a big bucket of water to make the mud wet. But the bucket had a leak. Water dripped out of the hole and made a puddle on the grass.

"Look, Tom, the bucket is broken!" Lily said. "We need more water for our pies!"

Tom frowned. He did not like the leak. He wanted to fix the bucket. He ran to the shed and looked for some tape. He found a roll of tape and brought it back to the bucket. He tried to stick the tape over the hole, but it did not work. The water was too wet and the tape was too sticky. The tape fell off and the water kept dripping.

"This is a bad bucket!" Tom said. "We need a new bucket!"

Lily nodded. She agreed with Tom. They needed a new bucket. But they did not have any money to buy a new bucket. They only had some coins that they found in the sofa. They wondered if that was enough.

"Maybe we can ask Mom for some money," Lily said. "She is rich. She has a lot of money in her purse."

Tom liked that idea. He thought Mom would give them some money for a new bucket. He and Lily ran to the house and looked for Mom. They found her in the kitchen, making lunch.

"Mom, Mom, can we have some money?" Tom asked. "We need a new bucket. Our bucket has a leak and we can't make mud pies."

Mom smiled. She saw the dirt on their faces and clothes. She saw the tape in Tom's hand and the coins in Lily's hand. She knew they had been playing in the garden.

"You don't need money for a new bucket," Mom said. "You can use this old pot instead. It has no leak and it can hold water. You can make mud pies with this pot."

She gave them a big pot that she did not use anymore. It was shiny and clean. Tom and Lily thanked Mom and took the pot to the garden. They filled it with water and poured it on the dirt. They made big and round mud pies. They were happy. They did not frown anymore. They smiled and laughed. They did not need a rich bucket. They had a good pot.
<|end|>


