Lily and Ben are playing in the park. They like to run and jump and slide. Lily sees a big swing. She wants to try it. She runs to the swing and sits on it.

"Push me, Ben!" she says. Ben pushes her gently. Lily feels happy. She swings higher and higher. She laughs and kicks her legs.

But then, the swing goes too high. Lily feels scared. She holds on tight. She wants to stop. She tries to slow down. But she can't. She lets go of the swing. She falls to the ground.

"Ow!" she cries. She hurts her knee. It bleeds a little. She feels sad and sore.

Ben runs to her. He sees her knee. He feels worried. He wants to help her.

"Lily, are you okay?" he asks. He hugs her. He wipes her tears. He takes a band-aid from his pocket. He puts it on her knee.

"There, there," he says. "It will be better soon. Don't be sad. I'm here."

Lily smiles a little. She feels better. She hugs Ben back. She says, "Thank you, Ben. You are a good friend. I'm sorry I fell. I won't swing so high next time."

Ben says, "It's okay, Lily. Accidents happen. I'm glad you're okay. Do you want to play something else?"

Lily nods. She says, "Yes, please. Let's play something else. Something safe and fun."

They hold hands and walk to the sandbox. They play with the sand and the toys. They forget about the fall. They have fun. They are happy.
