Tom and Mia are friends. They like to play together at the gym. The gym has many things to do. There are balls, mats, ropes, swings and slides. Tom and Mia have fun at the gym.

One day, Tom and Mia want to learn something new. They see a big hoop on the wall. It looks like a ring. They want to try it. They ask the teacher for help. The teacher is nice. She shows them how to hold the hoop and swing on it.

Tom goes first. He holds the hoop with both hands. He swings his legs and lifts his body. He feels like a bird. He says, "Whee! This is fun!" Mia claps for him. She says, "You are good, Tom!"

Then Mia goes. She holds the hoop with both hands. She swings her legs and lifts her body. She feels like a star. She says, "Wow! This is cool!" Tom cheers for her. He says, "You are good, Mia!"

Tom and Mia are glad. They learned something new. They hug the teacher and thank her. They say, "Thank you, teacher! You are nice!" The teacher smiles and says, "You are welcome, Tom and Mia! You are brave and smart!" Tom and Mia are happy. They love the gym.
