Anna and Ben were very happy. They were going to visit their grandma and grandpa. They loved their grandma and grandpa very much. They always had fun with them.

They got in the car with their mom and dad. They drove for a long time. They saw many things on the way. They saw cows and horses and trees and flowers. They sang songs and played games.

When they got to grandma and grandpa's house, they jumped out of the car. They ran to the door and knocked. Grandma and grandpa opened the door and hugged them.

"Hello, Anna and Ben! We are so glad to see you!" grandma said.

"Hello, grandma and grandpa! We missed you!" Anna and Ben said.

Grandma and grandpa took them inside. They showed them a surprise. They had a new puppy. The puppy was black and white and fluffy. He was very cute and friendly. He wagged his tail and licked their faces.

"Wow! A puppy! What is his name?" Anna asked.

"His name is Spot. He is a gift for you. You can play with him and take care of him when you visit us," grandpa said.

"Thank you, grandma and grandpa! He is the best gift ever!" Ben said.

Anna and Ben were very happy. They played with Spot in the yard. They threw a ball and he fetched it. They gave him treats and he did tricks. They cuddled him and he snuggled them.

They had an enormous smile on their faces. They loved their grandma and grandpa and their new puppy. They had a wonderful visit.
