Tim and Mia were playing in the park with their bikes. They liked to go fast and make turns and jumps. They had fun and laughed a lot.

But then Tim saw a big hole in the fence. He wanted to see what was behind it. He told Mia to follow him. He pushed his bike through the hole and went to the other side.

Mia was scared. She did not want to go to the other side. She saw a lot of smoke and noise and big machines. She thought it was a bad place. She shouted to Tim, "Come back, Tim! Come back!"

Tim did not listen. He was curious. He rode his bike closer to the machines. He saw a big pipe that was spitting out fire. He thought it was cool. He wanted to touch it.

But then he felt very hot and dizzy. He could not breathe well. He realized that the fire was taking away the oxygen. The oxygen was the air that he needed to live. He started to cough and cry. He wanted to go back to the park.

He turned his bike around and tried to ride back to the fence. But it was hard. He was very tired and sick. He fell off his bike and lay on the ground.

Mia saw him fall. She was very worried. She ran to the hole and called for help. She saw a man who was wearing a big hat and a coat. He was a firefighter. He had a hose that could spray water.

The firefighter saw Mia and Tim. He understood what happened. He ran to Tim and picked him up. He put a mask on his face that gave him oxygen. He said, "Don't worry, Tim. I will restore you. I will make you better."

He carried Tim to his truck and drove him to the hospital. Mia followed him on her bike. She was glad that the firefighter was there. She hoped that Tim would be okay. She learned a lesson. She would never go to the bad place again. She would stay in the park with her bike.
<|end|>


