Lily and Ben are twins. They like to help Mom and Dad with jobs. Today, they have a big job. They have to pick apples from the tree.

Lily and Ben put on their hats and boots. They take a basket and go to the tree. They see many red apples. They are happy.

"Look, Ben, I can pick this apple!" Lily says. She reaches up and pulls an apple. She puts it in the basket.

"Good job, Lily!" Ben says. He tries to pick an apple too. But he is too slow. The apple falls on his head. He says "Ow!"

Lily laughs. She gives Ben a hug. She says "It's okay, Ben. You can try again. We can pick apples together."

Ben smiles. He says "Thank you, Lily. You are a good sister. We can help Mom and Dad with the job."

Lily and Ben pick more apples. They fill the basket. They are proud. They take the basket to Mom and Dad. Mom and Dad are happy. They say "Well done, Lily and Ben! You are very helpful. We love you."

Lily and Ben hug Mom and Dad. They say "We love you too. We like to do jobs with you."

They eat some apples. They are sweet and juicy. They are happy.
