Anna and Ben were twins who loved Christmas. They wanted to see Santa Claus and get many gifts. They wrote letters to Santa and put them in a big red sock. They hung the sock on the chimney in the living room.

On Christmas Eve, they lay in their beds and tried to sleep. But they were too excited and curious. They wanted to sneak out and peek at the chimney. Maybe they would see Santa or hear his sleigh.

"Ben, are you awake?" Anna whispered.

"Yes, I am. Do you want to go downstairs?" Ben whispered back.

"Yes, let's go. But we have to be very quiet and careful. We don't want to scare Santa away." Anna said.

They got out of their beds and put on their slippers. They tiptoed down the stairs and hid behind the couch. They looked at the chimney and saw a big sack full of gifts. They also saw a plate of cookies and a glass of milk.

"Wow, look at all those gifts! Santa is so generous!" Ben said.

"Shh, I hear something. It sounds like bells and hoofs." Anna said.

They saw a flash of red and white and a big black boot. Then they heard a jolly voice.

"Ho ho ho! Merry Christmas, Anna and Ben! I'm glad you liked my gifts. And thank you for the cookies and milk. They were delicious. Now, go back to bed and have sweet dreams. I have to go and visit more children. Bye bye!" Santa said.

Anna and Ben were amazed and happy. They saw Santa! He was real and kind. They ran back to their beds and hugged their teddy bears. They fell asleep with smiles on their faces. They had the best Christmas ever.
