Tom and Lily were having lunch with their mom. They liked to eat sandwiches and fruit. Mom gave them each a napkin to wipe their mouths. Tom saw that his napkin had a picture of a hairy dog on it. He liked dogs, but he did not like hairy ones. He wanted a napkin with a smooth cat on it.

"Mom, can I have a different napkin?" he asked. "I do not like hairy dogs. They make me sneeze."

Mom smiled and said, "Sorry, Tom, we only have napkins with hairy dogs today. They are from your aunt's birthday party. She loves hairy dogs. You can use the other side of the napkin if you want."

Lily looked at her napkin and saw that it also had a hairy dog on it. She did not mind hairy dogs. She thought they were cute and fluffy. She wanted to make Tom happy, so she had an idea.

"Tom, do you want to trade napkins with me?" she offered. "I do not care about the picture. I only care about the napkin being clean."

Tom smiled and said, "Thank you, Lily. You are a good sister. I will trade napkins with you."

They swapped their napkins and finished their lunch. Mom was proud of them for being kind and sharing. She gave them each a hug and a kiss and said, "Now it is time for a nap. You both did a good job today."
