One day, Lily and Ben were playing in the park. They liked to slide, swing and run. But then, Lily fell down and hurt her knee. She cried and showed Ben her skin. It was red and had a little blood.

"Ow, ow, ow!" Lily said. "It hurts!"

Ben wanted to help Lily. He remembered that his mom had a box with things to fix skin. He ran to his mom and asked for the box. His mom gave him the box and followed him to Lily.

"Look, Lily, I have something to fix your skin," Ben said. He opened the box and took out a band-aid. It was not a normal band-aid. It had a picture of a unicorn on it. It was unusual.

"Wow, what is that?" Lily asked. She stopped crying and looked at the band-aid.

"It is a magic band-aid," Ben said. "It will make your skin better and you will feel happy."

Ben put the band-aid on Lily's knee. Lily smiled and thanked Ben. She felt better.

"Thank you, Ben, you are a good friend," Lily said.

"You are welcome, Lily, I am glad you are okay," Ben said.

They hugged and went back to play. They had fun with the unusual band-aid. They pretended that Lily had a unicorn power and Ben had a dragon power. They were happy.
