Tim and Sam were friends who liked to play with toys. They had many cars, planes, and trains, but they wanted something new. They decided to build a missile with some boxes, tubes, and tape. They worked hard and made a big missile that looked like a rocket.

"Wow, our missile is so cool!" Tim said. "We can pretend to fly to the moon or to another planet!"

"Yes, let's do that!" Sam agreed. "But first, we need to find a place to launch it. Where can we go?"

They looked around and saw a big house with a big yard. It belonged to Mr. Rich, who had a lot of money and a lot of things. He also had a big fence and a big dog.

"Let's go there!" Tim said. "Maybe Mr. Rich will let us use his yard. He has so much space and he is not home."

"OK, but we have to be careful. His dog is very loud and mean. He might bite us or our missile." Sam said.

They carried their missile to the fence and tried to climb over it. But the dog saw them and started to bark and run towards them. Tim and Sam got scared and dropped their missile. It fell on the ground and broke into pieces.

"Uh-oh, our missile is ruined!" Tim cried. "And the dog is coming! Run!"

They ran away from the fence and the dog. They left their missile behind and went back to their homes. They were sad and angry.

"Mr. Rich is so mean!" Tim said. "He has so much and he does not share. He does not let us play in his yard. He does not like us or our missile."

"Yes, he is mean!" Sam said. "But we are still friends. And we can still play with our other toys. Maybe we can build something else tomorrow."

They hugged and smiled. They were still friends and they still liked to play. They did not need a missile or a rich man to have fun.
