<|end|>
<|asst|>
Lily liked to read big books with many words. She had a dictionary that helped her learn new words. She was very independent and did not need help from anyone.

One day, a big dog came to her garden. It barked and ran towards her. Lily was scared and ran to her house. She grabbed her dictionary and held it tight.

The dog followed her and scratched at the door. Lily shouted, "Go away, dog! You are not nice!"

Her mom heard her and came to see what was wrong. She saw the dog and opened the door. She told the dog, "Shoo, shoo! This is not your home!"

The dog ran away and Lily hugged her mom. She said, "Thank you, mom! You protected me from the dog!"

Her mom smiled and said, "You're welcome, Lily! I'm proud of you for being brave and independent. And I'm glad you love your dictionary. It's a very useful book."
<|end|>


