<|end|>
<|asst|>
Sara and Ben are playing with their toys in the living room. Sara has a pink doll and Ben has a black car. They are having fun, but they are also making a mess. Toys are everywhere on the floor, on the couch, on the table.

Mom comes in and sees the mess. She is not happy. She says, "Sara and Ben, you need to clean up your toys. It is time for lunch. Put your toys in the box, please."

Sara and Ben do not want to stop playing. They say, "But Mom, we are not done yet. We want to play more. Can we clean up later?"

Mom shakes her head. She says, "No, you need to clean up now. If you clean up quickly, you can have a treat after lunch. How about some cookies?"

Sara and Ben like cookies. They decide to listen to Mom. They start to pick up their toys and put them in the box. Sara finds her pink doll under the couch. Ben finds his black car behind the curtain. They work together and soon the living room is clean.

Mom smiles and says, "Good job, Sara and Ben. You are very helpful. Now you can wash your hands and come to the table. I have made some sandwiches and some cookies for you."

Sara and Ben are happy. They say, "Thank you, Mom. We love you. And we love cookies." They run to the bathroom to wash their hands. Then they sit down at the table and enjoy their lunch and their treat. They are glad they cleaned up their toys.
<|end|>


