<|asst|>
Lily liked to write in her journal. She wrote about her family, her friends, and her dreams. She wrote with a purple pen and drew pictures with crayons. She kept her journal in a secret place under her bed.

One day, Lily's cousin Max came to visit. He was older than Lily and he was wealthy. He had many toys and clothes and books. He liked to show off and brag. He saw Lily's journal and wanted to see it.

"Let me see your journal, Lily," he said. "I bet it's boring and silly."

"No, Max, you can't see it," Lily said. "It's mine and it's private. Go play with your own things."

Max was angry and sneaky. He waited until Lily went to the bathroom and then he grabbed her journal. He ran to the living room and opened it. He laughed at Lily's words and pictures. He tore some pages and threw them on the floor.

Lily came back and saw what Max had done. She was sad and mad. She ran to Max and tried to get her journal back. She shouted, "Max, you're mean and rude! You bring back my journal right now!"

Max pushed Lily away and said, "No, I won't. Your journal is dumb and ugly. You're not wealthy like me. You have nothing good."

Lily's mom heard the noise and came to see what was wrong. She saw the torn pages and the crying Lily. She scolded Max and made him apologize. She said, "Max, you're in trouble. You don't bring other people's things without asking. You don't hurt their feelings. You don't act like a bully. You say sorry to Lily and help her fix her journal."

Max felt ashamed and sorry. He said sorry to Lily and helped her tape the pages. He gave her a hug and said, "Lily, I'm sorry. Your journal is not dumb and ugly. It's nice and creative. You're not nothing. You're my cousin and my friend."

Lily forgave Max and smiled. She said, "Thank you, Max. I'm sorry I called you mean and rude. You're not a bully. You're my cousin and my friend."

They hugged and played together. They shared their toys and books and dreams. They wrote in Lily's journal with a purple pen and drew pictures with crayons. They kept the journal in a secret place under their bed.
<|end|>


