Anna and Ben are best friends. They like to play with dolls and cars and books. One day, they go to the park with their moms. They see a big slide and run to it.

"Me first!" Anna says. She climbs up the ladder and slides down. "Whee!"

"Me too!" Ben says. He follows Anna and slides down. "Wow!"

They slide again and again. They have incredible fun. They forget about everything else.

But then, Anna feels something tickle her nose. She sneezes. "Achoo!"

"Are you okay?" Ben asks.

Anna rubs her nose. "I think so. But my nose is wet and cold."

She looks at her hand. She sees blood. "Oh no! My nose is bleeding!"

She starts to cry. "Mommy! Mommy!"

Her mom hears her and runs to her. "What happened, sweetie?"

"I don't know. I was sliding and then my nose hurt and now it's bleeding!"

Her mom hugs her and wipes her nose with a tissue. "It's okay, honey. Sometimes noses bleed for no reason. It will stop soon. You're very brave."

Ben comes to Anna. He gives her his favorite car. "Here, Anna. This is for you. I hope your nose feels better."

Anna smiles. She takes the car. "Thank you, Ben. You're very kind. You're my best friend."

They hug. Their moms smile. They go to the bench and have some juice and cookies. They share their toys and stories. They don't forget to have fun.
<|end|>


