<|asst|>
Lily and Max were best friends. They liked to play in the park every day. They liked to swing, slide and jog. Jogging made them happy and strong.

One day, they saw a big dog in the park. The dog was brown and fluffy. It had a red collar and a shiny tag. The dog looked friendly, but Lily and Max did not know the dog.

"Hello, dog," Lily said. "What is your name?"

The dog wagged its tail and licked Lily's face. Lily giggled. Max wanted to pet the dog too. He reached out his hand.

But then, a loud voice shouted. "Hey, get away from my dog! He is mine!"

Lily and Max looked up. They saw a boy running towards them. The boy was bigger than them. He had a mean face and a dirty shirt. He grabbed the dog's collar and pulled it away.

"Your dog?" Lily asked. "But he was playing with us. He is nice."

The boy snorted. "He is not nice. He is spoiled. He only likes me. You are not allowed to touch him. Go away!"

Lily and Max felt sad and scared. They did not like the boy. He was rude and selfish. They wanted to play with the dog.

"Please, can we play with your dog?" Max asked. "We will be gentle. We like dogs."

The boy shook his head. "No, you can't. He is my dog. You have nothing. You are nothing. Now go away, or I will make you go away!"

The boy pushed Max to the ground. Max cried out. Lily ran to help him. The dog barked and tried to get free. He did not like the boy either. He wanted to play with Lily and Max.

But the boy was stronger. He dragged the dog away. He yelled at Lily and Max. "You are stupid and ugly. You have no friends. You have no heart. Go away and never come back!"

Lily and Max hugged each other. They felt hurt and angry. They did not understand why the boy was so mean. They had a heart. They had each other. They had many friends.

They decided to ignore the boy. They got up and jogged away. They jogged to the other side of the park. They found a new place to play. They found a new friend. A cat. The cat was black and soft. It had a green collar and a bell. The cat was friendly and sweet. It purred and rubbed against Lily and Max.

"Hello, cat," Lily said. "What is your name?"

The cat meowed. Lily and Max smiled. They petted the cat. They played with the cat. They forgot about the boy and the dog. They were happy and strong. They had a heart.
<|end|>


