Lila liked to fold paper. She learned how to make a bird, a boat, a hat and a star. She used many colors of paper and put them on her shelf. She was proud of her paper things.

One day, she saw her grandma sewing with a needle and thread. She wanted to try too. She asked her grandma, "Can I sew with you?"

Her grandma smiled and said, "Yes, you can, but you have to be careful. The needle is sharp and the thread is thin. You have to hold them right and not poke yourself."

She gave Lila a piece of cloth, a needle and some thread. She showed her how to fold the cloth and make a stitch. Lila tried to copy her, but it was hard. The needle slipped and the thread tangled. She felt frustrated and said, "I can't do it. It's too hard."

Her grandma hugged her and said, "Don't give up, Lila. Sewing is a skill that takes time and practice. You are doing well for your first time. You just have to be patient and keep trying. You are a wise girl and you can learn anything you want."

Lila felt better and thanked her grandma. She decided to try again and again until she could sew a nice seam. She learned how to make a button, a pocket and a flower. She used many colors of thread and put them on her cloth. She was proud of her sewing things.
<|end|>


