Lily and Ben are friends. They like to play in the park. One day, they find a shiny stone on the ground. It is red and sparkly.

"Wow, look at this!" Lily says. "It is so pretty!"

Ben nods. He likes the stone too. He wants to keep it. He asks Lily, "Can I have it, please?"

Lily thinks for a moment. She likes the stone too, but she likes Ben more. She smiles and says, "Okay, you can have it. But you have to share it with me sometimes."

Ben agrees. He is happy. He says, "Thank you, Lily. You are very kind. I will share it with you always."

He puts the stone in his pocket. He feels it is warm and smooth. He thinks it is a charming stone. He hugs Lily and says, "You are my best friend."

Lily hugs him back. She says, "You are my best friend too."

They hold hands and run to the swings. They play and laugh. They are happy. They have a shiny stone and a good friend.
<|end|>


