<|asst|>
Tom and Lily were playing pirates in the garden. They had a big box that was their ship. They put a stick in the box for a mast and a sheet for a sail. They had hats and swords and a map.

"Ahoy, matey!" Tom said. "We are looking for treasure on a faraway island. Are you ready, Lily?"

"Aye, aye, captain!" Lily said. "But I am hungry. Can we have a snack first?"

Tom looked at the map. He saw a red X. "No, Lily, we have to find the treasure first. It is right here, under the big tree. Come on, let's go!"

They jumped out of the box and ran to the tree. They dug a hole with their hands and found a tin box. They opened it and saw shiny coins and jewels.

"Wow, we are rich!" Tom said. "We can buy anything we want!"

"Look, Tom, there is a chocolate bar in the box too!" Lily said. "Can we share it?"

"Of course, Lily, you are my best mate!" Tom said. He broke the chocolate bar in half and gave one piece to Lily. They ate the chocolate and smiled.

Suddenly, they heard a loud noise. It was their mom. She was calling them from the house.

"Tom, Lily, come inside! It is getting cold and dark. You have to wash up and get ready for dinner!"

Tom and Lily looked at each other. They did not want to leave their ship and their treasure.

"Can we play a little more, mom?" Tom asked.

"No, Tom, you have to come inside now. It is going to freeze tonight. You don't want to catch a cold, do you?" Mom said.

Tom and Lily sighed. They put the tin box back in the hole and covered it with dirt. They took their hats and swords and ran to the house.

"Bye, bye, ship!" Lily said. "We will come back tomorrow and play more pirates!"

"Bye, bye, ship!" Tom said. "You are the best ship ever!"
<|end|>


