Lila and Tom are friends. They like to play with toys and books. One day, they find a big box in the yard. They open the box and see a lot of shiny things inside. They are happy and curious.

"What are these?" Lila asks, picking up a small thing with buttons and a screen.

"I think it is a cell," Tom says, looking at another thing that looks like a cell. "My mom has one. She talks to it and it talks back."

"Wow, can we talk to them too?" Lila wonders, pressing some buttons.

"Maybe, let's try," Tom says, pressing some buttons too.

They hold the cells to their ears and wait. Nothing happens. They try again and again, but the cells are silent.

"These cells are not good," Lila says, feeling sad. "They do not talk to us."

"Maybe they need something," Tom says, thinking hard. "Maybe they need power."

"Power? What is power?" Lila asks, confused.

"Power is what makes things work," Tom explains. "Like the light and the TV and the fan. They need power from the wall."

"Oh, I see," Lila says, nodding. "But how do we give power to the cells?"

Tom looks around and sees a long thing with a plug at the end. He remembers that his mom uses it to charge her cell.

"Look, Lila, I found something," he says, holding the long thing. "This can give power to the cells. We just need to find a hole in the wall."

They look for a hole in the wall and find one near the door. Tom puts the plug in the hole and the long thing lights up. He feels happy and smart.

"Good job, Tom, you are dependable," Lila says, smiling. "Now let's set the cells on the long thing and see if they work."

They set the cells on the long thing and wait. After a while, the cells beep and show some words on the screen.

"Hello, this is a test message. Please reply if you receive it," the words say.

Lila and Tom are amazed and excited. They type some letters on the screen and press send.

"Hi, we are Lila and Tom. We are playing with your cells. Who are you?" they write.

They wait for an answer, hoping to hear from someone new. They do not know that the cells belong to their dad, who is at work and very surprised to get their message. He smiles and writes back.

"Hi, Lila and Tom. I am your dad. I am glad you are having fun with my cells. But please be careful and do not touch anything else in the box. I will be home soon and tell you more about them. I love you."
<|end|>


