Ben and Mia like to play in the park. They run and jump and slide and swing. They have fun with their friends and their toys.

One day, Ben and Mia are playing tag. Ben is it and he tries to catch Mia. Mia runs fast and tries to hide behind a tree. But Ben is faster and he tags Mia on her back.

"Got you!" Ben says. "You are it now!"

Mia laughs and chases Ben. She runs after him and tries to tag him on his arm. But Ben is clever and he dodges Mia. He runs to the slide and slides down.

Mia follows him and slides down too. But she slides too fast and she bumps her knee on the ground. She feels a sharp pain and she cries.

"Ow, ow, ow!" Mia says. "My knee hurts!"

Ben hears Mia and he stops. He runs to Mia and he sees her knee. It has a red scratch and a little blood.

"Oh no, Mia!" Ben says. "Are you okay?"

He hugs Mia and he tries to make her feel better. He looks around and he sees a clear bottle on a bench. It has water and a spray. He remembers that his mom uses it to clean his cuts.

He gets the bottle and he sprays some water on Mia's knee. It stings a little but it also cools the pain. He finds a band-aid in his pocket and he sticks it on Mia's knee.

"There, Mia," Ben says. "Your knee is clean and safe now. Does it still hurt?"

Mia stops crying and she looks at her knee. She sees the band-aid and she smiles.

"Thank you, Ben," Mia says. "You are a good friend. My knee feels better now."

She hugs Ben and he hugs her back. They are happy and they go back to play. They run and jump and slide and swing. They have fun with their friends and their toys.
<|end|>


