Lily and Ben are playing in the backyard. They have a big ball and a small ball. They throw the balls to each other and catch them. They laugh and have fun.

But then, a loud noise makes them stop. They hear a bark and a growl. They see a big dog running towards them. The dog is angry and scary. Lily and Ben are afraid.

"Run, Lily, run!" Ben shouts. He grabs the small ball and throws it at the dog. The dog chases the ball and leaves them alone. Lily and Ben run to the house. They slam the door and lock it.

They are safe now. They hug each other and breathe hard. They are still scared, but they are also brave. They rub their arms and legs. They have some scratches and bruises from the dog.

"Are you okay, Lily?" Ben asks.

"I'm okay, Ben. You are a good brother. You saved me from the dog," Lily says.

They smile and hug again. They are happy to have each other. They go to the kitchen and ask Mom for some cookies and milk. They tell Mom what happened. Mom is proud of them and gives them a kiss. She also rubs their backs and makes them feel better. She says she will call the dog's owner and tell him to keep his dog in his yard.

Lily and Ben eat their cookies and drink their milk. They are not afraid anymore. They are still friends with the balls. They decide to play with them inside the house. They are careful not to break anything. They have fun again.
<|end|>


