<|asst|>
Lily and Ben were playing with their toy animals in the garden. They liked to pretend they were in the jungle and make noises like the animals. Lily had a lion and Ben had a monkey.

"Roar!" Lily said, making her lion jump on the grass. "I am the king of the jungle. I have the most power. All the animals are afraid of me."

"Ooh-ooh-ah-ah!" Ben said, making his monkey swing from a branch. "You are not the king of the jungle. You are mean and scary. You make the animals cry."

Lily and Ben started to argue. They both wanted to be the best and have the most power. They did not want to share or be nice to each other.

Suddenly, they heard a loud noise from behind the fence. It sounded like a real lion. They stopped arguing and looked at each other with fear. They hugged their toy animals and ran to the house.

"Mommy, mommy, there is a lion in the garden!" they cried.

Mommy came out and saw what was making the noise. It was not a lion. It was a big dog. The dog had escaped from the neighbor's yard and was barking at the fence.

Mommy smiled and said, "Don't be afraid, children. That is not a lion. That is Max, the neighbor's dog. He is very friendly and compassionate. He likes to play and have fun. He is not mean or scary. He just wants to say hello."

Lily and Ben looked at the dog and saw that he was wagging his tail and licking his nose. He did not look like a lion at all. He looked like a nice dog.

They felt silly and ashamed. They had been mean and scary to each other, like the lion they thought they heard. They had not been friendly and compassionate, like the dog they saw.

They said sorry to each other and hugged. They decided to share their toy animals and be nice to each other. They learned that having power is not as important as having compassion. They also learned that sometimes things are not what they seem. They thanked mommy and went back to the garden. They invited Max to join their jungle game. They all had fun and made happy noises.
<|end|>


