Once upon a time, in a small house, there was a little girl named Sue. She loved to help her mom. Today, Sue wanted to help her mom clean the house. Sue's mom said, "Thank you for helping, Sue!"

In the living room, Sue saw a box of matches. She knew matches could be dangerous, so she asked her mom, "What should I do with these matches?" Her mom said, "Put them up high, so your little brother can't reach them." Sue put the matches on a high shelf.

Later, Sue's mom was looking for the matches to light a candle. She couldn't find them. Sue said, "I put them on the high shelf, so my brother can't get them." Her mom smiled and said, "Good job, Sue! You helped keep your brother safe and our house clean." Sue felt happy that she could help her mom.
<|end|>


