Once upon a time, there was a large fish named Fin. Fin loved to surf in the big blue sea. One day, while Fin was surfing, he saw a small fish named Gill. Gill was sad and lost.

"Hi Gill, why are you sad?" asked Fin. Gill said, "I need my mom, but I can't find her." Fin wanted to help. "Let's surf together, and find your mom," said Fin. They surfed and surfed, and soon they found Gill's mom.

Gill and his mom were happy. "Thank you, Fin," said Gill's mom. "You are a good friend." Fin smiled and said, "We all need friends to help us when we are lost." The moral of the story is that friends can help us when we need them.
<|end|>


