Once upon a time, there was a little boy named Tim. One day, Tim went for a walk and saw a big wall. He wanted to see what was behind the wall, so he found a way to climb it. When he got to the top, he saw a big, spicy pepper.

"Wow! That's a big pepper!" Tim said. He wanted to take the spicy pepper home, but he was scared. He thought the pepper might be too spicy for him. As he stood on the wall, a friendly bird flew by and saw Tim.

"Hi, Tim! Why are you scared?" the bird asked.

"I want to take this spicy pepper home, but I'm scared it's too spicy for me," Tim said.

"Don't worry, Tim! If you think it's too spicy, just share it with your friends. They can help you eat it," the bird said.

Tim smiled and thanked the bird. He took the spicy pepper home and shared it with his friends. They all had fun eating the spicy pepper together, and Tim wasn't scared anymore.
<|end|>


