Once upon a time, there was a sweet little girl named Lily. She loved to spread jam on her bread every morning. One day, she decided to go to the station with her mom. Lily was very excited because she had never been to the station before.

At the station, Lily saw a big train. It was so big and noisy that it made her jump. She held her mom's hand very tight. While they waited for their train, Lily saw a man selling jam. She wanted to buy some jam to spread on her bread at home.

Lily let go of her mom's hand and went to the man to buy the jam. But when she turned around, her mom was gone. Lily was scared and started to cry. She looked everywhere, but she could not find her mom. A nice lady saw Lily crying and tried to help her, but they could not find her mom. In the end, Lily was very sad and learned a big lesson about staying close to her mom.
<|end|>


