Once upon a time, there was a little boy named Tim. Tim had a big blue ball. He loved to play with his blue ball every day. One day, he met a girl named Sue. Sue wanted to play with the blue ball too.

"Can I play with your blue ball?" Sue asked. Tim did not want to share his blue ball. He wanted to keep it all for himself. This made Sue sad. They both wanted to play, but they did not know how to share.

Tim had an idea. He said, "Let's raise the blue ball high in the air and see who can catch it first." Sue thought this was a good idea. They both raised the ball high in the air and tried to catch it. They laughed and played together.

As they played, Tim and Sue learned to share the blue ball. They became good friends. They raised the ball high in the air and caught it together. They played happily ever after, and the blue ball brought them lots of wonder and fun.
