Once upon a time, in a small town, there was a boy named Tim. Tim loved to play with his toy cars and trucks. He had a big box of them, and each one had a special gear inside that made it go.

One day, Tim wanted to set up a race with his cars and trucks. He lined them all up, ready to go. He pushed each car and truck, making them zoom across the floor. Tim was so happy to see them race, but he noticed one car was not going as fast as the others. It was a small red car, and it seemed weak.

Tim felt sad for the weak red car, so he decided to help. He opened up the car and found the gear inside. The gear was old and worn out. Tim took the gear out and replaced it with a new, shiny one. He put the car back together and set it on the floor to race again.

This time, the red car was not weak anymore. It zoomed across the floor, faster than all the other cars and trucks. Tim was so happy that he could help his little red car. From that day on, the red car always won the races, and Tim knew that even the weakest car could be the fastest with a little help.
<|end|>


