Once upon a time, in a small town, there was a busy street. On this street, there were many people and cars. They all moved around a lot. It was always noisy and full of life.

One day, a little girl named Lily wanted to cross the busy street. She knew she had to be careful. She looked both ways and saw a big car coming. The car saw Lily too. The car stopped and let Lily go first. The car did a good thing called "yield". Lily said "thank you" and crossed the street safely.

On Sunday, Lily and her mom went for a walk on the busy street. They held hands and looked at all the people and cars. They had a fun time. Lily remembered to be careful and look both ways when crossing the street. And, the cars remembered to yield for her.
