Once upon a time, there was a clever little dog named Max. He lived in a small house with his family. One day, Max saw a big hole in the fence. He thought it was a great chance for an escape to have some fun outside.

Max went through the hole and met a big cat. The cat said, "I saw you escape. Why did you leave your home?" Max sighed and said, "I wanted to have fun outside." The cat smiled and said, "Let's play together, but remember to go back home later."

Max and the cat played all day. They ran, jumped, and laughed. But soon, Max started to miss his family. He said to the cat, "I had fun, but I need to go back home now. My family must be worried about me." The cat agreed and helped Max find his way home.

Max's family was so happy to see him. They hugged him and said, "We were worried about you, Max. Please don't escape again." Max learned that having fun is good, but it's important to stay safe and not make his family worry.

The moral of the story is: it's good to have fun, but always remember to stay safe and think about your family's feelings.
<|end|>


