Once upon a time, there was a little girl named Mimi. Mimi loved to cook with her mom. One Wednesday, Mimi and her mom were making a big pot of soup. Mimi's mom said, "Mimi, can you help me stir the soup?" Mimi was so happy to help her mom.

Mimi tried to stir the soup, but the spoon was very big and heavy. Mimi felt weak. She said, "Mom, I can't stir the soup. The spoon is too big for me." Her mom smiled and said, "Don't worry, Mimi. I'll help you." So, Mimi and her mom stirred the soup together.

As they stirred the soup, Mimi's mom told her a story. The story was about a little girl who never gave up, even when things were hard. Mimi listened to the story and felt stronger. She learned that even if you feel weak, you can still do big things if you try and ask for help. And from that day on, Mimi always tried her best and never gave up.
