Once upon a time, in a lively forest, there lived a little rabbit and a big bear. They were best friends. Every day, they played together and had lots of fun.

One day, while playing, the rabbit saw a quick bird flying in the sky. He told the bear, "Let's send a message to the bird!" The bear agreed, and they wrote a message on a leaf. The rabbit said, "Hello, quick bird! We want to be friends with you. Will you play with us?"

The quick bird saw the message and flew down to meet the rabbit and the bear. They all played together and had a great time. The bird was so fast, and the rabbit and the bear learned to be quick too. They were very happy to have a new friend.

The moral of the story is that making new friends can be fun and can help us learn new things. And when we are kind and send messages to others, we can make more friends and have even more fun.
