One day, a little girl named Lucy wanted a red waffle. She asked her mom, "Can I have a red waffle, please?" Her mom said, "We don't have red waffles, but I can make you a normal waffle."

Lucy was sad. She really wanted a red waffle. She thought, "How can I make a red waffle?" Then, Lucy had an idea! She found some red juice in the fridge. She poured the red juice on the waffle her mom made.

But, the waffle was not red. It was just wet and not yummy. Lucy started to cry. She still wanted a red waffle. Her mom heard her cry and came to help.

Her mom said, "I have an idea!" She took some red fruit and mashed it up. Then, she put the red fruit on the waffle. Now, Lucy had a red waffle! She was so happy, and the waffle was very yummy.
<|end|>


