Once upon a time, there was a little boy named Timmy. Timmy loved playing with his toys, especially his toy cars. One day, Timmy was playing with his cars outside when his friend Billy came over. 

"Wow, Timmy! Your cars are incredible!" Billy exclaimed.

"Thank you," Timmy said with a smile. "Which one do you want to play with?"

"I want to play with the red one," Billy said as he pointed to the car.

"Okay, but be careful with it. It's mine," Timmy warned.

Billy played with the red car for a little while, but then he accidentally broke it. Timmy was very upset and started to cry.

"I'm sorry, Timmy. I didn't mean to break it," Billy said.

But it was too late. Timmy's favorite car was broken and he couldn't fix it. The end.
