Lily was sad and didn't know what to do. She went outside to play and saw her neighbor, Mrs. Johnson, kneeling in her garden. Lily asked her what was wrong and Mrs. Johnson said her back hurt. Lily remembered her mom giving her a massage when she had a tummy ache and decided to help.

Lily gave Mrs. Johnson a massage and she felt much better. Mrs. Johnson said, "That was so kind of you. You have an original talent for making people feel better." Lily smiled and went back inside to draw. She realized that even if her drawings weren't original, she could still make people happy with them. The moral of the story is that helping others is always a good thing to do.
