Once upon a time, there was a little dog named Spot. Spot had a fake toy bone that he loved to play with. One day, while playing with his toy bone, he saw something shine in the sky.

Spot looked up and saw the sun shining very bright. He wanted to touch the shiny sun with his paw. So, he started to jump and jump, trying to reach the sun with his paw. But no matter how high he jumped, he could not reach the sun.

Spot's friend, a little bird named Blue, saw him jumping and asked, "What are you doing, Spot?" Spot said, "I want to touch the sun with my paw." Blue laughed and said, "The sun is too high for you to reach, Spot. But we can still enjoy its shine from here." Spot agreed, and they both lay down in the warm, sunny grass, happy to watch the sun shine together.
<|end|>


