Once upon a time, there was a boy named Tim. Tim loved to play golf with his dad. They would go to the big green field and hit the small white ball. Tim thought golf was fun, but sometimes it was hard.

One day, Tim and his dad went to play golf. Tim tried to hit the ball, but it was very hard. He looked at his dad and said, "Dad, can you give me help?" His dad smiled and said, "Of course, Tim. Let's try together."

Tim's dad showed him how to hold the golf club and swing. They tried again and again. Tim found it hard at first, but he did not give up. Finally, Tim hit the ball far away. Tim and his dad were very happy. They laughed and played more golf, knowing that it was okay if something was hard, as long as they had each other's help.
<|end|>


