Once upon a time, there was a big, reliable tree. This tree had many fruits. One day, a little girl named Mia went to the tree. She saw a pear. She wanted to eat the pear.

Mia asked her friend, a funny dog named Max, to help her. Max tried to jump and get the pear. He jumped and jumped, but he could not get it. Max looked at Mia and gave a little shrug.

Mia had an idea. She found a long stick. She used the stick to reach the pear. The pear fell down, and Mia and Max shared it. They were very happy and full. The reliable tree had given them a yummy treat.
<|end|>


