Once upon a time, there was a popular bird named Bob. Bob liked to fly high in the sky. He was friends with many animals.

One day, Bob had a job to deliver a letter to a faraway place. The letter was from a little boy to his grandma. Bob took the letter and started flying.

As Bob flew, he heard a loud noise. It was thunder! Bob was scared, but he knew he had to deliver the letter. So, he kept going. Finally, he gave the letter to the grandma.

The grandma was very happy. Bob was brave and did a great job. All the animals cheered for him. Bob was proud and flew back home.
<|end|>


