Once upon a time, there was a hungry boy named Tim. Tim loved to eat all kinds of food, but he did not like onions. One day, his mom made a big plate of food with onions in it. Tim saw the onions and did not want to eat them.

Tim's mom asked him to try the onions, but Tim said no. He did not want to eat the onions. Tim's mom was sad, but she did not make him eat the onions. Tim was happy that he did not have to eat the onions.

The next day, Tim's mom made food without onions. Tim was very happy and ate all of his food. Tim's mom was happy too because Tim was not hungry anymore. They both learned that it is okay to not like some foods, and they lived happily ever after.
<|end|>


