One day, a little girl named Sue went for a walk. She liked to skip. So, she skipped down the street. She saw her friend, Tom. Tom had gum. He was brave and gave Sue some gum. They both chewed the gum.

Sue said, "I like to skip. Do you like to skip, Tom?"

Tom said, "Yes, I like to skip too. Let's skip together!"

Sue and Tom skipped down the street together. They felt happy and brave. They chewed the gum and had fun. They skipped all the way to the park. They played there until it was time to go home.
<|end|>


