Once upon a time, in a hot desert, there lived a little cactus. The cactus was good and loved to make friends. Every day, the sun would rise, and the cactus would say "hello" to all the animals that passed by.

One day, a small bird came to the cactus. The bird said, "Hello, cactus! Can I sit on you?" The cactus was happy and said, "Yes, bird, you can sit on me. But be careful of my prickles." The bird was careful and sat on the cactus. They became good friends.

As the sun rose each day, the bird would come and sit on the cactus. They would talk and laugh together. The cactus and the bird were very happy. And they lived happily ever after.
<|end|>


