Once upon a time, in a small house, there lived a nosy cat named Whiskers. Whiskers liked to watch everything that happened in his home. One day, Whiskers saw his friend, a little girl named Lucy, taking a bath. Lucy was using shampoo to wash her hair. She made lots of bubbles and played with her toys.

Whiskers wanted to join the fun, but he knew cats don't like water. So, he sat by the tub and watched Lucy play. Lucy saw Whiskers and said, "Hi Whiskers! Do you want to play with my toys?" Whiskers just looked at her and gave a little sigh. He wished he could play, but he didn't want to get wet.

After Lucy finished her bath, she dried off and put on her pajamas. She found Whiskers still sitting by the tub, looking sad. Lucy picked him up and said, "Don't worry, Whiskers. We can play together now!" Whiskers was happy again, and they played all night until it was time for bed.
<|end|>


