Once upon a time, there was a happy mule named Mimi. She lived on a farm with her friends, the cow, the pig, and the sheep. They liked to play and run in the fields all day long.

One day, Mimi saw her friend, the cow, looking sad. "What's wrong?" Mimi asked. The cow said, "I am tired and need help to carry my milk to the farmer." Mimi wanted to support her friend, so she said, "I can help you!"

Mimi and the cow went to the farmer together. Mimi carried the milk and the cow walked beside her. They were both happy because they were helping each other. When they reached the farmer, he thanked them both and gave them a treat. From that day on, Mimi and the cow always supported each other and stayed happy friends.
<|end|>


