Once upon a time, there was a naughty dog named Max. Max liked to play with a big metal ball. He would push it with his nose and make it roll. Max was always happy when he played with his metal ball.

One day, Max saw a little girl named Lily. Lily was trying to learn a song, but she could not remember the words. Max wanted to help Lily, so he listened to the song and tried to repeat it. He barked the words to the song, and Lily laughed.

Lily and Max practiced the song together. Lily would sing, and Max would repeat the words with his barks. They played and sang until the sun went down. From that day on, Lily and Max became the best of friends, and they always helped each other.
