Once upon a time, there was a little girl named Lily. Lily had a doll named Daisy. Daisy was a lonely doll because Lily did not play with her. Daisy sat on the shelf all day, wishing for a friend.

One day, Lily's mom saw that Lily was not being nice to her little brother. She decided to punish Lily by taking away her favorite toy. Lily was sad and went to her room. She saw Daisy on the shelf and decided to play with her.

Lily and Daisy became best friends. They played together every day. Lily learned that being nice to others made her happy too. The moral of the story is to always be kind to others and you will never be lonely.
