One day, a little boy named Tim went with his mom to the park. It was a cold day, and there was ice on the ground. Tim saw his friend, Sam, playing near the ice. Sam was being very noisy and laughing.

Tim went to Sam and said, "Sam, be careful on the ice. It is slippery, and you can fall." Sam did not listen to Tim and kept playing. Tim tried to learn how to play on the ice too, but he was scared.

Soon, Sam slipped on the ice and fell down. He cried loudly. Tim's mom came and helped Sam. She told both boys, "You should listen to your friends when they tell you to be careful." The moral of the story is to always listen to good advice from friends.
<|end|>


