One day, a small, weak ant was walking in the park. He saw a big hammer on the ground. The ant thought, "I want to use this hammer to build a home." But the hammer was too heavy for the weak ant to lift.

A kind bee saw the ant trying to lift the heavy hammer. The kind bee wanted to help the ant. The bee flew over to the ant and said, "I can help you lift the hammer." The ant was happy and said, "Thank you, kind bee."

Together, they lifted the hammer and built a beautiful home for the ant. The ant was very happy and grateful. The bee had offered help when the ant needed it most. And now, they were the best of friends.
<|end|>


