Once upon a time, there was a little boy named Tim. Tim loved to play by the bridge near his house. One day, Tim saw a big girl on the other side of the bridge. She had a toy that Tim wanted to play with.

Tim walked over the bridge and said, "Hi, can I play with your toy? It looks fun." The big girl looked at Tim and said, "I will let you play with my toy if you can explain why you want to play with it." Tim thought for a moment and said, "I want to play with it because it looks fair and nice."

The big girl didn't like Tim's answer. She thought it was not a good reason. So, she said, "No, you cannot play with my toy." Tim felt sad and walked back home. He never got to play with the toy, and the big girl never shared with him.
<|end|>


