One day, a cat named Jazz went for a walk. The sun was shining and the sky was clear. Jazz was a happy cat who liked to play with his friends. On his walk, he found a big box. Jazz thought it would be fun to see if he could fit inside the box.

Jazz said to himself, "I want to see if I fit in this box!" So, he tried to put his head in the box. It was a tight fit, but his head went in. Then, he tried to put his body in the box. It was a very tight fit, but his body went in too. Finally, he tried to put his tail in the box. It was the tightest fit of all, but his tail went in. Jazz was so happy that he fit in the box!

Jazz's friend, a dog named Max, came by and saw the box. Max said, "Jazz, is that you in the box?" Jazz replied, "Yes, Max! I fit in the box, and it's so much fun!" Max laughed and said, "That's great, Jazz! Let's go play with our friends now." So, Jazz got out of the box, and they went to play with their friends. They had a fun day under the clear sky.
<|end|>


