Once upon a time, in a humble little town, there lived a kind man named Tom. Tom was known for making pretty pastel colors. He would supply these colors to everyone in the town, so they could paint their houses and make them look nice.

One day, a little girl named Amy came to Tom's shop. She said, "Tom, can you please supply me with some pastel colors? I want to paint a picture for my mom." Tom smiled and gave Amy the colors she needed.

As Amy painted her picture, all the people in the town stopped to watch. They loved the pretty pastel colors she used. When she was done, everyone clapped and cheered. Amy's mom was so happy and proud of her. The town learned that even a humble act, like sharing pastel colors, could bring happiness to others.
<|end|>


