One day, a dependable boy named Tim found a big egg in his yard. He did not know what was inside. He took it to his room and kept it safe.

After a few days, the egg started to move. Tim was very excited. He called his mom and said, "Mom, look! The egg is moving!" The egg cracked open and out came a baby dinosaur. Tim was so happy to see the dinosaur. He named it Dino.

Tim and Dino played together all the time. They became best friends. One day, Tim thought it was time to release Dino back to where he found the egg. He knew it was the right thing to do. So, he said to Dino, "Dino, I love you, but you need to go back to your family." Dino understood and went back to the wild. Tim knew he could always depend on Dino to be his friend, even if they were apart.
<|end|>


