One day, a little boy named Tim was playing in his yard. He saw a lonely butterfly flying around. Tim had a big net to catch the butterfly. He wanted to show it to his mom.

Tim said, "I will catch you, butterfly!" He ran with his net, but the butterfly flew away. Tim was sad. He looked around for another butterfly. He saw a big tree and thought, "Maybe there are more butterflies in the tree."

Tim walked to the tree and looked up. He saw a pretty bird in the tree. The bird said, "Tim, there is a big group of butterflies in the park. You can catch one there with your net." Tim was happy and said, "Thank you, bird!"

Tim went to the park with his net. He saw many butterflies and caught one. He ran home to show his mom. His mom said, "Good job, Tim!" Tim was happy and let the butterfly go. The butterfly flew back to its friends in the park.
