Once upon a time, in a big green forest, there lived a unique lion. He was not like other lions. He could not roar. All the other animals would laugh at him. The lion felt very sad. One day, he met a small rat who was also unique. The rat could not squeak like other rats. They became best friends.

One day, the lion and the rat were playing near a big tree. They heard a loud noise. It was a big, mean lion roaring. The big lion wanted to hurt the rat. The unique lion wanted to help his friend, but he could not roar.

The unique lion got a big idea. He asked the rat to help. The rat climbed up the tree and dropped a big nut on the mean lion's head. The mean lion ran away, scared. The unique lion and the rat were very happy. They knew that being unique made them special.
<|end|>


