Once upon a time, in a small town, there was a cat named Lucky. Lucky was a very lucky cat. One day, Lucky saw a big dog. The big dog wanted to catch Lucky. Lucky was scared.

Lucky said, "I need to escape!" So, Lucky ran and ran. The big dog chased Lucky. Lucky saw a goal. The goal was to climb a tall tree. Lucky thought, "If I reach the goal, I will be safe."

Lucky climbed the tall tree. The big dog could not climb. Lucky was safe. The big dog said, "You are lucky, cat." Lucky said, "Yes, I am. But we can be friends." The big dog agreed. They became friends.

The moral of the story is: even if you are scared, you can reach your goal and make friends.
