Once upon a time, there was a little train. The train was very sad because it was terrible at going fast. One day, a big train came by and saw the little train.

"Hi, little train! Why are you so slow?" asked the big train. The little train replied, "I am terrible at going fast. I wish I could be like you."

The big train thought for a moment and said, "I have an idea! Let's shut all the doors and windows. Maybe that will help you go faster." So, the little train shut all the doors and windows.

The little train tried to go fast, but it still could not. It felt even more terrible. The big train left, and the little train was all alone, feeling sad and slow.
