Once upon a time, there was a little chicken. The chicken lived on a farm with many other animals. The chicken had a small house to sleep in, but it was always empty. The chicken felt sad because it was lonely.

One day, the chicken decided to complain to the farmer. The chicken said, "I am sad because my house is empty. I need a friend." The farmer listened to the chicken and thought about what to do.

The next day, the farmer brought a big bag to the farm. The chicken was excited and thought the farmer was bringing a friend. But instead, the farmer took the chicken away. The chicken's house stayed empty and the other animals were sad.
