One day, a boy named Tim had a long toy. He liked to joke with his friends. He would say, "Look at my long toy! It can see through things like an x-ray!" His friends would laugh and play with him.

One day, Tim met a new friend named Sam. Tim showed Sam his long toy and said, "I can see through things with my x-ray toy!" Sam did not laugh. Sam said, "That's not true. Toys can't see through things."

Tim felt sad. He wanted to prove Sam wrong. He tried to use his long toy to see through a wall. But it did not work. Tim's friends saw him and laughed. They said, "Tim, your toy is not an x-ray. It's just a long toy."

Tim felt very sad. His friends did not want to play with him anymore. They did not like his jokes. Tim learned that it is not good to joke about things that are not true.
<|end|>


