Once upon a time, there was a pale little girl named Lily. She loved to go on journeys with her family. One day, Lily's mom and dad said they were going on a journey to the park.

Before they left, Lily's mom asked her to organize her toys. Lily did not want to do it. She wanted to go to the park right away. But her mom said, "We must organize first, then we can have fun."

Lily listened to her mom and started to organize her toys. It took some time, but she made her room neat and tidy. When she was done, her mom and dad were very happy. They went to the park and had a great time.

On their way back home, Lily saw her friend's house. Her friend was sad because she could not find her favorite toy. Lily told her friend about organizing her toys before going on a journey. Her friend listened and found her toy after organizing her room.

Lily learned that it is good to organize and keep things neat. It helps to find things easily and makes everyone happy.
<|end|>


