One day, a little boy named Tim went to the store with his mom. He was very excited because he was going to buy a new toy. They looked at many toys to find the best one. Tim saw a big red ball and said, "Mom, I want this one!"

His mom looked at the price and said, "This ball is too much money, Tim. Let's find a toy that is not so much money." Tim was sad, but he knew his mom would support him in finding a new toy.

They looked some more and found a small blue car. Tim was excited again and said, "Mom, can I get this car?" His mom looked at the price and smiled. "Yes, Tim. We can buy this car." Tim and his mom went home, and Tim played with his new car all day.
