Once upon a time, there was a big boat. The boat was very slow. One day, the boat saw a little fish in the water. The fish was sad.

The boat asked, "Why are you sad, little fish?" The fish said, "I want to go fast, but I am too small. I try and try, but I cannot go fast."

The boat wanted to help the little fish. The boat had an idea. It had a big anchor. The boat said, "Little fish, you can try to pull my anchor. It will make you strong and fast."

The little fish was happy. It tried to pull the anchor. At first, it was hard. But the little fish did not give up. It tried and tried.

Soon, the little fish was strong and fast. The boat and the little fish became good friends. They played in the water together. And they were both very happy.
