One day, a small and pale spider went to play outside. The spider was very happy because it was a sunny day. The spider loved to jump from leaf to leaf.

While jumping, the spider met a big red bug. The bug said, "Hey, little spider! Let's play together!" The spider said, "Yes, let's play! What do you want to play?" The bug said, "Let's play hide and seek!"

The spider and the bug started to play. The spider hid behind a big rock. The bug looked and looked but could not find the spider. Finally, the bug said, "Stop! I give up! Where are you, little spider?" The spider came out from behind the rock and said, "Here I am! I win!"

The spider and the bug played all day long. They became very good friends. From that day on, the pale spider and the big red bug played together every day.
