Once upon a time, in a small town, there lived a tall boy named Tim. Tim loved to play games with his friends. One day, Tim and his friends decided to play a match of racing.

Before the race, Tim's friend Sam said, "I am not tall like you, Tim. I don't think I can win." Tim smiled and said, "Don't worry, Sam. Being tall doesn't always mean you will win. Just try your best."

The race began, and all the friends ran as fast as they could. Tim and Sam were both doing well. In the end, Sam won the match! Tim and all their friends cheered for Sam.

After the race, Tim said, "See, Sam? Even though you are not tall like me, you still won the match. It's because you tried your best and didn't give up."

From that day on, Sam and all their friends learned that it's not about how tall you are, but how hard you try that matters. And they all played happily together, always trying their best.
