Once upon a time, there was a little girl named Lily. She was a patient girl who always waited for her turn. Lily had no sister to play with, so she decided to create a friend.

Lily took a big box and put funny clothes, shoes, and a hat in it. She drew a face on a balloon and put it on top. "Hello, friend!" said Lily. "Let's play together!"

Her new friend didn't talk, but Lily had fun dressing her up and talking to her. One day, Lily's mom saw her playing and said, "Lily, you are such a patient girl. I have a surprise for you!"

Lily's mom brought home a little baby. "This is your new sister, Emma!" said her mom. Lily was so happy! Now she had a real sister to play with and love.

From that day on, Lily and her sister, Emma, played together all the time. They laughed, shared, and had lots of fun. And Lily's box friend? She was still there, watching them play and smiling with her balloon face.
