One day, a green bug found a piano in the park. The green bug loved to play the piano. He would play it every day. But one day, a big dog came and wanted to play the piano too. The green bug and the big dog did not want to share the piano. They both wanted to play it all the time.

The green bug had an idea. He would write a note to the big dog. The note said, "Let's share the piano. We can both play it and be happy." The big dog read the note and thought it was a good idea. So, they both played the piano together. They took turns and made beautiful music.

The green bug and the big dog learned that sharing is good. When they shared the piano, they both could play and be happy. They became good friends and played the piano together every day. The moral of the story is to share and be kind to others.
