The big cow said, "I want to see the world. I am tired of working on the farm." The little pig and the fast horse were still sad, but they understood. They said goodbye to the big cow, and she left the farm.

The big cow saw many new things, but she was not happy. She missed her friends, the little pig and the fast horse. She wanted to go back to the farm, but she was lost. The big cow was very sad. She wished she had not left her friends.

The moral of the story is: be happy with what you have, because change is not always good.
