Once upon a time, there was a dog named Spot. Spot had a red collar around his neck. One day, Spot's owner decided to travel to a faraway place and brought Spot along.

On the way, Spot felt very thirsty and drank all the water from his bowl. But his owner forgot to refill it. Spot's belly was empty and he felt very sad.

After a long journey, they finally arrived at their destination. Spot was very happy to see a big yard to play in. But as he ran around, he got tangled in his collar and couldn't breathe. His owner was not around to help him and Spot couldn't escape. Sadly, Spot passed away. 

This is why it's important to always check that your pet's collar is not too tight and to never leave them alone for too long.
<|end|>


