Once upon a time, there was a little puppy named Spot. Spot had a big, fluffy tail that he wagged whenever he was happy. One day, Spot was playing in the park when he saw a rich-looking dog walking by.

"Hello there!" said Spot. "What's your name?"

"My name is Max," replied the rich dog. "I come from a very wealthy family."

Spot was impressed. He had never met a dog that was rich before. He wanted to be friends with Max, but he didn't know how to approach him. That's when Spot had an idea.

"I know!" said Spot. "Let's unite our tails together and become friends forever!"

Max thought this was a great idea and the two dogs wagged their tails together happily. But then, a mean cat came along and started teasing Spot and Max.

"You two don't belong together," said the cat. "Spot is just a scruffy little mutt and Max is a fancy, rich dog. You'll never be friends!"

Spot and Max were upset by the cat's mean words, but they didn't let it get to them. Instead, they stood up for each other and barked at the cat until it ran away.

From that day on, Spot and Max were the best of friends. They would wag their tails together and play in the park every day. And whenever they faced a bully or a mean cat, they would unite and stand up for each other.
<|end|>


