Once upon a time, there was a rabbit named Bouncy. Bouncy loved to jump high and far. He was very good at it. One day, Bouncy met a mouse named Squeaky. Squeaky had a nice tooth necklace. Bouncy wanted the necklace, so he asked Squeaky if he could have it. Squeaky said no because the necklace was very special to him.

Bouncy didn't like that answer, so he decided to take the necklace from Squeaky. He jumped at Squeaky and knocked him over. But when Bouncy picked up the necklace, he realized that he had hurt Squeaky. Bouncy felt very bad and gave the necklace back to Squeaky. Bouncy learned that it's not nice to take things from others and that it's important to be kind and respectful. From that day on, Bouncy made sure to use his jumping skills to help others and make them happy.
<|end|>


