Once upon a time, there was a big bear who lived in a cozy cave. Every day, he would go outside to play in the forest. One day, he found a shiny rock that he really liked. He wanted to measure it to see how big it was. He took out his ruler and measured the rock. It was a fair size, not too big and not too small.

The bear was very happy with his new rock. He wanted to show it off to his friends. He invited them over to his cave for a luxury tea party. They all had a great time drinking tea and eating cookies. The bear showed his friends his new rock and they were all very impressed. They thought it was a luxury rock because it was so shiny and pretty.

After the tea party, the bear and his friends went back outside to play. They decided to have a race to see who was the fastest. The bear won the race because he was the biggest and strongest. He was very proud of himself and his new rock. From that day on, the bear always carried his rock with him wherever he went.
<|end|>


