Once upon a time, there was a little girl named Lily. One day, Lily went outside to play in the rain. She loved to jump in the puddles and feel the wet drops on her face. Suddenly, her mom called her on the telephone. 

"Hi, Mommy!" Lily said, picking up the phone. 

"Hi, sweetie," her mom replied. "I just wanted to mention that it's getting late. It's time to come inside and get dry." 

Lily was sad to leave her fun in the rain, but she knew her mom was right. She said goodbye to her friends outside and went inside to change into warm, dry clothes. As she snuggled up with a blanket, she remembered how much fun she had playing in the rain and couldn't wait to do it again.
<|end|>


