Once upon a time, there was a little girl named Lily. She loved to play outside in the sunshine. One day, her mommy said, "Lily, let's go to the post office to get some stamps." Lily was excited because she had never been to the post office before. 

At the post office, Lily saw a big machine that allowed people to buy stamps. Her mommy gave her some money to put in the machine, and it gave her a stamp. Lily was so happy to have her very own stamp. 

After they left the post office, Lily saw a tall tree with branches that went really high. She asked her mommy if she could climb the tree, but her mommy said it was too dangerous. Lily was sad, but her mommy explained that it was important to be safe. 

Lily learned that sometimes we can't do everything we want, but it's okay because there are things that we are allowed to do, like buy stamps at the post office.
<|end|>


