Once upon a time, there was a family who lived in a house with a big carpet. The family had a brother and a sister who liked to play together. One day, they started to quarrel over a toy car. The brother wanted to play with it, but the sister didn't want to share.

The sister got angry and threw the toy car on the carpet. The brother got mad and pushed the sister. She fell and hit her head on the carpet. At first, it seemed harmless, but soon she started to feel sick. The family took her to the hospital, but it was too late. The sister had a serious injury and could not be saved.

The family was very sad and regretted the quarrel. They learned that it's important to share and not fight over things. They also learned that even harmless things can be dangerous if we don't take care. From that day on, they always remembered their sister and the lesson they learned.
<|end|>


