Once upon a time, there was a big gorilla in the jungle. He was very strong and had thick fur. One day, he went to the store to buy bananas. But when he got there, he saw that all the bananas were gone. He was very sad and angry because he loved bananas.

The gorilla asked the store worker where the bananas were. The worker said that they were all sold out. The gorilla didn't like that answer. He started to bang on the walls and throw things around. The store worker was scared and called for help.

Soon, some other animals came to the store to help calm the gorilla down. They brought him some other fruits to eat instead of bananas. The gorilla was still upset, but he was happy to have something to eat. From that day on, he learned to store some extra bananas at home so he would never run out again. The end.
<|end|>


