Once upon a time, there was an old motor. It was very tired and didn't work well. One day, a little boy wanted to play with the motor. He tried to make it work, but it wouldn't start. He felt sad and frustrated.

Then, the boy had an idea. He took a step back and looked at the motor. He saw that it was very dirty and had lots of dust on it. So, he got a cloth and cleaned the motor. After he cleaned it, the motor started to work again! The boy was so happy and excited.

But then, his little sister wanted to play with the motor too. They both wanted to play with it at the same time. They started to argue and fight over who could play with the motor. The boy remembered what he did before and took another step back. He thought about how he could solve the problem. Finally, he suggested that they take turns playing with the motor. They both agreed and were happy again.
<|end|>


