Once upon a time there was a brave girl. She had an arrow and she wanted to fix it. The arrow wasn't straight so the girl tried bending it. She tried and tried but the arrow was very strong and wouldn't bend.

The girl was feeling sad but then she had an idea. She decided to make the arrow flexible. She grabbed some sticky glue and stuck it on the arrow. Then she found some cloth and wrapped it around the arrow. 

Finally, the arrow was flexible! The girl was so happy that she fixed the arrow. Now it bent easily and she had lots of fun shooting it at targets. The girl was proud of her arrow because she had worked hard to fix it.
<|end|>


