Once upon a time, there was a little girl named Alice. She was three years old and full of life. One day, when Alice was walking in the park, she got very cold. She started to shiver and feel sad. She looked around, hoping to find a friend.

Suddenly, she saw an old man. He had thick white hair and a kind face. Alice smiled and said, â€œHi! I am cold. Can you help me?â€

The old man replied with a smile, â€œOf course! Sit on my bench and I will care for you.â€ Alice thanked him and sat down. The old man put a warm coat around her so she didn't feel cold anymore. He put his arm around her and brushed the hair away from her eyes.

Alice felt safe and warm. She said, â€œThank you for caring for me.â€ The old man replied, â€œIt was my pleasure.â€

Alice and the old man sat together for a while, talking and laughing. Alice found out that the old man was like a grandfather to her. She felt happy and loved. All the hardness of the cold vanished.
<|end|>


