Mummy was in the supermarket. She needs to buy lots of things for dinner. She saw a big board with some chunky carrots on it. She wanted to buy them, but it was very heavy. 

Mummy looked around and saw Pete. He was a clumsy boy. He was having a lot of trouble trying to pick up the board. Mummy smiled and asked him: 

"Can I help you with the board, Pete?"

Pete was so pleased.

"Yes please!" he said. 

Mummy picked up the board and put it in her trolley. Then she bought the carrots. 

Back at home, Mummy put the carrots on the table.

"Thank you for helping me buy the carrots, Pete," she said.

Pete smiled. He was glad he could help. 

Mummy and Pete enjoyed dinner together.
<|end|>


