<|asst|>
Once upon a time, there lived a farmer and his 3 children who loved to play together. One day, the farmer wanted to share some lovely wheat with his children, but they all refused. The farmer was sad to see that his children would not taste his wheat. He said to them, â€œLife is too short to waste it on things that you refuse. If you donâ€™t accept the things that come your way, you may miss out on something truly lovely.â€ The children thought about what their father had said and decided to try the lovely wheat. They all liked it and shared it with each other, enjoying every bite.

The moral of this story is that life should be enjoyed and we should not refuse opportunities that come our way. Even if something seems simple or ordinary, it could be more lovely and special than you know. By being open to trying new things, you can create wonderful memories.
<|end|>


