Once upon a time there was a nice kind girl named Jan. One day, Jan decided to pack her bag to go on an adventure. She put in a few snacks, a pencil and her scissors. Jan was so excited to go explore and find new things.

As Jan was walking she saw a large mountain. It was so tall and she knew she had to climb it one day! Jan kept walking and eventually she came across a river. It was so wide and Jan wanted to find a way across.

Jan remembered pack her scissors and started to cut pieces of rope. She made a rope bridge and crossed the river safely. She was so proud of herself and felt like she was becoming a real explorer.

But then Jan looked up and saw a big high wall blocking her path. "How can I get over it?" she wondered. Then Jan thought of the scissors she had packed and made a plan. She cut some small branches off of a nearby tree and used the scissors to put them together. She made a ladder and used it to climb over the wall. 

When Jan was on the other side, she was amazed. It was so beautiful and she wanted to explore more. She knew that packing those scissors was a good idea and it paid off in the end. Jan continued to explore and have many more adventures on her journey.
<|end|>


