Alice and David hoped to have fun together. They put on a different kind of clothes, put golf clubs on their backs and went out of their house. 

Alice said, "Let's have lots of fun and explore the golf course!". 

David replied, "Yes, and hope I can hit the golf ball very far!". 

Alice smiled, "Me too! I hope it will be very different!". 

They arrived at the golf course and had a great time together. They both hit the ball quite far and even managed to get a few holes-in-one! They were so excited. 

At the end of the day, they hugged each other and said goodbye. They had a wonderful time and were both filled with hope for the future.
