Once upon a time, there was a little girl named Zara who wanted to play with a toy train track she had seen in the store. She asked her mom if she could buy it, but her mom said she had to wait until her birthday.

Zara was very patient and waited every day for her birthday to come. Finally, when her birthday arrived, her mom brought her the track and they went home.

When they arrived, Zara saw a new toy in the box - a big lock! She asked her mom what it was and her mom said it was a key to unlock the track. Zara was so excited and asked her mom to help her.

Together, they used the key to unlock the track and Zara started building it. As she was building, her mom reminded her that sometimes it is important to be patient, because the things we work for are often more special and rewarding.

Zara smiled and thanked her mom. When she finished her train track, she was so proud of it. She thought to herself, being patient was worth it!
<|end|>


