Once there was a little girl called Lily. She lived in a small house in the countryside. One day, Lily was walking outside and she saw a new plant growing in her garden. She called her mom and asked her, "Mommy, what is this?" Her mom smiled and said, "That is a special plant; it's a strawberry plant. It will grow really big, and it will give us lots of delicious strawberries."

But then Lily noticed something disgusting on the plant. It was a slimy little insect. She said, "Mommy! It's gross! What is that?" Her mom laughed and said, "It's just a caterpillar, sweetie. It's not going to hurt the plant. Don't worry."

Lily thought it was still a bit disgusting. But she was also happy to know that her plant would give her yummy strawberries when it was ready. She smiled and said, "I can see strawberries already!"
<|end|>


