Once there was a lily growing in a meadow. Its petals were as white as snow and it was very fine to look at.

One day a young girl called Lucy walked by and saw the lily. Lucy liked the flower very much. She wanted to take it home.

The lily spoke and said, "Please don't take me away from here. I am very happy here". Lucy stopped and said, "Okay, I won't take you away".

The next day, Lucy came back to the meadow and saw the lily again. She repeated her question, "Do you want to come home with me?" The lily answered again, "No, I am happy here".

As Lucy walked away, she said she liked the lily very much. Lucy said, "Goodbye lily, I'll come back and see you soon".

And so Lucy returned to the meadow every day to visit the lily. Sometimes she would bring a friend to admire the fine flower. The lily was very happy and it was happy to repeat its answer, "No, I am happy here".
<|end|>


