Once upon a time, there was a little girl named Sarah. She wanted a nice gift for her birthday. So, she asked her mom, "Mom, can I borrow a present for my birthday?" Her mom said, "Yes, you can borrow a gift!"

Sarah was happy and said, "Thank you, Mom!" She went to the closet and opened the door. Inside, she found a shiny present wrapped up in a nice, tight bow. Sarah said, "Look! I found a birthday gift!"

Her mom smiled and said, "Yes, that is a nice gift for your birthday! You can borrow it for now." So Sarah happily took the present, thanked her mom, and ran off to show her friends her special gift. 

The end.
