<|asst|>
One day it was raining outside. Mandy and her mom were inside biking. "I want to go outside and play in the rain," said Mandy. 

Mandy's mom said, "No, it's too dangerous." But Mandy was very stubborn. 

She said, "I want to go outside! Please!" 

Mandy's mom sighed and said, "Okay, but stay close." 

Mandy put on her rain coat and ran outside. She stepped into the deep puddle and splashed around. She loved the feeling of the rain on her skin. 

Suddenly, Mandy heard a loud roar. She looked up and saw a big black cloud. It started to rain harder and the puddle grew even deeper. 

Mandy ran inside the house. Her mom was waiting in the kitchen with a salad. "You're soaked," said her mom. 

Mandy looked sadly at the floor. She knew she should have listened to her mom. 

The End.
<|end|>


