<|end|>
<|asst|>
Timmy was a playful three-year-old who loved spending time with his father. They would do everything together and nothing made Timmy happier than when his dad was around. One day, his dad made a suggestion that surprised Timmy. He suggested that they draw a face on the wall in their living room.

At first, Timmy was a little confused. He wasn't sure why they needed to draw on the wall, but his dad said it would be fun. So, Timmy hesitantly agreed. They worked together for a long time, coming up with the most adorable face Timmy had ever seen. 

Once the face was complete, Timmy was over the moon. He and his dad stood back to admire the wall. His dad then suggested something that gave Timmy the biggest shock. He suggested that the face have eyes that move. Timmy couldn't believe it but, sure enough, a few days later his dad hung a friendly smiling face with moving, sparkling eyes on the wall. 

Timmy had never seen anything like it! He was so amazed and delighted, and was soon spending hours each day talking and laughing with the friendly face on the wall. He had even named the face "Jimmy," after his dad. 

For Timmy, drawing the wall face with his dad was the most special activity he had ever done with his dad, and it would always stay in his happy memories, forever.
<|end|>


