<|asst|>
Once upon a time, there was a thoughtful girl who liked to look out the window. One day, she noticed a bird in the tree outside her window. The bird seemed to be looking back in at her. She waved her hand, and the bird chirped back at her.

The next day, the girl looked out the window again, but this time the bird was gone. She wondered where it went and asked her mom about it. Her mom said not to worry, that the bird would be back soon.

The day after that, the girl looked out the window and saw the bird there again. This time the bird was singing a different song, and seemed to be demanding something from the girl. She was truly curious about what it wanted, but she had no idea. 

Finally, the girl thought of just the right thing to give the bird. She opened the window and carefully placed some breadcrumbs outside. The bird seemed to be happy, and flew away with a smile. Suddenly it came back, however, and brought a small gift - a beautiful blue feather. The thoughtful girl was delighted, and smiled back at the bird.
