Once there was a little boy who was very adventurous. He explored the forest near his home and one day he found an old wreck. It looked like an old car, twisted and bent out of shape.

The little boy was curious and he wanted to know what caused the wreck. He put his hand on the twisted metal, and it was very hot. He realized that it had been in an accident, and he wondered who was driving.

Then he had an idea! He ran as fast as he could, so fast that the wind whistled in his ears. He raced back home and he told his mommy all about the wreck.

His mommy told him that it must have been a fast car to get so twisted, and that he should be careful in the future. She reminded him that cars drive fast and that he should never do something dangerous like run around near wrecked cars.

The little boy listened carefully, and from then on he always used caution when exploring. He knew that adventure and caution were two important things to remember.
<|end|>


