Once upon a time there was a little girl named Lily. She lived in a small house next to a mill. Every morning, Lily would watch the mill slowly rotate. It was long and gong.

One day, Lily was walking by the mill when she heard a strange noise. She went to investigate and saw a tiny mouse had gotten stuck in the wheels of the rotating mill.

"Oh no!" said Lily. She was worried that the little mouse was in danger.

Lily was determined to help the mouse. She thought and thought until she came up with a plan. She took a stick and used it to stop the rotating mill. When the mill stopped, the mouse was safe.

Lily carefully lifted the mouse out of the mill. She hugged him and thanked him for being so brave. The mouse scurried away happily into the nearby woods.

Lily smiled proudly as she heard the mill slowly rotates again. She was glad she was able to help the small mouse.
<|end|>


