Bobby was a tall boy with big dreams. Every day he went to the park and tried to reach the top of the slide. Everyone told him he was too small, but Bobby never gave up trying; his determination made him grow a little every day.

One sunny day, he was determined to reach the top of the slide, no matter what. He took a deep breath and pulled himself up. When he reached the top, Bobby was so proud of his victory! Everyone cheered.

The next day, however, the slide seemed higher. Bobby couldn't reach the top. He tried and tried, but the slide was too tall. Bobby began to worry; how was he ever going to reach the top?

Just then, Bobby's mom came and told him to try pulling with all his strength. Bobby concentrated hard and took a deep breath. He pulled harder than he ever had before and suddenly, he was at the top of the slide! His victory was even sweeter this time because he knew he had done it all by himself.
<|end|>


