Once there was a little girl named Amy. She could create magical sounds by mixing things. For instance, she could mix a spoon and a bowl to make a harmless sound.

She also liked to use her imagination when she was mixing her sounds. She would pretend she was a witch in search of an enchanted pond. She would do things like mix an empty bottle and a jar and pretend that it was bubbling water.

Once, one of Amy's friends came over and asked if he could mix sounds too. Amy happily said yes and together they made some really cool and harmless sounds. They clinked glass jars together and shook containers of different shapes and sizes. It all sounded like a magical orchestra!

When they finished their mixing, Amy's friend smiled and said it was the most fun he had ever had playing with sound. Then he thanked Amy for letting him join in the fun.

Amy just smiled and said that combining sounds was even more fun when shared with a good friend.
