Once, there was a mouse. The mouse scurried around the house and found a piece of cheese. It was very bitter. The mouse stared at the cheese for a moment.

The mouse was hungry, so it decided to eat the cheese anyway. With each bite, the mouse could taste the sweetness, but it was still too bitter for it to enjoy.

The mouse kept eating until the whole piece of cheese was gone. When it was gone, the mouse felt scared and lonely. It had made a mistake by eating something it didn't like.

The mouse started to feel sick. The bitter cheese had made it sick. The sick feeling kept getting worse until the mouse felt like it was going to die.

The mouse eventually died from eating the bitter cheese. It was a bad ending for the poor mouse.
