Once upon a time there was a green mask. It was a special mask, because it could rise. The mask floated up in the sky, higher and higher. It rose above the trees and past the clouds. It kept rising until it couldn't rise any more.

When the mask stopped rising, it came to rest on top of a tall, green hill. The mask liked its place on the hill. The grass was so green and the sky so blue.

The green mask was happy and content. From its place atop the green hill, the mask could see far and wide. It could see the town in the valley below and birds in the sky above.

The green mask was content in its new home atop the green hill. From there it could rise and fall with the sun, watching the world turn with each passing day.
