Once upon a time, a little dog named Lucky was running in a meadow. He ran too close to a big barn and stepped on some dangerous ice. It started to melt quickly and he realized it was too dangerous to stay. He ran away as quickly as he could, but it was too lateâ€” the ice melted and flooded the entire barn, making it nearly impossible for the animals inside to get out.

The animals were scared and Lucky knew he had to save them. He ran back to the barn and barked loudly to get their attention. He then started to run around the barn, leaving a trail of warm footprints behind. Finally all the animals escaped the barn before it was completely destroyed by the melting ice.

Lucky was very proud of himself and the other animals thanked him for his bravery. He ran back to the meadow where he had been playing and the animals went back to their own homes. From then on, Lucky always stayed much farther away from the dangerous ice.
