Once upon a time, there was a dinosaur. He was very cold and lonely. He wanted to find a friend he could trust.

One day, a water droplet fell from the sky and landed on the Dinosaur's nose. He looked up, and saw a group of birds flying. He thought they looked exciting, even if he wasn't sure he could trust them. So he made a brave decision - he followed the birds.

The birds took him to a forest with lots of trees. He saw other animals like bears, foxes, and even a butterfly! He felt a little bit warmer, and happy too. He trusted the birds.

The Dinosaur stayed in the forest for a long time and made new friends. He learned how to be brave and make new friends. Now he always trusts his friends, even when it is cold outside. The End.
