Once upon a time, there was a charming circle called Zoom. Zoom was in the sky, made of bright lights and sparkles. One day, a 3-year-old boy named John was looking up in the sky and saw Zoom twinkling brightly.

John looked curiously at Zoom and said, "What is that?" His mom replied, "That's Zoom, it's a charming circle." 

John wanted to go closer to Zoom, so his mom took him in her car. When they arrived, there were even more sparkles and lights around Zoom. John was amazed and asked, "Can I go inside?" 

His mom smiled and said, "Yes, but only if you promise to be careful." John promised and stepped inside Zoom. It was like a magical place full of wonder. He looked around and said, "Wow!"

John started to run around the inside of Zoom and he shouted, "I'm zooming!" His mom smiled and cheerfully said, "That's why it's called Zoom!" 

John happily stayed inside Zoom until it was time to leave. He said goodbye to Zoom, and his mom said, "Maybe we'll be back soon." As they drove away, Zoom stayed in the sky looking very charming.
