Once upon a time, there was a farmer with lots of wheat. Every day, he would attach tiny seeds of wheat to the soil in the garden. Then he would water the seeds and wait for them to grow.

Soon enough, the wheat grew big and strong. It was ready to be picked. The farmer was so happy - he could now make bread and other tasty treats.

The farmer carefully detached the wheat from the ground, then tied it together in bundles. He carried the bundles into the house and began to work. He used the wheat to make bread, cookies and cakes. Everyone in the house enjoyed the delicious treats.

The farmer was very pleased with his work. Thanks to his hard work, he was able to fill his home with tasty treats made from the wheat he had attached to the ground earlier.
