One day a girl picked up a twig. She looked at it closely and thought that it was interesting. She thought about the different things she could do with it. She decided to draw shapes and animals in the dirt, using it as a tool. She had lots of fun drawing, and before long she had many different pictures she could show to her friends.

The girl then realized that the twig wasn't just for drawing. She used it to pick and pluck dandelions from the ground. She made a wish as she blew on them and watched as the petals flew away.

Finally, the girl used the twig to make a whistle. She enjoyed making music and whistling tunes with it. When she was done playing, she put the twig down in a safe spot so she could pick it up next time.
