Once, there was a man who loved to drive. Every Sunday he would go for a drive in his car. One Sunday morning, he got in his car and drove as far as he could, until he reached a tight reef. He was curious and wanted to get a closer look.

So, he parked his car and slowly made his way to the edge of the reef, taking care with every step. After what seemed like a long time, he was at the edge of the reef, ready to look out over the ocean.

But as he peered over the edge, he realized that the reef was even tighter than he thought. He couldn't move or do anything, he was stuck! The man was so stuck that he had to wait a whole day and night before he was free to drive back home.

The man learned a lesson that day - that when things are tight, it's best to stay away!
<|end|>


