One day, Steve was playing with his toy cars. Suddenly, he heard a sweet sound coming from outside. Steve went to check what was happening.

He saw a bird perched on a branch. The bird was singing a lovely song. Steve thought it was so smart! He stayed and listened to the bird for a long time.

Steve decided to sing too. He opened his mouth to join in with the bird. He sang louder and louder. After a while, his mom heard him. She came to find him with a knife and a big smile on her face.

Steve's mom wanted to show her son how smart he was. With the knife, she carved a small flute out of a stick. Then she showed Steve how to make music by blowing into the flute.

