Once upon a time, there were two friends, Joe and Sam. Every day, they went to the park together and played. One day, they were walking to the park, when they saw a really nice tree. Joe said that he wanted to climb the tree and take a look around. Sam said, "No way! That's too dangerous!" But Joe didn't listen and started climbing anyway.

When he reached the top, Joe shouted down to Sam, "I guessed the top of the tree would be pretty high, but I had no idea it would be this high!" Sam shouted back, "I told you it was too dangerous! You should listen to me next time."

Then Joe noticed a funny looking point at the top of the tree. He pointed it out to Sam and asked, "What's that point there?" Sam said, "That's a funny looking point, but I don't know what it is." So Joe decided to climb down and take a closer look.

When he got down, Joe examined the point and then said, "Oh, I guess it's a hornet's nest! We shouldn't mess with it, that's really stupid." Sam agreed, and they both ran away from the tree as fast as they could.

The moral of the story is that it's important to listen to people who are trying to help you. Otherwise, you could end up in a dangerous situation.
<|end|>


