Once upon a time, there were two friends, Dave and Lucy. They wanted to meet and have a fun time together outside. They chose a sunny day in the park.

When they got to the park, they saw that the weather was nice and normal. Dave and Lucy were so excited, they ran around and had lots of fun. They laughed, jumped, and even flew a kite.

But soon, Dave and Lucy got too tired to play. They found a quiet spot and sat together. And then they noticed something. The clouds had started changing the weather. It wasn't so normal and calm anymore. Rain started to pour down, and Dave and Lucy had to quickly gather their things and go home.

When they got back, Dave said to Lucy, "Always make sure to check the weather before you decide to go out to play. That way, you won't get caught in bad weather!"

Lucy agreed and they went back inside, ready for their next adventure. Dave and Lucy learned a valuable lesson that day: always check the weather before going out and you won't get caught in a storm.
