Once upon a time there was a little girl who wanted to climb a very tall mountain. But the mountain was steep, and she struggled to get to the top. Her legs and arms felt tired and weak, and she felt like she had no power to keep going. But she didn't give up. She kept fighting against all the terrible obstacles, and took a few rest stops along the way. 

Finally, the little girl made it to the top of the mountain, and she had never felt so proud. She realized that the power to succeed was within herself the whole time. It wasn't easy, but she had made it.

The moral of this story is that if you work hard, you can do anything you set your mind to. You can get through even the most difficult tasks if you never give up. Even if it feels like the obstacles are too hard, never let those terrible things stop you from succeeding.
