<|asst|>
Charlie was in his bedroom and saw a beautiful orange parrot outside the window. He had never seen a parrot before, and it was the most beautiful thing he had ever seen! He watched it fly around the garden, spinning and twirling in the air. He opened the window and tried to talk to it, but the parrot flew away. 

Charlie was sad and a little bit scared, so he went back inside and continued to watch the orange parrot from his bedroom. After a few minutes, the parrot flew back and landed on the fence, chirping and making a lot of noise. Charlie was so excited to see the parrot again and started to wave his arms at it!

The parrot cocked his head and started to move closer to the window, as if it wanted to be friends with Charlie. Charlie felt so happy and decided that the parrot was now his best friend. From that day on he watched the orange parrot every day, and it even joined him for lunch sometimes!
<|end|>


