The little girl, Emma, was looking around her room. She had a pale notebook in her hand and was looking through the pages. Emma had lots of ideas and loved to write them in the notebook. Suddenly, Emma heard her mum's voice.

"Why don't you come and make me a cup of tea, Emma?" her mum asked.

Emma picked up the pale notebook and looked towards her mum with a big smile on her face. She was ready for the challenge! She marched off to the kitchen while still carrying the notebook in her hand.

Making a cup of tea was a lot of fun for Emma. She was fascinated by the steam rising out of the kettle. As she stirred the tea and waited for it to cool down, she looked around the kitchen. She spotted the notebook she had left there and quickly picked it up.

Emma grabbed a pencil and started adding some more ideas to her pale notebook before returning to the living room with the cup of tea. She had so many fun things to think about. Now it was time to tell her mum all about them!
<|end|>


