Once upon a time there was a bear who was very hungry and wanted to find something to eat. He saw a delicious strawberry so he decided to come and take it. But getting the strawberry was difficult. Every time the bear tried to grab it, the strawberry hopped away. The bear was determined to eat the strawberry and kept trying to get it. After a few tries, the bear finally caught the strawberry and he was so happy. He enjoyed it and went back to his home, feeling very content. 

The next day, the bear was hungry again but he noticed that all of the strawberries had gone. The bear was sad because he knew that getting a strawberry would be even harder now. He started to look for another one but never did find one. 

The bear remembered the difficult task of catching an elusive strawberry the previous day. He used the same tactics he used then to try and get a strawberry and soon enough he was able to catch one! As the bear ate, he realized how important it was to be determined and how much effort he had to put in to get what he wanted.
