Once upon a time there was a tall painter. The painter loved to paint pictures for everyone. They would make beautiful works of art with paint, paper and lots of bright colors. 

One day, the painter went to a special party. At the party everyone was eating treats and having fun. But the tall painter couldn't remember anything from the party. 

The next morning, the painter woke up with a big feeling of sadness. They were trying to remember why they were so sad, but the memory was blurry. 

The painter eventually remembered that at the party, their friends had made fun of their tall painting. The painter was very hurt. 

But the painter was determined to carry on anyway. They found happiness in their painting and made lots of beautiful pictures. The painter never forgot the pain of that day, but they also remembered the joy of painting.
