Once upon a time two little girls, Mei and Daisy, decided to travel together. The two girls knew they wanted to go somewhere unknown but they didn't know where. Mei looked to her friend and asked, "Where should we travel to?".

Daisy smiled, "Let's keep going until we find something special!" Daisy took a tiny yellow rug from her pocket and spread it out on the ground. "Let's lay down on this rug and close our eyes. Wherever we go, we will travel with the rug!"

The two girls spread out the rug and laid down with eyes closed. Everything around them started to move and swirl. Before they knew it, they had arrived in a strange, unknown land. 

Mei opened her eyes and smiled. "We did it, Daisy! We found somewhere new and exciting!". Daisy opened her eyes and laughed. "Yes we did! Let's explore this new adventure together!". 

The two friends explored the unknown land, having lots of fun and exciting adventures. When it was time to go home, the two girls hugged each other tight. "Thank you, Mei," said Daisy, "for such a wonderful travel!" Mei nodded and smiled, "I had so much fun! I can't wait until our next adventure".
<|end|>


