Once upon a time, there was a fragile doll called Molly. She was very old and her dress was starting to look worn and dull. But Molly didn't mind, she believed that she could still be beautiful.

So one day, Molly decided to try and make her dress look new again. She grabbed some yarn from the box and began to start polishing the dress with it. She wrapped the yarn carefully around each thread of the fabric and then gently pulled it back and forth. 

The dress started to become shinier and shinier as Molly polished it. It was soon a bright, sparkling pink again. Molly was so happy with the results. 

Molly thanked the yarn for making her beautiful again. She was so proud of the hard work she had done to make her dress look special. From then on, Molly kept her dress polished and beautiful to make sure that she always felt proud.
