Once upon a time, there was a pretty lion who liked to roar. Every day he roamed in the jungle and the other animals were scared of his loud roars. Even though he liked to roar, the lion had a mystery he wanted to solve.

One day, he ran into a friendly rabbit who said, "Hello lion. Can I help you solve your mystery?" The lion was excited and asked, "What is it?"

The rabbit replied, "I can show you something pretty if you come with me!" The lion followed the rabbit and soon they reached a magical pond. The lion saw that the pond was sparkling and it was so pretty.

The lion was amazed. He roared with happiness. The rabbit said, "The mystery of the pond is that its waters make wishes come true. It's magical." 

The lion thanked the rabbit and returned to the jungle. Ever since that day, whenever the lion is feeling sad he goes back to the magical pond to make a wish.
