Once upon a time, there was a lion looking for a place to hide. He searched and searched until he found a palm tree. It was an easy place to escape. 

The lion curled up in the palm leaves to sleep. He was so snug and warm, he felt like he could sleep forever.

Just then, two little birds were chirping. They were looking for a place to escape too. When they saw the lion in the palm leaves, they were somewhat scared. 

But the lion smiled and said, "Don't worry, I'm friendly. You can sleep here too, it's easy." 

So the birds hopped into the palm leaves with the lion and went to sleep.

The lion and the birds slowly woke up and flew away, back to their own homes. And they all lived happily ever after. The end.
