Once there was a girl called Betty. She was three years old and always so happy. 

One day, she was playing in the playground. She ran and ran until she tripped and fell onto her knees. She felt hurt and started to cry.

Then, a big man came over. He was wearing a funny hat. He bent down and softly said, "Betty, would you like me to lift you up?".

Betty nodded her head and the big man scooped her up. He held her close and carried her over to a bench where he sat her down.

He watched as Betty rubbed her hurt knees. Then, he smiled and said, "Everything will be alright".
