Once upon a time, there was an elderly lady named Mary. Mary was out for a walk one day when she heard a strange noise. She stopped what she was doing and listened. She heard it again - it was the sound of a baby crying! Mary followed the sound and saw a small infant sitting in the middle of a field. Mary slowly approached the infant, who had no one around him. Mary carefully picked up the infant who had been abandoned and smiled.

Meanwhile, the infant's parents had been out looking for him everywhere. Eventually, they found their way to the field where Mary was holding their baby. The joy on their faces! They thanked Mary for her kindness and took their little one home.

For months afterwards, Mary visited the infant and his family. Every time she visited that spring, the infant loved to follow her wherever she went. He was so happy to be part of a family again. Mary smiled, happy that the little one was safe.
