Once upon a time there was a blueberry bush. It was alive and happy, and it grew lots of juicy blueberries. A little rabbit lived nearby and every day he would come and rub against the bush. He loved how it felt against his fur.

One day, the little rabbit noticed that the bush didn't feel the same. It was dead. He was so sad. He rubbed harder against the bush, but nothing helped.

The next day, the little rabbit wanted to make sure that his blueberry bush would never die. He dug some soil around the base of the bush and gave it some water. Then he rubbed it with his furry hands and sang a song.

The blueberry bush heard the song, and slowly it started to come back to life. The little rabbit was so happy!

At the end of the story, the little rabbit learned a moral lesson. He had to take care of things that he cared about. If he did, they would always come back to life, even when times looked dire.
