Once upon a time, there were two best friends, Joe and Sam. They were playing in the park one day when they heard the sound of drums. It was a loud, marching beat that filled their ears.

Curious, they followed the sound and came upon a group of people in long, ancient robes. Joe and Sam excitedly watched as the people payed and marched in a long, winding line.

The march went on and on for what felt like forever! Joe and Sam were amazed at how the ancient people played their drums and moved their feet in perfect time.

At last, the march stopped, and Joe and Sam clapped and cheered. They thanked the ancient people for an unforgettable show, then said goodbye and ran back home. From that day on, Joe and Sam talked about the ancient march every day.
