Jim and Lucy were taking a walk in the woods. While walking, Lucy found a twig lying on the ground. "Look, Jim! A twig!" Lucy exclaimed. Jim nodded, excited to see what Lucy would do with it.

Suddenly, they heard a nosy noise coming from the trees above. They both stopped and looked up to see a small brown squirrel looking down at them. It was curious to see what the two children were up to.

Lucy smiled and waved to the nosy squirrel and it jumped down from the tree and began to part around their feet. Lucy was excited and happy to see it.

Jim however, wasn't so happy. He knew that the squirrel wouldn't be alone for long, and he warned Lucy that soon there would be others! But Lucy didn't listen, and she kept playing with the twig, unaware of the danger.

Jim shook his head and quickly grabbed the twig from Lucy's hand. "Come on", he said. "We better go. We don't want to be here when the other squirrels show up!" Lucy frowned but listened to Jim, and the two of them started walking away. 

The nosy squirrel watched them both leave, then quickly scurried away in the opposite direction.
<|end|>


