Once there was a boy named Tom. He was three and loved to explore! 
One day Tom put on his blue hat and went out for a walk. Tom loved to listen to the birds singing in the trees and the gentle buzzing of the bees as they flew around the flowers. 

Tom kept walking and soon he came across a pond. He saw some ducks swimming around and decided to sit and watch. Tom heard some funny quacking coming from the water and thought it was funny.

Just then, an old, gentle voice said, "Do you want to know why they're quacking?" Tom turned around to see an old man smiling at him. Tom nodded yes and the old man said, "Listen carefully and I'll tell you why." 

The old man said, "When ducks quack, it's because they are communicating with each other. They are telling one another that the area is safe or warning them to watch out for danger." Tom listened very closely and thanked the old man.

Tom thanked the old man and went back home, happy with the new things he had learned that day. He told all his friends about the ducks and the old man's explanation. Tom was glad he had been so curious and had listened to the old man and the ducks.
