Jenny saw the postman put a letter in each mailbox. Finally, she got the courage to ask what he was doing.

"I'm delivering letters," he said with a smile. 

Jenny felt relieved, but then the postman added, "but if you look in those letters, you'll find something bad."

Jenny was horrified. She peeked in the mailbox and sure enough, inside each letter was a nasty surprise. When Jenny arrived back home, she was no longer feeling happy. She knew it was too nosy of her to follow the postman.

The next morning, the postman passed by again, but this time he wasn't smiling. Jenny knew she had learned her lesson. Nosiness was unpleasant, and she promised herself to never follow the postman again.
