Once there was a little girl called Jane. She was three years old and very curious about the world. One day, she saw a wide table in the garden. She went over to it and spoke to it.

"Hello, table," Jane said with a smile. The wide table did not answer, but Jane did not mind. She sat on the table and looked around.

Jane saw some flowers and a bird. She noticed how brightly the sun was shining and she felt so happy. She spoke to the flowers, the bird and even the sun! Then she heard a sound.

Jane looked around and saw her mum. She was smiling and Jane knew that she was very pleased. Her mum sat beside her on the wide table and they both smiled.

Jane was so grateful that she could share this moment with her mum. She was so lucky. Even though the wide table was silent, Jane knew how special it was.
<|end|>


