One day Thomas saw an old lady. She was walking with a big bag and Thomas asked her why she had it. The old lady said that she was borrowing something from her neighbour. Thomas was confused, so he asked what it was. The old lady said it was an old chair.

When Thomas saw the chair, he was very excited. He asked his mum if he could borrow it too. His mum said yes and Thomas was so happy. His mum asked the old lady if he could borrow the chair and the old lady said it was okay.

Thomas took the chair home and put it in his bedroom. He was so happy to have the old chair. Every day, he would sit in it and pretend he was a king. Thomas loved his old chair and he was so glad he was able to borrow it.
<|end|>


