Once upon a time, there lived a little girl called Sarah. Sarah loved singing. Every day she sang a happy song. 
One day, her dad cooked some soup for dinner. It was Sarah's favourite soup. But when she tasted it, she realised it was fake! Sarah was so sad. She didn't want to eat the fake soup.

So Sarah stopped singing her happy songs. She was very upset and decided to stop singing altogether. Every day she stayed quiet, no matter how hard people tried to make her sing.

The days went by and finally Sarah found a new hobby: drawing pictures of herself singing. She drew pictures of herself singing her favourite songs. It made her feel happy again. 

But even so, Sarah never sang again. She was too scared that someone would trick her into eating fake soup again.
<|end|>


