Once upon a time, there was a girl named Margaret who loved the outdoors. Every day she would go for a walk, and see all the new things around her. One day, she spotted a green bottle with a strange odor. As she looked closer, she saw that it was poison! She was very careful to keep away from it.

The next day, however, Margaret noticed something strange happening. She saw the same green bottle, but it had moved! She was surprised, but knew that something must have moved it.

A few days later, Margaret found out what had moved the poison. It was her carelessness! She had been so focused on looking for new things that she didn't pay attention to where she had left the bottle.

Margaret was sad, but learned an important lesson that day. From then on, she always took care to make sure that the poison stayed in its place.
<|end|>


