Once upon a time, there was a little boy who loved the outdoors. He wanted to explore the world and go on grand adventures. One day, he decided to go for a walk in the forest near his house. As he walked, he heard a funny noise. It was a strange and mysterious sound.

As he kept walking, the boy saw a black raven in a tree above him. He was so excited to see such an amazing creature. The bird seemed to be watching him with its bright eyes.

The raven cawed, and the boy took a step forward. Then the bird flew away. "Please, come back!" the little boy said, but the raven was gone.

The boy kept walking and exploring the forest, but he never forgot the black raven.

Some time moved on and one day, the boy was walking in the same forest. Suddenly the same black raven appeared. The bird flew close to the boy's shoulder and stayed there.

The boy smiled; he was so happy that the raven had come back. He offered the bird a piece of bread from his pocket and the raven ate it with pleasure. From that day on, the bird followed the boy everywhere he went. The boy and raven were the best of friends.
<|end|>


