Claire was three years old and loved exploring her backyard. One day, she spotted a nail lying in the grass. She remembered that her dad had suggested making a treehouse. She pulled out the nail and handed it to him.

Her dad grabbed the nail and studied it. He smiled and said, "This is perfect." He began hammering the nail into the tree and flipping boards around it.

Claire watched him work and waited patiently. Finally, he was done. He stood back and said, "Here it is-- your treehouse!"

Claire smiled and thought it was the best treehouse in the world. It was modest and cozy, but it was all hers. She couldn't wait to go explore it. With a big smile, she said, "Thank you, daddy!"
