Once upon a time, there was a little boy called Max. He was playing outside and couldn't wait to have some fun. He ran through the garden, jumping in and out of the mud puddles. Suddenly, he slipped and fell. Max felt scared and guilty. He knew he had done something bad. 

He slowly stood up, and quick as a flash he saw his mother standing in front of him. His waist hurt, but he was too afraid to say anything. His Mum looked at him with sad eyes and said, "Max, why did you slip?". Max felt even more guilty, but he stayed quiet.

After a few moments, his mum smiled and said, "It's alright Max, don't feel guilty". She then helped him to get up and gave him a big hug. Max was so relieved that his mum wasn't cross with him. He knew then that no matter what he did, she would still love him.
