Once there was a little girl named Susie. She loved to play with her toys and go outside in the sunshine. But what she loved to do the most was write in her journal!

Every day, Susie wrote in her journal about her adventures. Sometimes she wrote about her friends and what they did, or the places she went. She even wrote down big events like the time she went to the beach.

But one day, Susie felt something different. She was feeling very dizzy. She wasn't sure why, so she went and lay down to rest. After a while, Susie felt better and got up. She decided to write about how she was feeling in her journal.

So Susie wrote about what it felt like to be a little bit dizzy and then how it felt to be better again. She even named the feeling she had in her journal. She called it "the dizzy feeling".

By writing down her feelings and giving them a name, Susie felt better. From then on, anytime she felt dizzy, she remembered the name she had given it and it made her feel better.

The End.
<|end|>


