Once there was a girl called Daisy. She loved to skip along the beach. One day, Daisy looked out across the big ocean and saw a sailboat. She skipped over to take a closer look.

The sailboat was reliable and white, with blue and yellow stripes. Daisy wanted to go on-board, so she asked the captain if she could join them. The captain smiled and said yes.

For hours Daisy skipped around the boat as it sailed over the ocean. When the coast came into sight, Daisy had to say goodbye to the captain and crew. But she knew she would be back again soon.

Daisy loved to explore the ocean and skip around the beach with her friends. Anything was possible when she was sailing out on the reliable ocean.
