Jill was tall and she could reach everything in the bathroom. One day, she needed to take a bath and started to take out the soap from the cupboard. She asked her mom, "Can I cut the soap?" Her mom was surprised and said, "What do you need to cut it for?" Jill said, "The soap is too big, I want to make it smaller so it fits in the bathtub." So her mom got a knife and Jill carefully cut the soap into smaller pieces. She put the pieces in the tub and filled it with water. Jill was so excited and happy that she could take a bath with the smaller pieces of soap!
