Once upon a time, there was a lonely tree. It was the only tree for miles. The tree needed oxygen to grow, but the air was not fresh. The tree began to rot from the inside out. 

The tree felt so alone, trapped in the stinky air. One day, it heard something rustling in the distance. A little wild animal came running up to the tree and saw it was in trouble. The wild animal thought hard and ran off, quickly coming back with a bag full of fresh air. 

The wild animal created a bubble of fresh air around the tree. This helped the tree get the oxygen it needed and it slowly started to heal itself. The tree and the wild animal became friends. Now, they spend their days playing together, the tree no longer lonely.
<|end|>


