Once upon a time, there was a little girl named Lily. She loved to bake cakes with her mom. One day, Lily's mom gave her a bowl and told her to mix the flour and sugar together. Lily mixed and mixed until it was all combined.

After that, Lily wanted to turn on the oven, but her mom told her to wait until she switched it on. While waiting, Lily saw a big piece of ice outside. She wanted to touch it, but her mom told her it was too icy and she might get hurt.

But Lily didn't listen. She ran outside and touched the icy piece. It was very cold and her hand hurt. She cried and cried until her mom came outside and took her inside to warm up. Sadly, Lily's hand was badly hurt and they had to go to the hospital. From then on, Lily always listened to her mom and never touched anything icy again. The end.
