Once upon a time, there was a little girl named Lily. One day, she was drinking hot chocolate from her favorite mug when she accidentally dropped it on the floor. She felt sad because her mug was now broken.

Lily's mom saw her daughter feeling frustrated and said, "It's okay, Lily. We can fix your mug with glue." Lily was happy to hear that and they glued the mug back together.

The next day, Lily's little brother was playing with a ball in the house. Lily warned him to be careful and not break anything. But he accidentally hit the mug and it broke again. Lily felt even more frustrated this time.

Her mom hugged her and said, "I know it's frustrating, but remember that things can always be fixed. What's important is that we learn from our mistakes and try to be more careful next time." Lily understood the lesson and felt better. From that day on, she made sure to keep her favorite mug in a safe place.
