Once upon a time, there was a little girl named Lily. She loved to eat rice every day. One day, her mommy told her that they were going to have a special dinner with her grandparents. Lily was shy and nervous to meet them.

When they arrived, Lily's grandpa asked her, "Do you like to polish things?" Lily nodded her head and said, "Yes, I like to polish my shoes." Her grandpa smiled and said, "Well, I have a special gift for you then." He gave her a shiny silver spoon and said, "This spoon is very special. It's made of silver and you can use it to polish things."

Lily was so happy and excited to have the spoon. After dinner, she went to the kitchen and used the spoon to polish the rice pot until it was shiny and clean. Her grandpa was very proud of her and said, "You did a great job, Lily. You're a very good polisher." Lily smiled and felt very proud of herself too.
