Once upon a time, there was a little boy named Tim. Tim loved candy so much that he ate it every day. His mom told him that candy was not good for his teeth and could make him sick. Tim didn't listen and kept eating candy.

One day, Tim's mom took him to the dentist. The dentist said that Tim had a lot of cavities and needed to stop eating candy. Tim's mom told him that she would prevent him from eating candy so that he could have healthy teeth.

Tim was sad at first, but then he realized that he could find other unique treats to enjoy. He discovered fruits like apples and bananas, which were just as sweet as candy but healthier. Tim was happy and his teeth were healthy too.
