Once upon a time, there was a little girl named Lily. She loved to play in the kitchen while her mom was cooking. One day, her mom was very busy making dinner for the family. Lily asked, "Mommy, can I help you?" Her mom replied, "Sure, you can blink the potatoes."

Lily didn't know what "blink" meant, so her mom showed her how to close and open her eyes quickly. Lily started to blink the potatoes and thought it was so much fun. Suddenly, her little brother came into the kitchen and said, "I'm hungry!" Lily's mom said, "Dinner will be ready soon, just wait a little bit longer."

Lily's brother looked sad, so Lily said, "Don't worry, I'll blink my eyes and make dinner come faster!" Her brother smiled and said, "Okay, let's both blink our eyes together!" So they both closed and opened their eyes quickly, hoping dinner would come faster. And before they knew it, dinner was ready and everyone sat down to eat together.
