Brownie said, "Sure, I will help you. Do you remember the number of trees you passed by?" The rabbit said, "Yes, I passed by five big trees." Brownie said, "Okay, let's go back and count the trees."

They walked back, and the rabbit counted the trees. Suddenly, they heard a loud noise. It was a hunter who wanted to catch Brownie. Brownie and the rabbit ran as fast as they could, but the hunter caught Brownie in a big case. The rabbit was very sad because he lost his friend Brownie.
