Once upon a time, there was a little girl named Lily. One day, Lily and her friend, Timmy, went to play in the park. They saw a big puddle of mud and they thought it looked funny. 

Lily said to Timmy, "Let's jump in the mud puddle!" 

Timmy replied, "I don't want to get muddy." 

Lily said, "It's okay, we can lift our feet high so we don't get too dirty." 

So they jumped and splashed in the mud puddle, lifting their feet high. They laughed and had so much fun. 

When they were done playing, they went home to take a bath and clean off all the mud. They both agreed that jumping in the mud was the funniest thing they had ever done.
<|end|>


