Once upon a time, there was a little boy named Timmy. Timmy loved to play with his toys, but his room was always very messy. His mommy would always tell him to clean up his toys, but Timmy didn't like to.

One day, Timmy's mommy came into his room and saw that the floor was filthy. She told Timmy that he needed to sort through his toys and put them away. Timmy didn't want to at first, but then he saw how dirty the floor was and knew he had to help.

So Timmy started to sort through his toys and put them away. It took a long time, but when he was done, the floor was clean again. Timmy felt very proud of himself for helping his mommy and keeping his room clean. From then on, he made sure to put his toys away every day so the floor would stay nice and clean.
