Once upon a time, there was a little girl named Lily. She loved to play dress-up with her mom's clothes. One day, she was playing with a hanger and accidentally dropped it on the floor. She got nervous because she didn't want to get in trouble. But her mom just smiled and said it was okay. 

Lily continued to play with the hanger and even pretended it was a magic wand. She twirled around in her princess dress and felt very happy. Suddenly, her little brother came in and wanted to play too. Lily was happy to share and they played together for a long time. 

At the end of the day, Lily's mom came in and saw the hanger on the floor. She picked it up and hung it back in the closet. Lily felt proud that she had shared her toy and didn't feel nervous anymore. She knew that her mom loved her no matter what. The end.
