Mia and Ben were playing in the garden. They liked to look for insects and put them in a jar. Mia was bossy and told Ben what to do. "You find the ants, I find the bees," she said.

Ben did not like ants. They bit him and made him cry. He wanted to find bees too, but Mia said no. "Bees are mine, ants are yours," she said. Ben was sad and angry.

He saw a big bee on a flower. He wanted to catch it and show Mia. He was quiet and careful. He moved his hand slowly to the flower. He was almost there. Then he heard a loud snap.

Mia had seen the bee too. She ran to the flower and snapped her jar over it. She smiled and said, "Ha! I got the bee. You are too slow, Ben."

Ben was very sad and angry. He felt a sting on his hand. He looked and saw an ant. It had bitten him. He cried and dropped his jar. His jar broke and the ants ran away.

Mia saw Ben crying and felt sorry. She said, "I'm sorry, Ben. I was too bossy. Do you want to share the bee?"

Ben nodded and smiled. He said, "Yes, please. And can we find some butterflies too?"

Mia nodded and smiled. She said, "Yes, we can. And I will be nice to you."

They hugged and went to look for butterflies. They were happy and played nicely. They liked insects and each other.
<|end|>


