Tom and Lily were playing with their toys in the garden. They had a lot of toys, but their favorite was a big pink pig. The pig could make funny noises and move its legs and tail.

"Let's number the pig's legs," Tom said. He liked to number things and learn new words. He pointed to the pig's front leg and said, "One."

Lily nodded and pointed to the other front leg. "Two," she said.

They moved to the back legs and said, "Three" and "Four." They were very happy and proud of themselves.

But then they heard a loud voice from the house. It was their mom. She sounded serious and angry.

"Tom and Lily, come inside right now! It's time for lunch and you have to wash your hands. And stop playing with that pig. It's dirty and it belongs to the farmer next door. He will be very mad if he sees you with it."

Tom and Lily looked at each other and felt scared. They did not know the pig was not theirs. They thought it was a toy. They quickly put the pig down and ran to the house. They hoped the farmer would not find out and take the pig away. They liked the pig and wanted to play with it again. Maybe they could number its ears and eyes next time.
