Anna and Ben were playing in the park. They saw a big yellow dog lying on the grass. The dog looked friendly and sleepy.

"Can we pet the dog?" Anna asked Ben.

"I don't know. Maybe we should ask the owner first," Ben said.

They looked around and saw a man sitting on a bench. He had a book in his hand. He looked smart and kind.

"Excuse me, sir. Is that your dog?" Anna called to him.

The man looked up and smiled. "Yes, that's my dog. His name is Wisdom. He's very gentle and loves children. You can pet him if you want."

"Thank you, sir. Why did you name him Wisdom?" Ben asked.

The man closed his book and walked over to them. He stroked the dog's fur and said, "Because he taught me a lot of things. He taught me how to be patient, loyal, and grateful. He taught me how to enjoy the simple things in life, like lying on the grass and feeling the sun. He taught me how to be a good friend. He's the wisest dog I ever met."

Anna and Ben nodded. They understood. They petted Wisdom and thanked the man. They learned something new that day. They learned that wisdom can come from anyone, even a big yellow dog.
<|end|>


