Tim and Mia were playing in the snow. They made a big snowman with a hat and a scarf. They gave him a carrot nose and two rocks for eyes. They were very happy with their snowman.

But then they saw a seal. The seal was lost and cold. He had swum too far from the icy water. He was looking for his family. He was sad and scared.

"Hello, seal," said Tim. "Why are you here? You need to go back to the water. It is too cold for you here."

The seal nodded. He wanted to go back, but he did not know how. He had followed a fish and got lost. He did not see any water or ice. He only saw snow and trees.

"Don't worry, seal," said Mia. "We will help you. We will solve your problem. We will find the water and ice for you. Come with us."

Tim and Mia took the seal by the flippers. They dragged him along the snow. They looked for signs of water and ice. They asked a bird, a squirrel, and a deer. They followed their directions.

Soon they saw a lake. The lake was frozen. There was a hole in the ice. The seal saw the hole. He saw his family. They were waiting for him. They were happy to see him.

"Thank you, Tim and Mia," said the seal. "You are very kind and smart. You solved my problem. You found the water and ice for me. You are my friends."

The seal gave them a hug and a kiss. He slid into the hole. He joined his family. He waved goodbye to Tim and Mia.

Tim and Mia waved back. They were glad they helped the seal. They went back to their snowman. They gave him a smile. They played some more in the snow. They had a fun day.
<|end|>


