Lily and Tom were playing in the park. They liked to pretend they were famous people. Lily was a singer and Tom was a king. They had a lot of fun.

"Look at me, I am the king of the world!" Tom said. He wore a paper crown and a cape. He sat on a bench and waved to the birds and the flowers.

"You are a great king, Tom. I admire you very much," Lily said. She wore a dress and a necklace. She sang a song for Tom and the park.

"Thank you, Lily. You are a wonderful singer. I admire you too," Tom said. He clapped his hands and smiled.

They were happy and proud of each other. They played until it was time to go home. They hugged and said goodbye.

"See you tomorrow, Tom. You are my best friend," Lily said.

"See you tomorrow, Lily. You are my best friend too," Tom said.

They went home with their moms. They had a good day. They dreamed of being famous.
