Lily was a little girl who liked to play with her dolls. She had many dolls, but her favorite was Anna. Anna had long hair, a blue dress and a big smile. Lily loved to brush Anna's hair and make her talk.

One day, Lily noticed that Anna was not smiling. She looked at Anna and saw that her dress was torn and her hair was tangled. Lily felt sad and asked Anna, "What happened to you? Why are you not happy?"

Anna did not answer. She looked weak and tired. Lily tried to hug her, but Anna felt cold and hard. Lily wondered if Anna was sick or hurt. She decided to take her to Mommy.

Lily ran to the kitchen, where Mommy was making lunch. She held Anna in her arms and said, "Mommy, Mommy, please help Anna! She is not smiling and she is weak and cold!"

Mommy looked at Lily and Anna. She saw the torn dress and the tangled hair. She smiled and said, "Don't worry, Lily. Anna is not sick or hurt. She is just a toy. Toys don't feel or talk like we do. They only look like they do."

Lily was confused. She said, "But Mommy, Anna is my friend. She always smiles and talks to me. She is not just a toy. She is real!"

Mommy hugged Lily and said, "I know, Lily. Anna is your friend and you love her. But she is not real like you and me. She is made of plastic and cloth. She can't feel or talk by herself. You make her feel and talk with your imagination. You are very clever and creative, Lily. That's why you have so much fun with Anna."

Lily thought about what Mommy said. She looked at Anna and said, "Is that true, Anna? Are you not real? Do I make you feel and talk?"

Anna did not answer. She still looked weak and cold. Lily felt a little sad, but also a little curious. She said, "Mommy, can you fix Anna? Can you make her dress and hair nice again? Can you make her warm and soft?"

Mommy nodded and said, "Of course, Lily. I can fix Anna. I can sew her dress and comb her hair. I can put her in the sun and make her warm and soft. Then you can play with her again and make her smile and talk."

Lily smiled and said, "Thank you, Mommy. You are the best. I love you and I love Anna."

Mommy smiled and said, "I love you too, Lily. And I love Anna too. She is a very special doll. She is your friend."
<|end|>


