Tom and Anna like to play in the garden. They have a ball and a net. They throw the ball and try to catch it with the net. Sometimes they miss and the ball rolls away. They run after it and laugh.

One day, they see a green plant in the corner of the garden. It smells nice and fresh. Tom picks a leaf and puts it in his mouth. He makes a funny face and spits it out. "Yuck! This is not candy!" he says.

Anna picks another leaf and smells it. She likes the smell. She breaks the leaf and rubs it on her hands. She feels cool and happy. "This is mint," she says. "Mommy uses it to make tea. It is good for you."

Tom and Anna decide to pick some mint and take it to Mommy. They fill their net with mint leaves and run to the house. They see Mommy in the kitchen. She is making cookies. The kitchen is tidy and warm.

"Look, Mommy, we have mint for you!" they say and show her their net. Mommy smiles and hugs them. She takes some mint and puts it in a pot of water. She says, "Thank you, Tom and Anna. You are very sweet and helpful. Mint tea is delicious and healthy. Would you like to try some with your cookies?"

Tom and Anna nod and sit at the table. They sip the mint tea and eat the cookies. They like the taste. They feel proud and happy. They love Mommy and the garden.
