Lily and Ben were playing with blocks in the living room. They liked to build towers and bridges and houses with the blocks. Sometimes they shared the blocks, and sometimes they fought over them.

One day, Lily wanted to use a blue block that Ben had in his hand. She asked him, "Can I have that block, please?" But Ben said, "No, it's mine. Go find another one."

Lily felt angry and sad. She wanted the blue block very much. She thought Ben was being mean and selfish. She decided to take the block from him. She reached out her hand and tried to grab the block. But Ben was faster. He moved his hand away and pinched Lily's arm hard.

"Ow!" Lily cried. "That hurts! Why did you pinch me?" She looked at her arm and saw a red mark. It was as big as an inch. She felt more angry and sad.

Ben felt sorry and scared. He did not mean to hurt Lily. He just wanted to keep his block. He thought Lily was being rude and greedy. He said, "I'm sorry, I pinched you because you tried to take my block. It's not nice to take things from others."

Lily and Ben stared at each other. They both felt weird. They did not like to fight. They liked to play. They realized they were both wrong. They said, "I'm sorry" and "It's okay" and hugged each other. Then they decided to share the blocks and build something together. They felt happy and proud. They learned to be kind and fair.
