Tom and Lily were playing in the park. They saw a big hill with a hole in it. They wanted to see what was inside.

"Let's go to the cave!" Tom said.

"OK, but be careful. It might be dark and scary," Lily said.

They ran to the hill and crawled into the hole. It was dark and cold. They saw some rocks and sticks and bugs. They also saw a big ball.

"Look, a ball!" Tom said. He picked it up and threw it to Lily.

Lily caught the ball and threw it back. They played catch for a while. Then Lily threw the ball too hard. It hit the wall of the cave and made a loud noise.

"Oops!" Lily said.

The noise woke up a big bear that was sleeping in the corner. The bear was angry and roared. It got up and ran towards Tom and Lily.

"Run!" Tom said.

They dropped the ball and ran out of the hole. The bear followed them. It was fast and big.

Tom and Lily were scared. They looked for a place to hide. They saw a big tree with a broken branch. They climbed up the tree and sat on the branch.

The bear reached the tree and tried to climb up too. But the branch was broken and weak. It could not hold the bear's weight. The branch snapped and the bear fell down.

"Ouch!" the bear said.

Tom and Lily saw that the bear was hurt. They felt sorry for the bear. They threw some nuts and berries to the bear.

"Sorry, bear. We did not mean to wake you up. Here, have some food," Lily said.

The bear ate the food and felt better. It looked at Tom and Lily and nodded. It was not angry anymore. It went back to the cave and slept.

Tom and Lily climbed down the tree and went back to the park. They learned a lesson. They should not go into caves without asking. They should also be kind to animals. They hugged each other and went home.
<|end|>


