Tom and Sam are best friends. They like to play with toy cars and rockets. One day, they find a big box in the garage. They wonder what is inside.

"Let's open it!" Tom says.

"OK, but be careful. It might be something bad." Sam says.

They lift the lid and see a shiny metal thing. It has a pointy nose and a long tail. It looks like a rocket, but bigger and stronger.

"Wow! What is this?" Tom asks.

"I think it is a missile. It can fly very fast and far. Maybe it can go to the moon!" Sam says.

They touch the missile and feel how cold and hard it is. They see a button on the side. They wonder what it does.

"Should we press it?" Tom asks.

"Maybe. But what if it makes a loud noise or a big fire?" Sam says.

They look at each other and smile. They are curious and brave. They decide to press the button together.

They count to three and push the button. The missile starts to beep and shake. They hear a voice from inside the box.

"Missile launch sequence initiated. Countdown: 10, 9, 8..."

Tom and Sam are scared and excited. They run out of the garage and watch the box. The lid flies off and the missile shoots out. It makes a loud roar and a bright trail. It goes up and up and up.

"Wow! Look at that!" Tom says.

"It is amazing! It is going to the moon!" Sam says.

They clap and cheer. They have just revealed a secret missile. They have made a successful launch. They are the best friends ever.
