Lila and Ben were best friends. They liked to play in the park and share their toys. One day, they saw a big flame in the sky. It was a balloon with fire inside. It looked very pretty and bright.

"Wow, look at that!" Lila said. "I want to go inside the balloon and fly high."

"Me too," Ben said. "But how can we do that?"

They saw a man with a hat and a coat near the balloon. He was holding a rope. He smiled at them and said, "Hello, little ones. Do you like my balloon?"

"Yes, we do," Lila and Ben said. "Can we go inside?"

The man nodded. "Sure, you can. But you have to promise me something. You have to be very careful and listen to me. The fire can be dangerous if you touch it or go too close. Do you understand?"

Lila and Ben nodded. They wanted to see the balloon very much. They said, "We promise. We will be careful and listen to you."

The man helped them climb inside the basket. He gave them each a cheerful hat and a coat. He said, "These will keep you warm and safe. Are you ready to fly?"

Lila and Ben said, "Yes, we are!"

The man pulled the rope and the balloon lifted off the ground. Lila and Ben felt very happy and excited. They saw the park, the trees, the houses, and the people below. They waved at them and shouted, "Hello!"

The man said, "You are very brave and good children. I'm glad you kept your promise. Now, let's enjoy the ride."
