Tom and Sue are friends. They like to play in the park. One day, they see a big box. It has a sign that says "test". They are curious.

"What is in the box?" Tom asks.

"I don't know. Let's open it and see," Sue says.

They open the box. Inside, there are many toys. There are cars, dolls, balls, and books. They are happy.

"Wow, look at all these toys! Can we play with them?" Tom says.

"Sure, why not? But we have to be careful. Maybe this is a test," Sue says.

"A test? What do you mean?" Tom says.

"Maybe someone is watching us. Maybe they want to see how we play with the toys. Maybe they want to see if we are good or bad," Sue says.

"That sounds crazy. Who would do that?" Tom says.

"I don't know. But we should be nice and share the toys. And we should not break them or make a mess," Sue says.

"OK, OK. You are right. Let's play nice and have fun," Tom says.

They start to play with the toys. They take turns and help each other. They make stories and sounds. They laugh and smile.

They are having so much fun that they do not notice a man. He is hiding behind a tree. He has a camera and a notebook. He is watching them. He is smiling too.

He is the one who put the box in the park. He is the one who made the test. He is a teacher. He wants to learn how children play and learn. He thinks Tom and Sue are very smart and kind. He is not crazy. He is happy.
