Tom and Anna are twins. They like to play in the park with their ball and their dog. But today, the sky is dark and loud. Mom says they have to go home.

"Mom, why is the sky so bad?" Tom asks.

"Because there is a storm, Tom. A storm is when the sky makes noise and rain and lightning. Lightning is when the sky makes bright flashes. It can be scary, but it is not bad. It is just part of nature," Mom says.

"But I don't like lightning. It hurts my eyes and makes me jump," Anna says.

"I know, Anna. But lightning can also be beautiful and powerful. And it helps the plants and the animals grow. Sometimes, lightning can even make a rainbow," Mom says.

They get home and Mom gives them milk and cookies. She tells them to lie on the couch and watch a movie. She says the storm will be over soon.

Tom and Anna lie on the couch with their dog. They watch a movie about a princess and a dragon. They forget about the storm for a while. But then, they hear a loud boom and see a bright flash.

"Mom, what was that?" Tom cries.

"That was thunder and lightning, Tom. Don't be afraid. It is just the sky saying hello," Mom says.

"Hello, sky. Please be quiet. We are trying to watch a movie," Anna says.

Mom laughs and hugs them. She says they are brave and smart. She says she loves them very much. They snuggle on the couch and watch the movie. They see a rainbow on the screen. They smile and feel happy. The storm is not so bad after all.
