Lily and Ben were playing in the forest. They liked to look for bugs and flowers and birds. They saw a big log that was old and brown. They wondered what was inside.

"Let's open it and see," Ben said. He kicked the log with his foot, but it did not move. He kicked harder, but it still did not move.

"Stop, Ben, you are hurting the log," Lily said. She touched the log gently with her hand. She felt something soft and warm. She heard a small sound.

"What is it?" Ben asked. He came closer and looked.

They saw a hole in the log. Inside the hole, there was a family of mice. There was a mama mouse, a papa mouse, and four baby mice. They had made a nest of leaves and fur. They looked scared and shy.

"Hello, mice," Lily said. "We are sorry we disturbed you. We are humble and kind. We just wanted to see what was in the log. We will not hurt you or take your home."

The mice looked at Lily and Ben. They saw that they were not mean or big. They saw that they were curious and friendly. They squeaked softly and came out of the hole. They sniffed Lily and Ben and rubbed their noses.

"Hello, children," the mama mouse said. "We are glad you are humble and kind. We are happy to share our log with you. You can come and visit us anytime. We will show you our bugs and flowers and birds."

Lily and Ben smiled and nodded. They thanked the mice and said goodbye. They left the log and went to find more things to explore. They were happy they had made new friends in the forest.
