Tom and Lily are friends. They like to play in the park. One day, they hear a noise. It is a fat dog. The dog is barking. He is hungry.

"Look, a fat dog!" Tom says. "He is loud."

"Maybe he wants a cookie," Lily says. "I have a cookie in my bag."

Lily takes out a cookie. She breaks it in half. She gives one half to Tom and one half to the dog.

"Here, doggy, have a cookie," Lily says. "Be nice."

The dog stops barking. He wags his tail. He eats the cookie. He licks Lily's hand.

"Thank you, Lily," the dog says. "You are kind."

Tom and Lily are surprised. They did not know dogs can talk.

"Wow, a talking dog!" Tom says. "Can you be our friend?"

"Sure, I can be your friend," the dog says. "My name is Spot. What are your names?"

"I am Tom and this is Lily," Tom says. "We like to play in the park."

"Me too," Spot says. "Can I play with you?"

"Yes, you can," Lily says. "Let's go to the slide."

