Anna and Ben like to exercise. They run and jump and play in the park. They have fun and feel good.

One day, they see a big slide. It is very high and shiny. Anna wants to try it. She climbs up the ladder and sits on the slide. She smiles at Ben and says, "Watch me!"

Ben watches Anna. He thinks she is brave and reliable. He knows she will not be scared. He waits for her to slide down.

But something goes wrong. Anna slides too fast and loses her balance. She falls off the slide and lands on the grass. She cries out loud. She hurts her knee and elbow.

Ben runs to Anna. He is worried and sad. He says, "Are you okay, Anna? I'm sorry you fell. Do you need help?"

Anna looks at Ben. She sees his kind face and hears his nice voice. She feels better. She says, "Thank you, Ben. You are a good friend. I'm okay. It was just an accident. Can you help me get up?"

Ben nods and helps Anna get up. He hugs her and says, "You're welcome, Anna. You are a good friend too. I'm glad you're okay. Let's go to the bench and rest. Maybe we can try the slide again later."

