<|asst|>
Lily and Ben like to go to the park with Mom. They enjoy playing on the swings, the slide and the seesaw. But their favorite thing is to ride the boat on the pond. Mom helps them put on life jackets and gives them a row to move the boat.

"Look, Lily, there are ducks on the water!" Ben says, pointing with his row. "Can we feed them some bread?"

"OK, but be careful not to drop the row," Lily says. She breaks a piece of bread and throws it to the ducks. They quack and swim closer to the boat.

Lily and Ben laugh as they watch the ducks eat the bread. They feel the cool breeze on their faces and the sun on their hair. They row the boat around the pond, waving to Mom on the shore. They have a lot of fun on the boat. They love the park.
<|end|>


