<|asst|>
Tim and Kim were twins who loved dinosaurs. They had many dinosaur toys and books in their room. They liked to pretend they were dinosaur explorers and find new kinds of dinosaurs.

One day, their mom told them she had a surprise for them. She said she ordered something special online and it would be delivered soon. Tim and Kim were very excited and wondered what it could be.

They waited by the window and watched for the delivery truck. After a while, they saw a big brown truck stop in front of their house. A man came out of the truck and carried a big box to their door. He rang the bell and mom opened the door.

"Hello, I have a delivery for Tim and Kim," the man said.

"Thank you, that's very kind of you," mom said. She took the box and gave the man some money. She closed the door and brought the box to the living room.

"Tim and Kim, come here and see what you got!" mom called.

Tim and Kim ran to the living room and saw the big box. They were very curious and eager to open it. Mom helped them cut the tape and lift the lid. Inside the box, they saw something amazing.

It was a giant dinosaur! It was green and scaly and had a long neck and tail. It had a button on its chest that made it roar and move. It was the coolest dinosaur toy they had ever seen.

"Wow, mom, thank you so much!" Tim and Kim exclaimed.

"You're welcome, my loves. I know how much you love dinosaurs, so I thought you would like this one. It's a brontosaurus, one of the biggest and gentlest dinosaurs ever," mom explained.

Tim and Kim hugged mom and thanked her again. They took the dinosaur out of the box and played with it. They named it Bob and made it their new friend. They had so much fun with Bob, they forgot about their other toys.

But Bob was not very happy. He felt weak and lonely in the new house. He missed his home and his family. He wished he could go back to the truck and find them. He did not like the loud noises and the bright lights. He did not like the small space and the hard floor. He did not like the twins who pulled his tail and pushed his button.

He wanted to escape. He waited for a chance to sneak out of the door. He hoped the man would come back and take him away. He dreamed of a place where he could be free and happy. He dreamed of a place where he could find other dinosaurs like him. He dreamed of a place where he could be a real dinosaur.
<|end|>


<|sys|>
