<|asst|>
Tom likes to write. He has a big book with many pages. He uses a crayon to make shapes and letters on the pages. He writes his name, his mom's name, and his dog's name. He writes about what he sees and what he likes.

One day, he writes on his chair. He thinks it is fun to write on the chair. He makes red and blue and green marks on the chair. He writes "Tom" and "chair" and "fun". He is very happy.

But mom is not happy. She sees the chair and she is angry. She says, "Tom, what did you do? You should not write on the chair. That is bad. The chair is not a book. You need to clean the chair now."

Tom is sad. He says, "I'm sorry, mom. I like to write. I did not know it was bad. How do I clean the chair?"

Mom says, "You need to use a cloth and some water. And you need to be alert. You need to watch where you write. You can only write on paper or in your book. Do you understand?"

Tom nods. He says, "I understand, mom. I will be alert. I will not write on the chair again. I will clean the chair now."

He takes a cloth and some water and he cleans the chair. He rubs and rubs until the marks are gone. He says, "Look, mom. The chair is clean. I'm sorry I wrote on it."

Mom smiles. She says, "Thank you, Tom. I'm glad you cleaned the chair. I know you like to write. But you need to be careful. Writing is good, but not on the chair. Next time, write on paper or in your book. OK?"

Tom says, "OK, mom. I will write on paper or in my book. Can I write now?"

Mom says, "Yes, you can write now. But first, give me a hug. I love you, Tom."

Tom hugs mom. He says, "I love you, mom. You are the best."

He goes to his book and he writes. He writes, "I love mom. She is the best. She helps me write. She helps me clean. She is alert. She is fun." He is very happy.
<|end|>


