<|asst|>
Tom had a pet parrot named Max. Max was deaf, so he could not hear Tom when he talked to him. But Tom loved Max anyway, and taught him some signs with his hands. Max learned how to say hello, bye, and I love you with his hands.

One day, Tom and Max went to the park with Tom's mom. Tom wanted to play on the slide, so he left Max on a bench with his mom. Max saw a big red balloon in the sky. He liked the balloon, and wanted to touch it. He flew off the bench and chased the balloon.

Max was very fast. He speeded through the air, and got closer to the balloon. But he did not see the tree in front of him. He crashed into the tree, and fell to the ground. He was hurt, and cried.

Tom heard Max cry, and ran to him. He saw Max on the ground, with a bump on his head. He was scared, and hugged Max. He said, "Max, are you okay? I'm sorry, I should have watched you. I love you, Max."

Max looked at Tom, and saw his worried face. He felt Tom's hug, and his love. He signed, "I love you, Tom." He was still hurt, but he was happy. Tom's mom came, and took Max to the vet. The vet said Max would be fine, but he should not fly for a while. Tom and Max went home, and cuddled on the couch. They were best friends.
<|end|>


