<|asst|>
Jill was a humble girl who liked to help her mom and dad. She did not have many toys, but she was happy with what she had. She had a doll, a ball, and a book of stories.

One day, it was her birthday. She was very excited. She hoped that her mom and dad would give her a candle to put on her cake. She loved candles. They made her feel warm and bright.

She helped her mom bake the cake. It smelled good. She helped her dad set the table. It looked nice. She waited for her mom and dad to bring the cake. She waited and waited.

She heard a knock on the door. She ran to open it. It was her friend Tom. He had a big smile and a small box. He said, "Happy birthday, Jill! I have a gift for you."

Jill thanked him and opened the box. Inside was a candle. It was pink and had a flower on it. It was the most beautiful candle she had ever seen. She hugged Tom and said, "Thank you, Tom! You are a good friend. This is the best gift ever."

She ran to the kitchen with the candle. She saw her mom and dad with the cake. They had forgotten to buy a candle. They looked sad. They said, "We are sorry, Jill. We wanted to give you a candle, but we did not have enough money. We hope you still like the cake."

Jill smiled and said, "Don't be sorry, mom and dad. I love you and I love the cake. And look, I have a candle. Tom gave it to me. He is a good friend. Can we put it on the cake and make a wish?"

Her mom and dad smiled and said, "Of course, Jill. You are a sweet and humble girl. We are proud of you. Let's put the candle on the cake and make a wish."

They put the candle on the cake and lit it. It glowed like a star. Jill closed her eyes and made a wish. She wished for more candles, more friends, and more happiness. She opened her eyes and blew out the candle. She heard Tom, her mom, and her dad clap and cheer. She felt warm and bright. She did not sigh. She smiled.
<|end|>


