Anna liked to play in the attic. It was a big room with many things to see. She had to open a door and climb some stairs to get there. Sometimes she found old toys, books, and clothes. She liked to pretend they were hers.

One day, she saw a big box in the corner. She had never seen it before. She was curious. She went to the box and opened it. Inside, she found a doll. The doll had long hair, a pretty dress, and shiny shoes. Anna thought the doll was very interesting. She picked it up and hugged it.

"Hello, doll," she said. "What is your name?"

The doll smiled and said, "Hello, Anna. My name is Lucy. I was waiting for you."

Anna was surprised. She did not know the doll could talk. She asked, "How do you know my name?"

The doll said, "I know many things. I was your grandma's doll when she was a little girl. She loved me very much. She put me in this box and told me to wait for you. She said you would love me too."

Anna felt happy. She said, "I do love you, Lucy. You are my new friend. Do you want to play with me?"

The doll said, "Yes, Anna. I want to play with you. Let's have fun in the attic."

Anna and Lucy played together for a long time. They had tea parties, read stories, and dressed up. They laughed and sang. They were very happy. Anna was glad she opened the box and found the interesting doll.
<|end|>


