Lily and Sam are friends. They like to play together. One day, they go to the park. They see a big open space. They want to dance.

"Can we borrow your music, please?" Lily asks a man with a radio.

"Sure, you can borrow my music. What do you want to hear?" the man says.

"We like happy songs. Songs that make us want to dance," Sam says.

The man smiles. He plays a happy song. Lily and Sam start to dance. They jump and spin and clap. They have fun.

The man watches them. He likes their dance. He joins them. He dances with Lily and Sam. They laugh and sing.

They dance until the song ends. Then they say thank you to the man.

"Thank you for letting us borrow your music. You are a good dancer," Lily says.

"Thank you for dancing with me. You are good dancers, too," the man says.

Lily and Sam wave goodbye. They go back to their moms. They tell them about their dance. Their moms are happy. They hug them.

Lily and Sam are happy. They had a good day. They like to dance. They like to make new friends.
<|end|>


