Sara likes to play quiz with her mom. Mom asks Sara questions and Sara tries to answer. Sara knows many things, like colors, animals and shapes. Mom is happy when Sara answers right.

One day, Sara and mom play quiz with Sara's friend Ben. Ben is deaf, so he cannot hear mom's questions. Ben uses his hands to talk. Sara knows some of his signs, but not all. Mom knows more signs, so she can ask Ben questions too.

Mom asks Sara, "What color is the sky?" Sara says, "Blue!" Mom asks Ben, "What color is the grass?" Ben signs, "Green!" Mom says, "Good job, both of you!"

Mom asks Sara, "What animal says meow?" Sara says, "Cat!" Mom asks Ben, "What animal says woof?" Ben signs, "Dog!" Mom says, "Very good, both of you!"

Mom asks Sara, "What shape has four sides and four corners?" Sara says, "Square!" Mom asks Ben, "What shape has three sides and three corners?" Ben signs, "Triangle!" Mom says, "Excellent, both of you!"

Sara and Ben are happy. They like to play quiz with mom. They learn new things and have fun. Mom is proud of Sara and Ben. She gives them hugs and smiles.
<|end|>


