Lily and Ben were playing in the bath. They had many toys: a duck, a boat, a frog and a cup. They made waves and splashed water. They had fun.

But then, Lily saw something scary. The water was going away. It was making a loud noise. It was going into a hole. The hole was the drain. Lily did not like the drain. She was afraid of it.

"Ben, Ben, help me!" Lily cried. "The water is going away! The drain will take our toys!"

Ben looked at the drain. He was not afraid of it. He knew it was just a hole. He had an idea.

"Don't worry, Lily. I have a plan. We can stop the water. We can use the cup. The cup is white. The cup is big. The cup can cover the hole. Watch me!"

Ben took the cup and filled it with water. He moved it quickly to the drain. He put it on top of the hole. He pressed it hard. The water stopped going away. The noise stopped. The toys were safe.

"Yay, Ben, you did it!" Lily cheered. "You are so smart! You succeeded!"

Ben smiled. He was happy. He helped his sister. He succeeded.

They hugged each other. They played with their toys. They forgot about the drain. They had fun.
<|end|>


