<|asst|>
Lily and Sam wanted to go to the zoo. They liked to see the animals and hear their sounds. They asked their mom and dad if they could go.

"Please, please, can we go to the zoo?" they said.

Mom and dad smiled and said, "Yes, we can go to the zoo today. But you have to be kind and listen to us. The zoo is a big place and we don't want you to get lost."

Lily and Sam nodded and said, "We will be kind and listen. Thank you, mom and dad."

They got in the car and drove to the zoo. They saw lions and tigers and bears. They saw monkeys and elephants and giraffes. They saw birds and fish and snakes. They had a lot of fun.

At the zoo, they met a nice lady who worked there. She showed them how to feed the goats and the sheep. She gave them some hay and said, "You can feed them, but be gentle. They are hungry, but they are also shy."

Lily and Sam took some hay and held it out to the goats and the sheep. The animals came closer and nibbled on the hay. They felt their soft fur and their wet noses. They said, "Hello, goats and sheep. You are so cute and kind."

The nice lady smiled and said, "You are very kind, too. You are good friends to the animals. Do you want to see more animals?"

Lily and Sam said, "Yes, please. We love the animals. Can we see the penguins next?"

The nice lady said, "Sure, follow me. The penguins are this way."

They followed the nice lady to the penguin pool. They saw the penguins swim and slide and waddle. They laughed and clapped and said, "The penguins are so funny and cool."

They had a wonderful day at the zoo. They thanked the nice lady and their mom and dad. They said, "The zoo is the best place ever. Can we come back again?"

Mom and dad said, "Maybe, someday. But now it's time to go home. You must be tired and hungry."

Lily and Sam said, "We are a little tired and hungry. But we are also happy and grateful. Thank you for taking us to the zoo."

They hugged their mom and dad and got in the car. They drove home and talked about their favorite animals. They fell asleep with smiles on their faces. They dreamed of the zoo.
<|end|>


