<|asst|>
Anna and Ben like to play outside. They look at the sky and see many clouds. Some clouds are white and fluffy. Some clouds are gray and thin. Some clouds are black and scary.

"Look, Anna, that cloud is very big and black. It looks like a monster!" Ben says.

Anna is not afraid. She has a ruler in her hand. She wants to measure the cloud. She holds the ruler up to the sky.

"I want to see how big the cloud is. Maybe it is bigger than our house. Maybe it is bigger than our school. Maybe it is bigger than the whole world!" Anna says.

Ben thinks Anna is silly. He laughs. He does not think the ruler can measure the cloud. The cloud is too far away. The cloud is moving. The cloud is changing shape.

"Anna, you cannot measure the cloud with a ruler. The ruler is too small. The cloud is too big. The cloud is not still. The cloud is not solid. You need a different tool to measure the cloud." Ben says.

Anna does not listen. She keeps trying to measure the cloud. She moves the ruler up and down. She moves the ruler left and right. She makes funny noises.

"Beep, beep, beep. I am measuring the cloud. The cloud is 100 feet long. The cloud is 50 feet wide. The cloud is 20 feet thick. The cloud is the biggest thing ever!" Anna says.

Ben shakes his head. He thinks Anna is making up numbers. He thinks Anna is pretending. He thinks Anna is having fun. He smiles. He joins Anna. He picks up a stick. He holds the stick up to the sky.

"Beep, beep, beep. I am measuring the cloud too. The cloud is 200 feet long. The cloud is 100 feet wide. The cloud is 40 feet thick. The cloud is bigger than the biggest thing ever!" Ben says.

Anna and Ben laugh. They measure the cloud together. They do not care if the cloud is black and scary. They do not care if the cloud is real or not. They do not care if the ruler and the stick are good tools or not. They only care about having fun. They are happy.
<|end|>


