Anna and Ben were playing in the living room. They liked to pretend they were in a castle, and the furniture was their throne and their bed. Anna wore a pretty dress and a crown. Ben wore a cape and a hat.

"Hello, my queen," Ben said, bowing to Anna. "I am your brave knight. I will protect you from the dragon."

"Hello, my knight," Anna said, smiling. "You are very kind. Where is the dragon?"

Ben pointed to the door. "He is outside. He is big and scary. He wants to take our castle and our furniture. But I will not let him."

Anna gasped. She was a little afraid of the dragon. She hugged Ben. "You are very strong. I trust you."

Ben hugged her back. He was a little afraid too, but he wanted to make Anna happy. He looked at the door. He saw something move. He recognized it. It was not the dragon. It was their dog, Spot.

"Look, Anna," Ben said, laughing. "It is not the dragon. It is Spot. He wants to play with us."

Anna looked too. She saw Spot. He was wagging his tail and barking. He was not big and scary. He was cute and friendly. She laughed too.

"Spot, you silly dog," Anna said, petting him. "You are not a dragon. You are our friend. Come and join our castle."

Spot licked their faces. He was happy. He liked to play with Anna and Ben. They liked to play with him. They had fun in their castle, with their furniture and their pretty clothes. They forgot about the dragon. They were not afraid. They were happy.
<|end|>


