<|asst|>
Sara was sad. She had a bad day at school. She did not listen to the teacher and she made a mess with the paints. The teacher gave her a lecture. She said Sara had to be more organized and follow the rules. Sara felt sorry and scared.

When Sara came home, she ran to her room and cried on her bed. She did not want to talk to anyone. She hugged her teddy bear and wished she could be a good girl.

Her mom knocked on the door and came in. She saw Sara crying and sat next to her. She gave her a hug and a kiss. She said, "I love you, Sara. I know you had a bad day, but you can do better tomorrow. Everyone makes mistakes sometimes. You just have to learn from them and try again. I'm here to help you and comfort you. You are a good girl, Sara. You are smart and kind and creative. You just have to be more organized and listen to the teacher. Can you do that, Sara?"

Sara nodded and wiped her tears. She said, "I'm sorry, mom. I love you too. I will try to be more organized and listen to the teacher. Thank you for comforting me, mom. You are the best mom ever."

Mom smiled and said, "You're welcome, Sara. You are the best daughter ever. Now, how about we go downstairs and have some cookies and milk? And maybe we can play a game or read a book together. Would you like that, Sara?"

Sara smiled and said, "Yes, mom. I would like that very much. Can I bring my teddy bear too?"

Mom said, "Of course, you can. Your teddy bear is always welcome. Come on, let's go. I'm proud of you, Sara."

Sara and mom got up and held hands. They went downstairs and had some cookies and milk. They played a game and read a book together. Sara felt happy and loved. She had a good day after all.
<|end|>


