<|asst|>
Lily liked to play with her toy parrot. She named it Polly and gave it hugs and kisses. She also liked to pretend that Polly could talk and say funny things.

One day, Lily saw a real parrot in the park. It was on a branch of a big tree. It had bright feathers and a long tail. Lily wanted to see it closer, so she ran to the tree and climbed up.

"Hello, parrot!" Lily said. "Do you want to be my friend?"

The parrot looked at Lily and said, "Hello, hello! I am stuck, stuck! Help me, help me!"

Lily saw that the parrot had a string around its foot. The string was tied to the branch. The parrot could not fly away.

"Oh, no!" Lily said. "Who did this to you? Don't worry, I will help you!"

Lily reached for the string and tried to untie it. It was hard and tight. She pulled and pulled, but it did not come off.

"Remove, remove!" the parrot said. "Please, remove!"

Lily had an idea. She took out her scissors from her pocket. She always carried them with her to cut paper and make crafts. She carefully cut the string with the scissors. The parrot was free!

"Thank you, thank you!" the parrot said. "You are kind, kind! You are my friend, friend!"

Lily was happy and proud. She had saved the parrot. She gave it a hug and a kiss.

"You are welcome, welcome!" Lily said. "I am glad, glad! You are my friend, friend!"

The parrot flapped its wings and flew to Lily's shoulder. It nuzzled her cheek and said, "I am grateful, grateful! You are the best, best!"

Lily smiled and laughed. She had a new friend. She named it Polly, too. She and Polly played and talked in the park. They had a lot of fun.
<|end|>


