<|asst|>
Lily was sad. She had a terrible day at school. Some big kids were mean to her and took her crayons. She ran home and cried in her room. She wanted her mom to comfort her, but mom was busy with the baby.

She looked around her room and saw her toy caterpillar. She loved her caterpillar. It was soft and green and had a smiley face. She hugged it and felt a little better. She whispered to it, "You are my best friend. You always make me happy."

The caterpillar seemed to hear her. It moved in her arms and made a small sound. Lily was surprised. She looked at it and saw that it was not a toy. It was a real caterpillar. It had crawled into her room through the window.

"Hello, little girl," the caterpillar said. "I'm sorry you had a terrible day. I came to comfort you. I like you. You are kind and gentle."

Lily smiled. She was not scared of the caterpillar. She was happy that it could talk. She said, "Hello, little caterpillar. Thank you for coming to comfort me. I like you too. You are soft and green and have a smiley face."

They became friends. They talked and played and laughed. Lily forgot about her terrible day. She felt happy and warm. The caterpillar comforted her and made her feel better. She gave it a kiss and said, "You are my best friend. You always make me happy."
<|end|>


