<|asst|>
Tim and Sam are friends. They like to play with toys and make things. One day, they find a big bottle of glue in the art room. They want to do something fun with it.

"Look, Tim, we can glue things together!" Sam says. He takes a furry ball and a paper cup and puts glue on them. Then he sticks them together. "Now I have a furry cup!"

"That is silly, Sam!" Tim says. He takes a furry hat and a paper plate and puts glue on them. Then he sticks them together. "Now I have a furry plate!"

They laugh and make more things with glue and furry things. They glue furry socks to a book, furry ears to a pencil, and furry tails to a chair. They have a lot of fun.

But then, the teacher comes in. She sees the mess they made. She is not happy.

"Tim and Sam, what did you do?" she asks. "You used all the glue and made a big mess! You glued furry things to everything! That is not nice!"

Tim and Sam feel bad. They did not mean to make the teacher angry. They say sorry to the teacher.

"We are sorry, teacher. We just wanted to do something fun. We did not know it was bad to glue furry things to everything," they say.

The teacher sighs. She tells them to help her clean up the mess. She says they can still do fun things, but they have to ask first and be careful with the glue.

Tim and Sam nod. They help the teacher clean up the mess. They take off the furry things from the things they glued. They put the glue and the furry things back in the art room. They say sorry again to the teacher.

The teacher smiles. She says it is okay. She says they are good boys. She says they can still play with the glue and the furry things, but only with her permission and supervision.

Tim and Sam are happy. They hug the teacher. They say thank you to the teacher. They learn a lesson. They do not glue furry things to everything anymore. They still have fun.
<|end|>


