<|asst|>
Anna and Ben are friends. They like to play in the park. One day, they find a lime on the ground. It is green and round.

"Look, a lime!" Anna says. "Do you like limes, Ben?"

Ben shakes his head. "No, I don't. They are sour and make my face funny."

Anna smiles. "I like limes. They are fresh and make my mouth happy."

She picks up the lime and peels it. She breaks it in half and gives one piece to Ben.

"Try it, Ben. Maybe you will like it this time."

Ben takes the lime piece and looks at it. He is not sure. He puts it in his mouth and bites it.

"Yuck!" Ben says. He spits out the lime and makes a face. "It is still sour and still makes my face funny."

Anna laughs. She eats her lime piece and enjoys it. She wipes her mouth with her hand.

"Sorry, Ben. I guess you don't like limes. Do you want to play something else?"

Ben nods. He throws away the lime piece and runs to the slide.

"Come on, Anna. Let's slide and swing and have fun."

Anna follows him. She throws away her lime peel and runs to the slide.

"Okay, Ben. Let's play and be happy."

They slide and swing and have fun. They are not quiet. They talk and laugh and shout. They are friends. They like different things, but they like each other.
<|end|>


