<|asst|>
Tom and Anna love to play soccer. They have a small pitch in their backyard, where they kick the ball and score goals. Sometimes, their dad joins them and teaches them new tricks.

One day, Tom and Anna are playing soccer when they see a big truck stop in front of their house. The truck has a powerful engine that makes a loud noise. The driver gets out and opens the back of the truck. He takes out a big box and carries it to their door.

"What is that?" Tom asks.

"Let's go see!" Anna says.

They run to the door and see their dad smiling. He opens the box and shows them what is inside. It is a new soccer goal, with a net and a frame.

"Wow!" Tom and Anna say.

"This is for you, kids. I know you love soccer, and I want to support your passion. Now you can practice and have more fun on your pitch." Dad says.

"Thank you, dad! You are the best!" Tom and Anna say.

They hug their dad and help him set up the new goal. Then they grab their ball and start playing again. They are very happy and excited. They take turns to shoot and defend. They cheer and clap for each other. They have a great time on their pitch, with their new goal and their powerful dad.
<|end|>


