<|asst|>
Jill liked to eat prunes. She liked how they were sweet and soft and good for her tummy. She always asked her mom for prunes when she was hungry.

One day, Jill saw a big bowl of prunes on the kitchen table. She ran to the table and grabbed a handful of prunes. She put them in her mouth and smiled.

"Jill, what are you doing?" her mom asked. She was surprised to see Jill eating so many prunes.

"I'm eating prunes, mom. They are yummy!" Jill said.

"Jill, you can't eat all the prunes. Those are for everyone. You have to share, honey." her mom said.

"No, mom. I want all the prunes. They are mine!" Jill said. She was angry and stubborn. She did not want to share. She demanded all the prunes.

"Jill, that's not nice. You have to be compassionate. Think about how other people feel. How would you feel if someone took all your toys?" her mom said.

Jill thought for a moment. She remembered how sad she was when her brother took her doll. She did not like that feeling. She looked at her mom and the bowl of prunes. She felt sorry.

"I'm sorry, mom. You are right. I have to be compassionate. I will share the prunes." Jill said.

She gave some prunes to her mom and some to her brother. They thanked her and smiled. Jill felt happy. She learned a lesson. She ate some prunes and gave some away. She was compassionate.
<|end|>


