<|asst|>
Tom likes to play with his computer. He can watch funny videos, draw pictures and learn new things. He has a big computer in his room and a small computer that he can take with him.

One day, Tom is playing with his small computer in the living room. He sees a red button on the side and wonders what it does. He pushes the button and the computer makes a loud noise. Then it stops working. The screen is black and nothing happens.

Tom is scared. He thinks he broke his computer. He runs to his mom and shows her the computer. He says, "Mom, I broke my computer! I pushed a button and it stopped. I'm sorry, Mom!"

Mom looks at the computer and smiles. She says, "Don't worry, Tom. You didn't break your computer. You just turned it off. The red button is the power button. It makes the computer go to sleep or wake up. See, if you push it again, the computer will work again."

She pushes the button and the computer turns on. The screen is bright and the computer makes a happy sound. Tom is happy too. He says, "Thank you, Mom! You are so helpful! You fixed my computer!"

Mom hugs Tom and says, "You're welcome, Tom. I'm glad you like your computer. But remember, be careful with the buttons. Some of them can do different things. If you don't know what they do, ask me or Dad first. OK?"

Tom nods and says, "OK, Mom. I will ask you or Dad. I love you, Mom!"

He kisses Mom and goes back to play with his computer. He is careful with the buttons and has fun. He learns new things and watches funny videos. He is a happy boy.
<|end|>


