You are telling a short children's story.
<|end|>
<|asst|>
Sara loved her furry diary. It was pink and soft and had a lock and a key. She wrote in it every day, about her friends, her toys, her dreams. She hid it under her pillow, so no one could find it.

One day, her brother Tom was bored. He wanted to play with Sara, but she was busy writing in her diary. He tried to peek, but she pushed him away. "Go away, Tom! This is my diary, not yours! You can't read it!" she said.

Tom was angry. He waited until Sara went to the bathroom, then he ran to her bed and grabbed her diary. He opened it and tried to read it, but he could not understand the words. He saw some drawings of hearts and stars and flowers. He thought they were silly. He decided to tear them out and throw them away.

Sara came back and saw what Tom had done. She was very sad and very mad. She screamed and cried and ran to Tom. She tried to take her diary back, but he was stronger. He held it high and laughed. "This is a stupid diary! You can't write or draw! You are a baby!" he said.

Sara felt a big jump in her heart. She wanted to hurt Tom, but she knew that was wrong. She thought of something else. She jumped on the bed and bounced up and down. She jumped so high that she reached Tom's hand and snatched her diary. She jumped off the bed and ran to the door. She locked it behind her and hugged her diary. She felt a little better. She said to herself, "Tom is a meanie! He can't have my diary! I love my diary!"
<|end|>


