Jill and Tom were twins who liked to play in the park. They saw a big oak tree with many leaves and acorns. They ran to the tree and tried to climb it.

"Look, Tom, I found a hole in the tree!" Jill said. She put her hand in the hole and felt something soft and furry. "I think there is an animal inside!"

Tom was curious and wanted to see the animal too. He reached for the hole, but Jill stopped him. "No, Tom, don't poke it! It might bite you!"

But Tom did not listen. He poked the hole with his finger and felt a sharp pain. He pulled his finger out and saw blood. He started to cry.

"Ow, ow, ow! It bit me! It bit me!" Tom shouted.

Jill felt sorry for Tom and hugged him. She saw a small gray head peek out of the hole. It was a squirrel. The squirrel looked at them with angry eyes and chattered its teeth.

"Go away, go away! This is my home! This is my acorn stash! I am a wealthy squirrel!" The squirrel said.

Jill and Tom were scared and ran away from the tree. They found their mom and dad and told them what happened. Their mom and dad cleaned Tom's finger and put a band-aid on it. They told them not to poke animals in the park.

Jill and Tom learned their lesson. They decided to play with the swings and the slides instead. They did not bother the squirrel or the oak tree anymore. They had fun and were happy.
<|end|>


