<|asst|>
Mia was anxious. She did not like the big school. She missed her mom and dad. She did not know the other kids. She did not understand the teacher's voice. It was loud and fast and hard.

One day, the teacher said they would play a game. She gave Mia a card with a picture of a cat. She said Mia had to find another kid with the same card and say hello. Mia looked around. She saw many kids with different cards. She did not see a cat.

She felt scared. She wanted to cry. She wanted to go home. She held her card tight and walked slowly. She hoped someone would help her.

Then, she saw a boy with a cat card. He was sitting on the floor, alone. He looked sad, too. Mia walked to him and showed him her card. He looked at her and smiled. He said, "Hi, I'm Ben. Do you like cats?"

Mia nodded. She liked cats. She said, "Hi, I'm Mia. I have a cat at home. Her name is Luna."

Ben said, "I have a cat, too. His name is Max. He is black and white."

Mia said, "Luna is gray and fluffy."

They started to talk about their cats. They forgot about the game. They forgot about the teacher. They forgot about their fears. They found a friend. They understood each other's voice. They felt happy.
<|end|>


