<|asst|>
Lily was a girl who liked to play with her dolls. She had many dolls, but her favorite was Anna. Anna had long hair, a pink dress and a big smile. Lily liked to talk to Anna and pretend they were friends.

One day, Lily saw a new girl in the park. She had short hair, a blue dress and a sad face. Lily wanted to make her happy, so she walked to her and said, "Hi, I am Lily. What is your name?"

The new girl looked at Lily and said, "I am Mia. I am new here. I have no friends."

Lily felt sorry for Mia. She said, "Do you want to be my friend? You can play with me and my dolls. I have many dolls, but Anna is my favorite. She is very interesting. She can sing and dance and tell stories."

Mia smiled and said, "Yes, I want to be your friend. Thank you for inviting me to play with you and your dolls. They look very nice. Can I hold Anna?"

Lily nodded and gave Anna to Mia. Mia held Anna and said, "Hello, Anna. You are very pretty. I like your hair and your dress. Can you sing for me?"

Anna nodded and sang a song for Mia. Mia clapped and said, "Wow, you are very good. Can you dance for me?"

Anna nodded and danced for Mia. Mia laughed and said, "Wow, you are very fun. Can you tell me a story?"

Anna nodded and told Mia a story about a princess and a dragon. Mia listened and said, "Wow, you are very smart. I like your story."

Lily watched Mia and Anna and felt happy. She said, "I am glad you like Anna. She is my best doll. But you are my best friend. I like you very much."

Mia hugged Lily and said, "I like you very much too. You are very kind. You are my best friend. Thank you for sharing Anna with me."

Lily and Mia played with Anna and the other dolls for a long time. They had a lot of fun. They did not notice that a bug was crawling on Lily's arm. The bug bit Lily and made her arm itch. Lily scratched her arm and said, "Ouch, something bit me. My arm is itching. It hurts."

Mia saw the bug and said, "Oh no, it is a bad bug. It made you itch. Let me help you. I have a cream for itches. My mom gave it to me. It makes itches go away."

Mia took out a small tube of cream from her pocket and put some on Lily's arm. She rubbed it gently and said, "There, it will be better soon. The cream is magic. It makes the bug bite disappear."

Lily felt the cream on her arm and said, "Thank you, Mia. You are very nice. The cream feels good. It makes the itch stop. The bug bite is gone."

Mia smiled and said, "You are welcome, Lily. I am happy to help you. You are my friend. Friends help each other."

Lily and Mia hugged each other and said, "We are friends. We are happy. We love Anna. We love each other."

The end.
<|end|>


