<|asst|>
Lily was a naughty girl. She did not like to eat her dinner. She only liked to eat cake and candy. She hid her dinner under her bed and told her mom she was full.

"Good girl, Lily. You ate all your dinner. Now you can have some cake," her mom said.

Lily was happy. She ran to the kitchen and took a big piece of cake. She ate it very fast. It was sweet and yummy. She wanted more.

She went back to the kitchen and saw another cake on the table. It was a big cake with pink frosting and sprinkles. It looked very pretty. Lily thought it was for her. She did not know it was for her mom's birthday.

She took a big bite of the cake. But it did not taste good. It tasted bad. It tasted like soap and dirt. Lily spat it out. She felt sick.

She heard her mom coming. She was scared. She ran to her bed and hid under the blanket.

Her mom came into her room. She saw the cake on the table. She saw the bite mark. She saw the dinner under the bed. She was angry.

"Lily, what did you do? You were very naughty. You did not eat your dinner. You ate my birthday cake. And you made a big mess. Why did you do that?" her mom asked.

Lily did not answer. She was sorry. She cried.

Her mom sighed. She was sad. She loved Lily, but she did not like her behavior.

She hugged Lily and said, "Lily, I love you, but you have to be a good girl. You have to eat your dinner. You have to ask before you take something. You have to say sorry when you do something wrong. Do you understand?"

Lily nodded. She said, "I'm sorry, mom. I love you too. I won't be naughty again. Can I have some water? The cake tasted bad."

Her mom smiled. She said, "Yes, you can have some water. And maybe a little piece of cake later. But first, you have to clean up your mess. And then you have to go to bed. It's late."

Lily agreed. She helped her mom clean up. She drank some water. She gave her mom a kiss. She went to bed. She dreamed of nice things. She hoped her mom would have a happy birthday.
<|end|>


