<|asst|>
Tom and Lily were best friends. They liked to play together in the park. One day, they saw a big red balloon tied to a bench. It looked very pretty and shiny.

"Wow, look at that balloon!" Tom said. "I want it!"

"Me too!" Lily said. "But it belongs to someone else. We can't take it."

Tom did not listen. He ran to the bench and untied the balloon. He held it in his hand and smiled. "Now it's mine!"

Lily was sad and angry. She followed Tom and said, "That's not fair! You stole the balloon! Give it back!"

Tom shook his head. He did not want to share. He ran away with the balloon. Lily ran after him. She tried to catch him, but he was too fast.

They ran across the park, past the swings and the slide and the sandbox. They did not see the big tree in front of them. Tom bumped into the tree and dropped the balloon. The balloon flew up in the air and popped. It made a loud noise.

Tom and Lily were both scared and surprised. They looked at the balloon pieces on the ground. They felt sorry for what they did.

They hugged each other and said, "I'm sorry. I was mean. I was silly."

They decided to be friends again. They picked up the balloon pieces and threw them in the trash. They went back to the bench and found a new toy. It was a funny memory game with cards and pictures. They played with it and had fun. They learned to share and be kind. They were happy.
<|end|>


