<|asst|>
Tom and Lily went to the beach with Mom and Dad. They liked to play in the sand and look for shells. They also liked to watch the big waves that came and went.

"Can we go in the water, Mom?" Lily asked.

"Not today, sweetie. The waves are too strong and dangerous. You might get hurt," Mom said.

"But I want to swim and splash," Lily said. She was sad.

Tom had an idea. He took Lily's hand and said, "Come on, Lily. Let's go to the rocks. We can still have fun there."

They ran to the rocks and climbed on them. They saw crabs and starfish and seaweed. They also saw a big seagull that flew over them.

"Hello, seagull," Tom said. "You are very wise. You know how to fly and find food. Can you tell us a secret?"

The seagull looked at them and made a loud noise. Tom and Lily laughed.

"Maybe he is saying hello back," Lily said.

"Or maybe he is saying that we are brave and smart for staying away from the waves," Tom said.

They smiled and waved at the seagull. They hoped he would come back and visit them again. They had a lot of fun on the rocks. They forgot about the water and the waves. They were happy.
<|end|>


