Lily was a clever girl who liked to help her mom. One day, she saw her mom's razor on the sink. She thought it was a toy and wanted to play with it. She picked it up and ran to her room.

"Look, mom, I have a toy!" she shouted.

"No, Lily, that's not a toy, that's a razor!" her mom said, following her. "It's sharp and can hurt you. Give it to me, please."

But Lily did not listen. She wanted to see what the razor could do. She tried to cut her doll's hair with it, but it did not work. She tried to cut her blanket, but it did not work. She tried to cut her book, but it did not work. She got angry and threw the razor on the floor.

CRACK!

The razor broke into pieces. Lily was scared. She saw blood on her hand. She had cut herself with the razor. She started to cry.

"Mom, mom, I'm sorry, I'm sorry!" she sobbed.

Her mom hugged her and took her to the bathroom. She washed her hand and put a band-aid on it. She threw away the broken razor and told Lily to never touch it again.

"It's okay, Lily, you're not in trouble, but you have to be careful," her mom said. "Razors are not toys, they are for grown-ups. Next time, ask me before you take something that is not yours, okay?"

"Okay, mom, I'm sorry, I love you," Lily said.

"I love you too, Lily, you're a clever girl, but sometimes you need to listen more," her mom said. "Now, let's go and read a book together, how about that?"

Lily nodded and smiled. She learned her lesson and never touched a razor again. She and her mom read a book and had a happy day.
<|end|>


