Anna and Ben like to play with their cart. It is a big cart with four wheels and a handle. They can put toys and books and snacks in the cart and pull it around the yard. They have a lot of fun with their cart.

One day, they are playing with their cart when they hear a loud snap. One of the wheels breaks off the cart and rolls away. The cart falls to the ground and spills everything. Anna and Ben are sad and scared. They do not know what to do.

They run to their mom and show her the broken cart. Mom looks at the cart and says, "Don't worry, we can repair it. We just need some glue and a new wheel. Do you want to help me?"

Anna and Ben nod and follow mom to the garage. Mom finds some glue and a wheel that looks like the original one. She puts some glue on the wheel and sticks it to the cart. She holds it for a while until it is dry. Then she turns the cart over and says, "There, it is fixed. Good as new."

Anna and Ben are happy and hug mom. They thank her for repairing their cart. They take their cart back to the yard and put their toys and books and snacks in it. They pull it around and laugh and smile. They love their cart. It is their favorite toy.
<|end|>


