Tim and Sam are friends. They like to play outside. One day, they see a big hill near their house. They want to climb the hill and see what is on the other side.

They hold hands and walk up the hill. They are not scared. They are brave. They see many things on the hill. They see flowers, bugs, rocks, and birds. They are happy.

But when they reach the top of the hill, they hear a loud roar. They see a big bear. The bear is angry. The bear wants to scare them. The bear runs towards them.

Tim and Sam are scared. They scream and run down the hill. They do not look back. They run as fast as they can. They run to their house. They slam the door and lock it.

They hug each other and cry. They are safe. They are glad. They do not want to play outside anymore. They want to stay inside and be sleepy. They say to each other:

"Let's never go to the hill again. The hill is bad. The bear is mean. We are lucky. We are friends."
<|end|>


