Tom and Lily wanted to go to the park. They liked to play on the swings and the slide. But Mom said they had to eat lunch first. She made them sandwiches and juice.

"Can we have some yogurt too?" Lily asked. Mom opened the refrigerator and took out a small cup of yogurt. She gave it to Lily and said, "Here you go, sweetie. But be careful, it might be sour. It has been in the refrigerator for a long time."

Lily opened the yogurt and took a big spoonful. She put it in her mouth and made a funny face. "Ew, this is sour!" she said. "It tastes bad!"

Tom laughed and said, "Let me try!" He took the yogurt from Lily and ate some too. He also made a funny face and said, "Yuck, this is sour! It hurts my tongue!"

Mom smiled and said, "I'm sorry, kids. I forgot to check the date on the yogurt. It is old and spoiled. You don't have to eat it. Throw it in the trash and I'll give you something else."

Tom and Lily threw the yogurt in the trash and rinsed their mouths with water. Mom gave them some cookies and milk instead. They ate them happily and said, "Thank you, Mom. These are yummy!"

Mom said, "You're welcome, kids. Now you can go to the park. But don't forget to brush your teeth when you come back."

Tom and Lily nodded and ran to the door. They put on their shoes and jackets and said, "Bye, Mom. We love you!"

Mom said, "Bye, kids. I love you too. Have fun at the park!"
<|end|>


