Lily and Ben were best friends. They liked to play with dolls and cars and books. They always shared their toys and snacks. They said they wanted to get married when they grew up.

One day, they went to the park with their moms. They saw a big cake and balloons and flowers. They saw a man and a woman in pretty clothes. They were getting married. Lily and Ben wanted to see.

"Can we go and watch?" Lily asked her mom.

"Sure, but we have to be quiet and respectful," her mom said. "They are having a special moment."

Lily and Ben nodded. They followed their moms to the cake and the flowers. They saw the man and the woman say nice things to each other and kiss. They saw them put rings on their fingers. They saw them smile and hug.

Lily and Ben thought it was beautiful. They clapped their hands and cheered.

"Yay, they are married!" Lily said.

"Like us!" Ben said.

They hugged each other and pretended to kiss.

But not everyone was happy. A boy and a girl who were also at the park saw Lily and Ben. They did not like them. They thought they were silly and gross. They decided to tease them.

"Hey, look at those babies!" the boy said. "They think they are married!"

"Yeah, they are so dumb!" the girl said. "They don't know anything about marriage!"

They laughed and pointed at Lily and Ben. They made faces and noises. They tried to take their toys and snacks.

Lily and Ben felt sad and angry. They did not like the boy and the girl. They did not like their mean words and actions. They wanted them to go away.

They complained to their moms.

"Mom, they are being mean to us!" Lily said.

"Mom, they are ruining our fun!" Ben said.

Their moms were helpful. They saw the boy and the girl and their bad behavior. They told them to stop and apologize. They told them to be nice and respectful. They told them to leave Lily and Ben alone.

The boy and the girl felt ashamed and scared. They said sorry and ran away. They did not bother Lily and Ben anymore.

Lily and Ben felt happy and safe. They thanked their moms and hugged them. They went back to their cake and their flowers. They went back to their dolls and their cars and their books. They went back to their play and their pretend marriage.

They were best friends. They liked each other very much. They said they wanted to stay married forever.
<|end|>


