Lily and Max were playing in the park with their mom. They saw a big fountain with water that went up and down. Lily wanted to go closer and see the water. Max followed her, but he was careful not to get wet.

"Look, Max, there are coins in the water!" Lily said. "Why are they there?"

Mom explained that some people throw coins in the fountain and make a wish. She said it was a fun thing to do, but they should not take the coins out.

Lily nodded, but she was curious. She wanted to make a wish too. She reached into her pocket and found a shiny coin. She threw it in the fountain and said, "I wish for a fancy dress!"

Max saw what Lily did and smiled. He also wanted to make a wish. He reached into his pocket and found his wallet. He opened it and saw a dollar bill. He thought it was a lot of money. He threw it in the fountain and said, "I wish for a big truck!"

Mom saw what Max did and gasped. She ran to the fountain and tried to get the wallet back. But the water was too deep and too fast. She got soaked and could not find the wallet.

"Oh, Max, why did you do that?" Mom asked. "That was your wallet, not a coin. You need it to buy things."

Max looked sad. He did not know he made a mistake. He said, "I'm sorry, Mom. I wanted to make a wish like Lily. I did not know the wallet was important."

Mom hugged Max and said, "It's okay, Max. I know you did not mean to. But next time, ask me before you throw anything in the fountain. And maybe we can find a cheaper way to make wishes."

Lily and Max nodded. They learned their lesson. They still liked the fountain, but they did not throw anything else in it. They played with the water and had fun. They hoped their wishes would come true.
<|end|>


