Mia and Leo were youth who liked to play in the park. They liked to spring on the swings, slide on the slides, and run on the grass. One day, they saw a big dog in the park. The dog was brown and furry, and had a long tail. Mia and Leo wanted to pet the dog, but the dog did not want to be petted.

"Come here, doggy!" Mia called. She ran towards the dog, but the dog ran away. Mia was frustrated. She wanted to be friends with the dog.

"Maybe he is scared," Leo said. He walked slowly towards the dog, and held out his hand. The dog sniffed his hand, but then barked and ran away. Leo was frustrated too. He wanted to play with the dog.

The dog ran to the other side of the park, where there was a fence. He jumped over the fence, and disappeared. Mia and Leo followed him, but they could not jump over the fence. They were too small.

"Where did he go?" Mia asked.

"I don't know," Leo said. "Maybe he lives there."

They looked at the fence, and felt sad. They wished they could see the dog again.

"Let's go back to the swings," Mia said. "Maybe he will come back later."

"Okay," Leo said. They walked back to the swings, and tried to have fun. But they still missed the dog. They hoped he was happy, wherever he was.
<|end|>


