Anna liked to organize her toys. She had a big box with many colors and shapes. She put the red toys in one corner, the blue toys in another, and so on. She felt happy when she saw her box neat and pretty.

One day, a lady came to visit Anna and her mom. The lady was pale and had a big bag. She smiled at Anna and said, "Hello, little girl. I am your mom's friend. Can I see your toys?"

Anna nodded and showed her the box. The lady looked at the toys and said, "Wow, you are very good at organizing. You have a lot of fun toys. Can I play with you?"

Anna was shy, but she liked the lady. She said, "Yes, you can play with me. What do you want to play?"

The lady opened her bag and took out a book. She said, "I have a book with stories and pictures. Do you like stories?"

Anna loved stories. She said, "Yes, I like stories. Can you read me one?"

The lady smiled and said, "Of course. Come, sit with me on the couch. We can read and play together."

Anna and the lady sat on the couch and opened the book. Anna saw a picture of a princess and a dragon. She said, "Wow, what is this story about?"

The lady said, "This story is about a brave princess who saves a dragon from a mean king. Do you want to hear it?"

Anna said, "Yes, please. I want to hear it."

The lady began to read the story. Anna listened and looked at the pictures. She felt happy and curious. She asked the lady many questions and the lady answered them. They had a lot of fun. Anna liked the lady and the book. She thought, "This is a nice day. I have a new friend and a new story."
<|end|>


