Tom had a rare toy. It was a bear with a red button on its chest. When he pressed the button, the bear would say "I love you, Tom". Tom liked to hug the bear and hear its voice. He took the bear everywhere with him.

One day, Tom and his mom went to the park. Tom played with his bear on the swings and the slide. He was very happy. But then, he saw a big dog running towards him. The dog barked and jumped on Tom. It grabbed the bear with its teeth and shook it hard. Tom was scared and cried. He ran to his mom and said "Mom, help! The dog has my bear!"

His mom ran to the dog and shouted "No, bad dog! Drop the bear!" The dog dropped the bear and ran away. Tom's mom picked up the bear and gave it to Tom. Tom hugged the bear and pressed the button. But the bear did not say anything. Tom looked at the bear and saw that the button was broken. He was very sad and said "Mom, the bear is broken. It can't talk to me anymore."

His mom looked at the button and said "Don't worry, Tom. We can repair the bear. We just need some thread and a needle. Come on, let's go home and fix it." She took Tom and the bear and walked to the car.

At home, his mom got some thread and a needle. She sewed the button back on the bear's chest. She gave the bear to Tom and said "There, it's done. Try it now." Tom pressed the button and heard the bear say "I love you, Tom". He smiled and said "I love you, too, bear. Thank you, mom, for repairing it." He hugged the bear and his mom and felt very happy.
<|end|>


