Lily and Ben are friends. They like to play in the park. One day, they see a new boy in the park. He has a big bike and a shiny medal.

"Who is he?" Lily asks Ben.

"I don't know. Let's go and say hello," Ben says.

They run to the new boy and smile.

"Hi, I'm Lily and this is Ben. We are friends. What is your name?" Lily says.

"Hi, I'm Max. I'm new here. I just moved with my mom and dad. This is my bike and this is my medal. I won it in a race," Max says.

"Wow, your bike is cool and your medal is shiny. Can we see it?" Ben says.

"Sure, here you go. But be careful, it's heavy," Max says. He gives them his medal.

Lily and Ben hold the medal and look at it. It has a picture of a bike and some words.

"What does it say?" Lily asks.

"It says 'First Place in the Bike Challenge'. I had to ride my bike very fast and do some tricks. It was fun but also dangerous. I fell down once and hurt my knee," Max says.

"Ouch, that sounds scary. Are you okay?" Ben asks.

"I'm okay. It was just a scratch. My mom put a band-aid on it. Do you want to see?" Max says.

He lifts his pant leg and shows them his band-aid. It has a star on it.

"Wow, that's a nice band-aid. You are brave," Lily says.

"Thank you. You are nice. Do you want to be my friends?" Max says.

"Yes, we want to be your friends. We can play together in the park. Do you want to try the slide?" Ben says.

"Yes, I love the slide. Let's go," Max says.

They give back his medal and run to the slide. They take turns sliding down and laughing. They have a lot of fun. They are happy. They are friends.
<|end|>


