Lily and her mom went to a big restaurant for lunch. Lily liked the restaurant because it had many colors and pictures on the walls. She also liked the food, especially the fries and the juice.

When they finished eating, Lily saw a man with a funny hat and a big smile. He was the chef, and he was making food in the kitchen. Lily wanted to say hello to him, so she asked her mom.

"Mom, can I wave to the chef?" Lily said.

"Sure, honey, you can wave to the chef. He likes to see happy customers," her mom said.

Lily got up from her chair and walked to the window where she could see the chef. She waved her hand and said, "Hi, chef! Thank you for the food!"

The chef saw Lily and waved back. He said, "Hi, little girl! You're welcome for the food! I'm glad you liked it!"

Lily smiled and ran back to her mom. She gave her mom a hug and said, "I like the chef, mom. He is nice and funny."

"I like him too, Lily. He is a good chef and a good friend," her mom said.

They paid for their lunch and left the restaurant. Lily waved to the chef again and said, "Bye, chef! See you soon!"

The chef waved to Lily and said, "Bye, little girl! See you soon!"
