Lily was hungry. She wanted to eat some eggs. She saw a big pot on the stove. She thought the eggs were in the pot. She climbed on a chair and reached for the pot.

"Stop, Lily!" Mom shouted. "The stove is hot! You will get hurt!"

Lily was scared. She let go of the pot. She fell off the chair. She started to cry.

Mom ran to Lily. She hugged her and checked her hands. "Are you okay, Lily?" Mom asked. "Did you touch the stove?"

Lily shook her head. "No, Mom," she said. "I wanted eggs."

Mom smiled. "I know, Lily. But the eggs are not in the pot. The pot has water. I was going to make pasta. The eggs are in the fridge. Come, I will make you some eggs. But first, we need to cool your hands. Let's put them under the tap."

Mom took Lily to the sink. She turned on the tap. She held Lily's hands under the cool water. Lily felt better. She stopped crying.

"Thank you, Mom," Lily said. "I'm sorry I worried you."

Mom kissed Lily's head. "It's okay, Lily. I love you. But next time, please ask me before you touch the stove. It can be very dangerous. Do you understand?"

Lily nodded. "Yes, Mom. I understand. Can we have eggs now?"

Mom laughed. "Yes, Lily. We can have eggs now. Let's go to the kitchen and make some together. But be careful, okay?"

Lily smiled. "Okay, Mom. I will be careful. I love you."

They went to the kitchen. Mom cracked some eggs in a bowl. Lily whisked them with a fork. Mom poured them in a pan. Lily watched them sizzle. Mom flipped them with a spatula. Lily clapped her hands. Mom put them on a plate. Lily sprinkled some cheese on them. Mom cut them into pieces. Lily ate them with a spoon. They were yummy.

Lily was happy. She had eggs. She had Mom. She did not worry. She was cool.
<|end|>


