Sara and Ben love to go to the zoo with Mom and Dad. They like to see the big and small animals, and hear the noises they make. They also like to eat ice cream and popcorn at the zoo.

One day, they went to the zoo and saw a new animal. It was a monkey with a long tail and brown fur. It was very funny and playful. It made Sara and Ben laugh when it swung from the trees and threw bananas at the other monkeys.

"Look, Mom, look, Dad, the monkey is so cheerful!" Sara said.

"Yes, he is, honey. He likes to have fun and make friends," Mom said.

"Can we play with him, Dad? Can we give him a banana?" Ben asked.

"Well, we can't go inside his cage, son. It's locked to keep him and us safe. But we can wave at him and talk to him from here," Dad said.

Sara and Ben nodded and waved at the monkey. The monkey waved back and made a funny face. He seemed to like them too. He grabbed a banana and peeled it. Then he threw the peel at Sara and Ben.

"Hey, that's not nice!" Sara said.

But she was not angry. She was just surprised. She picked up the peel and threw it back at the monkey. The monkey caught it and laughed. He threw another peel at Ben. Ben threw it back too. They started a game of catch with the banana peels.

Mom and Dad smiled and watched them play. They were happy to see Sara and Ben and the monkey having fun. They took a picture of them with their phone. They wanted to remember this cheerful day at the zoo.
<|end|>


