Anna and Ben are playing in the garden. They have a ball and a bike. They throw the ball and ride the bike. They have fun.

But then, Ben falls off the bike. He hurts his knee. He cries. Anna runs to him. She sees the bike. The bike is broken. The wheel is off. She is sad.

"Ben, are you OK?" Anna asks.

"Ow, ow, ow! My knee!" Ben says.

Anna hugs him. She says, "I'm sorry, Ben. It was an accident. Do you want a band-aid?"

Ben nods. He says, "Yes, please. And a hug."

Anna and Ben go inside. Mom sees them. She says, "What happened?"

Anna says, "Ben fell off the bike. The bike is broken. We're sorry, Mom."

Mom says, "Don't worry, sweeties. I'm glad you're OK. Let me look at your knee, Ben. I have a band-aid for you. And a hug."

Mom gives Ben a band-aid and a hug. She says, "The bike can be fixed. Maybe Dad can fix it tomorrow. Now, it's evening. Time for dinner and bed."

Anna and Ben say, "OK, Mom. Thank you."

They wash their hands and eat dinner. They brush their teeth and put on pajamas. They say good night to Mom and Dad. They go to bed.

They dream of playing in the garden again. With the ball and the bike. And each other.
