One day, Tom and Lily went to the park with their mom. They saw an enormous tree with many branches and leaves. Tom wanted to climb the tree, but Lily was scared.

"Come on, Lily, it will be fun!" Tom said. "Look, there is a big hole in the tree. Maybe we can find something inside."

"No, Tom, it is too high and too dangerous. What if you fall and hurt yourself?" Lily said. "And what if there is a sharp animal in the hole that bites you?"

Tom did not listen to Lily. He ran to the tree and started to climb. He reached the hole and looked inside. He saw something shiny and round. He reached his hand to grab it.

But then he heard a loud crack. The branch he was standing on broke and he fell to the ground. He dropped the shiny thing and it broke too. It was a glass ball.

Tom cried and cried. He had a big bump on his head and a cut on his hand. Lily ran to him and hugged him. She was sorry for him.

Mom heard the noise and came to see what happened. She saw Tom and Lily and the broken glass ball. She was angry and worried.

"Tom, what have you done? You could have been hurt very badly. And you broke someone's glass ball. That was not nice. You have to say sorry and be more careful next time." Mom said.

Tom nodded and said sorry. He felt bad for being naughty and hurting himself and the glass ball. He hugged Mom and Lily and said he loved them. He learned his lesson. He would not climb the tree again. He would play with Lily and have fun.
