Sara and Ben are twins. They like to play with their toys and watch TV. One day, they see a big truck on TV. The truck has a lot of letters and pictures on it. It is a news truck. The news truck goes to different places and tells people what is happening.

"Look, Ben, a news truck!" Sara says. "I want to see where it goes."

"Me too," Ben says. "Maybe it goes to the zoo or the park."

They watch the TV and wait for the news truck to show them something fun. But the news truck does not go to the zoo or the park. It goes to a house that is on fire. The house is very hot and has a lot of smoke. The news truck shows the firemen who are trying to put out the fire. The firemen have hoses and helmets and trucks.

"Oh no, that is bad," Sara says. "The house is burning. I hope no one is inside."

"Me too," Ben says. "That is scary."

They watch the TV and hope the firemen can save the house. Then they see something that makes them gasp. They see a dog running out of the house. The dog is black and white and has a red collar. The dog looks scared and dirty.

"Spot!" Sara and Ben shout at the same time. They recognize the dog. It is their dog. They lost him a week ago when he ran away from their yard. They have been looking for him everywhere. They miss him very much.

"Spot, Spot, it is us!" they say to the TV. "We love you, Spot!"

The news truck shows the firemen who see the dog. They pick him up and give him water and a blanket. They say he is a brave dog who escaped the fire. They say they will find his owners and bring him back to them.

Sara and Ben are very happy. They hug each other and smile. They can't wait to see Spot again. They know he is their dog and they are his family. They thank the news truck and the firemen for saving him. They say they have the best news ever.
