Ben and Mia like to create things with lumber. They have a big box of lumber pieces that their dad gave them. They can make houses, cars, animals, and anything they want.

One day, they decide to create a rocket. They find a long piece of lumber for the body, and four small pieces for the legs. They also find a cone-shaped piece for the nose, and a round piece for the window. They use glue and tape to stick them together.

"Look at our rocket!" Ben says. "It is so big and strong!"

"Yes, and it is bright too!" Mia says. "We can paint it with red and yellow and blue!"

They get their paint and brushes, and start to color their rocket. They make stripes and dots and stars on it. They are very happy with their work.

"Are you ready to fly to the moon?" Ben asks Mia.

"Yes, I am!" Mia says. "Let's go inside the rocket and count to ten!"

They climb inside the rocket, and pretend to buckle their seat belts. They look out the window, and imagine they see the sky and the stars.

"Ten, nine, eight, seven, six, five, four, three, two, one, blast off!" they shout together.

They make zooming and whooshing noises, and pretend their rocket is flying fast and high. They have a lot of fun, and feel like they are really in space. They are very proud of their rocket, and of their ability to create.
<|end|>


