<|asst|>
Anna and Ben were twins who liked to play in the forest. They were eager to find new things and have fun. One day, they saw a big mushroom with red spots on it. It looked like a hat.

"Wow, look at that mushroom!" Anna said. "Can we pick it?"

"I don't know," Ben said. "Maybe it is not good to eat. Maybe it is bad."

They went closer to the mushroom and touched it. It felt soft and wet. They smelled it. It smelled like dirt and grass.

"Maybe we can ask Mommy if we can eat it," Anna said. "She knows a lot about food."

"Okay," Ben said. "But how can we take it home? It is too big for our hands."

They looked around and saw a big leaf on the ground. They put the mushroom on the leaf and lifted it together. It was heavy, but they were strong.

They walked back to their house, holding the leaf with the mushroom. They were happy and proud of their find.

When they got home, they saw Mommy in the kitchen. She was making soup for lunch.

"Mommy, Mommy, look what we found!" Anna said.

"A mushroom!" Ben said.

They showed Mommy the mushroom on the leaf. Mommy looked surprised and scared.

"Oh, no, no, no!" Mommy said. "That is a very bad mushroom! It can make you very sick! You must never eat it or touch it!"

She took the leaf with the mushroom and threw it in the trash. She washed Anna and Ben's hands with soap and water. She hugged them and kissed them.

"I'm so glad you are okay," Mommy said. "You are very lucky. God was watching over you. You should pray and thank Him for keeping you safe."

Anna and Ben nodded. They did not understand why the mushroom was bad, but they trusted Mommy. They prayed and thanked God for their Mommy and their life. They ate the soup and forgot about the mushroom. They decided to play with their toys instead.
<|end|>


