<|asst|>
Lily and Sam were friends who liked to play outside. They had a wagon that they used to carry their toys and books. One day, a new boy named Ben moved in next door. He saw the wagon and wanted to play with it.

"Can I borrow your wagon?" he asked Lily and Sam.

"Sure, you can borrow it, but you have to be nice and share," Lily said.

Sam nodded and smiled. He liked to make new friends.

Ben took the wagon and put his own toys and books in it. He did not share with Lily and Sam. He pulled the wagon around the yard and ignored them. He was ignorant and rude.

Lily and Sam felt sad and angry. They wanted their wagon back.

"Hey, Ben, can we have our wagon back?" Sam asked.

"No, it's mine now. Go away," Ben said.

He pushed Sam and made him fall. Lily ran to help Sam and shouted at Ben.

"That's not fair! You can't keep our wagon! You have to give it back!" she said.

Ben laughed and ran away with the wagon. He did not care about Lily and Sam. He was a bad boy.

Lily and Sam cried and hugged each other. They wished Ben would be nice and return their wagon. They hoped he would learn to be a good friend.
<|end|>


