<|asst|>
Sara and Ben are friends. They like to play in the park. One day, they see a big dog. The dog is brown and furry. It has a long tail and sharp teeth.

"Wow, look at the dog!" Sara says. "It is so big and cute. I want to pet it."

"No, Sara, don't!" Ben says. "The dog is bad. It can bite you. Stay away from it."

But Sara does not listen. She runs to the dog and tries to hug it. The dog does not like it. It growls and snaps at Sara. Sara is scared. She cries and runs back to Ben.

"Are you okay, Sara?" Ben asks. He is worried. He sees a red mark on Sara's arm. The dog bit her.

"It hurts, Ben. The dog was bad. It hurt me." Sara says. She is sad and angry.

"I'm sorry, Sara. I told you to stay away from it. Come, let's go to the nurse. She can help you." Ben says. He takes Sara's hand and leads her to the nurse's office.

The nurse is kind. She cleans Sara's wound and puts a band-aid on it. She gives Sara a lollipop and a hug.

"You were brave, Sara. The dog was bad, but you are good. You will be fine." The nurse says.

"Thank you, nurse. You are nice." Sara says. She smiles a little.

Ben smiles too. He is glad Sara is okay. He gives her a kiss on the cheek.

"You are my friend, Sara. I care about you." Ben says.

"You are my friend too, Ben. I love you." Sara says.

They hug and hold hands. They are happy. They have learned a lesson. They will never go near a bad dog again. They will always listen to each other. They will always be friends.
<|end|>


