<|asst|>
Lily loved her pony, Max. He was brown and soft and had a long tail. Lily liked to brush his hair and feed him carrots. Sometimes, she rode on his back and he took her around the farm.

But Max was also stubborn. He did not like to do what Lily said. He wanted to go where he liked and eat what he liked. He did not listen to Lily or her dad. He made Lily angry and sad.

One day, Lily and Max went for a ride. Lily wanted to go to the pond, but Max wanted to go to the apple tree. He pulled and pulled on the rope, and Lily pulled and pulled back. They both shouted.

"Max, stop! You are a bad pony! You have to do what I say!" Lily said.

"Neigh! Neigh! I want apples! You are a mean girl! You have to do what I say!" Max said.

They fought and fought, until they both fell off. Lily hurt her knee and Max hurt his nose. They both cried.

Lily's dad heard them and came to help. He picked up Lily and hugged her. He checked Max and gave him a pat. He said, "Lily, Max, you have to be nice to each other. You are friends, not enemies. You have to share and take turns. Do you remember when you first met?"

Lily and Max nodded. They remembered. Lily remembered how she saw Max in the barn and how he licked her hand. Max remembered how he saw Lily in the field and how she gave him a carrot. They remembered how they played and laughed and cuddled.

They looked at each other and felt sorry. They said, "I'm sorry, Lily/Max. You are a good girl/pony. I like you. Can we be friends again?"

They hugged and kissed and said, "Yes, we can. Let's go to the pond and the apple tree together. We can have fun and be happy."

Lily and Max smiled and got back on. They followed Lily's dad to the pond and the apple tree. They shared the water and the apples. They were nice to each other. They were friends.
<|end|>


