<|asst|>
Lily liked to look at the books on the bookcase. She liked the pictures and the colors. She wanted to read the words, but they were too hard. She asked her mom to read to her.

"Mom, can you read me a story?" Lily said.

"Sure, honey. Which one do you want?" Mom said.

Lily pointed to a book with a princess on the cover. She liked princesses. They had pretty dresses and crowns.

Mom took the book and opened it. She read to Lily about the princess who lived in a big castle. She was very rich and had many things. But she was not happy. She wanted to have friends and play outside.

Lily listened to the story. She felt sorry for the princess. She did not want to be rich and lonely. She wanted to have fun and laugh.

"Mom, can the princess change?" Lily asked.

"What do you mean, change?" Mom said.

"Can she be like me? Can she go to the park and play with other kids? Can she wear jeans and sneakers?" Lily said.

Mom smiled. She hugged Lily and said, "Yes, she can. The princess can change if she wants to. She can choose to be happy and free. She can make her own story."

Lily smiled too. She liked that idea. She said, "Mom, can we make our own story?"

"Of course, we can. We can do anything we want. We have each other and we have books. We are rich in our own way." Mom said.

They closed the book and put it back on the bookcase. They got up and went to the park. They played and laughed. They made their own story.
<|end|>


