<|asst|>
Ben and Mia were very tired. They had played all day with their toys, their books and their dog. They had eaten a lot of bread and butter for dinner. Now it was time to go to bed.

But Ben and Mia did not want to go to bed. They wanted to stay up and watch TV with their mom and dad. They said, "Please, please, can we watch TV? Just a little bit?"

Mom and dad shook their heads. They said, "No, no, you have to go to bed. TV is not good for you at night. It will make your eyes hurt and your dreams bad. You need to sleep and rest."

Ben and Mia pouted. They said, "But TV is so fun and interesting. We want to see the animals and the cars and the people. We want to learn new things."

Mom and dad smiled. They said, "You can learn new things tomorrow. There are many books and games and puzzles that you can play with. TV is not the only way to learn. And TV is very expensive. We have to pay a lot of money to watch it. We have to save money for other things, like food and clothes and toys."

Ben and Mia yawned. They were starting to feel sleepy. They said, "OK, OK, we will go to bed. But can you read us a story first? A story about animals and cars and people?"

Mom and dad nodded. They said, "Of course, we can read you a story. A story that is fun and interesting and not expensive. Come on, let's go to your room and pick a book."

Ben and Mia hugged their mom and dad. They said, "Thank you, thank you, you are the best. We love you very much."

Mom and dad hugged them back. They said, "We love you too. You are our precious children. Now let's go to bed and have sweet dreams."
<|end|>


