<|asst|>
Lily and Tom were playing in the park. They liked to slide, swing and run. They saw a big tree with many leaves. They wanted to hide under the tree and pretend they were animals.

They ran to the tree and crawled under the leaves. They made noises like lions, monkeys and birds. They had fun.

But then they heard a loud laugh. It was a witch! She had a long nose, a black hat and a broom. She saw Lily and Tom under the tree. She wanted to catch them and make them her pets.

"Ha ha ha, I found you, little ones!" the witch said. "Come out, come out, or I will shake the tree and make you fall!"

Lily and Tom were scared. They did not want to be the witch's pets. They wanted to run away. But they did not know how to get out of the tree.

They whispered to each other. "What can we do?" Lily asked. "We have to be quiet and smart," Tom said.

They looked around and saw a big stick. They had an idea. They grabbed the stick and waited for the witch to come closer.

When the witch reached the tree, she smiled. She thought she had them. She grabbed the broom and started to shake the tree.

But Lily and Tom were ready. They used the stick to poke the witch in the nose. The witch screamed and dropped the broom. Lily and Tom jumped out of the tree and ran to the broom. They climbed on the broom and flew away.

"Bye bye, witch!" they shouted. "You can't catch us!"

The witch was angry and sad. She rubbed her nose and cried. She had lost her broom and her pets.

Lily and Tom were happy and brave. They flew to their home and told their mom and dad what happened. They hugged them and said they loved them.

They never played under the tree again.
<|end|>


