<|asst|>
Lily wanted a haircut. She had long hair that got in her eyes and mouth. She asked her mom to take her to the salon. Her mom said yes, but they had to wait for her dad to come home.

Lily was impatient. She saw scissors on the table. She thought she could cut her own hair. She took the scissors and went to the bathroom. She looked in the mirror and started to snip snip snip.

Her mom heard the noise and ran to the bathroom. She saw Lily with a mess of hair on the floor and on her head. She was shocked and angry. She said, "Lily, what did you do? You ruined your hair! You were selfish and did not wait for me. Now we have to buy a new haircut for you and it will cost a lot of money."

Lily felt sorry. She did not mean to make her mom mad. She said, "I'm sorry, mom. I wanted a haircut. I thought I could do it myself. I did not know it was hard. Please don't be mad at me."

Her mom hugged her and said, "I'm not mad at you, Lily. I love you. But you have to be careful with scissors. They are sharp and dangerous. And you have to listen to me. I know what is best for you. Come on, let's go to the salon and fix your hair. Maybe you can choose a nice color or a ribbon to make it look pretty."
<|end|>


