Lily and Ben were twins who liked to play with their toys. They had a big tree in their living room with many shiny things on it. They were called ornaments and they were very pretty. Lily and Ben wanted to touch them, but Mommy said no. She said they were breakable and not for playing.

One night, Lily and Ben woke up when it was dark. They heard a noise from the living room. They got out of their beds and tiptoed to the door. They opened it and saw a big man in a red suit. He had a big bag on his back and he was putting things under the tree. He was Santa!

Lily and Ben were very excited. They wanted to say hello to Santa and see what he brought them. They ran to the living room and shouted, "Santa, Santa, we are here!"

Santa turned around and smiled. He said, "Ho ho ho, hello Lily and Ben. You are very brave and tough to wake up and see me. But you should be sleeping, it is not time to open your gifts yet."

Lily and Ben looked at the tree and saw many boxes with ribbons and bows. They also saw some new ornaments that Santa had hung on the tree. They were very curious and wanted to touch them.

Santa said, "Be careful, these ornaments are very special. They are from different places in the world. They tell stories and make wishes. But they are also very fragile and can break easily. You have to be gentle and respectful with them."

Lily and Ben nodded. They reached for the ornaments and touched them softly. They felt warm and sparkly. They heard some sounds and saw some pictures in their minds. They saw snow and mountains and animals and people. They felt happy and amazed.

Santa said, "Do you like them? They are my gift to you. They will help you learn and dream and grow. But you have to promise me something. You have to promise to take good care of them and share them with each other. Can you do that?"

Lily and Ben said, "Yes, Santa, we promise. Thank you, thank you, thank you!"

Santa said, "You are very welcome, Lily and Ben. You are very good and sweet children. Now, you have to go back to your beds and sleep. I have to go to other houses and deliver more gifts. I will see you next year. Merry Christmas!"

Lily and Ben hugged Santa and said, "Merry Christmas, Santa! We love you!"

Santa hugged them back and said, "I love you too, Lily and Ben. Good night!"

Lily and Ben ran back to their beds and snuggled under their blankets. They closed their eyes and smiled. They had the best night ever. They had met Santa and he had given them the most wonderful ornaments. They could not wait to wake up and see them again.
<|end|>


