Lily and Sam like to play with puzzles. They have many puzzles with animals, cars, and flowers. They take out a big puzzle with a farm. The puzzle has many pieces and a big box.

"Can you help me, Sam?" Lily asks. She tries to lift the box, but it is too heavy. She cannot carry it to the table.

"OK, Lily. I will help you." Sam says. He goes to the box and puts his arms around it. He squeezes the box hard and lifts it up. He walks to the table and puts the box down.

"Thank you, Sam. You are strong." Lily says. She smiles and gives Sam a hug. They open the box and take out the pieces. They start to make the puzzle.

They find the pieces with the edges and the corners. They put them together to make the frame. Then they look for the pieces with the animals. They find a cow, a pig, a sheep, and a horse. They put them in the right places.

They have fun making the puzzle. They talk and laugh. They are happy. They finish the puzzle and see the farm. They clap their hands and cheer.

"We did it, Lily. We made the puzzle." Sam says.

"Yes, we did, Sam. We are good at puzzles." Lily says.

They look at the puzzle and smile. They are proud of their work. They love puzzles.
<|end|>


