Lila and Tom are friends. They like to play in the park. One day, they see a big cage. Inside the cage, there is a lion. The lion is sleeping.

"Wow, look at the lion!" Tom says. "He is so big and strong. I want to meet him."

"No, Tom, that is a bad idea," Lila says. "The lion is not a friend. He is wild and dangerous. He can bite you and hurt you. We should stay away from the cage."

But Tom does not listen to Lila. He is foolish. He thinks he is brave and smart. He climbs over the fence and goes near the cage. He tries to wake up the lion.

"Hello, lion, I am Tom. Do you want to play with me?" he says.

The lion opens his eyes. He sees Tom. He is angry and hungry. He roars loudly and shows his big teeth. He tries to break the cage and catch Tom.

Tom is scared. He realizes he made a mistake. He runs back to the fence and climbs over it. He joins Lila, who is waiting for him.

"Tom, you are so foolish!" Lila says. "You could have been eaten by the lion. You are lucky he was in the cage. You should never do that again. You should listen to me and be careful."

Tom nods. He is sorry and ashamed. He hugs Lila and says, "You are right, Lila. I was foolish. I will never do that again. You are a good friend. Thank you for saving me."

Lila smiles and hugs Tom back. She says, "You are welcome, Tom. I am glad you are safe. Let's go and play somewhere else. But no more lions, okay?"

Tom agrees. They hold hands and walk away from the cage. They learn their lesson and have fun. The lion goes back to sleep.
<|end|>


