<|asst|>
Anna and Ben like to play with cars. They have many cars of different colors and sizes. They make roads with blocks and race their cars on them. Anna likes the red car best. Ben likes the blue car best.

One day, they are playing with their cars on the floor. Anna says, "Let's see who is faster. I will use the red car and you use the blue car. We will start here and go to the door. Ready, set, go!" They push their cars and make vroom-vroom sounds.

Ben's car is very fast. It speeds ahead of Anna's car. Anna tries to catch up, but she can't. Ben's car reaches the door first. Ben says, "I win! I win! My car is the fastest!" He picks up his car and smiles.

Anna is upset. She wanted to win. She says, "No fair! Your car is bigger than mine. That's why you won. Give me your car and I will use it. Then we will see who is faster." She reaches for Ben's car.

Ben says, "No! This is my car. You can't have it. You have your own car. Use your own car." He pulls his car away from Anna. Anna gets angry. She says, "Fine! I don't want to play with you anymore. You are mean." She grabs her car and leaves. She goes to her room and slams the door.

Ben is sad. He likes to play with Anna. He says, "Anna, come back. Don't be mad. We can play again. We can use different cars. We can take turns. Please, Anna, come back." He waits for Anna to come back, but she doesn't. He sits on the floor and looks at his car. He wishes Anna would come back.
<|end|>


