<|asst|>
Lily and Tom were friends who liked to play in the park. They had many toys to share, because their parents were wealthy and bought them many things. But sometimes they did not agree on how to play, and they would discuss loudly.

One day, they were playing with a big red ball, and they both wanted to kick it. Lily said, "It is my turn, I want to kick the ball." Tom said, "No, it is my turn, I want to kick the ball." They both pulled the ball and shouted at each other.

A man who was walking his dog saw them and came over. He said, "What are you doing, children? Why are you fighting over the ball?" Lily and Tom stopped and looked at him. They felt ashamed and said, "We are sorry, sir. We both wanted to play with the ball, and we could not agree."

The man said, "Well, you know, the ball is not the most important thing in the world. There are many other things you can play with, or you can take turns with the ball. But the most important thing is to be kind and respectful to each other. You are lucky to have a friend to play with, and you should not let a ball cause trouble between you."

Lily and Tom nodded and said, "You are right, sir. Thank you for telling us. We will be nice to each other and share the ball." They smiled and hugged each other, and then they played with the ball and the dog. The man smiled and walked away, happy to see them get along.
<|end|>


