<|end|>
<|asst|>
Once upon a time there was a hairy bear. The bear loved to play outside and explore the woods. One day, the bear was playing near a cave and he heard something strange coming from inside. It sounded like people were talking! He got scared and decided to hide. 

He snuck into the cave and found three people talking. He could tell they were scared, too. He saw them looking for a place to stay. The bear wanted to help them, so he showed them a secret cave that he had found nearby. 

The people thanked the bear for helping them. They stayed in the secret cave for days, until it was safe for them to come out. Eventually, the bear and the people said goodbye and the bear went back to exploring the woods. 

The hairy bear never forgot his friends who he helped to hide. He was so happy to have helped them find a safe place to stay!
<|end|>


