<|end|>
<|asst|>
One day, a little girl named Anna was walking with her mom in the park. It was a nice, warm day, with a cool wind blowing. Anna felt the wind and began to shiver. Her mother noticed and said, "Oh Anna, be brave and don't shiver! Even when the wind blows you will be safe as long as you stay near me." 

So Anna held her mother's hand, and they continued walking. Along the way they found a post standing tall in the park. Anna's mother explained it was a post to show people the way. "Ah," said Anna, "like a sweet guidepost!" Her mother smiled and nodded.

When they had finished their walk, Anna's mother again said, "Remember Anna, always stay close, even when the wind blows. That way, you'll never feel lost. Being brave is the sweetest thing you can do." Anna never forgot her mother's words, and she kept them close in her heart. Whenever she felt like shivering, she instead thought about staying brave and happy. 

Anna's mom taught her an important lesson: sometimes, being brave can be the sweetest thing you can do.
<|end|>


