<|asst|>
Once upon a time, there was a little girl named Lucy. She was three years old and loved the ocean. Every day, she would take a trip with her family to the port and wave to the ships as they sailed away.

One day, her family decided to try something new. They picked a ship that was heading to a distant land. As they boarded the ship, Lucy noticed a box of spicy food on the deck. She started to reach for it, but her mom stopped her.

"No, Lucy," her mom said. "It's not safe. You don't know what's inside of it."

But Lucy didn't listen. She opened the box and found a strange and spicy powder inside. She quickly put some of it in her mouth and it tasted really strange.

Suddenly, Lucy started to feel very sick. She wanted to get off the ship, but it was too late. She passed away on the ship before it even reached the port.

The family was devastated. When they returned home, they spread Lucy's ashes into the ocean, waving goodbye to her one final time.
<|end|>


