Once, there was a little boy named Tom. Tom loved to take walks in the park. He loved to see the bright green grass and the big, fluffy clouds. On one of his walks, Tom saw something very special. He saw a shrimp! It was a small, pink shrimp in a distant pond.

Tom was very excited â€“ he had never seen a real shrimp before! He wanted to take a closer look, so he slowly crept towards the pond. When he was close enough, he carefully stuck his arm into the pond and took the shrimp in his hand. He was so happy!

Tom took the shrimp back home, gave it a little tank to live in and loved it very much. The shrimp and Tom were friends for many days, until one day Tom was sad â€“ the shrimp suddenly wasn't there! It had swum away to a distant pond, back where it came from. 

Tom was sad, but he was also happy â€“ he knew the shrimp was safe in its own home. He knew they would meet again in the future.
<|end|>


