Bob was walking through the park one day and stumbled upon a pond. He saw a little boy swimming in it, but he appeared to be in trouble. Bob became very serious, he knew he had to help him.

"Hello, do you need help?", asked Bob.

The little boy was too shocked to reply.

Bob ran to the edge of the pond and scrambled in, not even thinking of his own safety. He swam to the little boy and grabbed his arm, holding him up above the water.

"It's okay, you're safe now!", said Bob with a big smile on his face.

The little boy, calmer now, smiled back. "Thank you! You are very brave".

Bob smiled, feeling very proud. He carried the boy out of the pond and they looked at each other, both with serious faces.

Bob knew that the little boy was safe now, but he was also aware of the importance of being careful when in water. He patted the boy's arm and promised him he wouldn't forget.

They both went on their way, with a newfound respect for each other.
