Once there was a very intelligent lumberjack. He was always looking for ways to make his lumber better. One day, he offered to help two little boys who had come to his wood to find logs. They were so excited, they couldn't believe it. They hugged the lumberjack and thanked him.

He showed them where the logs were, and took out his saw. He offered to show them how to saw the logs. The boys watched intently as he sawed the lumber. They were amazed at how fast and efficient he was. After he was done sawing, the boys thanked him for the offer.

The lumberjack smiled. He was happy that he was able to help the two boys. He was very proud to have shown them how intelligent he was with sawing logs. The boys thanked the lumberjack again and went home with their load of lumber.
