Once upon a time there was a little girl who loved to dance. Every day she would twirl and jump to the rhythm of the music playing in her head. One day she wanted to pass her favorite song on to someone else so she clapped her hands and started to move.

The little girl shared the rhythm with her family and friends, hopping from one spot to the next. Everyone was having such a great time.

But then the little girl felt something uncomfortable deep in her stomach. She kept going and felt it get bigger and bigger, until eventually she had to stop and take a break. 

The little girl stepped away from the group and the rhythm quieted. She knew the feeling wouldn't pass until she was ready. So, she took a deep breath and started again. Soon, the rhythm was louder and she was happy to dance again.
<|end|>


