John and his dad were walking down the street when they saw an unusual automobile. The car was painted pink and had four big yellow wheels.

John wanted to get a closer look, so he started to walk toward it. His dad stopped him though and said he had to stay away.

John was embarrassed because he wanted to know more about the car. He knew he couldn't go any closer and he didn't understand why he wasn't allowed to.

Suddenly, an old man came out of the automobile. He smiled and said, "It's alright, I don't mind if John takes a closer look at my car."

John was very pleased. He walked up to the car and his dad gave him a pat on the back.

John spent a lot of time looking at the car and admiring the unusual design. He and his dad talked to the old man and asked lots of questions.

John and his dad were both delighted they had the chance to see an unusual automobile. They were glad they could both learn something new that day.
<|end|>


