Once there was a bad animal. He was always very grumpy and never seemed happy. One day, a little girl thought she could help the animal and make him happy. She got out her paints and set to work.

The girl used her paints to paint the animal. She painted him in all sorts of colors. Soon the bad animal was looking very happy. The little girl smiled and was very pleased with her work.

The bad animal was not grumpy anymore. He had lots of fun with the little girl, running and playing around. He was very happy now, and he thanked the little girl by licking her face.

The little girl enjoyed playing with the animal, and they were best friends from then on. She knew that her painting had truly made a difference.
