Jenny was a small girl who loved to play outside. She wanted to go to the park so she put on her favourite cap and ran outside. Suddenly she noticed a huge spider and started to scream. It was so big, she was scared and weak.

Her dad came running, saw the spider and quickly scooped her up in his arms. He tossed the spider out of the garden and then gave Jenny a big hug.

Jenny felt much better and brave enough to go to the park! She ran around and played on the swing. She was having so much fun that she didn't even notice when the sun started to go down. 

Jenny's dad called for her and she scrambled back to him. He put her cap on her head and back to the house they went. 

Jenny was happy that she had a dad who could come and protect her when she screamed.
<|end|>


