<|asst|>
One day, a comet came flying down from the sky. The little girl's eyes lit up when she saw it and she was filled with excitement.

"Look, Daddy!" she exclaimed. "A comet!"

"Yes, sweetheart", said Daddy. "Let's send a wish up to that comet and make your day a bit more peaceful."

The little girl smiled. She took a deep breath and wished for something special. She watched as the comet disappeared into the clouds.

The little girl was sad when she realized her wish was never sent. Daddy tried to cheer her up, but she was disappointed.

"Don't worry," he said. "Maybe we'll see another comet soon."

But the little girl never got the chance to make her wish again. The next day, a storm came and the comet was never seen again. And the little girl's wish was never sent.
<|end|>


