Billy was a very ordinary boy. He was playing in the park one day when he noticed a small rabbit. He smiled at it and the rabbit smiled too. Billy felt something special, something that he couldn't explain. He sat on the grass and stared into the rabbit's big blue eyes. 

"Hello," said Billy.
The rabbit nodded.

"Do you want to be my friend?" asked Billy.
The rabbit nodded again. 

Billy reached out and patted it on the head. He liked the way it felt. The rabbit felt safe and happy.

"Let's go on an adventure," said Billy. "A special dream adventure!"
The rabbit nodded and hopped away. 

Billy followed the rabbit, gaining more and more confidence along the way. He knew he had found a real friend. They went on a magical journey and both of them had a wonderful dream. 

When they awoke, Billy was sad for it was over. But he smiled when he thought about how ordinary his day had started, and how extraordinary it had become. The rabbit nodded in agreement.
