Once upon a time there was a helpful pig. He was always helping his farm friends whenever they needed him. One day, he was on his way to help his friend the cow when he suddenly felt his body tremble. He didn't know what was wrong. He felt an itchy feeling inside his belly.

He thought he might have done something wrong, so he decided to go and see a wise old frog. The frog took some time to think about what was wrong with the pig.

"I think I know," said the frog, "you have been too helpful! Helping your friends is very nice, but you must make sure that you take care of yourself too. Otherwise, you might get a strange itchy feeling inside your belly."

The pig thanked the frog for his advice. From then on, he was careful to look after himself, while still helping his friends. He discovered that the balance between taking care of himself and being helpful to his farm friends made him much happier. 

The moral of this story is that being helpful to think others is great, but it is also important to remember to take care of yourself too.
<|end|>


