Abby and her mom were walking down the street when suddenly, they heard a loud sound.

Abby's mom said: "What was that noise?"

Abby looked up and saw a broken parrot on the side of the road. The parrot hadn't moved since the loud sound.

Abby said: "Can we help the parrot?"

Abby's mom nodded and they both walked over to the parrot. Abby's mom lifted the parrot carefully, and stroked its head.

Abby said: "Is the parrot ok?"

Abby's mom smiled and said: "Yes, it's just a bit scared. We'll take him home and look after him."

Abby smiled and said: "Can I keep him?"

Her mom nodded and said: "Yes, as long as you take good care of him."

Abby was so happy that she lifted the parrot and hugged it tight.

The next day, the parrot was back to being its normal, noisy self. Abby smiled and said: "I'm so glad you are not broken anymore!"
<|end|>


