Once upon a time, there was a small and modest girl who loved to play in the garden. She would spend hours in the sunshine, and draw happy patterns with her fingers in the dirt. One day she stepped away from the garden and started to explore the world around her.

The girl was amazed by the incredible sights she saw; tall buildings, colorful plants, and bright blue skies. But she soon realized that nothing matched the beauty of her garden, and so she started to make plans to return home.

When she reached the garden gate, she stopped and said out loud:

"I've missed my happy patterns in the dirt. I'm so glad to be home!"

The words filled the garden with love, and soon the girl saw the plants begin to twirl and the dirt start to form into familiar patterns. She laughed with joy and rushed to lay down beside them and feel the sunlight on her face.

From that day on, she decided to visit the world, but never failed to return home to her patterns in the garden.
<|end|>


