Once upon a time, there was a spider named Terry. He lived in a deep, dark corner of the house, with cobwebs surrounding him. 

One day, Terry got a brilliant idea. He decided to take a closer look at his cobwebs. As Terry was inspecting them, he noticed something shiny at the end of one of the threads. 

Terry asked his friend, a beetle named Billie, "what do you see?"

Billie took a look and said, "I see a gem! How cool!"

Terry said, "Let's do the cobweb walk and see if we can find the gem."

Both Terry and Billie started the cobweb walk and soon enough, Billie found the beautiful gem. Terry cheered and said, "We did it! Thanks for helping me find this deep, shiny gem!"
