John had been walking through the park, looking for something special to do. He had noticed the duck pond over by the trees, and he decided to go over and have a closer look. 

As he walked closer, he saw the ducks swimming about and enjoying the sunshine. John was so excited to see them. He slowly made his way to the edge of the pond and stopped to watch the ducks. 

As he was watching, he heard one of the ducks quack loudly. He smiled and called out to the duck. The duck looked up and said, "Hello, young man! What are you doing here?" 

John told the duck that he just wanted to gain a better view of its wonderful feathers. The duck smiled and said, "Well, you must be careful when you approach a duck. I don't want to scare you away." 

John thanked the duck for its advice and stayed a little longer to enjoy the view of the pond. Before he left, he waved goodbye to the duck, who quacked in response. 

John learned a valuable lesson that day - to always be careful when approaching animals, even ducks!
