Max and Lily were playing in their backyard when Max noticed a strange rock. He knelt down and picked it up.

"Look Lily, a copper one," Max said. "It's so thin."

Lily leaned over and took a closer look. "Let me weigh it, Max," she said.

So the two of them shared the rock and Max held it up in the air. It weighed almost nothing.

"Wow," said Lily, her eyes wide. "It's so light!"

Max smiled. "It must be special," he said.

The two of them agreed to keep it safe and they tucked the thin copper rock away in a secret spot in the garden.

And now every day they went out to play they'd take turns weighing the rock. It never changed, always as light as a feather.
