Once upon a time there was a huge goat. Every day he would hop and bounce around the fields. One day he hopped too far and couldn't find his way back home. He kept hopping and finally came across a huge wall. He tried to jump over it but he was too big! He scratched and kicked, but the wall was too tall for him. 

The goat started to feel thirsty, so he stopped and looked for water. Suddenly, he heard a loud noise. Looking up he saw a huge man with a huge gun. He wanted to move but the man said 'stop'. The goat bleated and was scared, he knew he was in trouble. 

The man tied a rope around the goat and led him away. The goat was very sad because he wanted to go home. Sadly, he never made it back home. 

The moral of this story is to never wander too far away from home. Sometimes bad things can happen when you leave the safety of your home.
