Once upon a time, there was a small peach. It was so tiny, you could fit it in the palm of your hand. The peach wanted to balance on the edge of the table. So it carefully placed one end on the table and tried to balance. Suddenly, it wobbled and toppled over! The small peach tried again, but it kept toppling over. It just couldn't balance.

Just then, a magic fairy appeared. She waved her magic wand and whispered, "Balance, balance, balance." Suddenly, the small peach was balanced on the edge of the table! The peach was so happy. It couldn't believe it had managed to balance.

The peach stayed balanced for hours, until it was time for bed. The small peach was so proud of itself. It had managed to balance, thanks to the magic fairy's help.
<|end|>


