<|asst|>
Finn sat under the apple tree, looking at the sky. He liked to watch the clouds float by. Then suddenly, he saw an insect fly past. It was huge and black with green spots!

Finn gasped and got to his feet, his eyes wide and excited. He wanted to catch the insect. But it was too fast. Finn grew impatient and started to scream.

Just then, his mother walked out of the house. She heard Finn screaming and hurried to help. "What is it honey?" she asked.

Finn pointed to the insect and said, "Look, mom! An insect!"

His mother smiled and said, "That's nice honey, but why were you screaming?"

Finn said sadly, "I wanted to catch it, but it flew away too quickly."

His mother smiled and gave him a big hug. She said, "Don't worry, there will always be more insects tomorrow."

Finn smiled, feeling content. He headed inside with his mom, still dreaming of catching an insect.
<|end|>


