Bella was a gentle little girl. She lived in a small house with her parents.

One day, when Bella's parents were not home, a stranger came to their door. He knocked and waited patiently. When Bella opened the door he said, â€œWelcome to my home! Please come in and stay with me!â€

Bella was very scared, but she was too scared to run away. The man was gentle and kind, so she stayed. He offered her sweets and gentle stories.

But soon things changed. The man became unkind. He yelled at Bella and made her do things she didnâ€™t want to do. When Bella tried to leave, the man grabbed her and held her back.

Bella was very scared and she began to weep. She finally got away and ran out of the house, never to return. She never saw the man again, but the memories of his cruelty stayed with her and made her weep.
<|end|>


