Once upon a time, there was an adventurous little girl. She loved to explore and have fun. One day, the adventurous little girl found a puzzle. It was a funny puzzle, so she wanted to joke about it.

But then she saw a mean boy. He was very mad about the funny puzzle and he didn't want the little girl to joke about it. The little girl wanted to joke, but she was scared of the mean boy. 

The adventurous little girl thought of a plan. She decided to ignore the mean boy and keep joking about the funny puzzle. The mean boy tried to scare her, but she didn't give up. She kept joking until the mean boy finally left. 

The little girl felt brave and proud. She had been adventurous and it helped her make a joke that no one else could do.
