Once upon a time there was a little puppy. His name was Chris. One day Chris was playing in the garden when he saw something on the ground. It was a collar! It was a very pretty collar with sparkles on it.

Chris was happy and he put the collar around his neck. He rubbed the sparkles to make them shine. But then he felt something strange - he felt sad. He didn't know why but there it was.

Chris looked around but there was no one there. He lay down in the sunshine and rubbed his collar. He didn't know why he was so sad, but he wanted to make the sadness go away. He kept rubbing his collar until he felt better.

The sun went down, and Chris went to bed. He was a little bit happier, but he still wasn't sure why he was so sad. He hugged his collar and went to sleep.

The next morning he was feeling much better. He was happy and excited to wear his new collar. He rubs it and smiles - the sparkles still make him happy.
<|end|>


