Once upon a time, a little girl saw a very old vine growing on the side of the house. The vine was so long that it was almost touching the ground. She wanted to borrow the vine, so she asked her mom if she could. Her mom said yes, so the little girl got some scissors and carefully cut the old vine. 

The little girl used the vine to make a swing in the backyard. She hung it from a strong branch so that she could play on it all day. She enjoyed swinging on the old vine. 

At night, she brought the vine back to the side of the house. She said thank you to her mom for letting her borrow it. Then she gave the old vine a big hug before she went inside.
<|end|>


