Little Cora was a graceful three year old girl. Every night before she went to sleep, she would tell her mom and dad about her day at daycare. She had made lots of friends and learned lots of new things.

Today, Cora had to take an exam. At first, she was afraid, because she had never taken an exam before. Her mom and dad told her to just do her best and to behave. Cora took a deep breath and tried her best.

The exam was hard, but Cora kept her calm and kept trying. After the exam was over, Cora was so proud of herself. She had been so graceful and behaved so well. She beamed with happiness. 

Her mom and dad were so proud to see Cora happy and they gave her a hug. "We are so proud of you" they said. Cora hugged them back, feeling like the happiest three year old girl in the world.
<|end|>


