Jimmy was sad. He was missing his mommy. He wanted her to come back and comfort him. His dad saw how much Jimmy was missing his mommy and hugged him tight. He stroked Jimmy's hair and spoke in a kind voice.

Jimmy felt better. His dad picked him up and carried him to the kitchen. Together they went over to the sink. Jimmy's dad took out a bowl of healthy fruit from the fridge and set it on the counter. He arranged the fruit into a funny shape and asked Jimmy to smile. It worked! Jimmy smiled and his dad smiled too.

Jimmy's dad then opened the fridge and pulled out a cool, tall glass of milk. Jimmy loved milk and he drank it all up. He felt better and healthier.

Jimmy's dad hugged him one more time before saying goodnight. Jimmy felt comforted and snuggled into bed. Tomorrow was going to be a better day.
<|end|>


