Once there was a man walking in the woods. He was whistling as he walked. Suddenly, he heard a sound like a pistol. He stopped and looked around. He could see a harsh man holding a pistol in the bushes. The man was trying to rob him. The harsh man shouted for him to give him all his money, but the man didn't want to give up his hard-earned money. He thought for a moment, then the man started to whistle again. This time, he whistled louder and for longer. The harsh man got scared and ran away back into the bushes. The man was very relieved and grateful. He went home safely, still whistling all the way.
<|end|>


