<|asst|>
Once upon a time there were two siblings â€“ a brother and a sister. They were always together and they had a lot of fun. One night they were caught in a big storm. The brother told his sister to stay calm and not weep. But the sister was scared and she said to her brother: "I can't help it! I'm so frightened!"

The kind brother put his arms around her and said: "There's no need to be scared, little one. The storm will soon be over." So he hugged her tight and she slowly stopped weeping.

The next day the siblings talked about what had happened. The sister said: "I was so foolish to weep over the storm. Next time I'll try to be brave." The brother smiled and said: "You did the right thing â€“ I was proud of you for not crying on my neck!"

The moral of the story is: Sometimes it's ok to show your feelings, but it's important to be brave.
<|end|>


