Once upon a time, there was a big bucket. It was so big, it could fit a lot of things inside of it! Every morning, the bucket had a special name. It was called "the morning bucket".

One day, the morning bucket went for a walk. It stumbled across a big pile of leaves. The bucket was so excited, it started to jump and spin around!

When the morning bucket got back home, it was so tired from all of the jumping. It hopped into its bed and fell asleep.

That night, the bucket had a wonderful dream about the leaves. It dreamt of playing in them all day, laughing and having fun!

The morning bucket has been happy ever since. Every day it runs to the pile of leaves and plays. All it can think of is the special name it gave them: the leaf pile!
