Dave and Lily were out in the garden. Dave asked Lily to bury a big oat. Lily thought it would be difficult, but she agreed to try.

Lily started to dig a hole big enough to fit the oat in. Dave watched as Lily dug and dug. After a while Lily was so tired she couldn't dig anymore.

Dave said to her, "That's enough Lily, I'm going to finish burying the oat."

Lily was worried. She thought it was too difficult for Dave too, but she knew he liked to be helpful.

Dave started to bury the oat and finally it was all covered. 

But suddenly, Dave and Lily heard a loud squawking. A sad bird had been buried in the oat and was now stuck! Dave and Lily were so sad. 

The bird was too deep to just dig it out so they had to leave it buried. Dave and Lily went inside and never went back to the garden.
<|end|>


