Once upon a time there was a boy named Peter. He was a very mischievous and sometimes foolish little boy. He loved to do adventurous things and many times he got in trouble. 

One day, Peter was out in the garden when he saw a big toad hopping around. Peter thought it was very funny to watch the toad, so he got an idea. He decided to pinch the toad's toe.

When Peter pinched the toad's toe, it jumped in surprise. Peter started to giggle as he watched the toad hobble away. But when the toad was gone, Peter realized he had done something foolish and he felt sorry.

Peter never pinched the toad's toe again, and learned that it is important to be careful and not do silly things.
