Once upon a time, a boy named John wanted to travel. One day, he asked his mom if he could take a trip. She said yes, but he had to be careful. So, John packed his bag and set off.

He traveled through the woods and over the hills. Everything was exciting and new, but a little scary too. He kept walking until he came to a big lake. He hadn't seen a lake before and he was frightened. 

But then he noticed something that made him feel better. On the other side of the lake, he spotted a little boat. He liked boats, so he called out to the boatman and asked to take a ride across the lake. 

The boatman said yes and soon John was travelling again. He arrived safe and sound on the far side and was very glad he had taken the journey. 

After that, he never felt frightened yet when he wanted to travel.
