Once there was a girl called Lucy. She liked to watch the aeroplanes fly in the sky. She wanted to fly with them. She watched them everyday, dreaming of flying away.

One day her wish came true. An aeroplane landed in her garden. She was so excited and ran up to the pilot to ask if she could go with him. The pilot had compassion for Lucy and said, "Yes, you can come". 

As the aeroplane took off, Lucy felt like she was growing wings. They flew around the world, visiting lots of different countries. The pilot taught her lots of things and showed her how to be kind and compassionate just like him. 

When they landed, Lucy thanked the pilot for her wonderful adventure. She had learned so much on her journey and she will always remember it. 

The moral of the story is that kindness can take you anywhere!
