Once there was a bald man. He was walking in the park. He saw a jelly on the ground and he was really excited. He wanted to eat the jelly. He started to pass it to his mouth when a little girl rushed in front of him and grabbed the jelly. The bald man was sad. 

The little girl was the bald man's neighbour. The girl said, "I want this jelly! It's so tasty!" The bald man replied, "But I saw it first!" The girl crossed her arms and said, "no! It's mine now!" 

The bald man knew he could not win in this argument. He decided to make a deal with the girl. He said, "If you give me some of the jelly, I will get you some more from the store". The girl thought about it for a moment and soon agreed. They both shared the jelly and the bald man kept his promise. He bought the girl even more jelly from the store and the girl shared the jelly with everyone in the park. 

The bald man smiled. He was glad he could find a way to share the jelly. In the end, everyone was happy!
