Once upon a time, there was a wise ant. He wanted to go on an adventure, so he started to pack his things. But he wasn't sure what to bring.

Just then, he heard a voice. It was coming from a big bird. The bird said, "If you only bring a few things, then your adventure will be even more exciting!"

The ant thanked the bird for its wise advice. He looked around and found a few things he could bring with him. Then, he started on his journey.

He had so many adventures that it made him feel so small. But every time he felt like giving up, he remembered the bird's wise advice.

He was so happy that he shouted, "Thank you, wise bird!"

And with that, the little ant's journey ended, and he came home full of stories to tell.
<|end|>


