Once upon a time, there was a horse named Johnny. Johnny was very thoughtful, but he always felt like no one accepted him. One day, Johnny's owner brought home a beautiful automobile. Johnny was excited to see the automobile, but his owner said it was only for him. Johnny didn't understand why he couldn't have the same thing. He began to feel very sad. 

Johnny's owner saw how sad Johnny was, and he said, "Johnny, it's ok that you don't have the same thing. Automobile is for me. But I have something different for you. Something special."

The owner brought out a big shiny apple. Johnny was so excited he could hardly contain himself. "This is for me?" he asked. 

"Yes, Johnny, this is for you," the owner said.

From that day on, Johnny learned that it was ok to not have the same things as everyone else. He learned to accept others and their differences, and to be thankful for the things he had. He never felt sad or left out again.
<|end|>


