Once upon a time, there was a deer who was very rich. He had a big, fancy house in the woods and lots of money.
One day, he wanted to go for a drive. He hopped into his car and sped away. The wind in his fur made him feel so happy!
When he drove faster, he felt like he was flying. He looked out the window and he could see many different kinds of animals running and playing in the woods.

Finally, the deer reached a big field. He stopped the car and got out. He ran as fast as he could in the field, taking in the beauty of nature. It was so much fun!

The deer raced around the field, and soon he got so tired that he had to rest. He lay there, looking at the sky and feeling so happy and rich. 

He smiled and thanked the universe for the wonderful life he had.
