Once upon a time, there was a little girl. She wanted to go to the playground but it was raining. Her mum said that she could not go out and play. 

The little girl was sad and stuck inside. Then, she had an idea - she could make her own play area inside. 

The little girl found some mud in the garden and brought it inside. She made a big muddy mess in the living room! She moulded the mud into fun shapes and showed it to her mum.

At first her mum was not happy but then she had an idea too. The little girl and her mum made a mud kitchen! They made mud pies and mud ice cream and played pretend games.

The little girl was so happy and her mum was ready to accept the muddy mess they had made. They both laughed and had so much fun.
