Once upon a time, there was a little girl called Jane. Jane knew that her mommy was always busy, but one day she wanted to do something nice and help out. So she decided to buy a present for her mom.

Jane went to the store and saw lots of things, but she couldn't decide what to get. Then she saw something unusual: lotion. It was so pretty and sparkly! Jane had never seen anything like it before. She just had to buy it for her mom.

When Jane got home, however, mommy was not happy. Mommy said the lotion was too expensive and Jane should have bought something else. Jane was very sad because she just wanted to help out. 

But then Mommy hugged Jane and said, "It's OK, sweetheart. You were just trying to be helpful. I'm glad you bought me something so unusual and special." Jane was happy to hear that and smiled with relief. 

From that day on, Jane and her Mommy always worked together to do nice things for each other.
<|end|>


