"Look," said Mummy, pointing into the distance. "What do you see?"
"I see a gorilla," said Jack, his eyes wide with excitement.
Mummy smiled. "Let's go and take a closer look."

Jack and Mummy walked towards the gorilla, who was perched atop a tall tree. As they approached, the gorilla revealed a large pile of gold coins. Jack and Mummy gasped with amazement.

"What's all this?" said Jack.
Mummy stroked her chin. "I think the gorilla must be rich!"

Jack smiled and waved at the gorilla, who waved back and smiled. He was happy to share his wealth with Jack and Mummy.

Mummy and Jack said goodbye to the friendly gorilla, dazzled by his riches. Jack couldn't believe his eyes. He had made a new friend, and learnt a lesson that day â€“ that friendship can reveal the most unexpected surprises.
<|end|>


