Once upon a time, there was a girl named Lucy. She loved going for walks in the woods near her home, but she was always very careful. One day, she got lost in the woods and she became very frightened. She looked around, but she couldn't remember how to find her way home. Suddenly, she saw an orange in the grass. She thought it looked like a good idea to follow the orange, so she started walking in the same direction as the orange.

Lucy followed the orange for a long time and soon, she found her way out of the woods. She was so happy that she had not gotten lost. She picked up the orange and took it with her, so she would never lose it. Lucy was very relieved to be out of the woods and back at home. She smiled and said goodbye to the orange, thankful that it had helped her find her way.
<|end|>


