Once upon a time, there was a small child who was very eager to play. They asked their family to join them so they could play a game.

"Yes!" they said, "Let's play!"

So they all sat down and grabbed a few pieces of paper from the kitchen table. One of the pieces of paper had a skeleton drawn on it. 

The small child was happy, they were eager to match the pieces of paper and find out who had the skeleton! They held up the skeleton and asked everyone to match the pieces of paper with their skeleton.

But as soon as the pieces were matched, everyone started to laugh. They laughed until tears were streaming down their faces. The small child was confused, why was this funny? 

But then the family revealed the truth. The small child had been tricked! The skeleton was never actually theirs!
 
The small child felt sad and embarrassed by their mistake and never asked to play again.
<|end|>


