Once upon a time there was a wealthy family. They had all the nicer things that money can buy. One day their son, John, wanted to go to the park. His parents said no, but John did not listen, he took a gun and went to the park in secret.

At the park, John saw some of his friends playing and forgot all about the gun. He went to join them and have some fun. His parents were worried and set out to find him.

When they found him, they saw the gun lying next to him and became very scared. John had picked it up and was playing with it, not understanding the danger. His parents tried to take the gun away but it was too late. The gun went off and wounded John. He was taken to hospital and never recovered.

John's parents were devastated and remembered their warning about the gun. They had wanted to protect him and were heartbroken to think of the bad ending that had come from his choice to take the gun.
<|end|>


