Once there was a very helpful lumberjack. He worked very hard in the woods, cutting down the big trees. His seat was very uncomfortable, but he kept working because he was doing a good job.

One day, while he was working, a little 3 year old boy came walking in the woods. He had seen the lumberjack, and he wanted to help him. He brought the lumberjack a nice, soft seat to sit on.

The lumberjack was so glad! His back and legs felt much better. He thanked the little boy for being so helpful. From that day on, he was much more comfortable when he worked, and he always smiled when he thought of the kind little boy.
<|end|>


