Once there was a kind little girl named Jane. Jane wanted to buy something very special. She went to the store to buy colorful things.

At the store, Jane looked at all the colorful things. She wanted to buy something as bright as the rainbow in the sky. Jane wanted to buy something very kind.

Jane found a beautiful thing. It was bright blue and sparkly! Jane asked the storekeeper if she could buy it. The storekeeper said, "Yes, you can buy it." So Jane happily paid for the colorful thing with her pocket money. 

When she went home, Jane showed the thing to her mom and dad. They said it was very kind and smiled. Jane was so happy. She had bought something special with her own money.
