Once upon a time, there was a little girl named Molly who loved playing in her garden. She always loved burying her toys in the soil and finding them again.

One day, her mommy asked her to go to the store to get some milk. She was very excited and went to the store right away.

When she got there, Molly noticed that the store was very noisy and busy. Then she noticed something on the floor - it was her toy that she had buried in her garden earlier! She was so excited she picked it up and started to put it in her bag.

Just then, the store manager came over and said, "Excuse me, the item you are taking belongs to the store. You must pay for it or put it back."

Molly was disappointed, but she knew she had to put it back. She said, "I'm sorry, I don't have any money to pay for it."

"That's okay," said the store manager. "Why don't you put it back in the store and I'll give you a tip?"

Molly was very happy and thanked the manager. She was thrilled to have her toy back, and the tip was a nice bonus. Molly promised to be more careful next time and ran out of the store, into the garden. She buried her toy deep in the soil and smiled, happy that she had learned her lesson.
<|end|>


