Once upon a time there was a small farm with a barn full of hay. One day, a mean fox came along and wanted to spoil the hay. He wanted to make the animals in the barn jealous. 

The farmer noticed and decided to hide in the barn to protect the hay. The fox went around the barn and saw it was locked. He decided to try to get the hay by playing tricks on the animals. He told them he would give some hay to each of the animals, but he lied. 

The other animals were so jealous of the fox and wished he would be nice and share. The farmer heard the fox and came out of the barn and scolded him for not sharing. The fox learnt his lesson, he shouldn't spoil what isn't his, and he agreed to share the hay with all the animals. 

Since that day, all the animals have been sharing nicely and appreciating what they have. The moral of this story is to never spoil other people's things and be nice to share.
<|end|>


