Once upon a time, there were two friends, Jack and Dan. They loved to keep jokeing and have a laugh together.

One day, Dan had to go away for a while. Jack was sad and thought that he was going to miss Dan a lot.

But when Dan came back, Jack was so happy! They jokeed and laughed just like before.

Jack noticed that Dan had become very independent. He was doing things on his own, like cycling to the store for the first time. 

Jack was very proud of Dan, and wanted to help him keep being independent. So whenever Dan did things on his own, Jack gave him a big smile and said "great job".

The moral of the story is that it is important to support your friends so they can keep being independent.
<|end|>


