Once upon a time, a loved little elephant lived in the jungle. Everyday he would make friends with animals of the forest and have fun playing with them. The elephant felt so happy and comfortable that he could call the jungle his home.

One day, the little elephant noticed a big grey trunk lying besides a tree. He walked closer and closer and saw that the top of the trunk was open. What could it be? He wondered. He quickly popped inside to take a look.

Inside, he felt warm and peaceful. He had found his own special place! He smiled and settled in. From then on, the trunk was his special place of peace, where he could go whenever he wanted some quiet.

One day his animal friends stopped by. The elephant was so excited that he invited them in! They happily shared the trunk, talking, playing and laughing in the peaceful space. 

The little elephant realised that it felt nice to share his special place with his friends. He new that no matter what, they all belonged together in the trunk and in the jungle.
<|end|>


