Once upon a time there was a little boy named Timmy. He liked to race and he was very excited when his parents got him a racecar.

Each day, Timmy would race around the room and make a loud vroom-vroom sound. He began to love it so much that he found time to race everywhere and anywhere he could.

One day, Timmy was racing around the garden and he saw something silly. It was two frogs racing around, flying and jumping. Timmy thought it was funny and he laughed. The frogs were racing so fast and looked like they were having so much fun that Timmy wanted to join in.

Timmy clapped and cheered as the frogs raced around. He was so happy that he felt like he wanted to do something silly too. So he jumped up and raced around with the frogs. It felt like they were all having a lot of fun and they raced around until they were all tired.

When they were finished, Timmy hugged the frogs and said goodbye. He didn't know it but they shared a special love. Timmy smiled and continued to race around, knowing that love can make anyone feel happy.
<|end|>


