John was feeling very angry. He wanted to go home, so he insisted that his mum take him. But mum said no. She said it was too late. But John didn't listen and he kept insisting.

Mum tried to tell John why it was a bad idea to go home right now. She said it was dark outside and they needed to stay in the park until it was light again. But John kept insisting.

His mum got angry. She said it was time to go and they couldn't stay in the park any longer. But John still insisted. He said he wanted to go home now!

Finally, his mum gave in. She said ok, and they went home. John was very happy. He was glad to be home at last.
