Max was visiting the pond with his mommy. He had never been there before. His mommy explained that the pond was filled with fish, water plants and other things. 

Max was very excited. He looked all around to see what was there. Suddenly, he noticed a lot of ducks swimming around the pond. He asked his mommy why the ducks were all organized in a neat line.

His mommy explained that the ducks were swimming in single file so they could look for food. She pointed out that each duck was searching in its own row so they could get the best food. Then she told Max to watch where the ducks went once they found food. Max thought it was very cool so he watched and sure enough the ducks went back to the same neat line.

Max learned an important lesson that day. He learned that things can be organized and can help animals get food. It was a happy day at the pond.
<|end|>


