Once there was a little boy named Sam who loved to pretend. One day Sam saw a tray on the ground and he wanted to play with it. He picked it up and pretended he was flying. He flew around for a while, until he heard a loud noise coming from somewhere.
Sam got frightened and tried to fly lower and faster. He had flown too close to a building and knocked something loose. Before he knew it, something fell on his tray and broke it. Sam was so frightened and he started to cry.

He quickly put the broken pieces of the tray away and tried to pretend that nothing bad had happened. But in the end, he had to tell his mom what had happened and she was not happy. She told him that he should never pretend with something he didn't own. Sam learned his lesson and never pretended with trays again.
