Billy tucked away his toys and lay on the grass in the backyard. The sun was setting and it was getting scary and dark. He was feeling sleepy, so he decided to lay down and close his eyes. As he looked closely, he noticed something. On the tree that was close by, there was a nest with little eggs in it. Billy was very curious, so he waited and watched the nest closely. 

After a few minutes, two little birds flew out of the nest and landed right beside him in the backyard. They were so cute and Billy was so excited to see them. They started chirping and he even heard them say each other's names. Then they went back to the nest and rested on the tree branch. 

Billy was so happy that he fell asleep right there in the backyard. When he woke up the next morning, he saw the birds flying again. He smiled and ran inside to tell his mom what had happened. He would no longer be scared of the dark, because he knew his backyard was filled with sleepy birds to keep him company.
<|end|>


