John was a friendly three year old. He went to visit his grandfather, who had a big house with a bathroom. When he entered, John noticed there was something strange about the bathroom.

John asked his grandfather, "What's wrong with your bathroom?" His grandfather explained, "It doesn't have a lock. That's why I don't like it."

John said, "I can help you. I can put a lock on the bathroom door." His grandfather smiled at him and said, "Okay, that sounds like a good idea."

John found a lock and put it on the door. He was so proud of his work. But then, his grandfather said, "I don't like the lock. Take it off!"

John felt sad. He didn't want to take off the lock. He explained that he had worked so hard to install it. But his grandfather was really firm and didn't listen to John. John had to take off the lock and leave the bathroom without its lock. He was disappointed.
<|end|>


