Once upon a time there was a small girl called Lola. She was three years old and lived with her mom and dad in a big house with a garden. 
One day, Lola wanted to make a fire. Her mom and dad said she could, but only if she was careful and followed their rules. Lola followed the rules and made a nice fire. 
She was helping her mom and dad in the garden when it started to drizzle. Lola wanted to put the fire out before it got too wet. 
She tried but could not put the fire out by herself. She called for her mom and dad's help. 
When her parents arrived, they saw that Lola had done her best and tried to put the fire out. They praised her and said that she had been fit and worked hard. Mom and Dad answered Lola's call and put the fire out.

The moral of the story is: it is important to work together and answer your calls for help. Together, you can solve any problem!
