Once upon a time there was a kind princess. Whenever the princess was sad, she would go outside and trust a special rag. The rag was very rare because it was blue and sparkly. Whenever the princess touched it, she felt safe and happy. She kept the rag under her pillow whenever she went to sleep.

One day, a dragon flew into the princess' kingdom. The dragon was fierce and scared the people. But the princess was brave, she took out her trusty rag and held it tight in her hand. She told the dragon that it was wrong to be so mean and to leave her kingdom. The dragon roared and flew away. 

The people of the kingdom were glad and thanked the princess for protecting them. They gave the princess a special necklace to thank her for her bravery. She wore it every day and always kept her trusty rag close.
