Once there was a little baby bird who felt very far away from his family. He was flying higher and higher, taking big breaths of the cold air. But deep inside he felt sad and alone.

Just then, he felt a small, comforting hand on his wing. He looked up and saw his Mama bird! Mama Bird had flown a long, long way to find her little baby. She wrapped her wings around him and sang a sweet song.

Mama Bird flew with him, just above the clouds. She pointed out the bright stars in the night sky and whispered gentle words into his ear. Slowly, the little baby bird felt comforted by his Mama's presence.

The next morning, they flew back to the nest together. The little one was not so distant any more and he was happy once again.
