Once upon a time there was a girl named Amy. One day Amy wanted to explore, so she decided to go in the woods. She was walking along and suddenly she saw something appear. It was a big yellow buckle! Amy was so excited and she ran over to get it.

As soon as she touched the buckle she heard a voice behind her. It said, "That is my buckle. Give it back!" Amy was upset and she started to cry. She said, "I'm sorry. I didn't know someone owned it." 

The voice said, "I forgive you. Let's be friends." Amy was happy and she said, "Yes, friends!" 

The voice came from a friendly bear who had appeared from the trees. They smiled at each other and the bear gave Amy a hug. She took the buckle home and from that day she loved exploring the woods with her new friend. The end.
