Sally was a young girl. She was very impatient. She wanted to go out and play, but it was still too cold. She looked out the window and saw a turkey. Its tail was big and colorful. Sally was so excited. She ran outside to see the turkey.

The turkey was looking for some food. Sally watched as it jumped around the yard. Suddenly, it stopped. The turkey had found a bug. Sally watched as it gobbled up the bug.

Just then, Sally heard a noise. She looked around and saw a beautiful bluebird. It was singing a song. The bird flew up into the sky. Sally watched it fly higher and higher. Then, she heard the bird call again as it disappeared into the clouds.

The sun was shining brighter and brighter. Summer was coming soon. Sally couldn't wait. She knew that soon everything would turn green and the flowers would start to bloom. She couldn't wait for the spring.
