Once upon a time, there was a big prune tree. It was smooth and tall, and had lots of twigs and branches. Every morning, a small bird would come and attach himself to the prune tree. He would tuck his little head into his wings and close his eyes for a nap.

The bird loved to sleep in the tree because it was so smooth. He could feel the cool, smooth bark against his little feathers, and hear the birds singing in the branches.

When it was time for the bird to wake up, he would look for a prune to eat. He could feel the prune's smooth skin and taste its sweet juice. He thought it was the best fruit ever.

The little bird would attach himself to the tree again, until the next morning when he needed to look for his breakfast. He would always come back to the same tree, and it always welcomed him with its smooth branches. He was very happy in his little tree.

The End.
