Once there was a little girl who was very lonely. She had no friends to play with her.

One day, she had an idea. She decided to make rice to share with others. After she made the rice, she couldn't find anyone to eat with her. She was sad, but she decided to eat it herself.

Suddenly, she heard some footsteps. She rushed to the window to see who it was. It was a big, friendly bear!

The bear wanted to join the little girl for lunch. But the girl wanted to prevent the big bear from eating all the rice. So, she told the bear to bring some friends.

The bear went away and came back with some more animals. They all ate together and had fun.

The little girl was very happy! From then on, she wasnâ€™t lonely anymore. She always shared rice with her animal friends.
