Once upon a time, there were two friends named Tom and Polly. One day, Tom was in the park and wanted to show Polly something exciting. He pointed to the sky and explained that the sound was coming from an airplane. Polly was very curious and was anxious to try and take a ride. 

Tom carefully explained that even though it looked fun, it was actually very dangerous and she could get very dizzy. But Polly wouldn't take no for an answer, so Tom had to think of something.

Tom looked around and noticed the carousel nearby. He quickly pointed to it and explained that it was just as fun and wouldn't make Polly dizzy like the airplane. Polly was so excited, and the two friends enjoyed a nice ride together on the carousel. And they both lived happily ever after.
<|end|>


