Once upon a time, there was a huge twig in the woods. It was so tall that it reached up to the clouds. 

One day, a bird flew by and saw the huge twig. He flapped his wings and waved at it. But the twig did not move. 

So the bird flew off to find some friends. He found a fox and a squirrel. He told them about the huge twig. 

The fox, the squirrel and the bird flew back to the twig. They waved their tails and hopped up and down. But the twig still did not budge. 

Suddenly, the wind began to blow. It picked up the twig and sent it flying! All of the animals waved goodbye as the twig disappeared over the horizon.
<|end|>


