There was a family living next door to each other. The first family had a nice, clean grill in their backyard. The second family did not have a grill, and they often watched their neighbors enjoy theirs.

One day, the second family decided they wanted a grill too. The wife went to the store and when she came home, the husband was outside making a space for it. They were putting the grill together when the 3 year old daughter came outside. She was so excited that they were getting their own grill.

The daughter asked, "When will we be able to use the grill?" The father replied, "We will have to wait for the parts to come first." She got sad and asked, "Why can't we use it now?"

The mother said, "We have to put the parts together first, but we will be able to use it soon. We will miss our neighbors grill, but we can clean ours and make it sparkle like theirs." 

The daughter started to feel excited again, and jumped for joy! She was so excited to have a clean grill at their home.
<|end|>


