Once upon a time there was a small eye. The eye was so small that nobody could see it! But even though nobody could see it, the small eye still wanted to play.
It went up to a big eye and asked, "Will you play with me?" The big eye said, "No. I cannot see you. How can I play with you if I cannot see you?"

The small eye became very sad. Then, a kind eye saw the small eye and said, "I will play with you." The small eye felt so happy.
The kind eye said, "It is okay that you are small. I accept you." So the small eye and the kind eye played together for a long time and had lots of fun. 
The small eye was so happy to have a friend who accepted it just the way it was.
<|end|>


