Once upon a time, there was a little girl called Daisy. She was only three years old and very curious. 
One day, Daisy was walking through the park with her mum when she noticed something shiny on the ground. She picked it up and showed it to her mum - it was a big silver buckle! Her mum smiled and explained what the buckle was for. She showed Daisy how to use it to care for her favourite teddy bear, so that his clothes would stay nice and snug around him. Daisy was so proud of herself for learning how to do it, and gave her mum a big hug.

Afterwards, they went to the playground. Daisy's mum said it was time for a snack and surprised Daisy with a yummy lollipop. Daisy was delighted and ate it quickly, licking every last drop of the delicious sweet.

It was a very happy day for Daisy - she had learned how to care for her bear and eaten a yummy lollipop. She was very content and couldn't wait for her next adventure!
