Harry was a little boy. He was three years old. Every day, Harry tried to learn something new. One day he wanted to learn how to make his own thumbs messy.

He asked for his mum's help, but she said 'no'. His dad told him he had to work it out on his own. Harry thought and thought until he had a bright idea.

He went to the kitchen and found a bowl and spoon. He carefully scooped out some flour from a big jar and poured it into the bowl. Then, he put his thumbs into the flour and moved them around until they were really messy.

He was very proud of himself. He'd learned to make his thumbs messy all by himself!
