Mum and Dad took little Billy to the park. He saw some furry animals playing in the grass. He wanted to pet them, but he was scared. He started to cry softly, but Mum and Dad comforted him. They talked in calm voices and helped him understand that the animals were nice. So, Billy walked closer to the animals.

There was a big, hairy sheep standing by the fence. Billy was still a bit scared, but Mum showed him how to pet the sheep gently. So, he reached out his little hand and stroked the fuzzy fur. The animal felt soft and warm.

Billy smiled and looked around. He saw a furry rabbit hopping by, then a big, hairy cow munching grass. He was starting to feel brave, so he ran over to the cow and patted its fur. The cow looked at Billy and gave a soft moo.

Billy laughed and waved goodbye to the animals. The park was a safe and fun place. He felt happy and comforted, and he knew he would come back soon.
