Once upon a time, there was a bunny who loved to hop. Every day he would hop around, playing and having fun. 
One day, he heard a noise behind him and when he turned around he saw a mess! All around him was paper, boxes and toys. It was very messy!
The bunny was curious, so he hopped closer to explore. Suddenly, he heard a voice say, "Put it in order!" 
It was a mouse! She saw that the bunny wanted to help so she explained that she was trying to get her house in order. The bunny was pleased to help, so he jumped and hopped around, putting everything in the right place. 
When the mouse saw how tidy everything looked, she thanked the bunny and they played together. The bunny was so happy to have made a new friend. 
From that day on, the bunny and the mouse were best friends and they always remembered to keep their houses in order!
