John was a little boy who liked to wander. One day he was wandering in the park and he spotted a turkey. It was very big and quite messy. He had never seen one before and he wanted to get close to have a look. So he tip toed closer and closer. He sat down in the grass and the turkey walked over to him. It cautiously pecked at John's shoes. John thought it was so exciting and he stayed there for a while, watching the turkey. After a time, he started to wander again and he said goodbye to the turkey. As he walked away, he heard the turkey's loud gobble. He laughed and waved goodbye.
