Once upon a time there were two friends who did everything together. One day, they wanted to go for a walk in the woods, but they couldn't agree on which way to go.

The first friend wanted to go left, but the other wanted to go right. They disagreed and argued for a while. Then they spotted a big, empty barrel. They had an idea.

The two friends decided to flip the barrel to see which way they should go. They were patient, and they took turns flipping the barrel. Finally, it landed on its side and the top pointed to the right. 

The second friend was happy, but the first friend was sad. They both looked at the barrel and agreed to go the way it told them to. They hugged each other and went for a nice, peaceful walk.
<|end|>


