Once upon a time, there were two friends. One was called John, and the other Jane. Both of them loved to play together. 

One day, John and Jane wanted to play a game. Jane said, "Let's make a fence!" John thought it was a great idea, so they got some pieces of wood. Jane used her hands to make the wood pieces smooth, then John used his pen to print along the edges. 

When their fence was done, John looked at it. He said, "This looks so good!" Jane smiled and said, "That's because we worked together - look how much we can do when we help each other!" 

John and Jane learned that day that it is always better to work together. The fence they made taught them a very important lesson: a smooth fence is best built with cooperation.
