Once there was a large tool. It was very important to the people in the town. 

Every morning, a villager would carry the tool to the square to serve the people. Everyone in the town enjoyed the tool and were happy.

One day, a stranger came to the town. He said he wanted to serve the people too. The villager decided to let the stranger help. 

The stranger took the tool and started to use it. But then something terrible happened. The tool broke!

The townspeople were very sad. Without the tool, they no longer had a way to serve the people. The stranger apologized but it didn't help. 

The townspeople had to find a new way to serve the people. It was a very difficult task. They all felt bad that the large tool was ruined.
