Once upon a time, there was a fat cat called Fred. He was always hungry and looking for food. One day Fred decided to try and find food in the garden. He found some plastic containers. He thought they looked yummy. He started to eat them.

Suddenly, the owner of the garden, Mrs Brown, saw Fred eating the plastic. She was very cross. She told Fred to stop. She knew plastic wasn't food and it wouldn't make Fred stronger. She recommended that Fred should eat things like yummy fishes and birds that he could catch.

But Fred didn't listen. He kept eating the plastic. Mrs Brown decided she had to do something. She picked up Fred and put him back in her house. She put a bowl of food out for him and she didn't let him out again until she was sure the plastic was all gone.

Fred learned his lesson and from that day forward, he only ate the things Mrs Brown recommended.
