Today, the children went to the zoo. They saw many animals, like monkeys and tigers. They loved to watch the animals move and make noises! 

One of the children asked, "Why are the animals so heavy? What makes them so heavy?" 

The zookeeper smiled and explained, "The animals weigh a lot. That is why they look so massive!" 

The children looked amazed. The zookeeper continued, "You can see how the elephants weigh the most. They are the biggest animals here!" 

The children all nodded. They looked at the distant animals again and imagined how heavy they were. 

The children thanked the zookeeper before leaving the zoo. They went home feeling happy and amazed.
