Once upon a time there was a river. River was very wide and long.

One day, a little boy named Mark went to the river with his dad. He was so excited. When they got to the river, Mark saw a small boat on the water.

"Dad, can I get in the boat?" asked Mark.

"Yes, but you have to be very careful," said dad.

Mark was careful and he got in the boat. He took a paddle and started to paddle. Suddenly, he heard a loud bang!

Mark looked back and he saw that the door of the boat was shut tight. He was locked in the boat!

Mark was scared but his dad was there to help. His dad quickly opened the door and Mark got out of the boat.

Mark and his dad waved goodbye to the river and went home. Mark learned an important lesson that day: Always be careful around the river.
