The mommy duck went back to their house and got a huge rope. She tied the rope around the boat and then the ducks all started to pull. Slowly, the boat began to move out of the swamp and it was soon free!

The ducks were so happy. They started to cheer for themselves and danced around in their joy. Then, the mommy duck had the best idea yet. She told the ducks to reverse the rope and start pulling the other way. Slowly, the boat floated back into the swamp! The ducks had rescued the boat!

The ducks were so excited to have been able to help. They sang and cheered in their enthusiasm as they watched the old boat happily floating in the swamp.
