James was playing in the park. He loved to run around the trees and play tag with his friends. One day, as he was running, he heard a noise coming from a stream nearby. He glanced over and noticed a frog sitting on a rock. James thought the frog looked fragile, so he crept closer and decided to give it a pinch. But as he was reaching out his hand, the frog let out a croak, and it scared James! He jumped back and the frog hopped away, back into the stream. 

James was disappointed that he had scared the frog away. He felt guilty for trying to pinch it and gazed sadly at the stream. Suddenly, the frog popped its head out over the water and spoke: "It's okay. You didn't hurt me. Next time, just say hello before you come closer!"

James smiled and nodded. He said goodbye to the frog and promised to come back with a treat for it the next day. Then, he went back to playing tag with his friends.
