Once there was a little girl named Ella who wanted to climb a tall tree in her backyard. Her mom said she could use a rope to help pull herself up. Ella was excited to try, so she grabbed the rope and started climbing. She was graceful and determined as she made her way higher and higher. But soon, it became too hard. Her arms were tired and she couldn't keep going.

Ella wanted to keep trying, but she started to get discouraged. She decided to quit. Then, something amazing happened. As she said goodbye to the tree, she felt a sudden burst of strength. She kept hold of the rope and pulled herself up even higher. 

When Ella reached the top, she felt a sense of accomplishment and pride. She learned that had she just persevered a little bit longer, she could have made it to the top. Ella taught herself an important lesson that day: Never quit, even when things get hard!
