The fox said, "I'm here to give my opinion about the best way to make this forest better."

The rabbit was happy to hear this. He said, "That's great! Please tell me what your opinion is."

The fox said, "I think we should scatter seeds across the forest. That will make the forest beautiful."

The rabbit thought about this for a moment and said, "I agree. I think it's a very good idea!"

The rabbit and the fox scattered the seeds together. As they were working, they were both glad.

Moral: No matter who you are, it's always a great idea to think of ways to make things better.
