<|asst|>
Once upon a time, there was a messy pony. Her fur was all tangled and she was never groomed. The pony's owner was unkind to her, and never gave her any food or water. As days passed, the pony grew weaker and hungrier.

One day, the pony decided to escape. She ran away into the woods, but she still felt very hungry. She looked for some food, and eventually found some juicy grass. She ate as much as she could, until her belly was full.

However, the grass was not enough. The pony's hunger kept increasing. She kept looking for food, but she couldn't find any. She eventually got so weak that she couldn't stand up. The pony lay in the woods until she passed away.

The pony's hunger had grown too big in the end, and it was never satisfied.
<|end|>


