One day there was a little girl named Ella. She was 3 years old and wanted to go outside and play. But it was raining very hard. Ella saw a big puddle outside and decided it was time to have some fun. 

Ella ran over to the puddle, but she didn't want to get her shoes wet. So she found an old, rusty pedal in the grass and picked it up. She put the pedal in the middle of the puddle. 

Then Ella started to pour water onto the pedal. She splashed it with her hands and it looked like the pedal was going for a swim. Ella was laughing so hard she was about to fall down, but instead she kept pouring. 

But then the pedal started to move in circles - it was swimming alright, but it was swimming all by itself! Ella was so surprised, she didn't know what was happening. She was so excited she kept pouring even more water! 

But after a few seconds, the pedal stopped moving. It didn't seem so stupid anymore. Ella laughed and ran off to find more adventures.
<|end|>


