Casey was playing on the floor with her toys. She was having so much fun putting together blocks to make a castle. Suddenly, her mommy came in the room holding a pin. Mommy said to Casey, "Aren't I so smart for finding this pin?"

Casey said, "What's a pin?"

Her mommy smiled, held up the pin and said, "This is a pin. It's very small and can be used for different things. See how it sparkles in the light."

Casey smiled and said, "That's so cool! Can I have it?"

Mommy shook her head and said, "No, this is not for playing. If you disturb the pin you might get hurt."

Casey suddenly felt scared and stepped away from the pin. Then she looked around the room and saw all the toys she had been playing with. She hugged her mommy and said, "I'll leave the pin alone. I'd rather play with my toys."

Mommy smiled and gave Casey a big hug. "That's my smart girl," she said as they hugged.
<|end|>


