<|asst|>
Once upon a time, there was a small boy named Jack who loved to write. He wrote stories, drew pictures, and even wrote letters to his mom.

One day, Jack found a chest filled with paper, ink, and colored pencils. He was so excited and he ran to his mom to show her.

His mom said, "That's awesome, Jack! Where did you get it?"

Jack told his mom about the chest he found in the park. His mom looked concerned. She said, "I'm sorry, Jack. That chest looks wet, which means that it belongs to someone else. You should put everything back so it can belong to the right person. 

Jack reluctantly put the chest back in the park. He waited a few moments and soon he saw an old man walking towards the chest. The old man thanked Jack for finding it and told him that it had all his precious memories in it. 

Jack realized that it's important to respect people's property. He learned that if something doesn't belong to you, it's best to leave it alone and not take it. 

Jack smiled and went home, proud of himself for doing the right thing.
<|end|>


