One sunny day, a little boy named Tim was playing in the park. He was running around the playground and having lots of fun. 

There was a big, square sandpit in the park and Tim loved to kick the sand around. One day, he kicked too hard and flew out of the sandpit and landed on a patch of grass. 

But while Tim landed in the soft grass, he realised he had left something behind. His favourite red ball!

But the sandpit was too deep for him to climb out of. He started to cry until a friendly voice said â€œDonâ€™t worry, itâ€™s alright. If youâ€™re persistent, you can get the ball back.â€

Tim was surprised and he looked around to see who was talking. A tall rabbit was smiling at him and he said â€œItâ€™s easy. Just run around the sandpit three times and I promise you will get your ball back.â€

So Tim followed the rabbitâ€™s advice, and sure enough, after a few laps, his red ball appeared at the edge of the sandpit.

Tim was so happy. He thanked the friendly rabbit and ran off with his ball. He was definitely a persistent boy.
