Alex was so excited - his much-loved aunt was visiting for the weekend and he couldn't wait to see her!

"Mummy!, Alex shouted, "Auntie is here! I'm going to get her."

Alex ran to his aunt and gave her a big hug. She hugged him back and said, "Oh Alex, it's so nice to see you. You look so tall - you must be growing up so fast." 

Alex and his aunt began to play together. His aunt showed him how to make a soft pillow for his teddy bear, and Alex was very proud of the pillow he made!

But then Alex's mum walked in the room, and said "Alex, it's time to get ready for bed". Alex's aunt nodded, knowing it was time for him to leave. 

That night, as Alex lay in bed, he thought about brand-new pillow he had made. He thought of how his aunt had taken her time to explain and guide him, and he realised how important it was to mind his parents too.

With this in mind, Alex felt glad he had a special aunt to look up to, and he drifted off to sleep with a warm, happy feeling in his heart.
<|end|>


