<|asst|>
Once there was a little bird named Walter. He was very dependable and never worried about anything. He lived in a small tree by the river.

One day, Walter found a notebook on the ground. He picked it up and read, "Never worry and always be dependable." Walter thought it was strange, but he liked the message.

Walter wanted to share it with his friends, so he hopped around and told every bird he could find, "Never worry and always be dependable!"

One of his friends, a little sparrow named Sarah, was a bit scared. She asked Walter, "What if something bad happens? How can I not worry?"

Walter smiled and took out the notebook. He said, "Just remember what it says in here. If you stay dependable and don't worry, everything will be okay."

Sarah smiled too and understood. Walter had given her the best advice. From that day forward, she stopped worrying and stayed dependable.
<|end|>


