Once upon a time there was a little girl named Mary. Mary loved to dance and sing, but she had a problem. One day she noticed that her skirt was pale. Mary was unhappy and asked her mum for help.

Mum said, "Let's go and buy something new to replace the pale skirt."

So they went to the store together. Mary saw a bright pink skirt and said she wanted to try it on. Mum laughed and said, "Why don't we try that one. It looks pretty."

So Mary put on the new skirt and spun around the store. Everyone laughed and said how lovely it looked.

Mum said, "Let's buy this one. It will replace your pale skirt."

Mary smiled and said yes. She was so happy she had found the perfect skirt to replace the pale one. From then on she always felt beautiful when she danced.
<|end|>


