One day, there was a little boy called Lee. He found a big bowl of dough in the kitchen and he was so excited. He quickly grabbed a spoon and started to stir it. Then he added some sugar and stirred again. 

Suddenly, his mom came in to the kitchen and said, "Lee, what are you doing?"
Lee said, "Mommy, I am making dough."
His mom replied, "Yes, but dough needs to be washed before you can eat it."
Lee's face turned sad, but he quickly remembered that his mom always gives him good advice. 

So, he washed the dough and found it tasted much better and looked brighter. From that day on, Lee always remembered to wash whatever he wanted to eat. 

The moral of the story is to remember to always wash things before you eat them.
<|end|>


