Once upon a time, there was a little girl who loved to write. She would write all kinds of things, like stories and poems. One of the poems was so incredible that she wanted to keep it forever. So she decided to bury it. 

She went outside and found a spot in her garden that was perfect for burying her poem. She put a big spoonful of dirt on top and patted it down. Then she said goodbye to her poem and whispered, "I hope nobody finds it!" 

The little girl was happy that her poem was safe. Every day she would come and visit it, just to make sure it was still okay. She loved knowing that her poem would last forever, deep down in the warm, soft soil of her garden. 

The little girl thought that burying her incredible poem was the best thing she ever did!
<|end|>


