Timmy was happy; he had a new toy. It was colorful and had lots of buttons. He was excited to play with it. 

Mommy saw him and said, "Let's practice balancing with the toy. See if you can stand still." 

Timmy tried to stand still but it was hard. He tried balancing himself on the toy. After a few attempts he was able to balance. 

Mommy was so proud. "Good job Timmy. Balancing is very important," she said. 

Next they went to the playground. There was lots of equipment, a swing, a slide, a seesaw and a merry-go-round. 

Timmy wanted to try them all. Mommy said, "Let's try one at a time. We don't want to be too busy." 

So Timmy started with the swing and then he moved on to the slide. In the end, he had lots of fun balancing on all the different equipment. 

Mommy smiled, "You had so much fun balancing. Good job!"
<|end|>


