Once there was a nosy little girl named Anne. She wanted to buy a basketball, but she didn't have any money. She walked up to a man and asked him, "can I sell something to you?" The man was curious, so he asked Anne to show him what she had to sell.

Anne showed him a toy car. The man said he wouldn't buy the car but he knew someone who would. He took Anne to meet his friend and told him about the toy car that Anne had to sell. The friend bought it from Anne and she got enough money to buy the basketball she wanted!

When Anne got home with her basketball, her mom was very happy for her. Now Anne and her mom could play together outside in the yard. Anne was so happy that she sold her toy car for the basketball. She had a lot of fun every day playing with her mom.
<|end|>


