Once upon a time, there was a huge tree in the forest. Every day, the tree would gain bigger and bigger and its roots went deeper and deeper in the ground. Soon enough, the tree was so huge, it was the biggest in the whole forest.

Everyday, the children in the forest would come to the tree and climb it. They could go so high up, it felt like they were almost touching the sky! They would have so much fun up there.

Eventually, the roots of the tree grew so strong, they were like huge tentacles pushing through the ground. The kids in the forest were amazed and couldn't believe how big the tree had become.

The kids climbed it every day and even used the big roots to play games. They would slide down them, swing from them and even touch them.

The tree stayed in the forest for many years and the kids were so happy when the huge tree was around. But one day, the tree blew down in a big storm and the kids were sad. Nonetheless, they still held fond memories of the huge tree in the forest forever.
<|end|>


