Once there was a little boy who loved to explore. One day, he was out playing in the woods and found a big pile of lumber. He was so excited, he spent all day playing on it.

He would climb, jump and spin around. It was so big, he thought it was the best playground ever.

But something was wrong. The lumber started to move! The little boy was very scared. It was a snake!

It was very big and dangerous. The little boy jumped back and watched as the snake slithered away. But he knew he had to do something, so he carefully grabbed a stick and started to rub the lumber.

He rubbed and rubbed until all the rough edges were smooth. Then the little boy knew he was safe. He had a new playground and the snake was gone.
<|end|>


