<|asst|>
Once upon a time, there lived an old man by the ocean. Every day, he would take a boat out to sea and stare curiously at the horizon.

One day, it happened to be the most beautiful day yet - the sky was a brilliant blue and the sun shone in all its glory. As the old man gazed out across the endless ocean, he saw a graceful ship coming his way.

He quickly grabbed his binoculars and called out to the ship, 
"Ahoy! What brings you here?"

The ship slowly pulled up alongside the old man's boat, and a voice boomed out, "We are here to pour some grace on the ocean".

The old man was confused - why would they be pouring grace on the ocean? He watched with awe as the crew on the ship began to pour sparkling liquid into the ocean, making the waters glimmer and shine brightly.

The old man smiled. What a wonderful sight! He thanked the crew for their kind efforts, and he knew that his boat was now surrounded by grace - so much it was spilling over into the ocean of the world. 

The old man waved goodbye and set sail back to shore with a feeling of contentment.
<|end|>


