<|asst|>
Once upon a time, there were two children; one was named Alex and the other one was named Maria. Alex was jealous of Maria because Maria had a special cone that made her look taller. Alex wanted to have a cone like his friend Maria. 

So, one day Alex and Maria went to a special places that sold cones. Alex looked at all of the cones to find the perfect one. He wanted one that was heavy enough to make him as tall as Maria. He chose a cone that was very heavy, but he was still shorter than Maria. Disappointed, Alex took the cone home. 

That night, Alex was playing with his new cone when he heard a noise from outside. It was Maria, who had come to see him. She had brought a secret for Alex; it was a sack full of stones. Since Alex's cone was so heavy, it was the perfect size for stones. She had weighed the stones to make sure that Alex's cone was heavy enough. 

Alex was so happy to have found a special friend like Maria. He learned that when we can't get what we want, it can sometimes turn out to be something much better if we trust our friends. He learned that it's not wise to be jealous of other people's stuff. Alex and Maria remained good friends after that day.  The End.
<|end|>


