Lily liked to play with her drum. She liked the sound it made when she hit it with her sticks. She liked the rhythm of her drum. It made her happy and she danced.

One day, her drum broke. She hit it too hard and it made a loud noise. Then it was quiet. Lily was sad. She cried and hugged her drum.

Dad saw Lily crying. He asked her what was wrong. Lily showed him her drum. Dad said he could repair it. He took the drum and some tools. He worked hard and fixed the drum.

He gave the drum back to Lily. He told her to be gentle with it. Lily was happy. She thanked Dad and gave him a hug. She played with her drum again. She made a little rhythm with her sticks. She smiled and danced.
<|end|>


