Ben and Mia are friends. They like to play together. One day, they go to the park with their moms. They see a big slide. They want to go on the slide.

"Can we go on the slide, mom?" Ben asks.

"Yes, you can. But be careful and wait your turn," his mom says.

Ben and Mia run to the slide. They are enthusiastic. They love the motion of sliding down fast. They laugh and scream.

"Wow, this is fun!" Mia says.

"I want to do it again!" Ben says.

They go up and down the slide many times. They are happy. Their moms watch them and smile. They are proud of their children. They think they are brave and kind. They have a good time at the park.
