Anna likes to play with her dolls. She has many dolls, but her favorite is Lily. Lily has long hair, a pink dress and a fake smile. Anna likes to brush Lily's hair and talk to her.

One day, Anna's mom says they have to send Lily away. Anna is sad and asks why. Mom says Lily is old and broken. She says Lily has to go to a place where they fix dolls. Anna does not want Lily to go. She says Lily is not broken, she is perfect.

Mom says it will only be for a little while. She says Lily will come back soon and they can play again. She says they can visit Lily at the place where they fix dolls. Anna is still sad, but she nods. She gives Lily a big hug and a kiss. She says she will miss her.

Mom puts Lily in a box and takes her to the car. Anna goes with her. They drive to the place where they fix dolls. It is a big building with many windows. Mom says they have to leave Lily here. She says they will come back tomorrow to visit her.

Anna looks at the box. She sees Lily's fake smile. She hopes Lily is not scared. She hopes Lily knows she loves her. She says goodbye to Lily and waves. She says she will see her soon. She tries to be brave. She goes with mom to the car. She thinks about Lily. She wonders what they will do to her. She hopes they will be nice. She hopes they will make her happy. She hopes they will send her back soon.
