Lily and Ben were twins who liked to play in the garden. They had a big tree with many fruits. They liked to pick the fruits and share them with their friends.

One day, they saw a bird in the tree. The bird was singing a beautiful song. Lily and Ben wanted to talk to the bird.

"Hello, bird," Lily said. "What is your name?"

"Hello, children," the bird said. "My name is Blue. I live in this tree. I like the fruits here. They are sweet and juicy."

"Can we be your friends, Blue?" Ben asked. "We like the fruits too. We can share them with you."

"Of course, you can be my friends," Blue said. "You are kind and gentle. You belong in this garden. It is a peaceful place."

Lily and Ben smiled. They were happy to have a new friend. They picked some fruits and gave them to Blue. Blue thanked them and sang another song. They listened and enjoyed the music. They felt the sun and the breeze. They felt the love and the joy. They felt that they belonged.
