Sara and Ben were twins who loved to play pretend. One day, they decided to make a tea party for their stuffed animals. Sara put some cups and plates on a tray and Ben filled them with water and juice. They carried the tray to the living room, where they had set up a table and chairs.

"Be careful, Ben," Sara said. "Don't spill the drinks. Promise me."

"I promise, Sara," Ben said. "I'm very careful."

They put the tray on the table and invited their stuffed animals to sit down. They had a bear, a rabbit, a cat, and a dog. They poured the drinks and pretended to eat cookies and cake. They talked and laughed and had a lot of fun.

Suddenly, they heard a loud noise. It was their big brother, Tom, who had come home from school. He saw the tea party and smiled. He wanted to join them, but he was too big for the small chairs. He decided to sit on the floor instead.

"Hi, Sara and Ben," he said. "Can I have some tea?"

"Sure, Tom," Sara said. "But you have to be careful. Don't break the cups. Promise me."

"I promise, Sara," Tom said. "I'm very careful."

He reached for the tray and picked up a cup. But he didn't notice that the tray was not very stable. As he lifted the cup, the tray tilted and all the drinks spilled on the floor. The cups and plates crashed and broke. The stuffed animals got wet and dirty.

"Tom!" Sara and Ben cried. "You broke your promise! You ruined our tea party!"

Tom felt bad. He didn't mean to make a mess. He apologized to Sara and Ben and their stuffed animals. He helped them clean up the floor and the tray. He gave them a hug and said he was sorry.

"It's okay, Tom," Sara and Ben said. "We forgive you. But next time, please be more careful. Promise us."

"I promise, Sara and Ben," Tom said. "I'm very careful."

They smiled and hugged him back. They decided to make another tea party later, with a bigger table and chairs and an enormous tray. They invited Tom to join them again, as long as he kept his promise.
<|end|>


