<|asst|>
Ben and Lily wanted to mail a card to their grandma. They drew pictures of flowers and hearts on the card. They wrote "We love you, Grandma" with big letters. They put the card in an envelope and asked their mom for a stamp.

"Can we go to the mailbox now, Mom?" Ben asked.

"Not yet, sweeties. We have to go to the store first. We need to buy some squash for dinner. Do you want to help me pick one?" Mom said.

"Yes, Mom!" Lily said. She liked squash. It was orange and soft and sweet.

They got in the car and drove to the store. Mom gave them a basket and told them to look for the squash. They saw many different kinds of squash. Some were green, some were yellow, some were round, some were long.

"Which one should we get, Ben?" Lily asked.

"Let's get this one!" Ben said. He pointed to a big, orange squash. It looked like a pumpkin, but smaller.

"OK, Ben. That's a good one. It's called a butternut squash. It's very tasty and healthy. Let's see if it's available." Lily said. She looked at the price tag. It said $1.99 per pound.

"Is that a lot, Lily?" Ben asked.

"I don't know, Ben. Let's ask Mom." Lily said. They took the squash to Mom, who was buying some apples.

"Mom, can we get this squash?" Lily asked.

"Sure, honey. That's a nice squash. Let me weigh it for you." Mom said. She put the squash on the scale. It said 2.5 pounds.

"That's $4.98, kids. Do you have enough money?" Mom asked.

Ben and Lily looked at each other. They had saved some coins in their piggy bank. They had $5.00.

"Yes, Mom! We have enough money!" Ben said.

"Great! Then you can buy the squash with your own money. That's very grown-up of you. I'm proud of you, kids." Mom said.

She gave them the money and they paid the cashier. They put the squash in their basket and went back to the car.

"Now can we go to the mailbox, Mom?" Ben asked.

"Yes, of course. Let's go mail your card to Grandma. She will be very happy to receive it." Mom said.

They drove to the mailbox and Ben and Lily took turns to put the envelope in the slot. They waved goodbye to the card and hoped Grandma would like it.

They went home and Mom cooked the squash for dinner. It was delicious. Ben and Lily ate it all. They felt happy and full.

They called Grandma on the phone and told her about their day. They told her they mailed her a card and bought a squash. Grandma said she loved them very much and thanked them for the card and the squash. She said she would mail them a card back soon.

Ben and Lily smiled and said goodnight to Grandma. They hugged Mom and went to bed. They dreamed of flowers and hearts and squash.
<|end|>


