Lila was playing with her dolls in the garden. She liked to dress them up and make them talk. She had a pretty bracelet that her mama gave her. It was shiny and pink and had little flowers on it. She put it on her favorite doll, Anna.

But then she heard a loud noise. It was a big dog. It was black and hairy and had sharp teeth. It ran towards her and barked. Lila was very scared. She dropped her dolls and ran to the house. She cried for her mama.

The dog saw the dolls on the ground. It sniffed them and picked one up. It was Anna. The dog bit her and shook her. The bracelet fell off and got dirty. The dog did not like the bracelet. It spat it out and ran away.

Lila's mama came out and hugged her. She saw the dog running away and the dolls on the ground. She was angry and sad. She picked up Anna and saw the holes and the dirt. She picked up the bracelet and saw the filth. She said, "Oh, Lila, I'm sorry. That dog was very bad. He scared you and hurt your dolls and your bracelet."

Lila said, "Mama, can you fix Anna and my bracelet? They are my favorite things. I love them." Mama said, "I will try, Lila. I love you. You are brave. Let's go inside and clean them up." She took Lila and her dolls and her bracelet to the house. She washed them and sewed them and polished them. She made them look nice again. Lila was happy. She hugged her mama and said, "Thank you, mama. You are the best." Mama said, "You're welcome, Lila. You are the best, too." They smiled and played with the dolls and the bracelet. They were not scared anymore.
<|end|>


