Ben and Lily were playing in the garden. They had a big box of toys and they liked to make up stories with them. Ben had a toy car and Lily had a doll.

"Vroom, vroom, my car is very fast!" Ben said, zooming his car around the grass.

"My doll is very pretty, she has a pink dress and a bow," Lily said, brushing her doll's hair.

Suddenly, they heard a loud caw from a big black bird. It was a raven, and it was sitting on the fence. It looked at Ben and Lily with its shiny eyes.

"Hello, raven," Ben said. "Do you want to play with us?"

The raven cawed again and flew down to the box of toys. It picked up a toy truck with its beak and flew back to the fence.

"Hey, that's my truck!" Ben shouted. "Give it back, raven!"

The raven shook its head and cawed. It liked the toy truck. It was shiny and noisy.

"No, no, no, it's mine, mine, mine!" the raven said.

Lily frowned. She thought the raven was very nosy and rude. It should not take other people's toys.

"Raven, you are not nice," Lily said. "You should share and be kind. If you want to play with us, you have to ask first."

The raven looked at Lily and tilted its head. It thought for a moment. Then it nodded and cawed.

"Okay, okay, okay, I will share, share, share," the raven said.

It flew back to the box of toys and put the toy truck down. Then it picked up a toy ball and tossed it to Ben.

"Here, here, here, you can have this, this, this," the raven said.

Ben smiled and caught the ball. He threw it back to the raven.

"Thank you, raven," Ben said. "You are a good friend."

The raven cawed happily and played catch with Ben. Lily joined them with her doll. They had fun together in the garden. The raven was not nosy and rude anymore. It was nice and polite. It learned to share and ask.
<|end|>


