Sam and Mia are friends. They like to play outside. One day, it is very cold and windy. Sam and Mia wear warm hats and coats. They look for a place to play.

"Look, there is a big box!" Sam says. "We can make a shelter with it."

"Good idea!" Mia says. "Let's go inside the box."

They run to the box and lift it up. They find a spot under a tree. They put the box down and crawl inside. The box is cozy and dry. They have fun pretending it is their house.

"Hello, neighbor!" Sam says to Mia. "Do you want some tea?"

"Yes, please!" Mia says. "And some cookies, too."

They pretend to have tea and cookies. They laugh and talk. They do not feel the cold and the wind.

After a while, they hear a voice. It is Sam's mom. She is looking for them.

"Sam, Mia, where are you?" she calls.

"Here, mom!" Sam says. He and Mia come out of the box. They wave to Sam's mom.

"Are you okay?" she asks. "It is very cold and windy today."

"We are fine, mom!" Sam says. "We have a shelter. It is our house."

Sam's mom smiles. She sees the box and the tree. She thinks they are very clever and creative.

"That is a nice shelter," she says. "But it is time to go home now. Come on, let's go."

Sam and Mia say goodbye to their shelter. They pick up their hats and coats. They follow Sam's mom. They are happy. They had a good day.
