Sam is a boy who likes to help his mom. He helps her cook, clean and deliver things. Mom has a big iron that makes clothes smooth. Sam likes to watch the iron go up and down.

One day, mom says she has to deliver some smooth clothes to Mrs. Lee. She asks Sam if he wants to come with her. Sam says yes. He likes Mrs. Lee. She has a big dog and a nice garden.

Mom and Sam put the smooth clothes in a big bag. They walk to Mrs. Lee's house. The dog barks and wags his tail. He is happy to see them. Mrs. Lee opens the door and smiles. She thanks mom for the smooth clothes. She gives mom some money and Sam a cookie.

The cookie is tasty. It has chocolate chips and nuts. Sam says thank you and bites the cookie. Mom and Sam say goodbye to Mrs. Lee and the dog. They walk back home. Sam is happy. He helped mom and got a tasty cookie. He thinks delivering is fun.
