Sara was very happy. Today was her birthday. She wanted to see her friends and get presents. She put on her pink dress and ran to the door.

"Mom, can we go now?" she asked.

"Yes, sweetie, we can go. But first, look what came in the mail for you. A package!" Mom said, holding a big box.

Sara clapped her hands. "A package for me? Who is it from?"

"Let's open it and see," Mom said. She cut the tape and lifted the lid.

Sara peeked inside. She saw a brown bear with a red bow. She smiled. She loved bears. She reached for it.

But then, something terrible happened. The bear moved. It was not a toy. It was a real bear. It growled and showed its teeth. It jumped out of the box and ran around the room.

Sara screamed. Mom screamed. The bear knocked over the lamp and the vase. It scratched the couch and the rug. It was very angry and scared.

"Help! Help!" Sara and Mom shouted.

Dad heard the noise. He ran to the living room. He saw the bear. He grabbed a broom and tried to chase it away.

"Go away, bear! Go away!" he yelled.

The bear did not like the broom. It ran to the door. It opened it with its paw. It ran outside.

Sara, Mom, and Dad followed it. They saw the mailman on the street. He looked very confused.

"Sorry, sorry, I made a mistake. That package was not for you. It was for the zoo. I mixed up the labels. I'm so sorry," he said.

Sara, Mom, and Dad were very relieved. They were glad the bear was gone. They hugged each other.

"Wow, that was a very bad birthday surprise," Sara said.

"Yes, it was. But don't worry, honey. We still have your party. And your friends. And your cake. And your real presents. Come on, let's go and have some fun," Mom said.

Sara nodded. She was still a little scared. But she was also happy. She hoped she would never meet a bear in a package again.
<|end|>


