Sara and Ben were playing in the garden. They had a spray bottle and a bucket of water. They liked to spray water on the flowers and the grass. They pretended they were making rain.

"Look, Sara, look!" Ben said. He pointed to something shiny in the dirt. "What is that?"

Sara went closer and saw a small, round, colorful thing. It sparkled in the sun. "Wow, Ben, it's a gem!" she said. "Maybe it's a treasure!"

They dug around the gem with their hands. They tried to pull it out, but it was stuck. They sprayed water on it, hoping it would come loose.

Suddenly, they heard a loud noise. It was a big dog, barking and running towards them. The dog wanted to play, but Sara and Ben were scared. They dropped the spray bottle and the gem and ran to the house.

"Mommy, mommy, help!" they cried. "There's a big, loud dog in the garden!"

Mommy came out and saw the dog. She knew it was their neighbor's dog, Max. She called his name and he wagged his tail. She gave him a treat and he followed her to the fence.

"Sorry, kids, Max got out of his yard. He's friendly, but he's very excited. He likes to chase things," she said. "Are you OK?"

Sara and Ben nodded. They were still shaking. They hugged mommy and told her about the gem.

"Can we go back and get it, mommy?" Sara asked.

"Of course, sweetie. But be careful, it might be sharp or dirty. And don't spray water on it, it might ruin it," mommy said.

They went back to the garden, holding mommy's hand. They found the spray bottle and the gem. They cleaned it with a cloth and looked at it. It was very pretty.

"Can we keep it, mommy?" Ben asked.

"Sure, honey. It's your lucky gem. Maybe you can make a necklace or a bracelet with it," mommy said.

Sara and Ben smiled. They thanked mommy and hugged her. They were happy. They had found a gem and made a friend.
<|end|>


