Lily liked to watch the big boats on the water. She liked the colors and the sounds and the people. She wanted to be a sailor when she grew up. She asked her dad, who was a sailor, to take her on a boat someday.

"Maybe when you are older, Lily," her dad said. "Being a sailor is hard work. You have to be busy all the time and follow the rules. And sometimes you have to go away for a long time and miss your family."

Lily was sad. She did not want her dad to go away. She wanted to be with him and see the boats. She hugged him and said, "I love you, dad. Please don't go."

Her dad smiled and hugged her back. He said, "I love you too, Lily. I have to go for a little while, but I will return soon. I will bring you a gift from the sea. And maybe we can go on a boat together then."

Lily nodded. She hoped her dad would return soon. She waved goodbye to him as he left with his bag. She watched him get on a big boat with other sailors. She saw the boat sail away until it was a small dot on the water.

She waited for many days. She missed her dad a lot. She played with her mom and her toys, but she always looked at the water and wondered when her dad would come back. She dreamed of the gift he would bring her.

One day, she heard a loud horn. She ran to the window and saw a big boat coming back. She saw the colors and the sounds and the people. She saw her dad waving at her. She was so happy. She ran to the door and put on her shoes. She said to her mom, "Dad is back! Dad is back!"

She ran to the dock and jumped into her dad's arms. He hugged her and kissed her. He said, "I missed you, Lily. I'm so glad to see you. Look what I brought you from the sea."

He gave her a small box. She opened it and saw a shiny necklace with a shell. It was beautiful. She said, "Thank you, dad. It's the best gift ever. I love you."

He said, "You're welcome, Lily. I love you too. Do you want to go on a boat with me now?"

She nodded. She put on the necklace and held her dad's hand. They walked to the boat and got on. They sailed on the water and saw the colors and the sounds and the people. Lily was happy. She was a sailor with her dad.
<|end|>


