Tom and Lily were playing with their toy animals in the garden. They liked to make noises and stories for each animal. Tom had a big rhinoceros that he liked to pretend was very strong and scary. Lily had a small rabbit that she liked to pretend was very sweet and friendly.

"Roar!" Tom said, making his rhinoceros charge at Lily's rabbit. "I am the king of the animals! No one can stop me!"

"Stop, Tom!" Lily said, holding her rabbit close. "You are being too bossy! You can't hurt my rabbit! He is my friend!"

"But I want to play!" Tom said, making his rhinoceros stomp and snort. "It is fun to be the king! You have to do what I say!"

"No, I don't!" Lily said, getting angry. "You are not the king! You are just a mean boy! I don't want to play with you anymore!"

She turned around and ran away, leaving her rabbit behind. Tom paused for a moment, feeling sad and sorry. He wanted to say sorry to Lily and give her back her rabbit. But before he could, he heard a loud bark and saw a big dog running towards him. The dog saw the rabbit and thought it was a real one. It grabbed the rabbit in its mouth and ran away, tearing it apart.

Tom screamed and cried, but it was too late. The dog had ruined Lily's rabbit. Lily heard Tom's scream and came back, but when she saw what had happened, she cried too. She was very mad at Tom and blamed him for everything. She said she hated him and never wanted to see him again.

Tom felt very bad and wished he had not been so bossy. He wished he had been nicer to Lily and her rabbit. He wished he could go back and change everything. But he couldn't. He had lost his friend and her toy. He had learned a hard lesson. He had made a big mistake.
<|end|>


