<|asst|>
Lily loved to wear her mom's dresses and shoes. She liked to look at herself in the mirror and pretend she was a princess. She felt very beautiful and happy.

One day, she saw a new dress in her mom's closet. It was pink and shiny and had many flowers on it. Lily wanted to wear it very much. She took it out and put it on. She ran to the mirror to see how she looked.

"Wow, I look so pretty!" she said to herself. "I want to show this to my mom and dad. They will be so proud of me."

She went downstairs to find her parents. But she did not see the stairs very well. She tripped and fell. The dress ripped and got dirty. Lily cried and cried.

Her mom and dad heard her and came to help her. They saw the dress and were very sad.

"Lily, why did you wear this dress?" her mom asked. "This was a special dress for a special occasion. You should have asked me first."

"I'm sorry, mom," Lily said. "I just wanted to look beautiful like you."

Her dad hugged her and said, "Lily, you are always beautiful to us. You don't need to wear fancy clothes to be beautiful. You are beautiful because you are kind, smart and brave. That's what matters most."

Lily felt sorry and hugged her parents. She learned that beauty is not only about how you look, but how you act. She also learned to respect her mom's things and ask for permission. She said sorry to her mom and helped her fix the dress. Her mom smiled and said, "I love you, Lily. You are my beautiful princess."
<|end|>


