<|end|>
<|asst|>
Anna and Ben are twins. They like to play with their toys and books. But sometimes they get tired and need a nap. Mommy tells them to go to their room and sleep for a little while.

"Can we keep playing, Mommy?" Anna asks. She holds her doll and makes it talk.

"No, sweetie, you need a nap. You can play more later. Naps are good for you. They make you grow and learn," Mommy says. She gives Anna a kiss and tucks her in.

"But I'm not sleepy, Mommy," Ben says. He holds his truck and makes it zoom. "I want to play with my truck. It's impressive. It can go fast and make noises."

"I know, honey, your truck is impressive. But you need a nap too. You can play with your truck more later. Naps are good for you. They make you strong and happy," Mommy says. She gives Ben a kiss and tucks him in.

Mommy leaves the room and closes the door. Anna and Ben look at each other. They are not sleepy. They want to keep playing.

"Let's pretend we are asleep," Anna whispers. "Then Mommy won't know."

"OK," Ben whispers. "But don't make any noise."

They close their eyes and lie still. They think they are very clever. But soon they feel very cozy and warm. They forget about their toys and books. They fall asleep and have nice dreams. They have a good nap after all.
<|end|>


