<|asst|>
Sara and Ben were at the beach with Mom and Dad. They liked to play in the sand and splash in the water. They also liked to look for shells and rocks and other things that the sea left behind.

One day, they saw a big rock with a hole in it. Sara wondered what was inside. She wanted to peek. Ben was scared. He said there might be a monster or a snake or a spider. Sara said he was silly. She said it was just a rock.

She crawled closer to the hole and put her eye near it. She saw something move. It was red and shiny and had many legs and claws. It was a crab! Sara was surprised and excited. She called Ben to come and see.

Ben was curious but still nervous. He walked slowly to the rock and peeked with Sara. He saw the crab too. He thought it looked dull and boring. He said it was not a monster or a snake or a spider. He said it was just a crab.

The crab heard them and did not like them. It was angry and scared. It wanted them to go away. It snapped its claws and made a loud noise. Sara and Ben jumped back and screamed. They ran to Mom and Dad and told them what they saw.

Mom and Dad smiled and hugged them. They said they were brave and clever to find a crab. They said crabs were not dull and boring. They said crabs were amazing and beautiful. They said they would show them more crabs and other animals that lived in the sea. Sara and Ben were happy and eager. They wanted to learn more about the sea. They forgot their fear and went back to the beach with Mom and Dad.
<|end|>


