<|asst|>
Anna and Ben are friends. They like to play in the park. They see a big slide. They want to go on the slide.

"Let's go on the slide!" Anna says.

"OK!" Ben says.

They run to the slide. But they see a problem. There is a part of the slide that is hidden. They cannot see where the slide goes.

"Where does the slide go?" Anna asks.

"I don't know," Ben says.

They are scared. They do not want to go on the slide.

"Maybe there is a monster in the hidden part," Anna says.

"Maybe there is a trap in the hidden part," Ben says.

They look at each other. They do not want to go on the slide.

But then they hear a voice. It is a nice voice. It is coming from the hidden part.

"Hello! Who are you?" the voice says.

Anna and Ben are surprised. They look at the hidden part.

"Who are you?" Anna says.

"I am Sam. I am on the slide. I am having fun. Do you want to join me?" the voice says.

Anna and Ben are curious. They want to see Sam. They want to have fun.

"OK, we will join you," Ben says.

They go on the slide. They slide down the hidden part. They see Sam. He is a boy. He is smiling. He is not a monster. He is not a trap. He is a friend.

"Hi, Sam!" Anna and Ben say.

"Hi, Anna and Ben!" Sam says.

They are happy. They play on the slide. They have fun. They are friends.
<|end|>


