<|end|>
<|asst|>
Tom and Sue were playing with their toy soldiers and rockets in the backyard. They liked to pretend they were in a big war and make loud noises. Sue had a red rocket that could fly very fast and hit the bad guys. Tom had a green rocket that could shrink anything it touched.

"Watch out, Sue! I'm going to shrink your red rocket with my green one!" Tom shouted.

"No, you can't! My red rocket is too strong and smart for your green one!" Sue said.

They threw their rockets at each other, trying to hit the other's toy. But they missed and their rockets flew over the fence and into the neighbor's yard.

"Oh no! We lost our rockets!" Tom and Sue cried.

They ran to the fence and looked over. They saw their rockets lying on the grass, next to a big black dog. The dog was sleeping and did not see the rockets.

"Let's get our rockets back!" Tom said.

"Be careful, Tom! The dog might wake up and bite us!" Sue said.

Tom and Sue climbed over the fence and tiptoed towards their rockets. They reached them and grabbed them. But as they did, the dog opened its eyes and saw them. It growled and barked and jumped at them.

"Run, Sue, run!" Tom yelled.

They ran back to the fence, but the dog was faster. It caught up with them and bit Tom's leg. Tom screamed and dropped his green rocket. The green rocket hit the dog's nose and made it shrink. The dog became very small and ran away, yelping.

"Tom, are you okay?" Sue asked.

Tom looked at his leg. It was bleeding and hurt a lot. He started to cry.

"I'm not okay, Sue. The dog bit me and I'm bleeding. I need a band-aid and a hug." Tom said.

Sue hugged Tom and said, "Don't cry, Tom. I'll get Mom and she'll make you feel better. You're brave and strong, Tom. You saved us from the dog."

She ran to the house and got Mom. Mom came and saw Tom's leg. She cleaned it and put a band-aid on it. She hugged Tom and said, "You're a good boy, Tom. I'm proud of you. You and Sue were very lucky. The dog could have hurt you more. Next time, don't play with rockets near the dog. Rockets are dangerous and can make things dead."

Tom and Sue nodded and said, "We're sorry, Mom. We won't play with rockets near the dog again. We love you, Mom."

Mom smiled and said, "I love you too, Tom and Sue. Now, let's go inside and have some cookies and milk. You deserve a treat."
<|end|>


