<|asst|>
Lily and Tom are friends. They like to play with toys and sing songs. One day, they find a big box in the park. They open the box and see a big toy. It is a robot.

"Wow, look at this!" Lily says. "It is a robot. Maybe it can talk."

"Let's test it," Tom says. He pushes a button on the robot. The robot makes a funny voice. It says, "Hello, I am Robo. I can do many things. What do you want me to do?"

Lily and Tom laugh. They think the robot is funny. They ask the robot to dance, to sing, to tell jokes. The robot does everything they ask. They have a lot of fun.

But then, they hear a voice. It is a man. He says, "Hey, that is my robot. I left it here by mistake. Give it back to me."

Lily and Tom are scared. They do not want to give the robot back. They like the robot. They say, "No, it is our robot. We found it. We want to play with it."

The man is angry. He says, "No, it is not your robot. It is mine. I made it. It is very expensive. You cannot keep it. It is not nice to take things that are not yours."

Lily and Tom feel bad. They realize they are wrong. They say, "We are sorry. We did not know it was yours. We thought it was a toy. We had fun with it. But we will give it back to you."

The man is happy. He says, "Thank you. You are good kids. I am glad you had fun with my robot. But you should always ask before you use something that is not yours. That is the right thing to do."

Lily and Tom nod. They say, "We understand. We will ask next time. Can we say goodbye to the robot?"

The man smiles. He says, "Of course. You can say goodbye to the robot."

Lily and Tom hug the robot. They say, "Goodbye, Robo. You are a funny robot. We will miss you."

The robot says, "Goodbye, Lily and Tom. You are nice kids. I will miss you too."

The man takes the robot and leaves. Lily and Tom wave to him. They learn a lesson. They learn to respect other people's things. They also learn to have fun with their own toys and songs.
<|end|>


