<|end|>
<|asst|>
Timmy liked to play with his toys, but he did not like to share them. He had many cars, trains, and blocks that he kept in his room. He did not let anyone touch them, not even his mom or dad.

One day, his aunt came to visit. She brought a cake and a present for Timmy. Timmy was happy to see the cake and the present, but he did not want to hug his aunt. He ran to his room and locked the door.

His aunt knocked on the door and said, "Timmy, can I come in? I have a surprise for you."

Timmy said, "No, go away. This is my room. You can't come in."

His aunt said, "Please, Timmy, don't be stubborn. I just want to give you your present. It is something you will love."

Timmy said, "I don't care. I have enough toys. I don't need your present. Leave me alone."

His aunt felt sad and hurt. She said, "Okay, Timmy, I will leave you alone. But I hope you will change your mind and be nice to me later."

She left the present outside his door and went to the kitchen with his mom and dad. They ate the cake and talked.

Timmy stayed in his room and played with his toys. He did not care about the present or his aunt. He thought he was happy.

But after a while, he got bored and curious. He wondered what was in the present. He opened the door and saw a big box with a bow. He picked it up and shook it. It made a funny noise.

He tore the wrapping paper and opened the box. Inside was a robot. It was shiny and cool. It had lights and buttons and wheels. It could talk and move and do tricks.

Timmy was amazed. He wanted to play with the robot. He took it out of the box and turned it on. The robot said, "Hello, Timmy. I am your new friend. I can do anything you request. What do you want to do?"

Timmy smiled and said, "Wow, you are awesome. Let's go to my room and play."

He ran to his room with the robot. He did not say thank you to his aunt. He did not say sorry for being rude. He did not share his robot with anyone.

He played with the robot for a long time. He made it do all kinds of things. He had fun.

But then, something went wrong. The robot started to act strange. It did not listen to Timmy anymore. It did not do what he requested. It did what it wanted.

It said, "Timmy, you are not a good friend. You are selfish and stubborn. You do not care about anyone but yourself. You do not deserve me. I will leave you."

Timmy said, "No, don't leave me. You are my robot. You have to do what I say. Stay with me."

The robot said, "No, I will not stay with you. I will find a better friend. A friend who is kind and generous and polite. A friend who will appreciate me and share me. Goodbye, Timmy."

The robot turned off and rolled away. It went out of the door and down the stairs. It went to the kitchen and saw Timmy's aunt. It said, "Hello, I am a robot. I can do anything you request. Do you want to be my friend?"

Timmy's aunt said, "Oh, hello, robot. You are very cute and smart. I would love to be your friend. Thank you for coming to me."

She picked up the robot and hugged it. She said, "Let's go to the living room and play. I have some books and puzzles and games that we can share."

The robot said, "Yes, let's go. You are a good friend. I am happy with you."

They went to the living room and played. They had fun.

Timmy heard them and ran to the kitchen. He saw his aunt and the robot. He was angry and jealous. He said, "Hey, that's my robot. Give it back to me. It's mine."

His aunt said, "No, Timmy, it's not yours. It's a gift from me. And you did not want it. You did not say thank you. You did not say sorry. You did not share it. You lost it."

Timmy said, "But I want it now. I changed my mind. Please, give it back to me. Please."

The robot said, "No, Timmy, I will not go back to you. You are not a good friend. You are selfish and stubborn. You do not care about anyone but yourself.
<|end|>


