<|asst|>
Lily and Ben were having breakfast with Mom and Dad. They liked waffles with honey and butter. Mom made them in a special machine that made them look like squares with holes. Lily and Ben each had two waffles on their plates.

"Can we go to the park today?" Lily asked. She wanted to play on the swings and the slide.

"Sure, honey, after we finish eating and clean up," Mom said. "But remember, it's very cold outside, so you need to wear your hats and gloves and coats."

Lily and Ben nodded. They ate their waffles quickly and helped Mom put the dishes in the sink. Then they put on their warm clothes and followed Dad to the car. Mom stayed home because she had to work on her computer.

The park was not far from their house. Lily and Ben ran to the playground and climbed on the swings. They pushed each other and laughed. They saw some other kids playing with a ball and a dog. They wanted to join them, but Dad said they had to ask first.

"Hi, can we play with you?" Lily asked the girl with the ball. She had long brown hair and a white coat.

"Sure, I'm Mia, and this is Max," the girl said, pointing to the boy with the dog. He had short blond hair and a blue coat. "And this is Spot, our dog. He likes to catch the ball."

"Hi, I'm Lily, and this is Ben," Lily said, pointing to her brother. He had curly red hair and a green coat. "We like to play with dogs, too."

They all became friends and played together. They threw the ball and Spot ran after it. Sometimes he brought it back, and sometimes he ran away with it. They had to chase him and wave their arms to get his attention. They had a lot of fun.

But then, something bad happened. Spot saw a squirrel on a tree and ran after it. He forgot about the ball and the kids. He crossed the road without looking. A big truck was coming fast. It honked its horn loudly. The kids screamed. Spot was in danger.
<|end|>


