<|asst|>
Ben likes to help his mom in the kitchen. He likes to see what she puts in the oven. He likes to smell the yummy food. But sometimes his mom says he is too little to help. She says the oven is hot and he can get hurt.

One day, his mom is busy in the living room. She is talking on the phone. Ben sees the oven is on. He wants to see what is inside. He thinks maybe there is a cake or a pie. He pulls a chair and climbs on it. He reaches for the oven door.

But the oven door is very hot. It burns his hand. Ben screams and falls off the chair. He cries and cries. His mom hears him and runs to the kitchen. She sees his hand is red and swollen. She is very scared and angry. She says, "Ben, what did you do? I told you not to touch the oven. You are very naughty. You need to go to the doctor. You might have a bad scar."

Ben feels very sad and sorry. He wishes he listened to his mom. He wishes he did not touch the oven. He is frustrated with himself. He does not want to go to the doctor. He does not want to have a scar. He does not want to be naughty. He wants to be a good boy and help his mom. But he made a big mistake. He thinks he ruined everything. He thinks his mom does not love him anymore. He thinks this is the worst day ever. He thinks this is a bad ending.
<|end|>


