<|asst|>
Tommy likes to play with his toy alligator. He calls him Al. Al has a big mouth and sharp teeth, but he is not mean. He is Tommy's friend.

One day, Tommy wants to invite Al to his birthday party. He asks his mom if he can. His mom says yes, but he has to be careful. She says some people might be scared of Al.

Tommy is happy. He puts a party hat on Al and takes him to the park. He sees his friends and runs to them. He says hello and shows them Al.

"Look, this is Al. He is my toy alligator. He is coming to my party. Do you want to play with him?" Tommy says.

Some of his friends are curious and want to touch Al. They say he is cool and funny. But some of his friends are afraid and run away. They say he is scary and ugly.

Tommy is sad. He does not understand why they do not like Al. He hugs Al and says, "Don't worry, Al. You are not scary or ugly. You are my best friend. I like you just the way you are."

Then he sees a girl who is sitting alone on a bench. She has a broken doll in her hands. She looks sad too. Tommy walks to her and says, "Hi, I'm Tommy. What's your name?"

"I'm Lily. This is my doll. Her name is Daisy. But she is broken. Her arm fell off and I can't fix it." Lily says.

Tommy looks at Daisy and says, "I'm sorry. That's not fun. Do you want to play with me and Al? He is my toy alligator. He is not broken. He is very nice."

Lily looks at Al and smiles. She says, "Sure. He is cute. Can I hold him?"

Tommy nods and gives Al to Lily. She holds him gently and says, "Hello, Al. You are a good alligator. Do you want to be friends with me and Daisy?"

Al nods and smiles too. He says, "Yes, I do. You are a good girl. And Daisy is a good doll. We can all be friends and have fun."

Tommy, Lily, Al and Daisy play together and have a great time. They share their toys and their cake. They laugh and sing. They are happy.

Tommy is glad he invited Al to his party. He thinks Al is the best toy alligator ever. And he thinks Lily is a nice girl. He hopes they can play again soon. He thinks he has made two new friends. He thinks he has had the best birthday ever.
<|end|>


