<|asst|>
Tom and Lily were playing in the park. They liked to swing and slide and run. They saw a big black dog near the fence. The dog was barking loud and showing its teeth.

Tom and Lily were scared of the dog. They ran away from the fence and hid behind a tree. They hoped the dog would go away.

But the dog did not go away. It jumped over the fence and ran towards them. It wanted to play, but Tom and Lily did not know that. They screamed and cried for help.

A man came from the other side of the park. He saw the dog and the children. He ran to them and called the dog by its name. He said, "Rex, stop! You are scaring the kids!"

The man was the owner of the dog. He put a leash on Rex and said sorry to Tom and Lily. He said, "Rex is a friendly dog, but he is too big and loud. He does not mean to scare you. He just wants to say hello."

Tom and Lily stopped crying and looked at the dog. The dog wagged its tail and licked the man's face. The man said, "Do you want to pet Rex? He likes to be petted. He is a good dog."

Tom and Lily nodded and came out from behind the tree. They petted Rex and he licked their hands. They saw that he was not so scary after all. He was just a black dog who liked to play.

The man said, "I'm glad you are not scared anymore. Rex is sorry too. He will not jump over the fence again. He knows he has to stay in his yard. But if you ever want to play with him, you can come and ask me. I will let you play with him for a small price. Do you know what a price is?"

Tom and Lily shook their heads. They did not know what a price was.

The man said, "A price is something you give to get something else. For example, if you want to play with Rex, you have to give me a hug. A hug is a price. Do you understand?"

Tom and Lily nodded. They understood. They liked to hug. They hugged the man and said thank you. The man smiled and said, "You are welcome. Rex likes hugs too. He is happy to have new friends."

Tom and Lily hugged Rex too. They said goodbye to the man and the dog and went back to their swing and slide. They were not scared anymore. They had fun in the park.
<|end|>


