Tom and his mom went to the market. They saw many things to buy. Tom liked the fruits and the toys. He saw a big red apple and a small blue car. He wanted both.

"Mom, can I have the apple and the car?" he asked.

"Sorry, Tom, you can only choose one. We have a budget," his mom said.

Tom was confused. He did not know what a budget was. He looked at the apple and the car. He liked them both. How could he choose?

He saw a man with a camera. The man was taking pictures of the market. He had a big smile.

"Hello, little boy. Do you want to be in my picture?" the man asked.

Tom nodded. He liked pictures. He hoped the man would give him the apple and the car.

The man told Tom to stand next to a table. The table had many flowers on it. They were colorful and pretty. The man said they were for display. He did not know what display meant. He thought they were for smelling.

The man took the picture. He showed it to Tom and his mom. They looked happy.

"Thank you, little boy. You made my picture beautiful. Here, you can have a flower," the man said. He gave Tom a yellow flower.

Tom smiled. He liked the flower. He gave it to his mom.

"Thank you, Tom. You are very sweet. And thank you, sir, for the picture," his mom said.

"You're welcome. Have a nice day," the man said.

Tom and his mom left the market. Tom still wanted the apple and the car. But he was happy with the flower. He thought it was a good trade.
<|end|>


