<|asst|>
Anna and Ben liked to play outside. They liked to run, jump, and make noise. But today, it was raining. They could not play outside. They were sad.

Mom saw them looking out the window. She was thoughtful. She wanted to make them happy. She said, "Do you want to find a rainbow?" Anna and Ben nodded. They liked rainbows. They were pretty and bright.

Mom gave them each a glass of water and a paper. She said, "Come with me to the kitchen. We will make a rainbow." Anna and Ben followed her. They were curious.

Mom put the glass of water on the counter. She said, "Look at the window. What do you see?" Anna and Ben looked. They saw raindrops and clouds. They did not see a rainbow.

Mom said, "Now, hold the paper behind the glass. Move it until you see something." Anna and Ben did what she said. They moved the paper. Suddenly, they saw something. They saw a rainbow!

The glass of water made a rainbow on the paper. It had red, orange, yellow, green, blue, and purple. It was beautiful. Anna and Ben smiled. They said, "Wow! Thank you, Mom!"

Mom hugged them. She said, "You're welcome. I'm glad you like it. You can make a rainbow anytime you want. You just need water, light, and paper."

Anna and Ben were happy. They played with the rainbow. They made different shapes and colors. They forgot about the rain. They had fun. Mom was thoughtful. She made them happy.
<|end|>


