Tim and Kim are twins. They like to play hide and seek in the park. Tim is good at hiding. Kim is good at finding. They take turns to hide and seek.

One day, Tim hides behind a big tree. He waits for Kim to find him. He hears Kim's feet on the grass. He hears Kim's voice. "Where are you, Tim? I will find you!" Tim smiles. He is quiet. He does not want Kim to hear him.

He peeks from behind the tree. He sees Kim looking around. She does not see him. He peeks again. He sees a gray car on the road. The car is big and loud. The car goes very fast. Tim likes the car. He wants to see it better.

He forgets about Kim. He forgets about hiding. He runs to the road. He wants to see the gray car. He does not look left and right. He does not see the other cars. He does not hear Kim's scream.

"Tim, stop! Come back! It is not safe!" Kim runs after Tim. She is scared. She wants to save Tim. She sees the gray car. She sees Tim. She sees the other cars. She hopes Tim will be okay. She hopes the cars will stop. She hopes they will not hit Tim. She hopes they will not hit her. She hopes they will not hit the gray car. She hopes they will not hit the big tree. She hopes they will not hit the park. She hopes they will not hit anything. She hopes they will all be okay. She hopes. She runs. She screams. She peeks.
<|end|>


