<|asst|>
Tom and Mia were playing in the garden. They had a big tent that they could go inside and pretend to be explorers. They liked to look at the flowers, the bugs and the birds.

One day, they found a strange bottle on the grass. It had a label that said "Shrink Juice". Tom was curious. He wanted to see what it was. He opened the bottle and smelled it. It smelled like candy.

"Let's drink some!" he said to Mia. "Maybe it will make us small and we can see more things."

Mia was not sure. She thought it might be dangerous. But Tom was already taking a sip. He felt a tickle in his tummy. Then he started to shrink. He became smaller and smaller until he was as big as a mouse.

"Tom, stop!" Mia shouted. "You are too small! Come back!"

But Tom did not hear her. He was too busy looking at the grass and the ants. He thought it was fun to be so small. He ran towards the tent. He wanted to see what it looked like inside.

Mia was scared. She did not want to lose Tom. She grabbed the bottle and drank some too. She hoped she could find Tom and make him come back. She also started to shrink. She followed Tom's footsteps to the tent.

The tent was huge. It looked like a mountain. Tom and Mia had to climb up the ropes and the fabric. They finally reached the entrance. They crawled inside.

They saw many things they had never seen before. They saw a spider web, a feather, a button and a crumb. They also saw a big shadow. It was their cat, Luna. She had smelled them and followed them to the tent. She was hungry and wanted to play.

"Meow!" Luna said. She pounced on the tent. She shook it and scratched it. She tried to catch Tom and Mia.

Tom and Mia were terrified. They realized they had made a big mistake. They wished they had never drank the shrink juice. They wanted to be big again.

"Help!" they screamed. "Help us!"
<|end|>


