Lily and Max are twins. They like to play in the garden. They pick flowers and chase butterflies. Sometimes they get dirty and muddy.

One day, they find a big bush of blueberries. They are happy and hungry. They pick and eat the blueberries. They are sweet and juicy. But they also make their faces and hands purple.

"Look, Lily, you are a purple princess!" Max says.

"Look, Max, you are a purple dragon!" Lily says.

They laugh and run around the garden. They pretend to be a princess and a dragon.

But their mom sees them and is not happy. She says they have to bathe. She takes them inside the house. She fills the tub with warm water and bubbles. She puts them in the tub and scrubs them with a sponge.

"Mom, we don't want to bathe!" Lily says.

"Mom, we want to play more!" Max says.

They splash and kick the water. They make loud noises. They try to escape the tub.

But mom is firm and gentle. She says they have to bathe. She says they have to be clean and healthy. She says they can play again after they bathe.

She rinses them with clean water. She dries them with a towel. She puts them in fresh clothes. She hugs and kisses them.

"Mom, we love you!" Lily and Max say.

"Mom, we are sorry!" Lily and Max say.

Mom smiles and says she loves them too. She says they are good kids. She says they can have more blueberries for dessert. But only if they promise not to make a mess again.
<|end|>


