Ben and Lily were playing in the backyard. They had many toys, but they did not know what to do with them. They were bored.

"Let's organize our toys," Ben said. "We can put them in different piles."

"Okay," Lily said. "How do we organize them?"

Ben thought for a moment. He saw some wood on the ground. He had an idea.

"Let's use the wood to make signs," he said. "We can write the names of the toys on the signs. Then we can put the toys under the signs."

Lily liked the idea. She picked up a piece of wood and a crayon. She wrote "cars" on the wood. She put it on the grass. She found all the cars and put them under the sign.

Ben did the same. He wrote "balls" on another piece of wood. He put it next to Lily's sign. He found all the balls and put them under the sign.

They continued to organize their toys. They made signs for dolls, books, animals, and blocks. They had fun writing and sorting.

When they finished, they looked at their work. They were proud.

"Look, we organized our toys," Ben said. "Now we can find them easily."

"Yes, and we made our backyard look nice," Lily said. "This was not boring at all."

They smiled at each other. They decided to play with their toys. They had a lot of choices. They were not bored anymore.
<|end|>


