Tom and Mia are friends. They like to play in the park. One day, they see a big hill. They want to climb it.

"Let's go up there!" Tom says. "We can see our home from there."

"OK!" Mia says. "But we have to be careful. It is very high and far."

They start to climb. They hold hands and help each other. They see flowers and birds and rocks. They have fun.

But the hill is hard. They get tired and thirsty. They stop to rest.

"Are we there yet?" Mia asks.

"No, not yet." Tom says. "But we are close. Look, we can see the park and the road and the houses. Our home is there, too. It is distant, but we can see it."

They smile. They feel happy. They want to succeed. They want to reach the top.

They stand up and keep climbing. They are brave and strong. They do not give up.

Finally, they make it. They are on the top of the hill. They hug and cheer.

"We did it!" Tom says. "We succeeded!"

"We did it!" Mia says. "We are the best!"

They look around. They see the sky and the sun and the clouds. They see the trees and the fields and the river. They see their home and their families and their friends.

They wave and shout. They are proud and joyful. They are on the top of the world.
<|end|>


