Tom and Sue are friends. They like to play with cars and trucks. One day, they find a big, old truck in the yard. It is red and rusty. They want to drive it.

"Can we drive the truck?" Tom asks Sue.

"Yes, let's try!" Sue says. They climb into the truck. Tom holds the wheel. Sue pushes the buttons.

The truck makes a loud noise. It starts to move. Tom and Sue are happy. They drive around the yard.

But then, they see a big tree. It is in front of them. They are scared. They do not know how to stop.

"Help!" Tom yells. "How do we stop?"

"Push the reverse button!" Sue says. She points to a button. It has an R on it.

Tom pushes the button. The truck makes another noise. It starts to move backwards. Tom and Sue are relieved. They avoid the tree.

But then, they feel a bump. They hit something. They look behind them. They see a fence. It is broken. They also see a dog. It is angry. It barks at them.

"Uh-oh!" Sue says. "We broke the fence. And we made the dog mad."

The dog runs towards them. It shows its teeth. They are big and sharp. Tom and Sue are scared again. They do not like the dog.

"Let's get out of here!" Tom says. They jump out of the truck. They run away. They leave the truck and the dog behind.

They go back to their house. They are safe. They are also sorry. They did not mean to break the fence. And they did not mean to upset the dog.

They tell their mom what happened. She is not happy. She says they should not play with the old truck. She says it is dangerous. She says they have to say sorry to the dog's owner. And they have to help fix the fence.

Tom and Sue nod. They agree. They learned their lesson. They will not play with the old truck again. They will play with their own cars and trucks. They are smaller and safer. And they do not have teeth.
<|end|>


