Anna loves to sing and dance. She likes to perform for her family and friends. She has a big red curtain in her room that she uses as a stage. She pretends that she is a star and that everyone is watching her.

One day, she invites her best friend Lily to come and see her show. Lily is very excited and brings a basket of lemons as a gift. Anna says thank you and puts the basket on a table. She tells Lily to sit on the bed and wait for the show to start.

Anna goes behind the curtain and puts on a sparkly dress and a hat. She turns on some music and comes out from behind the curtain. She sings a song that she made up and dances around the room. Lily claps and cheers for her.

Anna is very happy and bows to Lily. She says, "Did you like my show?" Lily says, "Yes, I did. You are very good at singing and dancing. You are a star!" Anna says, "Thank you. You are a very good friend. Do you want to perform with me?" Lily says, "Yes, I do. That sounds like fun."

Anna and Lily go behind the curtain and choose some costumes and props. They decide to do a funny skit about two sisters who make lemonade. They come out from behind the curtain and act out their skit. They pretend to squeeze the lemons, pour the water and sugar, and taste the lemonade. They make funny faces and say, "Yuck! This lemonade is too sour!" They laugh and try to fix the lemonade by adding more sugar and water. They taste it again and say, "Mmm, this lemonade is very good. Do you want some?" They offer the lemonade to their stuffed animals and dolls.

Anna and Lily have a lot of fun performing together. They make each other laugh and smile. They finish their show and bow to their audience. They say, "Thank you for watching our show. We hope you liked it. Goodbye!" They close the curtain and hug each other. They are very happy and proud of their show. They share the real lemonade and cookies that Lily brought. They say, "Cheers!" and drink to their friendship.
<|end|>


