Lily and Tom were playing in the park. They liked to admire the flowers and the birds. They saw a big black dog with a shiny collar. The dog was barking and running around.

"Wow, look at that dog!" Tom said. "He is so big and black. I want to pet him."

"No, Tom, don't!" Lily said. "He might be a threat. He might bite you or scratch you. He is not our friend."

But Tom did not listen to Lily. He ran towards the dog and tried to touch him. The dog did not like that. He growled and showed his teeth. He snapped at Tom's hand.

"Ow, ow, ow!" Tom cried. "He hurt me! He hurt me!"

Lily ran to Tom and hugged him. She was scared and sad. She saw blood on Tom's hand. She shouted for help.

"Help, help, help!" Lily yelled. "Someone help us! The dog is a threat!"

A man came running. He was the dog's owner. He grabbed the dog and put him on a leash. He was angry and sorry.

"I'm so sorry, kids!" the man said. "My dog is not friendly. He is black, but he is not nice. He is a threat. You should not admire him or pet him. You should stay away from him. Are you okay?"

Tom and Lily were not okay. They were hurt and scared. They wanted to go home. They did not like the park anymore. They did not like the big black dog. They did not admire him. They only wanted to be safe.
<|end|>


