Tom and Mia are friends. They like to play with puzzles. Tom has a big puzzle with many pieces. Mia has a small puzzle with few pieces. They sit on the floor and start to make their puzzles.

"Look, I have a black cat in my puzzle," Mia says. She shows Tom her puzzle. It has a picture of a black cat and a red ball.

"That is nice," Tom says. He looks at his puzzle. It has a picture of a farm and many animals. He tries to find the pieces that fit together.

Mia finishes her puzzle quickly. She is happy. She puts her puzzle on the table. She looks at Tom. He is still working on his puzzle. He has many pieces left.

"Can I help you?" Mia asks. She wants to play with Tom.

"OK," Tom says. He is glad. He gives Mia some pieces. They work together.

They find the pieces that match the colors and shapes. They put them in the right places. The puzzle becomes complete. It is a tight fit. They see the whole picture of the farm and the animals.

"Wow, we did it!" Tom says. He is proud. He and Mia high-five.

"That was fun," Mia says. She is happy. She and Tom smile.

They put their puzzles away. They decide to play with something else. They are good friends. They like to help each other.
