Lily was a clever girl who liked to play with her toys. She had a lot of dolls and animals and cars and blocks. She liked to make them talk and do funny things. She also liked to dress them up in different clothes.

One day, she found a hanger in her closet. It was a big hanger with a hook and a bar. She thought it looked like a swing. She wanted to make her toys swing on it. She took the hanger and put it on the door knob. Then she picked up her favorite doll, Anna, and put her on the bar. She pushed Anna gently and made her swing back and forth.

"Look, Anna, you are flying!" Lily said. "Wee, wee, this is fun!"

Lily's mom heard her voice and came to see what she was doing. She saw Lily and Anna swinging on the hanger. She smiled and said, "What a clever girl you are, Lily! You made a swing for your doll!"

Lily was happy that her mom liked her idea. She said, "Thank you, mom! Do you want to swing too?"

Lily's mom laughed and said, "Maybe later, sweetie. But first, let's put the hanger back in the closet. We don't want to lose it or break it."

Lily nodded and took Anna off the hanger. She gave her a hug and said, "You are a good flyer, Anna. But now it's time to rest."

She put the hanger back in the closet and the doll back in her bed. Then she gave her mom a hug and said, "I love you, mom. You are clever too."

The end.
