Lily and Tom are friends. They like to play in the park. One day, they see a new girl on the swing. She has long black hair and a red dress. She looks sad.

"Hi, what is your name?" Lily asks the new girl.

The new girl does not answer. She looks at Lily and Tom with big eyes.

"Can we play with you?" Tom asks.

The new girl shakes her head. She points to her mouth and makes a sound.

"She can't talk," Lily says. "Maybe she is sick."

"Or maybe she speaks a different language," Tom says. "Like Spanish or French."

"What is a language?" Lily asks.

"A language is how you say words," Tom says. "Some people say different words than us."

"Can we learn her language?" Lily asks.

"Maybe," Tom says. "But we need to be nice and friendly first."

They go to the water fountain and fill a cup. They bring it to the new girl.

"Here, drink this," Lily says. "It will make your mouth wet. Dry mouth is not good."

The new girl takes the cup and drinks. She smiles and says, "Thank you."

"Wow, she can talk!" Tom says.

"What did she say?" Lily asks.

"She said thank you," Tom says. "That is a word we know."

"Maybe we can teach her more words," Lily says.

"Maybe we can learn more words from her," Tom says.

They sit on the swing with the new girl. They start to talk and play. They are happy. They have a new friend.
<|end|>


