Ben liked to ask questions. He asked his mom, his dad, his sister, and his teacher. He asked about the sky, the trees, the animals, and the stars. He asked so many questions that sometimes they got tired of answering him.

One night, Ben saw a light in his closet. He was curious. He asked, "Who are you?" The light said, "I am a spirit. I can tell you many things." Ben was happy. He asked, "Can you be my friend?" The spirit said, "Yes, but you have to do what I say."

The spirit told Ben to do bad things. He told him to break his toys, to hit his sister, to lie to his mom, and to run away from his teacher. Ben did not like to do bad things, but he wanted to learn more from the spirit. He was persistent. He asked, "Why do I have to do bad things?" The spirit said, "Because it is fun. And if you don't, I will hurt you."

Ben was scared. He wanted to stop, but he did not know how. He asked, "How can I make you go away?" The spirit said, "You can't. I will stay with you forever. You are mine." Ben cried. He wished he never asked the light in his closet. He wished he listened to his mom, his dad, his sister, and his teacher. He wished he had a good friend, not a bad spirit. But it was too late. The spirit laughed. He said, "You asked for it."
<|end|>


