Lily liked to draw and paint. She was very creative. She had many colors and papers in her drawer. She liked to make pictures of animals and flowers and people.

One day, Lily wanted to draw a big rainbow. She opened her drawer and looked for her colors. But she could not find them. She only saw some old socks and books and toys. She was very sad and angry. Where were her colors?

She asked her mom and dad. They said they did not know. They said maybe her brother Sam took them. Sam was older and liked to play tricks. Lily did not like Sam. She thought he was mean and silly.

She went to Sam's room and knocked on the door. She heard Sam laughing inside. She opened the door and saw Sam with her colors. He was using them to make a mess on his wall. He had drawn a big face with a long nose and big teeth. He had used all her colors and mixed them together. He saw Lily and said, "Look, Lily, I made a picture of you!"

Lily was very hurt and angry. She wanted to cry and scream. She said, "Sam, you are bad! You took my colors and made a mess! You made me suffer! Give me back my colors!"

Sam laughed and said, "No, Lily, these are my colors now. You can't have them. Go away!"

Lily ran to her mom and dad and told them what Sam did. They were very upset and went to Sam's room. They saw the mess and scolded Sam. They said, "Sam, you are in trouble! You took Lily's colors and made a mess! You made her suffer! You have to apologize and clean up!"

Sam said, "Sorry, Lily, sorry, mom and dad. I was just having fun. I did not mean to make you suffer."

Lily said, "It's not fun, Sam. It's mean. You have to be nice and share. You have to be creative, not messy."

Sam said, "OK, Lily, I will try. Can we be friends?"

Lily said, "Maybe, if you give me back my colors and help me draw a rainbow."

Sam said, "OK, Lily, I will. Let's go to your drawer and get some papers."

Lily and Sam went to Lily's drawer and got some papers. They used Lily's colors and drew a big rainbow. They were both creative and happy. They did not suffer anymore. They hugged and said, "We love you, mom and dad." Mom and dad smiled and said, "We love you, too, Lily and Sam."
<|end|>


