Lily was a naughty girl. She liked to play with things that were not hers. One day, she saw a shiny key on the table. She wanted to see what it could unlock. She took the key and ran to the basement.

In the basement, there was a big metal box. It had a lock on it. Lily put the key in the lock and turned it. The box opened with a click. Inside, there were many old papers and books. They looked dusty and brown. Lily was curious. She took out some papers and books and threw them on the floor.

"Look what I found!" she shouted. She did not hear her mom coming down the stairs.

"Lily, what are you doing?" her mom asked. She was angry and scared. She saw the papers and books on the floor. She smelled something burning. She looked at the box and saw a small flame.

"Lily, you have to get out of here! The box has ash in it! It is from a fire that happened a long time ago. It is very dangerous!" her mom said. She grabbed Lily and ran to the door.

But the door was locked. Lily had locked it with the key. She had left the key in the box. The flame was getting bigger and bigger. The papers and books were catching fire. The smoke was filling the air.

"Help! Help!" Lily and her mom cried. They banged on the door. They hoped someone would hear them and unlock the door. They learned a hard lesson. Lily should not have been naughty. She should not have played with things that were not hers.
<|end|>


