Sara and Ben are at the beach with their mom and dad. They like to play in the sand and splash in the water. They have a big bucket and a small shovel. They want to make a sand castle.

"Look, Sara, I have a whale!" Ben says. He shows Sara his shovel. He has filled it with wet sand and shaped it like a whale. He has made a tail and a fin and a mouth.

"That is a good whale, Ben. But it is not pink. Whales are not pink," Sara says. She has a pink hat and a pink dress. She likes pink very much.

"Yes, they are. Some whales are pink. Like this one," Ben says. He points to the water. Sara and Ben see a big splash. They see something pink and shiny. It is a whale!

"Wow, Ben, you are right! There is a pink whale!" Sara says. She and Ben run to the water. They wave at the whale. The whale waves back with its tail. It makes a loud noise. Sara and Ben laugh.

"Hello, pink whale! We have a sand whale for you!" Ben says. He and Sara put their sand whale on the shore. The pink whale comes closer. It looks at the sand whale. It nods its head. It likes the sand whale.

"Thank you, Sara and Ben. You are very kind. I like your sand whale. It is a good friend," the pink whale says. It speaks with a soft voice. Sara and Ben are surprised. They did not know whales can talk.

"You are welcome, pink whale. You are very pretty. We are happy to meet you," Sara says. She and Ben smile. They are happy too.

The pink whale smiles back. It says goodbye. It swims away. Sara and Ben wave. They go back to their mom and dad. They tell them about the pink whale. Mom and dad are amazed. They hug Sara and Ben. They have a wonderful day at the beach.
<|end|>


