Lily and Ben liked to play in the garden. They had many toys, but their favorite was the big box of blocks. They could build anything they wanted with the blocks: houses, towers, bridges, and more.

One day, they decided to build a path with the blocks. They wanted to make a path from the door to the swing. They worked hard and used many blocks. They were happy with their path. It was fine and long and colorful.

But then, Max came. Max was Lily's big brother. He was not nice. He saw the path and laughed. "What is this? A path for ants? This is silly. I want to play soccer here. Move your blocks, or I will kick them away!"

Lily and Ben were scared and sad. They did not want to move their blocks. They liked their path. They said, "No, Max. This is our path. We made it. You can play soccer somewhere else. Please, do not kick our blocks."

Max did not listen. He was angry and mean. He kicked the blocks and broke the path. Lily and Ben cried. They ran to their mom and told her what Max did.

Mom was not happy. She went to the garden and saw the mess. She called Max and scolded him. "Max, how could you do this? You broke your sister's and your friend's path. That was not nice. That was rude and selfish. You should be sorry and help them fix it."

Max felt ashamed. He knew he was wrong. He said, "I'm sorry, Lily. I'm sorry, Ben. I was mean. I did not think about your feelings. Can I help you build your path again?"

Lily and Ben were still sad, but they forgave Max. They said, "Yes, you can help us. Thank you for saying sorry. We can share the garden and play together."

They all worked together and built the path again. It was even better than before. They had fun and learned to be kind and respectful. Mom was proud of them. She gave them hugs and cookies. They were happy.
<|end|>


