Tom and Jen were twins. They liked to play with their toys and their dog, Max. Max was big and furry and liked to chew on bones. Sometimes he chewed on Tom and Jen's toys too, but they did not mind. They loved Max very much.

One day, Tom and Jen's mom gave them a new toy. It was a tall giraffe with a long neck and spots. Tom and Jen were very happy. They thanked their mom and ran to their room with the giraffe. They named it Gigi and hugged it and played with it. They showed it to Max, who sniffed it and wagged his tail.

Mom called them for lunch. Tom and Jen put Gigi on their bed and went to the kitchen. They ate sandwiches and juice and cookies. They told mom how much they liked their new toy. Mom smiled and said she was glad. She told them to finish their lunch and then brush their teeth.

Tom and Jen did as mom said. They ran back to their room, eager to play with Gigi again. But when they opened the door, they saw something that made them gasp. Gigi was not on their bed. She was on the floor, torn and ripped. Max was sitting next to her, licking his lips. He had chewed on Gigi and ruined her.

Tom and Jen cried. They were very sad and angry. They yelled at Max and told him he was a bad dog. Max looked guilty and whined. He did not mean to hurt Gigi. He just liked to chew on things. He did not know Gigi was a toy and not a bone.

Mom heard the noise and came to the room. She saw what had happened and felt sorry for Tom and Jen. She hugged them and said she was sorry too. She said she would try to fix Gigi or get them a new one. She said Max did not know better and he still loved them. She said they should forgive him and be nice to him.

Tom and Jen calmed down. They looked at Max, who wagged his tail and licked their faces. They remembered how much they loved Max and how he was their best friend. They decided to forgive him and be nice to him. They hugged him and said they were sorry for yelling at him. They said they still loved him.

Mom smiled and said she was proud of them. She said they were good twins and good friends. She said she would take them to the store and let them pick a new toy. She said they could choose anything they wanted, as long as it was not too tall or too chewy.
<|end|>


