Anna and Ben are friends. They live in a big city with many cars and buildings. They like to play in the park with their toys. One day, they bring their bikes to the park and ride around.

"Look at me, Anna!" Ben says. "I can go very fast!"

"I can go faster!" Anna says. She pedals hard and tries to catch up with Ben.

But then, Anna's bike makes a loud noise. She stops and looks at her bike. Her tire is flat. She feels sad.

"Ben, my bike is broken!" she cries. "I can't ride anymore!"

Ben comes back and sees Anna's bike. He feels sorry for her.

"Don't cry, Anna," he says. "I have an idea. You can replace your bike with mine. I can share with you."

"Really?" Anna says. "You are very nice, Ben. Thank you!"

They switch bikes and ride together. Anna smiles. She thinks Ben is an incredible friend. They have fun in the park. They forget about the flat tire. They are happy.
