Sam and Mia like to play in the river. They have a big raft that they can sit on and paddle. They pretend they are pirates and look for treasure.

One day, they see a shiny box on the other side of the river. They want to get it, but there is a problem. There is another raft with two boys on it. They also want the box.

"Let's race them!" Sam says. "The first raft to reach the box wins!"

"OK!" Mia says. "But we have to paddle fast and hard!"

They start to paddle their raft. The other boys paddle their raft too. They are both very close to the box.

"Come on, we can do it!" Sam says.

"We are almost there!" Mia says.

They paddle harder and harder. They reach the box at the same time as the other boys. They both grab the box and pull.

"Let go, it's ours!" one of the boys says.

"No, it's ours, we got here first!" Sam says.

They tug and tug. The box opens and something falls out. It is a big, shiny trophy.

"Wow, look at that!" Mia says.

"It's perfect!" Sam says.

They stop pulling and look at the trophy. It has a picture of a raft and a word on it. The word is "WIN".

They smile and laugh. They share the trophy with the other boys. They are all happy. They have won the perfect prize.
<|end|>


