Ben is not sleepy. He wants to play more. He says to Lily, "No, don't go. Let's play more. It is fun."

Lily shakes her head. She says to Ben, "No, I am too sleepy. I need to rest. You can play more if you want."

Ben thinks for a moment. He likes to play, but he also likes Lily. He does not want her to be sad. He says to Lily, "OK, let's go home. We can play again tomorrow."

Lily smiles and says, "Thank you, Ben. You are a good friend."

They hold hands and walk to their homes. They put their scooters away and say goodbye. They go to their beds and fall asleep. They dream of playing with their scooters again.
