Sam liked to play with his toy plane. He made it zoom and fly in the air. He pretended he was the pilot and he had to go on a big adventure. He said, "Vroom, vroom, I am the pilot!"

One day, he saw a real plane in the sky. It was big and shiny and loud. He wanted to see it up close. He ran to the window and opened it. He leaned out and waved at the plane. He said, "Hello, pilot, can I come with you?"

But the wind was strong and cold. It blew Sam's hat off his head. It flew away with the plane. Sam was sad and scared. He said, "Oh no, my hat, my hat!"

Mom saw Sam at the window. She was worried. She said, "Sam, what are you doing? Come back inside, it is not safe!" She ran to the window and pulled Sam in. She shut the window and hugged him. She said, "Sam, you are safe now. You should not open the window by yourself. It is dangerous. You could fall or get sick."

Sam was sorry. He said, "I am sorry, Mom. I just wanted to see the plane. I wanted to be the pilot." Mom smiled and said, "I know, Sam. You have a big imagination. But you have to be careful and listen to me. You can play with your toy plane and pretend to be the pilot. But you have to stay inside and be safe. OK?" Sam nodded and said, "OK, Mom. I love you." Mom said, "I love you too, Sam. Now, let's go and find you a new hat."
