Lily liked to play in her room. She had many toys and books and a big wardrobe. Sometimes she opened the wardrobe and looked at the clothes. She liked to try on different hats and scarves and pretend she was someone else.

One day, she opened the wardrobe and saw something new. It was a big hole in the back of the wardrobe. It was dark and mysterious. Lily was curious. She wanted to know what was behind the hole. She crawled inside the wardrobe and went through the hole.

She found herself in a strange place. It was cold and white and there were many trees. She saw a lamp post and a sign that said "Narnia". She did not know what Narnia was. She heard a sound and turned around. She saw a big lion with a golden mane. He looked at her and smiled.

"Hello, little girl," he said. "Who are you and how did you come here?"

Lily was scared and amazed. She did not know how to answer. She did not know if the lion was friendly or not. She did not know what to do. She wished she was back in her room. She wished she never went through the hole. She wished she never opened the wardrobe.
