Lily and Ben are friends. They like to play in the park. They see a big tree with many oranges. The oranges are round and bright.

"Look, Ben, oranges!" Lily says. "I want one. Can you get one for me?"

Ben nods. He is tall and strong. He tries to reach an orange, but it is too high. He leans on the tree and jumps, but he cannot catch it.

"Let me help you, Ben," Lily says. She finds a stick on the ground. She gives it to Ben. "Use this to hit the orange."

Ben takes the stick. He swings it at the orange. He hits it hard. The orange falls down. Lily catches it.

"Yay, we did it!" Ben says. He smiles. He drops the stick and hugs Lily.

"Thank you, Ben," Lily says. She peels the orange. She breaks it in half. She gives one half to Ben. "Here, you can have some too."

They sit under the tree and eat the orange. It is sweet and juicy. They share and laugh. They are happy. They are clean. They do not make a mess. They are good friends.
