Lily and Ben are playing with their toys in the living room. They have a lot of fun making noises and pretending to be animals. Lily has a big jug that she fills with water and pours on the plants. Ben has a small car that he drives around the carpet.

"Look, Lily, I can make my car go fast!" Ben says, zooming his car past Lily's jug.

"That's nice, Ben, but be careful not to spill my water!" Lily says, holding her jug tightly.

Lily and Ben play for a long time, until they hear their mom calling them from the kitchen.

"Kids, it's time for a snack and a nap!" Mom says. "Come and wash your hands and have some cookies and milk."

Lily and Ben run to the kitchen, leaving their toys behind. They are very hungry and thirsty, and they enjoy their snack. Mom gives them each a glass of milk and a cookie.

"Thank you, Mom!" Lily and Ben say.

"You're welcome, my loves," Mom says. "Now, let's go to your room and have a nap. You must be very sleepy after playing so much."

Lily and Ben nod. They are feeling sleepy, and they want to cuddle with their mom. They follow her to their room, where they have a big bed with soft pillows and blankets. Mom tucks them in and kisses them on their cheeks.

"Sleep well, my sweeties," Mom says. "I love you very much."

Lily and Ben hug their mom and say, "We love you too, Mom."

They close their eyes and drift into a peaceful sleep, dreaming of their toys and their jug.
