Sara and Ben went to the big water with Mom and Dad. They saw many fish and shells and rocks. They liked to splash and swim and play. Sara saw something shiny and pink in the water. She wanted to touch it.

"Look, Ben, what is that?" Sara asked.

Ben looked and said, "I don't know. It is weird. It has no eyes or mouth or fins. It is like a bag of water with strings."

Mom heard them and said, "That is a jellyfish, Sara and Ben. It is a kind of animal that lives in the water. But you should not touch it. It can hurt you with its strings. They are called stingers. They can make you feel ouchy and red."

Sara and Ben learned something new. They did not touch the jellyfish. They said, "Thank you, Mom, for telling us. We do not want to get hurt. We want to have fun."

They swam away from the jellyfish and found a starfish. They touched it gently. It was hard and bumpy. They liked it. They learned more about the big water and the animals in it. They had a lot of fun.
