Anna and Ben love to race. They race to the park, they race to the swings, they race to the slide. They race with their legs, they race with their bikes, they race with their scooters. They like to see who is faster and who can win.

One day, they race to the big hill. They want to go down the hill on their scooters. Anna goes first. She pushes hard with her foot and zooms down the hill. She feels the wind in her hair and the sun on her face. She is happy and excited.

Ben goes next. He pushes harder with his foot and zooms faster than Anna. He wants to catch up with her and win the race. He does not see the rock on the road. He hits the rock with his heel and falls off his scooter. He rolls and rolls on the grass. He feels pain in his heel and his head. He is sad and dizzy.

Anna hears Ben cry. She stops her scooter and runs to him. She sees his heel is red and his head is dirty. She hugs him and says sorry. She helps him stand up and walk to the bench. She gives him her water and her cookie. She says he is brave and strong.

Ben feels better. He thanks Anna and hugs her back. He says she is kind and sweet. He says he does not care about the race. He says he is happy to have her as his friend. They smile and hold hands. They are happy and dizzy.
