Tom was a gifted boy who liked to run very fast. He could speed past all the other kids in his class and win every race. He felt happy and proud when he ran.

One day, he wanted to show his mom how fast he could run. He asked her to watch him from the window. He put on his shoes and ran out of the door. He did not look where he was going. He did not see the big truck on the road.

The truck was very loud and very big. It could not stop in time. It hit Tom with a loud bang. Tom fell to the ground and did not move. He was very hurt and very sad.

His mom saw what happened and screamed. She ran out of the door and hugged Tom. She cried and called for help. She hoped Tom would be okay.

But Tom was not okay. He had to go to the hospital. He had many broken bones and a big cut on his head. He had to stay in a bed with many wires and tubes. He could not run or play or smile. He needed a lot of massage to make his muscles work again. He was very angry and very scared.

He wished he had not run so fast. He wished he had looked where he was going. He wished he had listened to his mom. He learned a hard lesson. He was not happy and proud anymore. He was sorry and sad.
