Sara was a big sister. She had a baby brother, Ben. Ben was an infant. He was very small and cried a lot. Sara sometimes did not like Ben. He took Mom and Dad's time. He made noise when Sara wanted to play. He smelled bad when he needed a new diaper.

One day, Sara was playing with her dolls in her room. She heard Ben crying in his crib. Mom and Dad were busy in the kitchen. Sara thought, "I don't want to mind Ben. He is annoying. I want to play with my dolls." She ignored Ben's cries and kept playing.

But Ben did not stop crying. He cried louder and louder. Sara felt sorry for Ben. She thought, "Maybe he is hungry or lonely or scared. Maybe he needs a hug or a toy or a song. Maybe he wants to play with me." She put down her dolls and went to Ben's crib. She saw Ben's red face and wet eyes. She said, "Hi, Ben. I'm Sara. I'm your big sister. Do you want to play with me?"

Ben looked at Sara and stopped crying. He smiled and reached for her hand. He made a happy sound. Sara smiled back and picked him up. She said, "You are a good baby, Ben. I love you. I'm glad you are my brother." She hugged him and kissed his cheek. She took him to her room and showed him her dolls. They played together and had fun.

Mom and Dad heard Ben's happy sound and Sara's voice. They came to Sara's room and saw them playing. They said, "Sara, you are a great big sister. You are very kind and helpful. You mind Ben very well. We are proud of you. We love you and Ben very much." They hugged and kissed Sara and Ben. Sara and Ben hugged and kissed Mom and Dad. They were a happy family.
