Anna and Ben are brother and sister. They like to play with their toys and read books. They are very happy because tomorrow is a holiday. They do not have to go to school or do homework. They can have fun all day.

"Ben, what do you want to do on the holiday?" Anna asks.

"I want to go to the park and ride the big slide. And I want to feed the ducks and eat ice cream. What about you?" Ben says.

"I want to go to the zoo and see the big animals. And I want to pet the fluffy rabbits and eat popcorn. Can we do both?" Anna says.

"Maybe we can. Let's ask Mom and Dad. Come on, let's go find them." Ben says.

They run to the living room, where Mom and Dad are watching TV. They jump on the couch and hug them.

"Mom, Dad, can we go to the park and the zoo tomorrow? Please, please, please!" Anna and Ben say together.

