Lily likes her pink sheet very much. She sleeps with it every night. It is soft and warm and smells like her mom. She hugs it when she has bad dreams.

One morning, Lily wakes up and does not see her pink sheet. She looks around her bed and on the floor, but it is not there. She feels sad and scared. Where is her pink sheet?

She runs to her mom and dad's room and knocks on the door. "Mom, dad, where is my pink sheet?" she asks.

Her mom opens the door and smiles. "Good morning, Lily. Your pink sheet is in the wash. It was dirty and needed to be cleaned. Don't worry, you will get it back soon."

Lily does not like this answer. She wants her pink sheet now. She starts to cry and stamp her feet. "No, no, no! I want my pink sheet! I need my pink sheet! Give me my pink sheet!"

Her dad comes out of the room and picks her up. He hugs her and tries to calm her down. "Lily, Lily, it's okay. We know you love your pink sheet, but sometimes things need to be washed. It's good to have clean things. How about we have some breakfast and then we can play with your toys until your pink sheet is ready?"

Lily sniffles and looks at her dad. She is still sad, but she is also hungry. She nods and wipes her eyes. "Okay, dad. But can I have my pink sheet soon?"

Her dad kisses her cheek and says, "Of course, Lily. As soon as it is dry, you can have your pink sheet back. I promise."

Lily smiles a little and hugs her dad. She hopes her pink sheet will be ready soon. She misses it very much.
