<|asst|>
Lily and Ben are playing in the kitchen. They like to pretend they are chefs and make food for their toys. Lily has a big pot and Ben has a spoon. They put water and salt and pasta in the pot and stir it.

"Is it ready?" Ben asks.

"Not yet. We have to wait for the water to boil. Then we can finish the pasta," Lily says.

They look at the stove and see bubbles in the pot. They are happy. They turn off the stove and drain the water. They put the pasta in a bowl and add some cheese.

"Yum, yum! This looks good," Ben says.

They take the bowl and go to the table. They see their toys waiting for them. They have a teddy bear, a doll, a truck and a dinosaur.

"Here you go, friends. We made pasta for you. It is very tasty," Lily says.

They give some pasta to each toy and pretend they are eating. They make noises like "mmm" and "ahh". They have fun.

But then they hear a loud noise. It is their mom. She is coming home from work. She is fast. She opens the door and sees the mess in the kitchen. She sees the pot, the spoon, the cheese and the water on the floor. She sees the cabinet open and the pasta box empty.

"Oh no! What have you done?" she says.

Lily and Ben look at their mom. They are scared. They drop the bowl and run to their mom. They hug her and say sorry.

"We were playing, mom. We were chefs. We made pasta for our toys. We wanted to finish it before you came home," Lily says.

"We didn't mean to make a mess, mom. We were having fun. We love you, mom," Ben says.

Mom looks at them. She is angry, but she is also tired. She loves them too. She sighs and smiles.

"I love you too, kids. But you can't play with the stove and the cabinet. It is dangerous and messy. Next time, ask me first. OK?" she says.

"OK, mom. We are sorry. Can we help you clean up?" they say.

"Yes, you can. Thank you. And maybe later, we can have some real pasta for dinner. How does that sound?" she says.

"Good, mom. We like pasta. And we like you," they say.

They hug their mom again and then go to the kitchen. They help her clean up the mess. They are good kids. They finish their work and then play with their toys. They are happy.
<|end|>


<|sys|>
