<|end|>
<|asst|>
Anna loved to draw pictures. She had many crayons and papers in her room. She drew flowers, animals, houses and people. She was very proud of her pictures. She wanted to show them to her mom and dad.

One day, Anna decided to draw a picture of her family. She took a big paper and some crayons. She drew herself, her mom, her dad and her baby brother. She gave them all smiles and colorful clothes. She wrote her name at the bottom. She was very happy with her picture.

She wanted to hang her picture on the fridge. She was an independent girl. She did not need help. She took a stool and climbed on it. She reached for a magnet on the fridge. But she was too small. She lost her balance and fell. Her picture flew in the air.

"Anna!" her mom shouted. She ran to her. She saw Anna on the floor. She was scared. She hugged her. "Are you okay, sweetie?" she asked.

Anna nodded. She was not hurt. But she was sad. She looked for her picture. She saw it on the floor. It was dirty and torn. She started to cry. "My picture!" she sobbed.

Her dad came to her. He saw her picture. He felt sorry for her. He picked it up. He smiled. "It's a beautiful picture, Anna," he said. "You are a great artist. Don't worry. We can save it. We can tape it and clean it. It will look good again."

He took Anna and her picture to the table. He got some tape and a cloth. He fixed her picture. He wiped the dirt. He showed it to Anna. "See? It's almost like new," he said.

Anna smiled. She was happy. She hugged her dad. "Thank you, daddy," she said. "You saved my picture."

Her mom smiled too. She kissed her. "You are very brave, Anna," she said. "You are an independent girl. But sometimes it's okay to ask for help. We are always here for you."

Anna nodded. She understood. She loved her mom and dad. She loved her picture. She hung it on the fridge with a magnet. She showed it to her baby brother. He clapped his hands. They all admired her picture. It was a picture of her family.
<|end|>


