<|asst|>
Lily was going to the circus with her mom and dad. She was very happy. She liked to see the animals and the tricks. She wanted to see the clown too. She heard that the clown was funny and made people laugh.

When they got to the circus, they found their seats. Lily saw a big tent with many colors. She saw a ring with sand and lights. She saw people and animals walking around. She saw a man with a big hat and a whistle. He was the ringmaster. He said hello to everyone and told them to get ready for the show.

The show started. Lily saw a lion and a tiger jump through hoops. She saw a lady fly in the air with a rope. She saw a man ride a bike on a wire. She saw a monkey play with a ball. She clapped and cheered. She was having fun.

Then she saw the clown. The clown had a big red nose and big shoes. He had a funny suit and a funny hat. He had a flower on his chest. He came out of a small car with many other clowns. He tried to do tricks, but he always messed up. He fell down, he got wet, he lost his hat. He made funny faces and noises. He made everyone laugh.

But Lily did not laugh. She was nervous. She did not like the clown. She thought he was scary. She did not like his nose or his shoes or his flower. She did not like his tricks or his noises. She hid behind her mom and dad. She did not want to look at the clown. She wanted him to go away.

Her mom and dad saw that she was nervous. They hugged her and told her that the clown was not scary. He was just silly. He was trying to make people happy. They told her that she could look at something else if she wanted. They pointed to a big elephant that was coming next. They asked her if she wanted to see the elephant.

Lily nodded. She liked elephants. She thought they were big and gentle. She peeked from behind her mom and dad. She saw the elephant. The elephant had a long trunk and big ears. He had a blanket on his back. He walked around the ring. He lifted his trunk and made a sound. He balanced on a ball. He bowed to the people. He made Lily smile.

Lily forgot about the clown. She watched the elephant. She was happy again. She enjoyed the rest of the show. She saw more animals and more tricks. She saw the clown again, but he did not make her nervous anymore. He made her giggle. She learned that the clown was not scary. He was funny. She had fun at the circus.
<|end|>


