Lily was nervous. She was going to a new school today. She did not know any of the other kids or the teacher. She held her mom's hand as they walked to the door.

"Hello, you must be Lily," the teacher said with a smile. "I'm Miss Rose. Welcome to our class. We have a lot of fun here. Do you want to meet your new friends?"

Lily nodded shyly. Miss Rose took her hand and led her to a group of kids who were playing with blocks and dolls. "This is Sam, Mia, Ben and Zoe. They are very nice. Can you say hi to them?"

"Hi," Lily said softly. The other kids smiled and said hi back. They asked her if she wanted to play with them. Lily said yes and joined them. She liked the blocks and the dolls. They were fun.

Soon it was time for lunch. Lily opened her backpack and took out her food. She had a sandwich, an apple and a cookie. She looked around and saw that the other kids had different foods. Sam had a pizza, Mia had a salad, Ben had a burger and Zoe had a soup.

"What do you have?" Zoe asked Lily.

"I have a sandwich, an apple and a cookie," Lily said.

"That sounds good. Can I try a bite of your sandwich?" Zoe asked.

"Sure. Can I try a sip of your soup?" Lily asked.

"Of course. Here you go," Zoe said. They swapped their food and tasted each other's. They both liked it.

"Yum, this is good. Do you like my soup?" Zoe asked.

"Yes, it's very good. Do you like my sandwich?" Lily asked.

"Yes, it's very good. Thank you for sharing," Zoe said.

They smiled and ate their food. They enjoyed it. They also enjoyed talking and laughing with the other kids. Lily was not nervous anymore. She was happy. She had made a new friend. She liked her new school.
<|end|>


