Lily and Tom were playing hide and seek in their grandma's house. Lily was the seeker and Tom was the hider. Lily counted to ten and then looked for Tom. She went to the living room, the kitchen, the bathroom, but she could not find him. She wondered where he was.

She decided to check the bedroom, where grandma was sleeping. She opened the door quietly and saw a big lump under the sheet on the bed. She thought it was Tom and ran to the bed. She pulled the sheet and shouted, "I found you!"

But it was not Tom. It was grandma. And grandma was not sleeping. She was very still and cold. Lily noticed that grandma's face was pale and her eyes were closed. She felt scared and confused. She did not know what was wrong with grandma.

She called for Tom, but he did not answer. He was hiding in the closet, and he did not hear her. She called for mom and dad, but they were not home. They had gone to the store, and they had told Lily and Tom to be good and not to bother grandma.

Lily started to cry. She hugged grandma and hoped she would wake up. But grandma did not wake up. Grandma was gone.
<|end|>


