The other bird replied, "Fly to a lower branch where it's not so deep in the leaves. That way, you'll be safe from the wind."

The little bird listened and flew to a lower branch. The wind stopped blowing and the little bird felt much better. From that day on, the little bird always asked for help when it needed it.
