Once upon a time, there was a little girl named Lily. She loved to talk and play with her friends, but she didn't like it when they spoke in a language she didn't understand. One day, Lily was playing with her friends when they started speaking in a language she didn't know. She felt left out and sad.

Lily went to her mom and said, "My friends are speaking a stupid language I don't know." Her mom replied, "Lily, it's not nice to call something stupid just because you don't understand it. Maybe you can ask your friends to teach you."

Lily went back to her friends and asked them to teach her their language. They were happy to help and taught her some new words. Lily felt happy and included again. From then on, she knew that it's important to try and learn new things instead of calling them stupid.

The moral of the story is that we should always try to learn new things and be open to different languages and cultures.
<|end|>


