Once upon a time, there was a little girl named Lily. She loved to hear stories from her grandma. One day, she went to her grandma's house and said, "Grandma, I want a story please." 

Her grandma smiled and said, "Of course, my dear. I have a harmless story about a little bunny who wanted to make new friends." 

Lily was excited and asked, "What did the bunny do, grandma?" 

Her grandma replied, "The bunny went to the forest and met a friendly squirrel and a kind deer. They played together and had lots of fun. The bunny was very happy to have new friends." 

Lily smiled and said, "That's a lovely story, grandma. Thank you for telling me." And with a big hug, she went home, dreaming of her own adventure in the forest with new friends.
<|end|>


