Once upon a time, there was a little girl named Lily. She loved going to the zoo to see all the animals. One day, she saw a big, fluffy panda. The panda was eating bamboo and looked very happy.

Lily wanted to play with the panda, so she tried to catch it. But the panda was too fast and ran away. Lily was sad, but she didn't give up. She tried again and again, but the panda was always too quick.

One day, Lily had a perfect idea. She brought some bamboo with her and offered it to the panda. The panda was so happy that it stayed with Lily and they played together all day. From that day on, Lily and the panda were best friends and caught bamboo together every day.
