Later that day, Timmy's friend asked him if he had done his homework. Timmy didn't want to tell the truth, but he knew it was important. So, he said, "No, I haven't done my homework yet." His friend was happy that Timmy told the truth.

The next day, Timmy had a test at school. He studied hard and did his best. When he got his test back, he saw that he had gotten an A! Timmy was so happy and felt very successful.
