Once upon a time, there was a little mole. The mole loved to dig holes in the ground. One day, while digging, the mole found a shiny rock. It was very interesting to the mole. 

The mole imagined all the things it could do with the shiny rock. It could show it to its friends or use it as a decoration. But then, a bird swooped down and snatched the shiny rock from the mole's paw. 

The mole was sad and didn't know what to do. It had lost its interesting shiny rock. But then, the mole had an idea. It dug a deep hole and covered it with leaves. When the bird flew over, it fell into the hole and the mole got its shiny rock back. The mole was happy again and continued to imagine all the adventures it could have with its shiny rock.
