Once upon a time, there was a little girl named Lily. She loved to play outside and help her mommy in the garden. One day, Lily's mommy gave her a small plant to take care of. The plant was very green and had pretty flowers. Lily promised to water it every day and make sure it grew big and strong.

But one day, Lily accidentally broke the plant while playing. She felt very sad and thought her mommy would be angry. She tried to put the plant back together with tape, but it didn't work. Lily went to her mommy with tears in her eyes and told her what happened.

To Lily's surprise, her mommy wasn't angry at all. She hugged Lily and said, "It's okay, accidents happen. We can plant a new one together." And that's exactly what they did. They planted a new plant and this time, Lily was very careful not to break it. When the flowers bloomed, they smelled sweet instead of sour like the last one. Lily was so happy and proud of her new plant.
