Once upon a time, there was a bird named Tweety. Tweety lived in a nest high up in a tree. One day, Tweety met a squirrel named Sammy.

Sammy said, "Hey Tweety, let's plan to go on an adventure together!"

Tweety thought it was a great idea and said, "Sure, let's go!"

As they were flying and running through the forest, Tweety noticed that Sammy was being selfish. Sammy was only thinking about himself and not about Tweety.

Tweety felt sad and said, "Sammy, it's not nice to be selfish. We should think about each other and have fun together."

Sammy realized that Tweety was right and apologized. They continued their adventure together, but this time, they made sure to think about each other's feelings. The moral of the story is that it's important to be kind and not selfish.
<|end|>


