Once upon a time, there was a little boy named Timmy. Timmy was very impatient. He always wanted things right away and didn't like waiting. One day, Timmy went to the park with his mommy. He saw some big kids playing on the swings and wanted to join them.

Timmy's mommy said he had to wait his turn, but Timmy was too impatient. He ran over to the swings and tried to jump on, but he fell down and got embarrassed. The big kids laughed at him, but Timmy's mommy hugged him and said it was okay. Timmy learned that sometimes you have to wait your turn and not be too impatient.
