Once upon a time, there was a monkey named Max. Max loved bananas, but he was very spoiled and always wanted more. One day, Max's friend Lily came to visit him.

"Hi Max, do you want to play with me?" asked Lily.

"No, I want bananas," replied Max.

"But you've already had so many today. You should eat something else," suggested Lily.

Max didn't listen and kept whining for bananas. Suddenly, Lily had an idea. She took a piece of paper and started to fold it. Max watched curiously.

"What are you doing?" asked Max.

"I'm making a banana out of paper. See, it looks just like the real thing!" said Lily.

Max was amazed and forgot all about his craving for bananas. He and Lily played together happily, and Max learned that sometimes it's fun to try new things instead of always wanting the same old thing.
<|end|>


