Once upon a time, there was a boy named Timmy. Timmy lived in a big house with his mommy and daddy. They were very wealthy and had lots of toys.

One day, Timmy and his mommy went to the park. Timmy loved the park because he could play on the swings and slide. While they were there, Timmy saw a man with a brush. The man was painting a picture of the park.

Timmy said, "Wow, that's a nice picture. Can I have it?" The man said, "No, I need it for my art show." Timmy was sad, but he didn't cry.

Later that day, Timmy and his mommy went home. But when they got there, they saw that their house was on fire! They tried to call the fire department, but it was too late. Their house burned down.

Timmy was very sad. He said, "Mommy, I wish we could go back to the park and see the man with the brush. Maybe he could paint a picture of our house." But it was too late. The end.
<|end|>


