Once upon a time, in a small house, there was a gloomy pot. The pot was sad because no one ever looked at him. He sat on a shelf all day, feeling lonely.

One sunny day, a happy little girl named Lily came to visit the house. She looked around and saw the gloomy pot. "Why are you so sad, pot?" she asked. The pot was surprised that someone was talking to him. "No one ever looks at me," he said.

Lily wanted to help the pot feel better. She took him down from the shelf and put pretty flowers in him. "Now everyone will look at you and see how beautiful you are," she said. The pot started to feel happy. From that day on, the pot was no longer gloomy, and he and Lily became the best of friends.
<|end|>


