Once upon a time, in a small garden, there was a little herb. The herb was green and smelled nice. One day, a big bird came to the garden. The bird was hungry and impatient. The bird saw the herb and wanted to eat it.

The herb said, "Please don't eat me, big bird! I am just a small herb and I won't fill your tummy." But the bird was so impatient, it did not listen. It tried to pick up the herb with its beak to eat it.

Just then, a strong wind blew and made the bird drop the herb. The herb fell back into the garden, safe and sound. The bird was sad and flew away, still hungry.

The herb was happy to be back in the garden. It thanked the wind for saving it. From that day on, the herb and the wind became good friends. They played together in the garden every day, and the herb grew big and strong. And the bird learned to be more patient and find other food to eat.
<|end|>


