Once upon a time, in a small town, there was a dull vehicle. It was old and slow. Every day, the vehicle would work hard to help people. It would take them to the store, to school, and to the park.

One day, a shiny new vehicle came to town. Everyone liked the new vehicle because it was fast and pretty. They stopped using the dull vehicle. The dull vehicle felt sad and stopped working.

Soon, the shiny new vehicle got tired and broke down. The people in the town had no way to go to the store, school, or park. They realized that they should have taken care of the dull vehicle because it worked hard for them. The moral of the story is to appreciate and take care of what you have, even if it's not the newest or prettiest.
<|end|>


