Once upon a time, in a small house, there lived a little boy named Tim. Tim had a big toy box in his room. One day, Tim wanted to find his favorite toy car. It was dark in his room, and he couldn't see very well.

Tim said, "I need to find my toy car!" He started to look in his toy box. But the toy box was very dirty. Tim didn't like to touch the dirty toys. As he was searching, he stumbled on a big toy truck. "Ouch!" Tim cried.

Tim's mom heard him cry and came into the room. "What happened, Tim?" she asked. Tim said, "I stumbled on a big toy truck, and it hurt!" His mom looked at the dark, dirty room and said, "It's time to clean up, Tim!"

Tim didn't want to clean up, so he kept looking for his toy car. But the room was too dark and dirty. Tim stumbled again, and this time, he fell and bumped his head. Tim cried, and his mom came back into the room. "I told you to clean up, Tim," she said. But Tim didn't listen, and now he had a big bump on his head.
<|end|>


