Once upon a time, there was a little girl named Lily. She loved to be creative and play outside. One day, she went for a walk near a bridge. The bridge was over a small river. Lily liked to watch the water flow under the bridge.

Lily saw a flower near the bridge. It was not blooming yet. She said to the flower, "Hello, little flower! When will you bloom?" The flower said, "I will bloom when the sun comes out and warms me up."

The next day, the sun came out and the flower started to bloom. Lily was very happy to see the flower bloom. She said, "You are so pretty when you bloom!" The flower said, "Thank you, Lily! I'm happy that you like me."

Lily and the flower became good friends. They played near the bridge every day. Lily liked to be creative and make up stories about the flower and the bridge. And they lived happily ever after.
