One day, a little boy named Tim went outside to play. He played in the mud and got very dirty. His shirt was filthy. He didn't care because he was having so much fun. He made mud pies and threw them at the trees.

Tim's mom looked out the window and saw how dirty he was. She came outside and said, "Tim, you need to change your shirt. It is filthy!" Tim didn't want to stop playing, but he knew his mom was right.

He went inside and demanded a new shirt. His mom gave him a clean shirt to wear. Tim put on the clean shirt and went back outside to play. But this time, he stayed away from the mud. He didn't want to get his new shirt dirty.
<|end|>


