Once upon a time, there was a little dog named Spot. Spot loved to jog in the park. One day, while jogging, he met a big dog named Max. Max was very important in the park because he was the leader of all the dogs.

Spot said, "Hi, Max! Let's jog together!" Max replied, "No, I don't want to jog with you. You are too little." This made Spot very sad, and he went home to his mom. Spot's mom saw that he was sad and asked, "What's wrong?" Spot told his mom about Max and how he didn't want to jog with him because he was too little.

Spot's mom said, "Don't worry, my dear. Let's discuss this with Max." The next day, Spot and his mom went to the park to talk with Max. Spot's mom said, "Max, it's not nice to not jog with Spot just because he's little. Everyone is important, and we should all be friends." Max thought about it and said, "You're right. I'm sorry, Spot. Let's jog together."

From that day on, Spot and Max jogged together in the park every day. All the dogs in the park learned the important lesson that everyone is important, no matter how big or small they are. And they all became good friends.
<|end|>


