Once upon a time, in a small town, there was a boy named Tim. Tim loved to play with his toy sack. He would put all his toys in the sack and carry it everywhere. Tim felt safe when he had his sack with him.

One day, Tim went to the park with his mom. He saw his friend, Sue, playing on the swings. Tim ran to Sue with his sack, excited to play. He said, "Sue, look at my sack! We can play with my toys together!"

Sue liked the idea and they started to play. Tim and Sue took turns putting toys in the sack and taking them out. They made a game of it. They would do a fun motion with their hands and say, "In goes the toy!" Then they would do another motion and say, "Out comes the toy!" They laughed and played until the sun began to set.

As it was getting dark, Tim's mom said it was time to go home. Tim and Sue put all the toys back in the sack. They said goodbye to each other and promised to play again soon.

That night, Tim went to bed with his sack by his side. He felt safe and happy, knowing he had a great day with his friend Sue. And he knew that tomorrow would bring more fun and games with his toy sack.
<|end|>


