Once upon a time, in a big forest, there was a little bird named Tim. Tim had a dream to soar high in the sky. But he was afraid of the fierce wind that blew through the trees.

One day, Tim met a wise old owl. The owl said, "Don't be scared, little bird. You can soar high if you are brave and try your best." Tim wanted to be brave, so he listened to the owl and decided to try.

Tim flew through the forest and found a maze made of tall trees. He was scared, but he remembered what the wise old owl said. He took a deep breath and flew into the maze. As he soared through the maze, the fierce wind helped him find his way out.

When Tim came out of the maze, he was so happy and proud. He had faced his fear and now he could soar high in the sky. From that day on, Tim was never afraid of the fierce wind again. He knew that with bravery and trying his best, he could do anything.
