Once upon a time, there was a sleepy cat named Kitty. Kitty lived in a little structure made of wood. She loved to sleep all day and play all night. One day, Kitty met a new friend, a dog named Buddy.

"Hi, I'm Buddy!" said the dog. "Do you want to play with me?"

Kitty yawned and said, "I'm sleepy now. Can we play later?"

Later that day, Kitty and Buddy played together. They played with a ball, and they played with a stick. But then, they found a big toy. It was so big that they could not play with it together.

"We need to separate the toy," said Kitty.

Buddy agreed, "Yes, let's separate it and then we can play!"

So, Kitty and Buddy separated the toy into two parts. Now, they could play with the toy together. They played and played until they were both very sleepy. Then, they went to their little structure and slept side by side. And they were the best of friends from that day on.
