One day, a boy named Tim was watching his favorite cartoon on TV. He loved the funny animals and the bright colors. His friend, Sam, came over to play with him. Sam saw the cartoon and thought it was very funny too.

"Can I watch the cartoon with you?" Sam asked. Tim said, "Yes, but don't steal my toy while I'm not looking!" Sam promised he wouldn't steal anything.

While they were watching the cartoon, a big, rough dog came into the room. The dog saw Tim's toy on the floor and took it in his mouth. Tim and Sam were so busy watching the cartoon that they didn't see the dog steal the toy.

When the cartoon was over, Tim looked for his toy but couldn't find it. He said, "Sam, did you steal my toy?" Sam said, "No, I didn't! I promised I wouldn't!" They looked around the room and saw the rough dog with the toy in its mouth.

