One day, a little girl named Mia went to the park with her mom. They sat on the grass and watched the birds in the sky. Mia loved to watch the birds fly and sing. She saw a small, upset bird sitting on a branch. The bird looked sad and didn't sing like the other birds.

Mia asked her mom, "Why is that bird upset?" Her mom said, "Maybe it lost its friends or can't find food." Mia wanted to help the bird feel better. She looked around and saw some bread on the ground. She picked it up and broke it into small pieces.

Mia walked closer to the tree and said, "Don't be upset, little bird. I have some food for you." She threw the pieces of bread on the ground near the bird. The bird hopped down from the branch and started to eat the bread. It looked happier now.

Soon, the bird started to sing a beautiful song. Mia and her mom smiled as they watched the happy bird. They knew they had made a new friend at the park. And from that day on, every time they went to the park, they brought some bread for their little bird friend.
