Once upon a time, in a small village, there lived a poor little girl named Lily. Lily loved nature and playing with her friends. She liked to go to the park and watch the birds, trees, and flowers.

One day, Lily saw a pretty red ball in the park. She wanted to play with it but didn't know who it belonged to. So, she asked her friend Tom, "Can I borrow this ball, please?" Tom said, "I don't know whose ball it is, but I think it's okay to borrow it for a little while."

Lily and Tom played with the red ball all day long. They had so much fun in the sun, laughing and running around. They made sure to take care of the ball and not lose it. At the end of the day, they put the ball back in the park, under a big tree, so its owner could find it.

The next day, when Lily and Tom went to the park, they saw a little boy looking sad. He was searching for his red ball. Lily said, "We found your ball yesterday and played with it. We put it under that big tree over there. We only borrowed it for a little while. We're sorry if we made you sad."

The little boy was happy to find his red ball and thanked Lily and Tom. They all played together and became good friends. From that day on, they always shared their toys and had lots of fun in the beautiful nature of the park.
