Once upon a time, there was a small, humble bird named Billy. Billy was very shy and did not like to talk much. One day, he was flying in the park and saw a big stone. He thought it would be fun to sit on the stone and watch the other animals play.

As Billy sat on the stone, he saw a squirrel named Sammy. Sammy was very friendly and liked to talk to everyone. He came over to the stone and said, "Hi, Billy! Do you want to play with me?" Billy was too shy to answer and just looked at the ground.

Sammy didn't understand why Billy was so quiet. He thought maybe Billy was embarrassed. So, Sammy said, "Don't be embarrassed, Billy. We are all friends here." Hearing this, Billy felt better and smiled. He finally said, "Okay, Sammy, let's play!"

From that day on, Billy was not so shy anymore. He played with Sammy and the other animals every day. They all had lots of fun together, and Billy was happy to have such good friends. And the big stone in the park became their favorite place to meet and play.
