One day, a little boy named Tim went to the park with his mom. They brought a big sandwich for lunch. Tim was very hungry, so he asked his mom, "Can I eat the sandwich now, please?" His mom said, "Yes, you can."

As Tim tried to grab the sandwich, a big bird flew down and took it away. Tim was sad and said, "Oh no, the bird took our sandwich!" His mom thought for a moment and said, "We need an intelligent plan to get it back."

Tim and his mom looked around and saw a big tree. They decided to climb the tree to get closer to the bird. When they reached the top, Tim said, "Hey bird, can we please have our sandwich back?" The bird looked at Tim and said, "I'm hungry too. Can we share the sandwich?"

Tim thought it was a good idea. He said, "Yes, we can share the sandwich." The bird flew down and gave the sandwich back to Tim. They all sat together and enjoyed the sandwich. Tim was happy that he could solve the problem and make a new friend.
