One day, a little girl named Amy was playing in her yard. She loved to dig in the ground and look for bugs. Her mom watched her from the window to make sure she was safe.

Suddenly, Amy found a little bug that was stuck in the ground. She wanted to help the bug, so she said, "Don't worry, little bug. I will send you back to your home." She picked up the bug and placed it on a leaf.

Amy looked around and saw a big tree with lots of leaves. She thought the bug would be safe there. So she walked to the tree and put the bug on one of the branches. "There you go, little bug. Now you are safe," she said.

The bug was happy to be back in its home. It waved its tiny legs at Amy to say thank you. Amy smiled and waved back. She knew she had done a good thing by helping the bug.

From that day on, Amy always made sure to help any bugs she found in the ground. And her mom was always there to watch and make sure she was safe.
