Once upon a time, there was a little monkey named Momo. Momo lived in a big tree with lots of vines. He loved to swing from vine to vine, playing with his friends all day long. Momo was always very happy.

One day, Momo began to worry. He was very hungry, and he could not find any food. He looked for bananas, but there were none. He looked for apples, but there were none. Momo was sad and did not know what to do.

Then, Momo's friend, a little bird named Bibo, saw him looking sad. Bibo asked Momo why he was worried. Momo told Bibo that he was hungry and could not find any food. Bibo wanted to help Momo, so they went on a search together. They looked high and low, and finally, they found a tree with lots of yummy fruit. Momo and Bibo ate the fruit and were not hungry anymore. They played on the vines, happy and full. From that day on, Momo knew he could always count on his friend Bibo when he was worried.
<|end|>


