Once upon a time, there was a big blueberry tree. Two friends, a bunny and a squirrel, loved to eat the sweet blueberries. One day, they saw a big, dangerous snake near the tree. The snake wanted to eat the blueberries too.

The bunny and the squirrel were scared, but they wanted to share the blueberries with the snake. The snake was happy to share. They all picked blueberries together. The snake was not dangerous anymore.

After they picked the blueberries, the bunny, the squirrel, and the snake sat under the tree. They ate the blueberries and laughed. They were all friends now. They learned that sharing was good and made everyone happy.
<|end|>


