<|asst|>
Once upon a time, there was a flexible seal named Sammy. Sammy lived in the sea with his friends. They liked to play games and swim together. One day, Sammy met a new friend named Timmy the Turtle. Timmy was not as flexible as Sammy, but they still had fun together.

Sammy and Timmy played a game to see who could gain the most fish. They swam fast and tried to catch the fish. Sammy was very good at the game because he was so flexible. He could twist and turn to catch the fish. "I can gain more fish than you, Timmy!" said Sammy. Timmy tried his best, but he could not catch as many fish as Sammy.

As they played, a big shark came near them. The shark wanted to eat Sammy and Timmy. Sammy was too busy trying to gain more fish and did not see the shark. Timmy saw the shark and swam away as fast as he could. But Sammy was not fast enough. The shark ate Sammy.

The moral of the story is: Do not be too focused on winning or gaining things. It is important to pay attention to your surroundings and be safe.
<|end|>


