One day, a little girl named Mia found a tiny beetle in her garden. The beetle was original, not like the other bugs she had seen. It had pretty colors on its back. Mia liked the beetle and wanted to be its friend.

Mia said to the beetle, "Hi, little beetle! Do you want to play with me?" The beetle nodded its head and climbed onto Mia's hand. They played together all day. Mia showed the beetle her toys and even let the beetle ride on her shoulder.

As the sun began to set, the beetle looked sad. Mia asked, "What's wrong, little beetle?" The beetle told her that it needed to go home. Mia didn't want the beetle to leave, but she knew it was the right thing to do. She said, "I will lend you my toy car so you can go home faster." The beetle smiled and thanked Mia. They said goodbye, and the beetle drove away in the toy car. Mia knew she had made a new friend and hoped to see the beetle again someday.
<|end|>


