One day, a little boy named Tim went to the store with his mom. They wanted to buy some yogurt. Tim was very alert, looking around at all the colorful things in the store. He saw a big jar of yogurt on a high shelf. Tim wanted to get it by himself.

"Mom, can I raise my hand to get the yogurt?" Tim asked. His mom said, "Yes, but be careful." Tim raised his hand up high and tried to grab the jar of yogurt. But it was too high for him.

Suddenly, the jar of yogurt fell and broke on the floor. Tim was sad and his mom was not happy. They had to tell the store man what happened. The store man was not happy either. Tim and his mom had to pay for the broken jar of yogurt and go home without any yogurt.
<|end|>


