One day, a clumsy cat named Tom went for a walk. He heard music coming from a big house. He walked to the door and saw a little girl named Lisa playing the piano. Tom liked the music and wanted to join her.

Tom said, "Can I play music with you?" Lisa smiled and said, "Yes, you can play the drums." But Tom didn't know how to play the drums. He tried to hit the drums but he was so clumsy that he fell down. Lisa laughed and said, "Don't worry, Tom. We can try something else."

Lisa gave Tom a flute to play. Tom tried to play the flute but he couldn't make any music. He felt sad and said, "I don't want to play music. I'm too clumsy." Lisa looked at Tom and said, "Don't refuse to try. We can find something you can play."

Lisa gave Tom a tambourine. Tom shook the tambourine and made music. He was happy that he could join Lisa. They played music together all day long. Tom learned that even if he was clumsy, he could still have fun and make music with his new friend.
<|end|>


