Once upon a time, in a small town, there were two teams. One team was very nice and the other team was spoiled. The spoiled team always wanted to win and did not care about the other team's feelings. They would push and yell at the other team.

One day, a big race was coming up. The town had to choose which team would run the race for them. The nice team wanted to try their best, but the spoiled team just wanted to win. The town did not know what to do.

In the end, the town chose the nice team to run the race because they were kind and good to each other. The spoiled team was sad, but they learned that being nice is more important than winning. The moral of the story is to be kind and work together, because that is what makes a team strong.
<|end|>


