Once upon a time, there was a little girl named Sue. Sue had a favorite sock. It was a mild day when Sue went to play outside with her sock. She liked to make it dance in the wind.

Sue saw a small cat. The cat looked sad. Sue wanted to help the cat feel better. She thought that maybe the cat would like her sock. So, she offered her sock to the cat. The cat sniffed the sock and started to play with it.

The cat was very happy with Sue's sock. Sue felt happy, too. She knew that her sock had a new friend. From that day on, Sue and the cat played together every mild day. And they all lived happily ever after.
