Once upon a time, in a big park, there was a loyal pigeon. The pigeon had many friends. They played together every day. The pigeon was very nice to all the other birds.

One day, a little bird was in trouble. It could not find its way back to its nest. The loyal pigeon saw the sad little bird and wanted to help. The pigeon said, "I will help you find your home."

The loyal pigeon and the little bird looked for the nest together. They asked other birds for help. Finally, they found the nest. The little bird was very happy. The other birds saw how the pigeon helped and they liked the pigeon even more.

This story teaches us to value friendship and helping others. When we are loyal and kind, we make many friends. Friends are important and make us happy.
