Baby Bird told Mommy Bird about the cat. Mommy Bird became alert. She thought of a plan to save them. She told Baby Bird, "Bow to the cat and be nice. Maybe the cat will not eat us if we are nice."

Baby Bird went to the cat and bowed. "Please, do not eat us, Mr. Cat," said Baby Bird. The cat thought about it. He decided not to eat the birds because Baby Bird was so nice. The cat left, and Mommy Bird and Baby Bird were safe in their nest again.
