One day, a little girl named Lily went to play outside. It was a hot day, so she put on her hat and shoes. As she walked, she saw a big tree with a swing. Lily loved to swing, so she ran to the tree.

"Hi, Tree!" said Lily. "Can I swing on you?" The tree nodded, and Lily started to swing. She swung high and low, laughing and having fun. But then, she forgot to hold on tight and fell off the swing. "Ouch!" she cried, as she hurt her thumb.

Her mom heard her cry and came running. "What's wrong, Lily?" her mom asked. "I fell off the swing and hurt my thumb," Lily said, showing her mom her thumb. Her mom hugged her and said, "Don't worry, it will be okay. Next time, don't forget to hold on tight." Lily nodded and promised to remember. Soon, her thumb felt better, and she went back to play on the swing, holding on tight this time.
<|end|>


