Once upon a time, there was a little boy named Tim. He loved to go to the library. The library was full of books. Tim liked to read books about animals, cars, and fun things. One day, he saw a new book. The book was cheap. It was not like the other books. He wanted to read it.

Tim took the cheap book to his mom. He asked her to read it to him. His mom smiled and said, "This book is not a good book for you, Tim. It is not nice." Tim felt sad. He wanted to read the cheap book. His mom said, "Let's find a better book. A book that is nice and teaches us good things."

They looked for a new book together. They found a book about being kind to others. Tim's mom read the book to him. Tim liked the story. It made him feel good. He learned that being nice to others is important. He did not want to read the cheap book anymore.

One day, Tim saw a girl at the library. She was reading the cheap book. Tim felt embarrassed. He knew the cheap book was not nice. He wanted to help the girl. He went to her and said, "I know a better book. It is about being kind. Do you want to read it with me?" The girl smiled and said, "Yes, I would like that."

Tim and the girl read the kind book together. They both learned a lot. They became friends. The moral of the story is to choose good books that teach us to be kind and good to others.
<|end|>


