Once upon a time, there was a little girl named Sue. Sue had a pet dog named Max. They loved to play and stay together all day. One day, they went to the park to play. Sue threw a ball, and Max ran to catch it. But Max did not see a big, stupid hole in the ground. He fell into the hole and could not get out.

Sue was sad and scared. She did not know what to do. She saw a kind old lady sitting on a bench. Sue went to the lady and said, "Please help me. My dog Max fell into a hole, and I don't know how to get him out." The kind old lady told Sue, "Don't worry, dear. Let's pray together for Max to be safe and for help to come."

So, Sue and the old lady held hands and prayed for Max. Soon, a man with a big rope came to the hole. He put the rope down, and Max grabbed it with his teeth. The man pulled Max out of the hole. Sue was so happy to see Max safe again. She hugged Max and thanked the man and the old lady.

From that day on, Sue and Max were more careful when they played at the park. They always looked out for each other, and they never forgot the power of prayer. And every night, Sue would pray for her family, friends, and her pet dog Max before going to sleep.
