Once upon a time, there was a caterpillar who was very lonely. He had no friends to play with and felt sad all the time. One day, he met a beautiful butterfly who became his friend. They played together and had fun.

But one day, the butterfly had to leave to go to a faraway land. The caterpillar felt very sad and missed his friend. He hated being alone again. 

Days passed, and the caterpillar started to feel strange. He spun a cocoon around himself and stayed inside for a long time. When he finally came out, he was no longer a caterpillar but a butterfly, just like his friend. But he was still alone, and he missed his friend very much. 

Sadly, the butterfly never saw his friend again. He flew around, looking for his friend, but he was nowhere to be found. The lonely butterfly realized that he should have cherished the time he spent with his friend and not taken it for granted. He flew away, feeling sad and alone once again.
