Once upon a time, there was a little girl named Lily. One day, Lily and her mom went to the park to play. Lily saw a big, green frog and said, "Mommy, look at that thing! It's so big!" Her mom said, "Yes, Lily, it's a frog."

Lily wanted to catch the frog, but she was too nervous to get close to it. Her mom said, "Don't be scared, Lily. He won't hurt you." Lily said, "Okay, Mommy. But can we record him instead?" Her mom said, "Sure, we can take a video of him on my phone."

Lily and her mom recorded the frog and watched the video over and over again. Lily was so happy that she got to see the big, green thing again. From that day on, Lily loved going to the park to record all the things she saw.
<|end|>


