Once upon a time, there was a clumsy cat named Mittens. Mittens liked to play with yarn and chase butterflies. One day, Mittens saw a bird and tried to catch it, but he tripped and fell into a mud puddle.

Later that day, Mittens heard a noise outside. He looked out the window and saw the police car driving by with its lights flashing. Mittens wondered what was happening.

Suddenly, Mittens heard a beautiful sound. It was his owner singing in the shower. Mittens loved when his owner sang because it made him feel happy. Mittens started to purr and dance along to the song.

The next day, Mittens was playing with his yarn when he heard a loud noise. It was the police car again! This time, they were coming to his house. Mittens was scared, but then he remembered his owner's singing. He started to sing too, hoping it would make everything okay.

When the police arrived, they saw Mittens singing and dancing. They realized that there was no emergency and that everything was okay. Mittens felt relieved and happy that his singing helped. From that day on, Mittens knew that singing could make things better.
<|end|>


