Once upon a time, there was a little girl named Lily. She loved to play with her toys every day. One day, her mom gave her a new toy. It was a puzzle with letters on it. Lily didn't know what the letters meant, but she loved to play with it anyway.

One day, Lily's friend came over to play. Her friend was very ignorant and didn't know many words. Lily showed her the puzzle and asked her to help her solve it. Her friend didn't know what to do, but Lily taught her how to put the letters together to make words.

After they finished the puzzle, Lily's friend was so happy. She said to Lily, "Thank you for teaching me how to play with words. I didn't know they could be so much fun." Lily smiled and said, "You're welcome. Now we can play with words together."

From that day on, Lily and her friend played with words every day. They learned new words and had fun putting them together. Lily realized that it was important to help others and share the things she loved. The moral of the story is that playing with words can be fun and it's always good to help others.
