Once upon a time, there was a little boy named Tim. Tim liked to play outside in the sun. One day, Tim saw dust on the ground. He picked it up and threw it in the air. The dust made him sneeze. Tim's face turned red because he felt embarrass.

Tim's friend, Jane, saw him and said, "Why is your face red, Tim?" Tim told her about the dust and how it made him sneeze. Jane laughed and said, "That's okay, Tim. We all sneeze sometimes!"

They decided to get a drink to help Tim feel better. They found a lemon and squeezed it into a cup. They took a sip and made a face. The lemon was very bitter! They laughed and decided to add some sugar to make it taste better.

After their lemonade, Tim and Jane played in the sun all day. They forgot about the dust and the bitter lemon. They were happy to be friends and have fun together.
<|end|>


