Once upon a time, there was a big, wise owl named Wisdom. He lived in a tree with his best friend, a little cat named Nappy. They were very useful to each other. Wisdom would help Nappy find food, and Nappy would help Wisdom stay clean by licking his feathers.

One day, Wisdom told Nappy that he had a feeling they would find something great if they went on a walk together. Nappy was excited, but he was also very tired. He wanted to take a nap first. Wisdom agreed and said they would go on the walk after Nappy's nap.

Nappy took a short nap, and when he woke up, they went on their walk. As they walked, they found a big, shiny box. They opened the box, and inside, they found lots of yummy treats! Nappy was so happy he took a nap before their walk, because now they had lots of food to share. Wisdom knew that good things would come, and they both learned that sometimes, taking a nap can lead to great surprises.
<|end|>


