Once upon a time, there was a gray cat named Tom. Tom liked to play with a twisty toy. The twisty toy was his favorite. Tom would twist and turn the toy all day long.

One day, Tom saw a little girl named Sue. Sue also had a twisty toy. Tom wanted to play with Sue's toy, but Sue said, "No, this is mine." Tom was sad, but he still had his own twisty toy.

Tom and Sue played with their own twisty toys. They twisted and turned them together. They became friends and had fun. They learned to share their toys and play together. And they lived happily ever after.
