Once upon a time, in a small house, there lived a little girl named Amy. Amy had a small toe that would sometimes hurt. One day, she went outside to play in the sun with her best friend, Tim.

As they played, Amy's small toe began to hurt. She started to panic and said, "Ouch! My toe! Tim, help me!" Tim looked at her and said, "Don't worry, Amy. Let's go to your mom."

They went to Amy's mom, who looked at her toe and gave her a big hug. She said, "It's okay, Amy. Your toe will feel better soon." Amy felt better and thanked her mom and Tim for helping her. From that day on, Amy knew that even when she was scared, her friends and family would always be there to help her.
