Once upon a time, on a clean Tuesday morning, a little girl named Lily went outside to play. She wanted to search for something fun to do. The sun was shining, and the birds were singing. Lily felt happy.

As she walked, Lily saw a small, green frog. The frog was searching for a friend. Lily thought the frog was cute and wanted to help. She looked around and found a pretty, yellow butterfly. The butterfly also wanted a friend.

Lily brought the frog and the butterfly together. They became best friends and played all day long. Lily felt proud that she could help them find each other. With a big smile, she went home to tell her mom about her new friends.
