One day, a little boy named Tim went to play outside. He liked to run, jump, and discover new things. Today, he wanted to find something special. As he walked, he saw a fine, big tree with many leaves. Under the tree, Tim found a piece of paper.

Tim picked up the piece of paper and looked at it. It had a picture of a treasure chest on it. Tim was excited and showed the paper to his friend, Sam. "Look, I found a treasure map!" said Tim. Sam looked at the map and smiled. "Let's find the treasure!" said Sam.

Tim and Sam followed the map. They walked and walked until they found a big rock. Behind the rock, they discovered a small box. They opened the box and found shiny, pretty stones inside. Tim and Sam were so happy. They took the stones home and showed them to their families. Everyone loved the stones and the story of how Tim and Sam found the treasure.
