Once upon a time, in a small town, there was a boy named Tim. Tim was very angry all the time. He would yell and hate playing with other kids. One day, a new kid named Sam came to town. Sam was very patient and always happy.

Sam wanted to be friends with Tim, but Tim was angry and did not want to play. Sam did not give up. He kept trying to play with Tim, even when Tim said mean things. Sam was very patient and never got mad.

One day, Tim saw how patient and happy Sam was, and he started to feel bad for being angry all the time. He decided to try being patient too. Slowly, Tim learned to be kind and play with others. In the end, Tim and Sam became best friends. The moral of the story is that being patient and kind can help change an angry heart.
<|end|>


