Once upon a time, there was a little pencil who lived in a big box. The pencil was very sad because it was small and helpless. It wanted to stand up tall like the other pencils, but it just couldn't.

One day, a kind crayon saw the sad pencil and asked, "Why are you so sad?" The pencil replied, "I want to stand up tall like the other pencils, but I can't." The crayon thought for a moment and said, "I have an idea! Let's ask the ruler for help."

The crayon and the pencil went to the ruler, who was very wise. The ruler listened to their story and said, "I can help you stand tall, little pencil." The ruler then stood behind the pencil and helped it stand up straight.

The pencil was so happy that it could finally stand tall like the other pencils. It thanked the crayon and the ruler for their help. From that day on, the pencil, crayon, and ruler were the best of friends, always helping each other when they needed it.
<|end|>


