One day, a big gorilla named Bobo lived in the forest. Bobo was not like other gorillas. He was bald. He had no hair on his head. Bobo was sad because he looked different.

Bobo had a friend, a little bird named Peep. Peep wanted to help Bobo. So, they went on a trip to find hair for Bobo's head. They walked and walked until they saw a big tree.

Peep had an idea. Peep took some soft leaves from the tree. Peep put the leaves on Bobo's head. Now, Bobo had hair! Bobo was happy. He felt complete. Bobo and Peep went back home, and all the animals liked Bobo's new hair.
