Once upon a time, in a tidy little town, there lived a girl named Sue. Sue loved horses. She had a big picture of a horse in her room. Sue wished she could have a horse.

One day, Sue went to the farm. She saw a big, strong horse. The horse was brown and had a long tail. Sue asked the farmer, "Can I borrow your horse?" The farmer said, "Yes, but you must bring it back soon."

Sue was so happy! She rode the horse around the tidy town. They went fast and slow. They went up and down. The people in the town smiled and waved. Sue had a great time with the horse. When it was time to go home, Sue took the horse back to the farm. She thanked the farmer for letting her borrow the horse. And from that day, Sue and the horse were the best of friends.
