Once upon a time, there was a nosy little dog named Spot. Spot loved to sniff around and find out what everyone was doing. One day, Spot saw a big cat with a long neck. The cat's name was Fluffy.

Spot wanted to be friends with Fluffy, so he decided to lead Fluffy to his favorite park. He wagged his tail and barked, "Come on, Fluffy! Let's go play!" Fluffy looked at Spot and thought it might be fun, so she followed him.

At the park, Spot and Fluffy played and ran around. They had so much fun together. Spot liked Fluffy's long neck because it helped her reach high things. Fluffy liked that Spot was nosy because he always found new things to explore. They became best friends and played together every day.
