One day, a little girl named Lucy went to the park with her mom. They saw a big ice cream truck. Lucy was very happy. Her mom said, "You can choose one ice cream." Lucy thought and thought, "Which one should I pick?"

While Lucy was thinking, she saw a dirty dog playing in the mud. The dog looked very happy, but it was so dirty! Lucy laughed and pointed at the dog. Her mom said, "Yes, the dog is dirty, but we need to choose your ice cream."

It was a hot day, and Lucy finally chose a big, cold ice cream cone. She was so excited to eat it. But as she took her first bite, the dirty dog ran by and bumped into her. Her ice cream fell on the ground! Lucy was sad, but her mom said, "Don't worry, we can get another one." Lucy smiled and chose another ice cream cone. This time, she held it tight and enjoyed her cold treat on the hot day.
