Once upon a time, in a small garden, there was a magic herb. This herb would only appear when the sun was shining bright. It was a very slow-growing plant, but all the animals loved it.

One day, a little rabbit named Remy came to the garden. He saw the magic herb and wanted to take a bite. The herb was so slow to grow that Remy had to wait for a long time. He sat down and watched the herb grow, little by little.

Finally, the magic herb was big enough for Remy to eat. He took a small bite and something amazing happened. Remy could now hop faster than any other rabbit in the forest! He was so happy and thanked the magic herb. From that day on, Remy was the fastest rabbit and always remembered the slow-growing magic herb that helped him.
