Once upon a time, in a big field, there lived a helpful mouse. The mouse had many friends because he liked to help everyone. One day, the mouse saw a big bird stuck in a bush. The bird was sad and scared.

The helpful mouse went to the bird and said, "Don't worry, I will help you." The mouse and the bird started to discuss how to get the bird out of the bush. The mouse had an idea. He said, "I will chew the branches to make them loose, and you can fly away."

The mouse chewed the branches, and the bird was free. The bird was very happy and said, "Thank you, helpful mouse! You saved me!" They became good friends and played together every day.

The moral of the story is that even a small creature like a mouse can be helpful to others. It's important to be kind and help those in need, no matter how big or small you are.
