Once upon a time, there was a little girl named Lily who lived on a ranch. She had a big brown horse named Max who was very slow. One day, Lily went to her mom and said, "Mom, Max is so slow. Can he learn to run faster?" 

Her mom replied, "Yes, Lily. Max can learn to run faster if we practice running every day." 

So, Lily and her mom started practicing running with Max every day. They ran around the ranch and Max started to run faster and faster. One day, Lily's dad came home and saw Max running fast. He said, "Wow, Max is running so fast now!" 

Lily replied, "Yes, Dad. Max learned to run faster because we practiced every day." From that day on, Max was no longer slow and Lily was very happy that she could ride him faster around the ranch. The end.
