Benny was anxious to know more about the moon. So, he hopped up to his mom and asked her, "What's the moon?" His mom explained, "The moon is a big rock that orbits the Earth." Benny was amazed by this and wanted to learn more about the universe.

Later that night, Benny saw a shooting star and made a wish to explore the universe. The next day, Benny and his friends decided to build a rocket ship out of cardboard boxes. They worked hard and finally finished it. They climbed inside and blasted off into space.

As they explored the universe, they found a planet made entirely of bouncing balls. They bounced around on the planet and had so much fun. But then, they realized they were running out of fuel for their rocket ship. They had to find a way to get back home. Benny remembered the shooting star and made a wish to find their way back. Suddenly, a bright light appeared and they were back on Earth. Benny and his friends were so happy and proud of their adventure.
