Suddenly, Timmy's tummy started to hurt. He went to his mom and said, "Mommy, my tummy hurts." His mom asked, "Did you chew your candy before swallowing it?" Timmy shook his head no.

His mom explained, "You have to chew your food, or else it will hurt your tummy." Timmy nodded and said sorry. From that day on, Timmy always chewed his food before swallowing it.

Timmy also learned that eating too much candy made him feel smelly and not good. He decided to only eat a little bit of candy each day. And that is how Timmy learned to take care of his tummy and his body. The end.
