Once upon a time, there was a little girl named Lily. She loved to play with her toys and her cat, Mittens. One day, Lily's mommy asked her what she wanted to be when she grew up. Lily said she wanted to be a doctor so she could help people feel better.

Lily's mommy was proud of her and told her that she could be anything she wanted to be when she grew up. Lily felt happy and independent because she knew she could make her own choices.

As the years went by, Lily worked hard in school and learned many things. When she turned 18 years old, she went to college to study to become a doctor. And she did! Now, Lily helps sick people every day and she loves her job. She feels proud to have followed her dream and become an independent woman.
<|end|>


