Once upon a time, there was a big farm with lots of animals. There was a cow, a pig, a horse, and a chicken. They all lived together in a big barn. One day, the chicken said to the pig, "I bet I can poke you with my beak faster than you can poke me with your nose."

The pig said, "I'm very competitive, so I accept your challenge!" They started poking each other, but they were having so much fun that they didn't realize they were knocking over hay bales. Suddenly, a spark flew from the hay and started a fire. The animals tried to put out the fire, but it was too big.

Sadly, the barn burned down and all the animals lost their home. They had to find new places to live. The chicken felt very bad for starting the fire and apologized to the other animals. They forgave her, but they all knew they had to be more careful in the future. The end.
<|end|>


