Once upon a time, there was a little boy named Timmy. Timmy was very excited because his mommy said they were going to a restaurant for dinner. When they got to the restaurant, Timmy's mommy told him to behave and be a good boy. 

Timmy sat in his little chair and looked at the menu. He saw a picture of a yummy ice cream sundae and he wanted to order it. His mommy told him that he could have the sundae, but he needed to leave a little tip for the nice waitress who was going to bring it to him.

When the waitress came over, Timmy smiled and said "Please may I have a sundae?" The waitress smiled back and said "Of course, sweetie!" When she brought the sundae over, Timmy remembered what his mommy said and left a little tip on the table.

Timmy felt very proud of himself for being a good boy and leaving a tip. He enjoyed his sundae and had a great time at the restaurant with his mommy.
<|end|>


