Once upon a time, there was a big, wild forest. In the forest, there was a rabbit and a squirrel who were friends. They liked to play together and share nuts. 

One day, the rabbit found a big carrot and wanted to keep it all for himself. He was being selfish and didn't want to share it with his friend, the squirrel. The squirrel felt sad and left to find his own food. 

As the rabbit was eating his carrot, he accidentally split it in half. He felt bad for being selfish and decided to give half of the carrot to the squirrel as an apology. The squirrel forgave him and they continued to play and share their food in the wild forest. The end.
<|end|>


