Once upon a time, there were two friends, Tom and Jerry. They both loved to eat grapes. They always went to the same grape tree to eat grapes. One day, Tom said to Jerry, "Let's go to a different grape tree. Maybe the grapes there will taste better."

Jerry thought it was a good idea and they went to a different grape tree. But when they got there, they saw a sign that said, "Do not eat the grapes. They are not ready yet." Tom didn't care and he ate a grape anyway. Suddenly, a man came out and slapped Tom's hand. Tom felt bad and realized that he should have listened to the sign.

The moral of the story is to always listen to the rules and not do things that could get you in trouble. And also, it's not good to be different just for the sake of being different. Sometimes, it's better to stick with what you know is good and right.
<|end|>


