Once upon a time, there was a little elephant named Ellie. She loved to play in the rain and splash in the puddles. One day, Ellie was walking in the forest when she saw her friend, Sammy the Squirrel. 

"Hi, Sammy!" Ellie exclaimed. 

"Hi, Ellie!" replied Sammy. "What happened to your trunk? It looks wet." 

"I was playing in the rain," Ellie explained. "I love the rain." 

"I don't like the rain," said Sammy. "It makes my fur all wet." 

Ellie smiled. "That's okay, Sammy. Maybe one day you'll like the rain like me!"
