Once upon a time, there was a little girl named Lily. She loved to play outside in the garden with her hose. She would water the flowers and the grass every day. But one day, she couldn't find her hose. She looked everywhere but it was nowhere to be found. She started to feel nervous because she loved her hose and didn't want to lose it. 

Lily's mom saw that she was upset and asked her what was wrong. Lily told her about her missing hose. Her mom promised to help her find it. They looked in the shed, under the bushes, and in the garage, but they couldn't find it. They had to delay their gardening until they found the hose. 

Finally, after searching for a long time, they found the hose behind a big rock. Lily was so happy and relieved to have her hose back. She watered the flowers and the grass with a big smile on her face. From that day on, she made sure to put her hose away in a safe place so she wouldn't lose it again.
