Once upon a time, there was a little boy named James. He had one wish and it was to grow the biggest lemon in the whole world.

Every day he went to his garden to take care of the ground and water his lemon tree. He would work very hard and talk to the tree too.

One day, James put some seeds into the ground and he said, "Grow, little lemons, grow!"

He waited patiently and after a few weeks he saw three little lemons growing on the tree. They were very small but James was very happy.

He decided to pick the biggest one and cut it open. He took a bite and said, "It's a bit spicy!"

James had done it! He had grown the biggest lemon in the world. He had worked hard and used his imagination to make his dream come true.
