Billy and mum were at the park. Billy wanted to try and lift something heavy. Mum showed him a big rock. "Can you lift this?" she asked. Billy nodded and tried very hard. But the rock was much too heavy and he couldn't lift it. 

Then they looked up and saw an incredible sight - a hot-air balloon! It was lifted high up in the air by the wind. The weather was perfect for flying. 

"Can I lift that?" asked Billy, pointing at the balloon. Mum smiled and said, "Let's go and see if we can get close." 

They ran to the hot-air balloon and, when they were close enough, Billy was able to reach out and touch it. "Wow, this is incredible!" said Billy. He couldn't believe how light it was - he was able to lift it up with just one hand.
