Once upon a time there was a big room that filled with large things. On one side was a table with cords sticking out of it. In the middle of the room, there was a large box. Jack and Jill were playing around the box and pointing at the things in the room.

Jack said to Jill, "Let's point at the cord." So Jack and Jill each took a turn pointing at the cords. 

"This cord looks especially interesting," said Jack.

Instead of answering, Jill just kept staring at the cord. Then she slowly reached her hand out to touch it. 

Jack knew that this was not a good idea and said, "Wait! We don't know what that cord might do. Maybe it's better not to touch it."

Jill listened to Jack and took a step back. But they kept looking at the cord and wondering why it was so large.

Later that night, Jack and Jill found out why the cord was so large. It turned out that it was connected to the large box in the middle of the room. And when Jill had reached for the cord, she had accidentally pressed a button that opened the box. Inside, there were lots of fun toys and games. 

Jack and Jill were so excited to discover all the fun things that were inside the box, and after that, they always remembered to be careful with the large cord.
<|end|>


