Once upon a time, there was a princess named Daisy. Daisy was always very careful, but one day she made a mistake. As she was walking through the castle, she slipped on the floor and dropped her bottle of strong perfume.

Her mommy said, â€œOh no, Daisy - be careful. You could hurt yourself if you slip again.â€ She also added, â€œMaybe we should find something better for you to do.â€

Daisy decided she wanted to try something new, something that was safer. She wanted to learn how to play the piano. Daisy got a piano and began to practice. After a few weeks of hard work, she had learned some songs. She was very proud of herself.

The moral of the story is that being careful is important. A little extra caution today can save you a lot of trouble down the road. Slip-ups can be avoided if we make a plan, focus on our task, and practice hard.
