Once upon a time there was a very old bottle. It was ancient, and had been kept in the same place for hundreds of years.

One day, a three year old little girl found the bottle. She picked it up and began playing with it. She shook it back and forth, amazed as the bottle made a tinkling noise.

As she shook it, the little girl realized she could hear something inside. She tried to open the old bottle, but it wouldn't budge. She asked her dad for help.

Her dad took the bottle and used his tools to open it. He pulled out a long, rolled up piece of paper. The girl couldn't believe her eyes!

As they unrolled the paper, the little girl and her dad realized it was an old, ancient map. It showed them the way to a secret treasure. They rushed off, eager to find the treasure. 

It was a truly exciting adventure, but at the end of it the little girl and her dad realized that the best treasure was the ancient bottle they had found.
