Timmy and his hat were having a day at the park. The sun was shining and the sky was a bright blue. Timmy felt comfortable in the sun. His hat was brilliant in the sunlight. 

Suddenly, a dark cloud appeared overhead. The cloud started to rumble and quickly became bigger and bigger. A few drops of rain started to fall. 

Timmy looked up and said "Uh-oh. My hat will melt in this rain!" He put his hat on his head and started to run home.

But, it was too late. The rain started to pour heavily and his hat started to melt. 

Timmy felt very uncomfortable. He had to go home without his hat. He knew he would have to explain to his mom why his hat was gone forever.
