Once upon a time, there was a squirrel. He was walking around in the park, feeling very confused. He had no clue where he was or where he was supposed to go.

Suddenly, he heard a voice talking to him. It was a little boy. He was wearing a blue shirt and had brown hair.
 
The little boy said, "Hi, squirrel! I want to attach something to you. Will you let me?"

The squirrel was quite confused and just stared at the boy. He couldn't believe the boy wanted to attach something to him.

The boy felt the squirrel's confusion, so he said, "Don't be scared. It's nothing bad. I just want to attach something cool to your fur."

The squirrel was still a bit confused, but he agreed.

The little boy smiled and carefully attached a small bell to the squirrel's fur. The squirrel was scared at first, but it quickly realised that the bell was actually quite nice and fun. 

The squirrel thanked the boy and ran off with his new accessory attached to his fur, feeling much less confused.
<|end|>


