Once upon a time there were two friends, Larry and Kate. They liked to play together a lot. One day, their mum said that Larry had to take a new job. Larry was sad because he wanted to play with Kate all day. 

But Kate was sure that Larry's new job would be good for him. "It will be peaceful," she promised, giving Larry a hug. 

So, Larry went off to take his new job and he was very brave. And sure enough, when he returned Katie was right: his new job was very peaceful. He could work outside and listen to the birds singing. 

At the end of each day, Kate and Larry went to the park to play together. Larry was so happy to have his job and his best friend. His new job made their friendship even better.
