Cecil and his sister, Abigail, were walking across a field when they spotted a brick. Cecil was very excited to find it and he asked Abigail to help him find a spot to settle it. Abigail was skeptical and sad, but she agreed to help. 

"What are you going to do with the brick, Cecil?" asked Abigail. 

"I'm going to build a house with it," Cecil said with a smile.

Abigail was still feeling a bit skeptical, but she believed Cecil's enthusiasm and together they found a good place to settle the brick in the ground.

Once it was settled, Cecil and Abigail exchanged glances and they both knew that they had made something extraordinary: a foundation for Cecil's house. Cecil was filled with great joy and Abigail was happy for him, but at the same time, she couldn't help feeling a bit sad knowing that Cecil would soon be leaving home. 

No matter how hard Abigail tried to stay positive, she was reminded of the fact that this little brick was a reminder of a far away future, a future in which Cecil would be gone.
<|end|>


