Once upon a time there was a great big bear. He was honest and kind, and he loved to go for walks in the forest. One day, he came across a small hand. It was so tiny, the bear had never seen one so small. He smiled and softly said â€œHello!â€ He was surprised to find the hand belonged to a little bird.

The bird was very hungry and asked if the bear could feed him. The bear was glad to help and looked for some food for the small bird. He noticed some fresh berries on a branch and carefully picked them up, putting them on the ground so the bird could reach them.

The bird thanked the bear and started to eat the berries, happily singing a song of joy. The bear was delighted and he sat with the bird until it was full. Then, he said goodbye and continued his walk in the forest, happy that he had been honest and kind.
