Once upon a time, there lived a little girl called Lola. She was three years old and very curious.

One day, Lola was walking around her house when she noticed something unusual. On her bedroom floor there was a tiny creature. It was a little baby mouse!

Lola ran to get her Mum who had a very compassionate look on her face when she saw the mouse.

Mum gently picked up the mouse and said, â€œOh my! This little one must have lost its way!â€ 

Lola's Mum sensed that the mouse was scared and she wanted to help. She urged Lola to make a warm and cosy home for the mouse from a shoebox.

Together, with Lola's help, they filled the shoebox with plenty of food and cotton wool for the mouse to make a bed.

Afterwards, Lola's mum smiled. She was glad that the mouse was somewhere safe and urged Lola to take good care of the mouse. 

Lola smiled back with happiness. She was glad that she had been able to help with her kind and compassionate actions.
