Once upon a time, there was a little girl named Amy who loved to march. Every day she would go out in her front yard and march around and around.

One day as she was marching, she spotted something on the ground. It was a beautiful marble! She picked it up and examined it. Then, she put it into her pocket and kept on marching.

Amy marched and marched until she came across a rude man. Amy looked up at the man and asked, "What are you doing here?"

The man scowled and shouted, "That's none of your business! Now, go away!"

Aghast, Amy quickly marched away. She was so glad to get away from the rude man. She ran straight to her Mom, and showed her the marble.

Her Mom smiled, and said, "Oh what a beautiful marble! Where did you get it?"

Amy explained, "I got it while I was marching in the front yard!"

Amy and her Mom smiled and hugged each other. All's well that ends well!
