Once upon a time there were two best friends, Matt and Anne. Both of them liked to play together. One day, Matt found a shiny metal box in the garden. He showed it to Anne and asked her "What is it?" However, Anne didn't understand what it was. 

Matt said, "I think it is a metal box, but let's open it and see." Anne was excited and said, "Oh, let's do it!" They opened the box and found a boring toy inside. 

Anne said, "Hmm, it looks dull. I don't really understand what this toy is for." Matt answered, "Maybe it will get more interesting when we play with it together!" Anne agreed and they both had a lot of fun with their new toy. 

At the end of the playtime, they both agreed that though the toy was boring to look at, it was very fun to play with. They understood that some things may look a bit strange or boring, but can still be enjoyable.
