Once upon a time, there was a huge steam engine chugging along its tracks. Little Mick was on the train, peeking out the window, looking for rabbits and birds as the engine flew past. Suddenly, Mick saw something huge in the sky! It was a giant eagle! Mick was so excited, he shouted - "Look! A giant eagle is flying!"

Mick's mom smiled and said, "Yes, look how high it is flying!"

Mick shouted, "Come on, let's go outside and see the eagle!"

So they stepped out onto the platform of the station and watched the huge eagle fly higher and higher into the sky. Its wings spread wide, and its feathers shone in the sun. It looked like it was made of steam! 

Mick's mom held Mick's hand and said, "Let's go back inside, before we get too cold."

Mick waved goodbye to the huge eagle, as it flew off into the sky.
