Meg and Mop quickly ran into the house. As they watched through the window, the sky lit up with a mild flash of lightning. Meg was scared, but Mop was calm and he nudged Meg's arm reassuringly with his head.

â€œIt's ok, Meg,â€ he said in his quiet, bunny way. â€œJust remember that it's always best to be prepared, even when things seem mild.â€

Mop's words gave Meg courage, and she soon stopped worrying. She hugged Mop close and thanked him for his wise words. From then on, Meg was always sure to prepare for future storms, even if they were mild ones.
