Once upon a time, there was a dull swan. All the other swans were so colourful and lively but the dull swan was plain. All the other swans flew away to catch their food, but the dull swan stayed at the pond alone.

Eventually, a kind old woman came by the pond and noticed the dull swan. She couldn't help but feel sorry for the lonely swan and she gently wrapped the swan in her warm coat and took it to the park.

At the park, the dull swan saw a beautiful lake filled with swans, and it quickly ran away from the kind old woman and flew towards the lake. All the other swans were instantly attracted to the dull swan because of its unique colour. The dull swan was so happy and it never felt alone again.

The moral of the story is that you don't need to be the same as everyone else to be accepted. Always stay true to yourself and you will always find someone who appreciates you for who you really are.
