She flew and flew until she found a monkey. The monkey said hello and the prune said hello back. 

They played and laughed together until the monkey tried to take the prune. The prune was scared so she slapped the monkey with her smooth skin. 

The monkey was so surprised that he ran away. The prune was happy. She had made a new friend and was no longer lonely. 

The end.
