Once there was a little girl who loved to guess. She would guess what object was in her hand, what shapes were in the sky, and what color the tree was outside her window.

One day she decided to go for a walk outside. She saw some flies in the sky and said to them, "Can I guess your name?" The flies, of course, didn't answer, but she guessed anyway. "I think your name is Fluffy," she said.

But then something strange started to happen. Every time the girl guessed, a regular fly would appear and buzz around her head. She started to get scared because she didn't understand why the regular fly kept appearing. After a few minutes of buzzing around her head, the fly flew away and the girl felt better.

The little girl continued her guessing game, but after a while she noticed the regular fly buzzing around her again. She started to get frustrated and yelled, "Why can't you just go away?" 
Suddenly the regular fly flew away and the girl felt relieved. She realized that maybe this fly was just trying to communicate and that her guessing was annoying it. From then on, she would guess a few times and then stop for a moment so the fly could rest. 

The little girl and the regular fly continued their games together, guessing and flying around. She would guess, the fly would fly, and they would both be happy.
<|end|>


