But the fairy was angry and flew away.

Zoe was very sad that the fairy didn't want to be her friend. Zoe's mum came over to her and said, 
"Zoe, why were you so angry with the fairy? You must learn to be kind to everyone so you can make lots of friends"

Zoe thought it was important to be nice, so she decided to never be angry with anyone again.

The next day, the fairy came back and Zoe had a chance to make things right. She smiled and waved at the fairy, saying "Hello! I'm Zoe. Can we be friends?". 
The fairy was so pleased and they became best friends.

Zoe learnt a valuable lesson that day. She realised that if you be kind and friendly, you can have lots of friends.
