Mum was with Lucy and they were having a great time. Lucy was sitting in the kitchen, playing with her toys. "Mum," Lucy said, "I have a joke!" 

Mum laughed and looked at Lucy with a big smile. "Tell me your joke, Lucy!"

"Why did the chicken cross the playground?" Lucy asked, her eyes twinkling.

Mum thought for a moment. "I don't know, why did the chicken cross the playground?"

"To get to the other slide!" Lucy said and laughed.

Mum smiled, gave Lucy a kiss and said: "Let's have fun and go outside to the park now." 

The two of them got up and went outside to the park. Lucy saw the blue slide and ran to it. She was so excited! She quickly went up the stairs and got to the top. She looked down and said: "Mum, why do I need a pass to go down the slide?" 

Mum looked at Lucy, smiled and said: "You don't need a pass now, but soon you'll be big enough to go down the slide by yourself. Then you'll need a pass!" 

Lucy smiled and was happy. She felt so grown up! Little did she know, her mum was foreshadowing...the next day Lucy woke up and found an envelope with a blue pass in it
<|end|>


