Once upon a time, there was a little pup called Spot. He had big floppy ears, four soft paws and the cutest little tail. Spot loved to play.

One day, Spot was running around, chasing his tail when he heard a yelp. He stopped and saw a tiny kitten who had got her tail stuck in a bush. Spot was worried and ran over to help. He tugged gently at the kitten's tail until free.

"Thank you Spot," meowed the little kitten.
"What are friends for," replied Spot.

The little kitten smiled and asked, "Do you want to play?".

Spot was delighted! He nodded and said, "Yes, let's play." They played for hours, pouncing, chasing each other's tails and rolling around in the grass.

But, after a while, Spot's tail started to hurt. He yelped and lay down.

The little kitten came over and said,"Are you OK Spot?".

Spot nodded and said, "I think I just need a rest."

So, the little kitten curled up next to Spot and they both had a nap.  And, when they woke up, Spot's tail felt much better and they were ready to play again.
