Once upon a time, there was a brave little girl called Amy. She had a cool hat on her head and she loved exploring the world around her. 
One day, Amy decided to go on an adventure. She had heard so many stories about the monsters that lived in the dark woods. She was so excited to go explore! 
As evening came, Amy entered the dark woods. What she saw next made her gasp. Amidst the darkness there were bright stars twinkling in the sky. Amy was so happy to welcome her new surroundings.
But then, out of nowhere, an unexpected nightmare appeared. It looked so scary! Amy was filled with fear, but she knew she had to be brave. 
"Don't worry," said a voice. It was a friendly bird, perched on a tree. "I will fly with you to the end of the woods. Together, we can get out of here." 
Amy thanked the bird and held onto his feathers tightly. Suddenly, the journey seemed a little less scary. A cool breeze washed over them and the stars above shone brighter.

Together, Amy and the bird flew through the dark woods until they reached the end. The bird said goodbye and flew away. 
Amy felt relieved and happy, she had conquered the dark woods! Amy welcomed the bright sun, she was so glad the nightmare was over.
