Once upon a time there was a charming bear. He was walking through the forest and he smelled something sweet. It was honey! He saw a beehive high in the tree. He wanted to reach it, but he was too small.

He thought to himself, â€œHow can I get the honey?â€ Suddenly he saw a tall tree nearby. He was determined to get the honey, so he decided to climb up the tree. He worked hard, gripping each branch with his little paws and slowly he rose up the tree.

Just as he was about to reach the beehive, he felt a gentle breeze on his fur. He looked down and saw a beautiful bird. Surprised, he asked the bird, â€œAre you going to get the honey too?â€

The bird smiled and said, â€œNo little bear, I am here to help you. Spread your wings and rise up the tree, just like the bee!â€

The little bear was filled with joy. He did as he was told, spread his wings and flew up the tree. Soon he was up with the beehive and he ate as much honey as he liked.

