One day a deaf girl named Sarah was playing in her garden with her friends. They were picking flowers and having fun when they heard a loud noise. Sarah didn't know what it was and started to feel scared.

Sarah's friends told her it was just a big truck passing by, but she didn't believe them. Sarah was annoyed at her friends and decided to part ways. She walked away sadly without saying goodbye.

Sarah kept walking and eventually came to a big field with a pond in the middle. She started to explore it and soon found a path leading to a big house.

Suddenly someone came out of the house and shouted at Sarah. She was scared and started to run away. But the person followed her, and she soon realized it was the house's owner, who was deaf like her.

The man was angry at Sarah for trespassing on his property, but when he heard her talking he realized she was deaf too. He smiled and welcomed her to his home. 

Together they talked about the noise that scared her earlier and Sarah realized it was just a thunderstorm! She thanked the man for his help and the two made plans to meet again.
