Once upon a time there was a little girl called Sarah. She loved the sun, the moon and the stars that shone in the sky so brightly.

One day Sarah went to the park. She saw a group of birds circling high above her and was amazed how they flew together in the air without bumping into each other.

"Wow! Look how they fly together", said Sarah.

Suddenly, a deep rumble filled the air, and Sarah started to become frightened. All around people were running, not away from the sound, but towards it!

"What is happening?" cried Sarah.

An old man answered, "It is the sound of war, my child."

Sarah was confused. She didn't understand what war meant, but she knew it must be something bad. She watched as the people got thinner and thinner, and their faces became sadder and sadder.

But then one day, the rumble stopped. Sarah looked up again and saw the birds circling in the air, and she realised that the war was over. And with time, the people became happy again and their faces became brighter and brighter.

Sarah knew that wars were never good. But she also knew that with time, peace could eventually become again.
<|end|>


