Once upon a time there were two best friends who liked to play together every day. They were Gilly and Billy, and every day they would go for a walk in the park. One day when they were in the park, Gilly noticed a small bird with a broken wing. Gilly pointed to the bird and said to Billy, "Look, the bird needs help." Billy thought for a moment and he said, "Let's get the bird some food and water so it can heal." Gilly smiled and nodded in agreement. 

The two friends went to their homes and gathered food. When they returned to the park, they found the bird still there. They put the food in a little dish and sat with the bird until it ate. Then Gilly and Billy went back home.

The next day, when Gilly and Billy went back to the park, they found the bird had gone. But they knew that they had been useful, and they were happy. From that day, Gilly and Billy always remembered the moral of their story, which was this: when you see something that needs help, use your mouth to point out the problem and come up with a solution.
