Once upon a time there was a farmer named Steven. He was an honest farmer who had lots of animals and a big farm. Every day he would go out to his farm and supply the animals with food and water.

One day, when Steven was supplying the animals, his daughter Mary came to him and asked, "Dad, can I please help you today?" Steven thought for a moment and then said, "Of course, Mary. But you have to make sure you are being honest and doing a good job." 

Mary worked very hard all morning and helped Steven with the animals. She was so happy that she had been able to help her dad. But when it was time to go, Steven said to Mary, "You did a good job today, but there is still a lot to do. Can you come back tomorrow to help again?"

Mary was excited and agreed to come back. She knew that if she kept up the hard work, she would be able to help Steven even more in the future. As she and Steven walked away, Steven smiled to himself. He knew that if Mary kept up her honest work, they would be able to supply the farm with all it needs in no time.
