One day, the flea said to the turtle, "Let's have a race!" The turtle was a bit embarrassed but he agreed. The flea excitedly hopped away and the turtle followed behind slowly.

The flea was so fast that he crossed the finish line first. When the turtle finally made it, he was embarrassed and a bit sad.

The flea could see this, and he said to the turtle, "It's ok that you're slow, that's the way you are! Let's still stay friends and keep helping each other out." The turtle smiled and was glad he had such a good friend.
