Once upon a time there was a little bird called Sam the Sparrow. Sam was very adventurous and loved to soar through the sky each day. One day, Sam got an idea - he wanted to fly higher than any bird ever before. He wanted to touch the clouds and learn what was up in the big sky world.

Sam left his nest and flapped his wings so hard that he was sure he'd make it up into the clouds. He rose higher and higher until he looked down and saw that he had left even the tallest trees behind. Suddenly, a gust of wind caught him off-guard and he lost his balance. Sam was falling fast!

He thought he was gone for sure until he saw a shiny pen on the ground. He grabbed hold of the pen and was able to steady himself. Unfortunately, the pen was not strong enough and snapped in two, leaving Sam to fall to the ground. 

Fortunately, Sam survived the fall but from then on, he was too scared to soar ever again.
