One day, a boy named James was playing in his bedroom when he heard a loud noise coming from outside. He rushed out of the house to investigate and saw a shiny lollipop in the garden. He was so excited by it, he ran up and grabbed it.

He couldn't believe his luck and popped it in his mouth. But when he started to suck on it, he noticed it wasn't an ordinary lollipop. Instead, it was filled with tomato sauce!

James yelled out in surprise, "What are you doing here?". His mum heard his cries and came running out of the house. She saw what was happening and laughed.

"I was trying to make a surprise for you," she said. "This is a special kind of lollipop, it's a savoury lollipop!"

James was really disappointed. He frowned and said, "That's not what I was expecting. I wanted an ordinary lollipop!"

His mum smiled and said, "Well, next time I'll make you an ordinary lollipop. Now go and eat your savoury lollipop!".

So James rushed inside, still a bit disappointed, but at least he still had a lollipop.
