Mama was out of breath when she came home, after a long day at work. She was always busy, but this day was especially hard. She was so tired that she forgot to pick up her son Tom at daycare.

Tom noticed right away, and he started to cry. He felt helpless and alone. "Mama, why didn't you come?" he asked.

Mama felt terrible. She gave him a pinch on his arm and hugged him tight. "I'm so sorry, Tom," she said. "Please forgive me."

Tom nodded and wiped his tears away. He knew that Mama was very busy, but he still wanted her to remember him.

"Mama, can you help me hang my new calendar on the wall?" he asked, trying to cheer up Mama.

Mama smiled and pressed her nose against his. "Of course, silly!" she said. "I can't wait to see it!"

So together, Tom and Mama hung the calendar on the wall and together, they laughed. Mama promised to try her best to never miss picking him up again. Tom was happy, and he knew that even when he felt helpless, his Mama was always there for him.
