Once there was a little girl named Christine. She loved to measure things. Today, she was going to measure her mom's coffee. So she went to the kitchen and saw her mom stirring her coffee.

"Mom, can I measure your coffee?" Christine asked.

"Yes, sweetie!" her mom replied, smiling.

Christine was so excited she ran to get a ruler. She carefully measured the coffee and then asked, "How much is it?"

Her mom looked at the ruler and replied, "One cup."

"Yay!" said Christine, "Can I have some?"

Her mom smiled and said, "Of course, as long as it's fair."

So Christine had some coffee and it was the best cup of coffee she ever had. From that day on, Christine measured her mom's coffee every morning, just so she could have a fair amount for herself.
