John was a three-year-old boy who loved looking out of his bedroom window. Every morning he would watch the birds fly by, and look at the trees and the sky. One day, John saw something in the distance which made him jump. It was an enormous volcano.

John wanted to get closer, so he went outside and started running towards the volcano. He could feel the sun on his face, and he heard the birds singing as he ran. When John arrived, the volcano was even more enormous than he thought it would be.

He stood there, feeling scared and awed by the sight of the volcano. But then he saw smoke coming out of it, and he knew he had to be brave. John took two steps closer when suddenly, a deep booming sound started to grow.

John looked around, but he couldn't see anyone. Then, as the noise got louder, he saw a man who had appeared out of nowhere. The man laughed and said to John, 'Don't worry, my boy. Volcanoes like this don't erupt very often - the sound you heard was just this one waking up!'


John smiled and watched as the smoke from the volcano slowly faded away. He knew he would remember this enormous volcano forever.
