Emma ran to get her parents. "Please help Curry," she said. "He is stuck in the tree and he can't get down."

Her parents smiled and said, "That's funny. Cats can jump. Why can't he jump out of the tree?"

"I don't know," said Emma.

At that moment, they realized that Curry's waist was too big to fit through the branches. 

"Oh, Curry," said Emma's parents. "You have to remain in the tree until you become thinner. Then you can jump down safely."

Emma understood what they meant and looked at Curry sweetly. But then she thought of the solution.

"Let's give Curry some yummy apples," she said. "It will help him to stay slim so he can get down from the tree."

The family decided this was a great idea. So, every day they gave Curry an apple. Soon enough Curry got slim enough to fit through the branches
