Once upon a time, there was a weak little man. One day, he had to go and wash his car. He opened up the garage and he got out his bucket and sponge. 

But when he looked inside the car, he noticed that it was all oily. He didn't know what to do. 

Then he had an idea. He went to the store and bought some oil. He thought that he could wash the car and then use the oil to make it shine. 

When he came back, he started to wash the car. But after he finished, the car still looked oily. He used all the oil! 

The man started to cry. "Oh no! Now my car looks so bad!" he said. He was too weak to fix it himself. So there was nothing he could do. He left the garage feeling very sad.
<|end|>


