Once upon a time there was a little girl who loved to help her Mommy. Every day, the girl would dust and wipe around their house, happily singing as she worked.

One day, the girl's mommy asked her to help her in her office. The girl was very excited, even though she had never seen the inside of an office before. 

When they arrived, the girl saw a furry little creature on the floor. "Oh no!" said her mommy. "That's a mouse! We must wipe him out of the office before he does any damage." 

The girl thought for a moment and said, "But Mama, instead of wiping him away, why don't we open the window and let him go outside? That way, he will have enough food and a safe place to stay". Her mommy smiled and said, "What a good idea! You are very thoughtful, my love."

When the girl opened the window, the mouse scurried out, away from the office, and the girl and her mommy laughed. 

The moral of the story is: be kind to animals and try and find a better solution if you can!
<|end|>


