Once upon a time, there was a little girl named Sarah. She was three years old and loved to explore. One day, Sarah was walking along the beach and looking out at the ocean.

Suddenly, she saw something pale in the distance. She ran forward and saw that it was a beautiful reef! Sarah was so excited that she stopped to observe it closely.

As she stared, Sarah noticed something else. She saw a little fish, swimming inside the reef. She wanted to follow the little fish, so she started to swim.

Sarah swam closer and closer to the reef and the little fish swam just as fast to stay away. Finally, Sarah got so close that she could touch the reef. The little fish stopped swimming and stared at Sarah.

"Hello," said Sarah. The fish blinked and swam away. Sarah laughed, her voice echoing in the stillness of the ocean. She was so happy that she followed the little fish, and thanked the reef for being so beautiful.
<|end|>


