Once upon a time there was a wise fox who lived in the forest. One day he saw a rabbit. He called out to him and said, "Hey, Rabbit! Come here!"

The rabbit came over to the fox and asked, "What do you want?" The fox said, "I would like you to do me a favor. I need you to rush to the village and get me a bow." 

The rabbit said, "I'll do it, but why do you need it?" The fox said, "There's a secret I need to tell you. With the bow I can shoot arrows and protect the forest from danger."

The rabbit raced off to the village, and returned with the bow. The fox thanked him and said, "From now on, I'll be wise and use this bow to protect the forest. That way we can all be safe." 

The rabbit was so impressed with the fox's wisdom, he spread the word to all the other animals in the forest. Ever since then, every animal in the forest has known to be wise and look out for one another. 

The moral of the story is: be wise and look out for one another.
<|end|>


