Once upon a time, there was a tough elephant. He lived in the jungle and loved to play the trumpet. Every day, he would march around in the jungle playing his trumpet. All the animals around him would cheer and dance. 

One day, the elephant got very tired. He sat down and said to the other animals, "I need to get some sleep".

The other animals said, "OK! But only for a little while!" 

The elephant said, "OK. I will take a nap and then continue playing my trumpet". So he laid down in the grass and fell fast asleep.

After a while, he woke up. When he opened his eyes, all the animals were still there, waiting for him. He smiled and said, "Let's play my trumpet again!"

And they did. All the animals in the jungle danced and cheered as the tough elephant played his trumpet. They were so happy and loud, the sound echoed through the trees. 

And they all lived happily ever after!
