Henry was playing in the park with his toy bunny when he noticed something furry poking out of the ground. He examined it closer and realized it was a long, furry strip. 

Confused, he looked around to see if anyone else noticed it, but everyone else was too busy to notice.

He bent down and squeezed the furry strip in his hands. He was surprised when he heard a meow!

He looked around, but didn't see anything. He squeezed the furry strip again and suddenly got a response.

"Meow! Let me out of here!" said a tiny, fluffy kitten.

Henry excitedly dug around the furry strip until he freed the little kitten. He scooped it up in his arms and gave it a big hug. 

The kitten purred happily, thankful to be free. Henry smiled in delight and the two of them happily played together in the park for the rest of the day.
