Once upon a time there was a little boy named Henry. He was three-years old and he loved skipping. Every day, Henry's mom gave him an cookies as a snack.

One day, Henry got two cookies. He smiled and started to skip around the house. As he skipped, one of the cookies fell and broke into smithereens. 

Henry started to cry. He looked around to make sure his Mom couldn't see him, but she had already seen what had happened.

"Oh, Henry," said his Mom softly. "It is ok. Let's go get another cookie."

Henry stopped crying and smiled. He put the other cookie into his pocket and they both went out to the store to get another cookie. 

At the store, Henry chose his favorite cookie and he skipped all the way home with his mom. When he got home, he ate the cookie and shared the other cookie with his Mom. 

Henry was so happy and he never stopped skipping.
