There was once a little girl called Maggie. She was three years old and loved to have fun. One day, Maggie was playing in her garden when she heard a loud voice. She looked around and saw nothing. She decided to get closer to find out where the voice was coming from.

When she got close, she saw a parrot. He was brightly coloured and very loud! She asked the parrot where it came from and he said, "I was just flying through and saw a nice garden, so I decided to take a rest here."

Maggie thought it was very interesting to find a parrot in her garden and she asked, "Can I talk to you?" The parrot said, "Of course you can! I love talking to people."

Maggie and the parrot talked for hours and she learned so much about animals and nature. Maggie had a great time and said goodbye to the parrot before heading inside for dinner.
