Once upon a time there was a nosy mouse named Mabel. Every day she would hang around the barn in search of food.

One day, she found a mound of cheese in a corner and she quickly munched away. Suddenly, she heard a soft snoring coming from behind a pile of hay.

Mabel crept closer, determined to find out what was causing the noise. Peeking around the haystack, she saw a sleeping cat with a very full stomach.

Mabel noticed her cheese was gone but the cat's stomach still looked full. She was confused and wanted to know where the food was coming from.

So, Mabel decided to get nosy and try to wake up the cat. She scurried over to the cat and jumped up on its head.

The cat quickly woke up and eyed Mabel suspiciously. It growled and hissed at the little mouse, causing her to run away in fear.

Mabel hung around the barn for the rest of the day, determined to figure out why the cat's stomach was so full. She soon realized that the place she had found the cheese before must have been the cat's hiding spot.

Mabel learned a very important lesson that day: never get too nosy!
<|end|>


