One day, there were two friends, Marco and Elsa. They wanted to go to the park, but it was too far away to walk. 

"Let's take a taxi!" suggested Marco.

"That will be too expensive," said Elsa. "It's better to walk."

But Marco did not want to walk. He thought and thought, until finally he had an idea. "Let's run!" he said. 

The two friends ran and ran, until at last they reached the park. They laughed and cheered, and hugged each other in celebration.

"We succeeded!" said Marco.

