Once upon a time there lived two friends, Joe and Tim. Joe liked to play tricks, so one day he decided to dare Tim to go into the huge cave. Tim was very scared, but Joe promised him he wouldn't get hurt. So Tim took a deep breath and got out his rag, which he used to hold onto. 

As they entered the cave, it became very dark. Joe lit a torch to help guide the way. They looked around and noticed drawings on the walls. Tim asked Joe, "What do these drawings mean?" Joe laughed and said, "Well, that's a surprise! You have to get closer to see." 

So, they walked carefully up to the drawings and saw that they were actually huge and very colorful dragons. Tim was amazed and couldn't believe it. Joe said, "Now, I dare you to touch one!" Tim was scared but bravely reached out and touched one. Suddenly, the lights in the cave started shining and the dragon moved. 

Tim jumped back and laughed. Joe hugged him and said, "I knew you could do it." They both said goodbye to the dragon, then packed up their rag and went home.
