One day a happy bunny named Freddy hopped out of his warm fur burrow. He was excited to explore the forest around him. Suddenly, he felt a chill and his fur stood on end. He was feeling anxious! 

Just then, he heard a frightened cry. It was coming from a small squirrel.

Freddy jumped over to the squirrel and asked "What's wrong?"

The Squirrel shivered and said "I'm so scared! A big, scary cat is chasing me!"

Freddy told him not to worry. He said "Let's sit down so that the cat won't see us."

The Squirrel was relieved and sat down with Freddy. They turned their backs to the forest to hide.

The cat passed by, but couldn't see them. They were safe!

The Squirrel thanked Freddy and ran off, no longer anxious.

Freddy smiled, happy that he had been able to help his little friend. He settled back into his warm fur burrow and fell asleep.
