Once upon a time there was a little girl named Lily. She wanted to buy some candy from the store, but all she had was a penny. She asked her mom if she could go to the store, and mom said yes. 

When she got to the store she asked the shopkeeper for the candy, but he said he wouldn't sell it for just a penny. Lily was sad and frustrated. She asked him why he wouldn't mix her penny, but the shopkeeper just ignored her. 

Just then, a wise old man stepped in. He knew Lily was ignorant and wanted to teach her a lesson. He started to explain that money should be respected and not just mixed into anything you want. Everyone listened to his wise words, and the shopkeeper decided to give Lily the candy in exchange for her penny. 

Lily was very happy. She thanked the old man, the shopkeeper, and her mom. From that day forward, Lily was very respectful of her money.
