Once upon a time, there was a little girl called Jill. She was three years old. One day, Jill saw her Grandma cooking in the kitchen. She watched Grandma add a pinch of seasoning to the cooking mix.

"Grandma, what are you cooking?" Jill asked.

"Oh, I'm making cookies," Grandma replied.

"What's a cookie?" Jill asked, puzzled.

"It's a yummy treat that you can eat," Grandma said with a smile. 

Jill was so excited to try the cookies, but Grandma said that it would take a year before they were ready.

"A whole year?" Jill exclaimed.

"That's right," said Grandma. "The cookies have to cook for at least a year before they're ready to eat!"

Jill couldn't even imagine how tasty the cookies would be after a year of cooking. She was so curious about the unknown taste.

So, Jill made herself a promise that she would try the cookies when Grandma said they were ready.

"I can't wait!" she said with a laugh.
