Once upon a time, there was a hero named Bob. Bob was brave and generous and always tried to help others. One day, he heard a call for help coming from the deep dark forest nearby. Without hesitation, he ran to the forest to save whoever was in trouble. 

He quickly found a little bird in distress. The bird had gotten stuck in a tree and couldn't get down. Bob quickly climbed up the tree and rescued the bird. He brought the bird back to its nest, and the bird thanked Bob with a sweet song.

As Bob turned to leave, he noticed a sour smell nearby. He followed the smell and found out that a bear was trapped in a cage. He knew he had to help, so he quickly released the bear. 

But the bear was very angry. He roared at Bob and called him names. Bob tried to apologize, but the bear wouldn't listen. He attacked Bob, and Bob ran away quickly.

The moral of this story is that you should be careful when helping others. Not everyone will be as thankful as the bird, so it's important to use caution. Also, make sure to use your common sense when helping, or else you might end up in a bad situation.
<|end|>


