One day, a little girl named Abbi was playing in her garden. She was holding a bright yellow bucket in her hands and as she wandered around, she spotted something interesting in the corner of the garden. It was a small, green cactus. Abbi had never seen a cactus up close before and it made her very excited. She held out her bucket and carefully put the cactus inside.

But when Abbi turned to head back inside, she heard a voice. It was her mother, who was standing in the doorway. "What do you have there Abbi?" she asked.

Abbi proudly showed her mother the cactus in her bucket. "It's a cactus," she explained.

Abbi's mother smiled. "That is a very special kind of cactus," she said. "If you take good care of it and hold it close, it will be very bright. Will you take good care of it, Abbi?"

Abbi nodded and gave her mother a big hug. She held the cactus close to her heart and made a promise to herself to take good care of it. 

A few months later, Abbi's garden was starting to look very different. Instead of the small green cactus, there were now a dozen of them in a variety of colors. Every one of the cacti was the brightest it could possibly be. Abbi had kept her promise to her
<|end|>


