Sam was very excited this morning. He had just received the approval letter for his passport! He clapped his hands and shouted, "We are going on an adventure!"

Just then, his mom said, "Let's go and sign the papers!" Together, they went to the passport office. Sam was very excited. He saw people sitting at desks and colourful stamps everywhere. He knew that he was going to have lots of fun.

When they got to the counter, Sam's mom signed the papers and the lady gave her a very special stamp. Sam was ecstatic! He had never seen such a beautiful stamp before.

Finally, the papers were done and the lady said, "Congratulations Sam! You have your passport now!" Sam said, "Thank you! I am very grateful." His mom gave him a big hug and kissed his forehead. 

It was a very special moment for them both and Sam was really excited about his upcoming adventure.
