Once upon a time there lived a little mouse in a big house. One day, the mouse wanted to escape, so she got out of the house and started to run. Suddenly, a big cat appeared and tried to fight with the tiny mouse. The mouse was scared and she started to cry. Luckily, the mouse saw a small hole in the ground and she ran into it.

The mouse then said, "Where can I go?" But the hole was empty. She knew she had to find a way to get out from the dark empty cave. She felt around and found a secret door. The mouse opened the door and she escaped from the fight.

The mouse was so happy and she ran and ran. After a long time, she arrived at a beautiful meadow. There was no fight and the meadow was not empty; it had many colourful flowers, small trees, and buzzing bees. The mouse was so excited and she danced in the meadow with her friends.
