Once upon a time, there was a little girl named Sarah who wanted to act like the birds outside her window. She watched them fly around and wanted to join them. She was very persistent and kept asking her mom if she could.

One day, Sarah's mom said, "Yes, you can act like the birds outside the window!"
Sarah was ecstatic and immediately ran to her window. But, when she got there, she noticed that there was a screen stopping her from flying outside!
Sarah looked sadly at her mom and said, "How can I act like the birds if I can't get out the window?"

Sarah's mom looked around the room and spotted an old laundry basket. She told Sarah, "If you use the basket, then you can fly like the birds outside the window!"
Sarah was so excited and quickly grabbed the basket. She put it up to the window and climbed inside. Then, with a jump and a flap of her arms, she was flying in circles around the room!

Sarah was so persistent that day, and with her mom's help, she was able to act like the birds outside her window.
