Once upon a time, there was a little bird. She was very happy and loved to play. She had bright purple feathers and loved singing sweet songs. 

One day, the bird was out flying in the warm sunshine. Suddenly, she heard a loud noise from the ground below. It was a thief! He was trying to steal some of the other animals' food.

The little bird was scared and flew away quickly. She landed on a branch and cried out for help. "Help, help! someone stop the thief!" 

Just then, a big lion came out of the forest. He was strong and brave. "Don't worry bird," he said. "I'll lay him out with one powerful swipe of my paw!" 

And with a single powerful swat, the lion scared away the thief. All the animals cheered, and the little bird was so thankful! From that day on, the bird spread the word of the lion's bravery and watched over the other animals.
