It was an exciting day in the park. All the children were playing, laughing and having a great time. Little Johnny was there too, running around having fun. He noticed a shiny toy on the ground, and decided to pick it up.

He was about to take it with him when his mom noticed him. She told him to put it back because it wasn't his. Johnny didn't want to, but he put it back anyway.

Then Johnny saw a little girl playing with a big stuffed dog. He wanted it more than anything and asked the girl if he could play with it. The girl seemed spoiled and told Johnny she wanted to keep it for herself. Johnny was very mad, he wanted the stuffed dog yet nothing he said made the girl change her mind.

Johnny's mom came over, and tried to explain to the little girl that it wasn't nice to keep something that belonged to someone else. The little girl seemed to understand and gave it to Johnny. He was thrilled, and thanked the girl. 

Johnny found out that it's always better to be nice and share than to be spoiled and selfish. He hugged the stuffed dog lovingly and kept it close. From that day forward, Johnny and the little girl were the best of friends.
<|end|>


