Once upon a time there was a little girl named Lucy. She loved animals and dreamed of becoming a Veterinarian one day. One day, one of Lucy's pets, a rabbit named Hop, was very sick. Lucy's parents took Hop to the Vet, who was called Dr. Smith. 

At the Vet's office, Dr. Smith told Lucy that Hop was very sick, and needed an operation right away. Lucy was scared and began to cry, but Dr. Smith said not to worry and that he could help Hop. 

Lucy watched and waited while Dr. Smith operated on Hop, who was very alert throughout the process. Finally, the operation was over and Hop was feeling much better. Lucy was so relieved and said to Dr. Smith, "Thank you for taking such good care of my pet!"

Lucy was glad that Hop was feeling better. Still, she couldn't help but miss him while they were apart.
