Jack and his dad were walking in the park. Jack had a brand new toy with him. It was a colorful frame with colored blocks that he could sort.

"Daddy, what do I do with this?" Jack asked.

"Well, Jack," said his dad, "it's a sort of game. See, you have to match the colors of the blocks. When you put two colors together the frame will show you the pattern you've made. It's very competitive - you have to try and get the best pattern!"

Jack couldn't quite understand, but he wanted to try. He started sorting the blocks into different colors. He struggled a bit, but his dad was patient with him and showed him how it was done.

After a while, Jack started getting more and more confident with the sorting. He was concentrating very hard, until at last he had created a perfect pattern that he was proud of.

As the sun began to set, Jack and his dad stood up and started walking home. Jack had learnt a lot in the park and was excited for the next time he could play the competition game again.
<|end|>


