Once upon a time, there was a little boy called Tim. He was very curious and loved to explore. One day, he decided to go for a walk in his garden.

As Tim was walking, he noticed a small key on the ground. He bent down to pick it up and suddenly heard a voice.

"Give me back the key!" the voice said.

Tim looked up and saw a little old man in a funny hat. He said, "I just wanted to pick it up and have a look!" 

"That key is mine," the old man said. "It's very special." 

Tim thought the key was very interesting and he wanted to keep it. But the old man said, "If you give me the key, I will give you something tasty in return." 

Tim's tummy rumbled. He didn't want to give the key back, but the thought of something tasty made him mention to the old man that he would like to take the deal. 

The old man handed Tim a yummy cookie and thanked him. Then he quickly ran into his house and locked the door with the key.

Tim smiled to himself and ate his tasty cookie. He was glad he had made the right choice.
<|end|>


