One day, Bob was playing with his toy car outside. He was pushing it around and crashing it into rocks. Suddenly, Bob saw a big, yellow bird in the sky. He wanted to grab it, but it was so high in the sky. 

"Oh no! I can't grab it," Bob said. 

But Bob thought of a plan. He had his toy car, so he decided to rub it with the rocks. Soon enough, the toy car was all shiny and the yellow bird was so clear in the sky. 

Bob quickly jumped into his car, ready to grab the yellow bird. He drove as fast as he could and reached the bird, grabbing it in his hands. He was very happy. 

Bob waved his arm around with the yellow bird in his hands and smiled. He was so excited. He had grabbed the yellow bird!
