Once upon a time, a little girl named Jane lived in a big city. Jane was only three years old. One day, her mum took her for a walk in the park.

"Look Jane," her mum said, "That tree is green. Do you remember the colour green?"

Jane smiled and nodded. She loved the colour green. She looked around and saw a little white rabbit hopping around. It was so ordinary, but she still liked to watch it.

Jane's mum smiled and said, "Good girl, remember what you saw today."

Jane nodded and promised to remember the green tree and the hopping rabbit. They walked around the park together, taking in all the ordinary sights and sounds. 

Finally, they walked back home. From then on, Jane remembered the green tree and the ordinary rabbit whenever she went to the park.
